en_text: Bisonal variants reported on in 2014 and 2015 used a simple XOR cipher for C2. Some Bisonal samples encrypt C2 communications with RC4.
Text: 2014年和2015年报告的Bisonal变体在C2中使用了一个简单的XOR密码。一些Bisonal样本用RC4加密C2通信。

en_text: A version of XTunnel introduced in July 2015 obfuscated the binary using opaque predicates and other techniques in a likely attempt to obfuscate it and bypass security products.
Text: 2015年7月推出的XTunnel的一个版本使用不透明的谓词和其他技术混淆了二进制，很可能是试图混淆它并绕过安全产品

en_text: A version of XTunnel introduced in July 2015 inserted junk code into the binary in a likely attempt to obfuscate it and bypass security products.
Text: 2015年7月推出的XTunnel的一个版本在二进制文件中插入了垃圾代码，很可能是为了混淆它并绕过安全产品

en_text: In 2016, APT28 conducted a distributed denial of service (DDoS) attack against the World Anti-Doping Agency.
Text: 2016年，APT28对世界反兴奋剂机构进行了一次分布式拒绝服务（DDoS）攻击

en_text: 3PARA RAT command and control commands are encrypted within the HTTP C2 channel using the DES algorithm in CBC mode with a key derived from the MD5 hash of the string HYF54&%9&jkMCXuiS. 3PARA RAT will use an 8-byte XOR key derived from the string HYF54&%9&jkMCXuiS if the DES decoding fails
Text: 3PARA RAT的命令和控制命令在HTTP C2通道内使用CBC模式下的DES算法进行加密，密钥来自于HYF54&%9&jkMCXuiS字符串的MD5散列。如果DES解码失败，3PARA RAT将使用从HYF54&%9&jkMCXuiS字符串衍生的8字节XOR密钥。

en_text: 3PARA RAT uses HTTP for command and control.
Text: 3PARA RAT使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: 3PARA RAT has a command to retrieve metadata for files on disk as well as a command to list the current working directory.
Text: 3PARA RAT有一个检索磁盘上文件元数据的命令，以及一个列出当前工作目录的命令

en_text: 3PARA RAT has a command to set certain attributes such as creation/modification timestamps on files.
Text: 3PARA RAT有一个命令可以设置某些属性，如创建

en_text: 4H RAT has the capability to obtain file and directory listings.
Text: 4H RAT具有获得文件和目录列表的能力

en_text: 4H RAT uses HTTP for command and control.
Text: 4H RAT使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: 4H RAT obfuscates C2 communication using a 1-byte XOR with the key 0xBE.
Text: 4H RAT使用一个1字节的XOR与密钥0xBE进行混淆C2通信

en_text: 4H RAT has the capability to create a remote shell.
Text: 4H RAT有能力创建一个远程外壳

en_text: 4H RAT has the capability to obtain a listing of running processes (including loaded modules).
Text: 4H RAT有能力获得正在运行的进程列表（包括加载的模块）

en_text: 4H RAT sends an OS version identifier in its beacons.
Text: 4H RAT在其信标中发送一个操作系统版本标识

en_text: Regin stage 1 modules for 64-bit systems have been found to be signed with fake certificates masquerading as originating from Microsoft Corporation and Broadcom Corporation.
Text: 64位系统的Regin第一阶段模块被发现使用伪装成来自微软公司和博通公司的假证书签名

en_text: ABK can extract a malicious Portable Executable (PE) from a photo.
Text: ABK可以从照片中提取一个恶意的可移植执行文件（PE）

en_text: ABK has the ability to download files from C2.
Text: ABK有能力从C2下载文件

en_text: ABK has the ability to decrypt AES encrypted payloads.
Text: ABK有能力解密AES加密的有效载荷

en_text: ABK has the ability to identify the installed anti-virus product on the compromised host.
Text: ABK有能力识别被攻击主机上安装的反病毒产品

en_text: ABK has the ability to use cmd to run a Portable Executable (PE) on the compromised host.
Text: ABK有能力使用cmd在被攻击的主机上运行便携式可执行文件（PE）

en_text: ABK has the ability to inject shellcode into svchost.exe.
Text: ABK有能力向svchost.exe注入shellcode

en_text: ABK has the ability to use HTTP in communications with C2.
Text: ABK有能力在与C2的通信中使用HTTP

en_text: adbupd contains a copy of the OpenSSL library to encrypt C2 traffic.
Text: adbupd包含一个OpenSSL库的副本，用于加密C2流量

en_text: adbupd can use a WMI script to achieve persistence.
Text: adbupd可以使用一个WMI脚本来实现持久化

en_text: adbupd can run a copy of cmd.exe.
Text: adbupd可以运行cmd.exe的副本

en_text: admin@338 has sent emails with malicious Microsoft Office documents attached.
Text: admin@338发送了附有恶意的微软Office文档的电子邮件

en_text: admin@338 has exploited client software vulnerabilities for execution, such as Microsoft Word CVE-2012-0158.
Text: admin@338利用客户端软件漏洞进行执行，如微软Word CVE-2012-0158

en_text: admin@338 has attempted to get victims to launch malicious Microsoft Word attachments delivered via spearphishing emails.
Text: admin@338试图让受害者启动通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件发送的恶意微软Word附件

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following command following exploitation of a machine with LOWBALL malware to list local groups: net localgroup administrator >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台带有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器后，使用以下命令列出本地组： net localgroup administrator >> %temp%\download

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following command following exploitation of a machine with LOWBALL malware to obtain information about services: net start >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台带有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器后使用了以下命令，以获得有关服务的信息：net start >> %temp%\download

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following command after exploiting a machine with LOWBALL malware to acquire information about local networks: ipconfig /all >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台装有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器获取本地网络信息后，使用了以下命令：ipconfig

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following commands after exploiting a machine with LOWBALL malware to obtain information about the OS: ver >> %temp%\download systeminfo >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台装有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器获取操作系统的信息后，使用了以下命令： ver >> %temp%\download systeminfo >> %temp%\download

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following commands after exploiting a machine with LOWBALL malware to obtain information about files and directories: dir c:\ >> %temp%\download dir "c:\Documents and Settings" >> %temp%\download dir "c:\Program Files\" >> %temp%\download dir d:\ >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台装有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器获取文件和目录信息后，使用了以下命令： dir c:\>%temp%\download dir "c:\Documents and Settings" >%temp%\download dir "c:\Program Files\" >> %temp%\download dir d:\> %temp%\download

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following commands following exploitation of a machine with LOWBALL malware to enumerate user accounts: net user >> %temp%\download net user /domain >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338行为人在利用一台装有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器列举用户账户后，使用了以下命令：net user >> %temp%\download net user

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following command to rename one of their tools to a benign file name: ren "%temp%\upload" audiodg.exe
Text: admin@338演员使用以下命令将他们的一个工具重命名为一个良性的文件名：ren "%temp%\upload" audiodg.exe

en_text: admin@338 actors used the following command following exploitation of a machine with LOWBALL malware to display network connections: netstat -ano >> %temp%\download
Text: admin@338演员在利用一台带有LOWBALL恶意软件的机器后，使用了以下命令来显示网络连接：netstat -ano >> %temp%\download

en_text: A variant of ADVSTORESHELL encrypts some C2 with 3DES.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL的一个变体用3DES对一些C2进行加密

en_text: A variant of ADVSTORESHELL encrypts some C2 with RSA.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL的一个变体用RSA对一些C2进行加密

en_text: Some variants of ADVSTORESHELL achieve persistence by registering the payload as a Shell Icon Overlay handler COM object.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL的一些变体通过将有效载荷注册为Shell Icon Overlay handler COM对象来实现持久性

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL stores output from command execution in a .dat file in the %TEMP% directory.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL将命令执行的输出存储在%TEMP%目录下的一个.dat文件中

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can create a remote shell and run a given command.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以创建一个远程shell并运行一个给定的命令

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can perform keylogging.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以进行键盘记录

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can list connected devices.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以列出连接的设备

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can list files and directories.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以列出文件和目录

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can list running processes.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以列出正在运行的进程

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can enumerate registry keys.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以列举注册表键

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can delete files and directories.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以删除文件和目录

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL can run Systeminfo to gather information about the victim.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL可以运行Systeminfo来收集受害者的信息

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL collects, compresses, encrypts, and exfiltrates data to the C2 server every 10 minutes.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL每10分钟收集、压缩、加密和外流数据到C2服务器

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL is capable of setting and deleting Registry values.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL能够设置和删除注册表值

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL is capable of starting a process using CreateProcess.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL能够使用CreateProcess启动一个进程

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL connects to port 80 of a C2 server using Wininet API. Data is exchanged via HTTP POSTs.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL使用Wininet API连接到C2服务器的80端口

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL achieves persistence by adding itself to the HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run Registry key.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL通过将自己添加到HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run注册表的键值来实现持久性

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL exfiltrates data over the same channel used for C2.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL通过用于C2的同一渠道渗出数据

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL compresses output data generated by command execution with a custom implementation of the LempelCZivCWelch (LZW) algorithm.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL用Lempel-Ziv-Welch（LZW）算法的定制实现来压缩命令执行产生的输出数据

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL encrypts with the 3DES algorithm and a hardcoded key prior to exfiltration.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL在渗出前用3DES算法和硬编码密钥进行加密

en_text: ADVSTORESHELL has used rundll32.exe in a Registry value to establish persistence.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL在一个注册表值中使用了rundll32.exe，以建立持久性

en_text: Most of the strings in ADVSTORESHELL are encrypted with an XOR-based algorithm; some strings are also encrypted with 3DES and reversed. API function names are also reversed, presumably to avoid detection in memory.
Text: ADVSTORESHELL中的大多数字符串都是用基于XOR的算法加密的；有些字符串也是用3DES加密并反转

en_text: Agent.btz obtains the victim username and saves it to a file.
Text: Agent.btz获取受害者的用户名并将其保存到一个文件中

en_text: Agent.btz saves system information into an XML file that is then XOR-encoded.
Text: Agent.btz将系统信息保存到一个XML文件中，然后进行XOR编码

en_text: Agent.btz drops itself onto removable media devices and creates an autorun.inf file with an instruction to run that file. When the device is inserted into another system, it opens autorun.inf and loads the malware.
Text: Agent.btz将自己丢到可移动媒体设备上，并创建一个autorun.inf文件，其中有运行该文件的指令

en_text: Agent.btz attempts to download an encrypted binary from a specified domain.
Text: Agent.btz试图从一个指定的域下载一个加密的二进制文件

en_text: Agent.btz collects the network adapter’s IP and MAC address as well as IP addresses of the network adapter’s default gateway, primary/secondary WINS, DHCP, and DNS servers, and saves them into a log file.
Text: Agent.btz收集网络适配器的IP和MAC地址，以及网络适配器的默认网关的IP地址、主网关的IP地址

en_text: Agent.btz creates a file named thumb.dd on all USB flash drives connected to the victim. This file contains information about the infected system and activity logs.
Text: Agent.btz在与受害者相连的所有USB闪存驱动器上创建一个名为thumb.dd的文件

en_text: Variants of Anchor can use DNS tunneling to communicate with C2.
Text: Anchor的变种可以使用DNS隧道来与C2通信

en_text: Anchor can determine the public IP and location of a compromised host.
Text: Anchor可以确定被攻击主机的公共IP和位置

en_text: Anchor can determine the hostname and linux version on a compromised host.
Text: Anchor可以确定被攻击主机的主机名和linux版本

en_text: Anchor can execute payloads via shell scripting.
Text: Anchor可以通过shell脚本来执行有效载荷

en_text: Anchor can support windows execution via SMB shares.
Text: Anchor可以支持通过SMB共享的窗口执行

en_text: Anchor can install itself as a cron job.
Text: Anchor可以作为一个cron job来安装自己

en_text: Anchor has used cmd.exe to run its self deletion routine.
Text: Anchor使用cmd.exe来运行其自我删除程序

en_text: Anchor has used NTFS to hide files.
Text: Anchor使用了NTFS来隐藏文件

en_text: Anchor has obsuscated code with stack strings and string encryption.
Text: Anchor用堆栈字符串和字符串加密来掩盖代码

en_text: Anchor has used HTTP and HTTPS in C2 communications.
Text: Anchor在C2通信中使用了HTTP和HTTPS

en_text: Anchor has used ICMP in C2 communications.
Text: Anchor在C2通信中使用了ICMP

en_text: APT12 has sent emails with malicious Microsoft Office documents and PDFs attached.
Text: APT12发送的电子邮件附有恶意的微软Office文档和PDF文件

en_text: APT12 has used blogs and WordPress for C2 infrastructure.
Text: APT12使用博客和WordPress作为C2基础设施

en_text: APT12 has used multiple variants of DNS Calculation including multiplying the first two octets of an IP address and adding the third octet to that value in order to get a resulting command and control port.
Text: APT12使用了DNS计算的多种变体，包括将一个IP地址的前两个八位字节相乘，并将第三个八位字节加入该值，以得到一个结果的命令和控制端口

en_text: APT12 has used the RIPTIDE RAT, which communicates over HTTP with a payload encrypted with RC4.
Text: APT12使用了RIPTIDE RAT，它通过HTTP与一个用RC4加密的有效载荷进行通信

en_text: APT12 has used RIPTIDE, a RAT that uses HTTP to communicate.
Text: APT12使用了RIPTIDE，一个使用HTTP进行通信的RAT

en_text: APT12 has attempted to get victims to open malicious Microsoft Word and PDF attachment sent via spearphishing.
Text: APT12试图让受害者打开通过鱼叉钓鱼发送的恶意微软Word和PDF附件

en_text: APT12 has exploited multiple vulnerabilities for execution, including Microsoft Office vulnerabilities (CVE-2009-3129, CVE-2012-0158) and vulnerabilities in Adobe Reader and Flash (CVE-2009-4324, CVE-2009-0927, CVE-2011-0609, CVE-2011-0611).
Text: APT12已经利用了多个漏洞进行执行，包括微软Office漏洞（CVE-2009-3129，CVE-2012-0158）和Adobe Reader和Flash的漏洞（CVE-2009-4324，CVE-2009-0927，CVE-2011-0609，CVE-2011-0611）

en_text: APT18 obfuscates strings in the payload.
Text: APT18混淆了有效载荷中的字符串

en_text: APT18 can collect system information from the victim’s machine.
Text: APT18可以从受害者的机器上收集系统信息

en_text: APT18 can upload a file to the victim’s machine.
Text: APT18可以将一个文件上传到受害者的机器上

en_text: APT18 can list files information for specific directories.
Text: APT18可以列出特定目录下的文件信息

en_text: APT18 uses cmd.exe to execute commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: APT18使用cmd.exe在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: APT18 uses DNS for C2 communications.
Text: APT18使用DNS进行C2通信

en_text: APT18 uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: APT18使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: APT18 establishes persistence via the HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run key.
Text: APT18通过HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run键建立了持久性

en_text: APT18 actors deleted tools and batch files from victim systems.
Text: APT18行动者从受害者系统中删除了工具和批处理文件

en_text: APT18 actors leverage legitimate credentials to log into external remote services.
Text: APT18行动者利用合法的凭证来登录外部远程服务

en_text: APT18 actors used the native at Windows task scheduler tool to use scheduled tasks for execution on a victim network.
Text: APT18行动者使用Windows任务调度器的本地工具，在受害者网络上使用计划任务进行执行

en_text: An APT19 HTTP malware variant used Base64 to encode communications to the C2 server.
Text: APT19的一个HTTP恶意软件变体使用Base64来编码与C2服务器的通信

en_text: An APT19 HTTP malware variant decrypts strings using single-byte XOR keys.
Text: APT19的一个HTTP恶意软件变体使用单字节的XOR密钥解密字符串

en_text: APT19 sent spearphishing emails with malicious attachments in RTF and XLSM formats to deliver initial exploits.
Text: APT19发送了带有RTF和XLSM格式的恶意附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件，以提供最初的漏洞

en_text: APT19 configured its payload to inject into the rundll32.exe.
Text: APT19将其有效载荷配置为注入rundll32.exe中

en_text: APT19 used Regsvr32 to bypass application control techniques.
Text: APT19利用Regsvr32绕过应用控制技术

en_text: APT19 launched an HTTP malware variant and a Port 22 malware variant using a legitimate executable that loaded the malicious DLL.
Text: APT19利用加载恶意DLL的合法可执行文件，启动了一个HTTP恶意软件变体和一个22端口恶意软件变体

en_text: APT19 used Base64 to obfuscate commands and the payload.
Text: APT19使用Base64来混淆命令和有效载荷

en_text: APT19 used HTTP for C2 communications. APT19 also used an HTTP malware variant to communicate over HTTP for C2.
Text: APT19使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: APT19 used PowerShell commands to execute payloads.
Text: APT19使用PowerShell命令来执行有效载荷

en_text: APT19 used -W Hidden to conceal PowerShell windows by setting the WindowStyle parameter to hidden.
Text: APT19使用-W隐藏来隐藏PowerShell窗口，将WindowStyle参数设置为隐藏

en_text: APT19 uses a Port 22 malware variant to modify several Registry keys.
Text: APT19使用端口22恶意软件的变体来修改几个注册表键

en_text: APT19 used an HTTP malware variant and a Port 22 malware variant to collect the victim’s username.
Text: APT19使用一个HTTP恶意软件变体和一个22端口恶意软件变体来收集受害者的用户名

en_text: APT19 used an HTTP malware variant and a Port 22 malware variant to collect the MAC address and IP address from the victim’s machine.
Text: APT19使用一个HTTP恶意软件变体和一个22端口恶意软件变体来收集受害者机器的MAC地址和IP地址

en_text: APT19 attempted to get users to launch malicious attachments delivered via spearphishing emails.
Text: APT19试图让用户启动通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件发送的恶意附件

en_text: APT19 collected system architecture information. APT19 used an HTTP malware variant and a Port 22 malware variant to gather the hostname and CPU information from the victim’s machine.
Text: APT19收集系统架构信息。APT19使用一个HTTP恶意软件变体和一个22端口恶意软件变体来收集受害者机器的主机名和CPU信息。

en_text: APT19 downloaded and launched code within a SCT file.
Text: APT19下载并启动了SCT文件中的代码

en_text: APT19 performed a watering hole attack on forbes.com in 2014 to compromise targets.
Text: APT19在2014年对forbes.com进行了一次灌水攻击，以损害目标

en_text: APT1 has sent spearphishing emails containing hyperlinks to malicious files.
Text: APT1发送了包含恶意文件超链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT1 has sent spearphishing emails containing malicious attachments.
Text: APT1发送了含有恶意附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT1 listed connected network shares.
Text: APT1列出了连接的网络共享

en_text: APT1 used the ipconfig /all command to gather network configuration information.
Text: APT1使用ipconfig APT1使用了ipconfig APT1使用的是ipconfig APT1使用了ipconfig的

en_text: APT1 used the net use command to get a listing on network connections.
Text: APT1使用net use命令来获取网络连接的清单

en_text: APT1 has used the Windows command shell to execute commands, and batch scripting to automate execution.
Text: APT1使用Windows命令外壳来执行命令，并使用批处理脚本来自动执行

en_text: APT1 uses two utilities, GETMAIL and MAPIGET, to steal email. GETMAIL extracts emails from archived Outlook .pst files.
Text: APT1使用两个工具，GETMAIL和MAPIGET，来窃取电子邮件

en_text: APT1 uses two utilities, GETMAIL and MAPIGET, to steal email. MAPIGET steals email still on Exchange servers that has not yet been archived.
Text: APT1使用两个工具，GETMAIL和MAPIGET，来窃取电子邮件

en_text: APT1 used the commands net localgroup,net user, and net group to find accounts on the system.
Text: APT1使用命令net localgroup,net user,和net group来查找系统上的账户

en_text: APT1 used the commands net start and tasklist to get a listing of the services on the system.
Text: APT1使用命令net start和tasklist来获取系统上的服务列表

en_text: APT1 gathered a list of running processes on the system using tasklist /v.
Text: APT1使用任务列表收集了系统中正在运行的进程列表

en_text: APT1 used a batch script to perform a series of discovery techniques and saves it to a text file.
Text: APT1使用一个批处理脚本来执行一系列发现技术，并将其保存到一个文本文件

en_text: APT1 has collected files from a local victim.
Text: APT1已经收集了本地受害者的文件

en_text: APT1 has used RAR to compress files before moving them outside of the victim network.
Text: APT1在将文件转移到受害者网络之外之前，使用了RAR来压缩文件

en_text: APT28 installed a Delphi backdoor that used a custom algorithm for C2 communications.
Text: APT28安装了一个Delphi后门，使用自定义算法进行C2通信

en_text: APT28 has saved files with hidden file attributes.
Text: APT28保存了具有隐藏文件属性的文件

en_text: APT28 deployed the open source tool Responder to conduct NetBIOS Name Service poisoning, which captured usernames and hashed passwords that allowed access to legitimate credentials. APT28 close-access teams have used Wi-Fi pineapples to intercept Wi-Fi signals and user credentials.
Text: APT28部署了开源工具Responder来进行NetBIOS名称服务中毒，它捕获了用户名和哈希密码，允许访问合法凭证。APT28的近距离访问团队使用Wi-Fi菠萝拦截Wi-Fi信号和用户凭证。

en_text: APT28 has collected information from Microsoft SharePoint services within target networks.
Text: APT28从目标网络内的微软SharePoint服务中收集信息

en_text: Part of APT28's operation involved using CHOPSTICK modules to copy itself to air-gapped machines and using files written to USB sticks to transfer data and command traffic.
Text: APT28的部分操作涉及使用CHOPSTICK模块将自己复制到空气盖的机器上，并使用写入U盘的文件来传输数据和指令流量

en_text: Part of APT28's operation involved using CHOPSTICK modules to copy itself to air-gapped machines, using files written to USB sticks to transfer data and command traffic.
Text: APT28的部分操作涉及使用CHOPSTICK模块将自己复制到空气盖的机器上，使用写入U盘的文件来传输数据和命令流量

en_text: APT28 has performed timestomping on victim files.
Text: APT28对受害者文件进行了时间篡改

en_text: APT28 has conducted SQL injection attacks against organizations' external websites.
Text: APT28对组织的外部网站进行了SQL注入攻击

en_text: APT28 sent spearphishing emails which used a URL-shortener service to masquerade as a legitimate service and to redirect targets to credential harvesting sites.
Text: APT28发送的鱼叉式钓鱼电子邮件使用了一个URL缩短器服务来伪装成合法服务，并将目标重定向到证书采集网站

en_text: APT28 sent spearphishing emails containing malicious Microsoft Office attachments.
Text: APT28发送了含有恶意微软Office附件的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT28 has intentionally deleted computer files to cover their tracks, including with use of the program CCleaner.
Text: APT28故意删除电脑文件以掩盖其踪迹，包括使用CCleaner程序

en_text: Later implants used by APT28, such as CHOPSTICK, use a blend of HTTP and other legitimate channels for C2, depending on module configuration.
Text: APT28后来使用的植入物，如CHOPSTICK，根据模块配置的不同，使用HTTP和其他合法渠道混合进行C2

en_text: APT28 regularly deploys both publicly available (ex: Mimikatz) and custom password retrieval tools on victims.
Text: APT28经常在受害者身上部署公开可用的（例如：Mimikatz）和定制的密码检索工具

en_text: APT28 has exploited CVE-2014-4076, CVE-2015-2387, CVE-2015-1701, CVE-2017-0263 to escalate privileges.
APT28 has used CVE-2015-1701 to access the SYSTEM token and copy it into the current process as part of privilege escalation.
Text: APT28利用CVE-2015-1701访问SYSTEM令牌并将其复制到当前进程中，作为权限升级的一部分

en_text: APT28 has used CVE-2015-4902 to bypass security features.
Text: APT28利用CVE-2015-4902来绕过安全功能

en_text: APT28 exploited a Windows SMB Remote Code Execution Vulnerability to conduct lateral movement.
Text: APT28利用Windows SMB远程代码执行漏洞，进行横向移动

en_text: APT28 has used the WindowStyle parameter to conceal PowerShell windows.
Text: APT28利用WindowStyle参数来隐藏PowerShell窗口

en_text: APT28 has used pass the hash for lateral movement.
Text: APT28利用传球进行横向移动

en_text: APT28 has used legitimate credentials to gain initial access, maintain access, and exfiltrate data from a victim network. The group has specifically used credentials stolen through a spearphishing email to login to the DCCC network. The group has also leveraged default manufacturer's passwords to gain initial access to corporate networks via IoT devices such as a VOIP phone, printer, and video decoder.
Text: APT28利用合法凭证获得初始访问权，保持访问权，并从受害者网络中渗出数据。该组织特别使用了通过鱼叉式钓鱼邮件窃取的凭证来登录DCCC网络。该组织还利用制造商的默认密码，通过VOIP电话、打印机和视频解码器等物联网设备获得对企业网络的初始访问。

en_text: APT28 used other victims as proxies to relay command traffic, for instance using a compromised Georgian military email server as a hop point to NATO victims. The group has also used a tool that acts as a proxy to allow C2 even if the victim is behind a router. APT28 has also used a machine to relay and obscure communications between CHOPSTICK and their server.
Text: APT28利用其他受害者作为代理来转发命令流量，例如使用一个被破坏的格鲁吉亚军事电子邮件服务器作为跳转点，连接北约受害者。该组织还使用了一个作为代理的工具，以允许C2，即使受害者在路由器后面。APT28还使用一台机器来中继和掩盖CHOPSTICK和他们的服务器之间的通信。

en_text: APT28 has exploited Microsoft Office vulnerability CVE-2017-0262 for execution.
Text: APT28利用微软Office漏洞CVE-2017-0262进行执行

en_text: APT28 encrypted a .dll payload using RTL and a custom encryption algorithm. APT28 has also obfuscated payloads with base64, XOR, and RC4.
Text: APT28使用RTL和自定义加密算法对一个.dll有效载荷进行了加密

en_text: APT28 has used tools to take screenshots from victims.
Text: APT28使用工具对受害者进行了屏幕截图

en_text: APT28 has used several malicious applications to steal user OAuth access tokens including applications masquerading as "Google Defender" "Google Email Protection," and "Google Scanner" for Gmail users. They also targeted Yahoo users with applications masquerading as "Delivery Service" and "McAfee Email Protection".
Text: APT28使用了几个恶意应用程序来窃取用户的OAuth访问令牌，包括伪装成 "Google Defender""Google Email Protection "和 "Google Scanner "的Gmail用户应用程序。他们还针对雅虎用户使用伪装成 "交付服务 "和 "McAfee电子邮件保护 "的应用程序。

en_text: APT28 has used several malicious applications that abused OAuth access tokens to gain access to target email accounts, including Gmail and Yahoo Mail.
Text: APT28使用了几个滥用OAuth访问令牌的恶意应用程序，以获得对目标电子邮件账户的访问，包括Gmail和雅虎邮箱

en_text: APT28 has used a UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) rootkit known as LoJax.
Text: APT28使用了一个名为LoJax的UEFI（统一可扩展固件接口）rootkit

en_text: APT28 has used a brute-force/password-spray tooling that operated in two modes: in brute-force mode it typically sent over 300 authentication attempts per hour per targeted account over the course of several hours or days.
Text: APT28使用了一种暴力手段 APT28使用了一种粗暴的 APT28使用了暴力手段 APT28使用了一种粗暴的方式

en_text: APT28 has used a brute-force/password-spray tooling that operated in two modes: in password-spraying mode it conducted approximately four authentication attempts per hour per targeted account over the course of several days or weeks.
Text: APT28使用了一种以两种模式运行的暴力/密码喷洒工具：在密码喷洒模式下，它在几天或几周内对每个目标账户每小时进行大约四次认证尝试。

en_text: APT28 used weaponized Microsoft Word documents abusing the remote template function to retrieve a malicious macro.
Text: APT28使用武器化的微软Word文档，滥用远程模板功能来检索一个恶意的宏

en_text: APT28 uses a tool to infect connected USB devices and transmit itself to air-gapped computers when the infected USB device is inserted.
Text: APT28使用一个工具来感染连接的USB设备，并在插入受感染的USB设备时将自己传输到有空气的计算机

en_text: APT28 used a publicly available tool to gather and compress multiple documents on the DCCC and DNC networks.
Text: APT28使用一个公开的工具来收集和压缩DCCC和DNC网络上的多个文件

en_text: APT28 uses a module to receive a notification every time a USB mass storage device is inserted into a victim.
Text: APT28使用一个模块，在每次将USB大容量存储设备插入受害者体内时接收通知

en_text: APT28 uses a tool that captures information from air-gapped computers via an infected USB and transfers it to network-connected computer when the USB is inserted.
Text: APT28使用一种工具，通过受感染的USB从空气中的计算机捕捉信息，并在插入USB时将其传输到网络连接的计算机

en_text: APT28 attempted to get users to click on Microsoft Office attachments containing malicious macro scripts.
Text: APT28试图让用户点击含有恶意宏脚本的微软Office附件

en_text: APT28 executed CHOPSTICK by using rundll32 commands such as rundll32.exe "C:\Windows\twain_64.dll". APT28 also executed a .dll for a first stage dropper using rundll32.exe. An APT28 loader Trojan saved a batch script that uses rundll32 to execute a DLL payload.
Text: APT28通过使用rundll32命令执行CHOPSTICK，如rundll32.exe "C:\Windows\twain_64.dll" 。APT28还使用rundll32.exe执行了一个用于第一阶段的dropper的.dll。一个APT28加载器木马保存了一个批处理脚本，使用rundll32来执行一个DLL有效载荷。

en_text: APT28 has used the Office Test persistence mechanism within Microsoft Office by adding the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Office test\Special\Perf to execute code.
Text: APT28通过添加注册表键HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Office test\Special\Perf来执行代码，使用了Microsoft Office内的Office Test持久性机制

en_text: APT28 has used COM hijacking for persistence by replacing the legitimate MMDeviceEnumerator object with a payload.
Text: APT28通过用一个有效载荷替换合法的MMDeviceEnumerator对象，利用COM劫持来实现持久性

en_text: APT28 has delivered JHUHUGIT and Koadic by executing PowerShell commands through DDE in Word documents.
Text: APT28通过在Word文档中的DDE执行PowerShell命令来交付JHUHUGIT和Koadic

en_text: APT28 downloads and executes PowerShell scripts.
Text: APT28下载并执行PowerShell脚本

en_text: APT28 has collected emails from victim Microsoft Exchange servers.
Text: APT28已经从受害者的微软Exchange服务器上收集了电子邮件

en_text: APT28 has retrieved internal documents from machines inside victim environments, including by using Forfiles to stage documents before exfiltration.
Text: APT28已经从受害者环境中的机器上获取了内部文件，包括通过使用Forfiles在渗出前对文件进行分级

en_text: APT28 has cleared event logs, including by using the commands wevtutil cl System and wevtutil cl Security.
Text: APT28已经清除了事件日志，包括通过使用wevtutil cl System和wevtutil cl Security命令

en_text: APT28 has used tools to perform keylogging.
Text: APT28已经使用工具进行键盘记录

en_text: APT28 has downloaded additional files, including by using a first-stage downloader to contact the C2 server to obtain the second-stage implant.
Text: APT28已经下载了更多的文件，包括通过使用第一阶段的下载器联系C2服务器以获得第二阶段的植入物

en_text: APT28 has deployed a bootkit along with Downdelph to ensure its persistence on the victim. The bootkit shares code with some variants of BlackEnergy.
Text: APT28与Downdelph一起部署了一个bootkit，以确保其在受害者身上的持久性

en_text: APT28 used SMTP as a communication channel in various implants, initially using self-registered Google Mail accounts and later compromised email servers of its victims.
Text: APT28在各种植入中使用SMTP作为通信渠道，最初使用自我注册的谷歌邮件账户，后来又入侵了其受害者的电子邮件服务器

en_text: APT28 added "junk data" to each encoded string, preventing trivial decoding without knowledge of the junk removal algorithm. Each implant was given a "junk length" value when created, tracked by the controller software to allow seamless communication but prevent analysis of the command protocol on the wire.
Text: APT28在每个编码字符串中加入 "垃圾数据"，防止在不了解垃圾清除算法的情况下进行简单的解码。每个植入物在创建时都被赋予一个 "垃圾长度 "值，由控制器软件跟踪，以允许无缝通信，但防止对电线上的命令协议进行分析。

en_text: APT28 has used Forfiles to locate PDF, Excel, and Word documents during collection. The group also searched a compromised DCCC computer for specific terms.
Text: APT28在收集过程中使用Forfiles来定位PDF、Excel和Word文件。该小组还在一台被破坏的DCCC电脑上搜索了特定的术语。

en_text: APT28 has stored captured credential information in a file named pi.log.
Text: APT28在一个名为pi.log的文件中存储了捕获的凭证信息

en_text: APT29 has used multiple software exploits for common client software, like Microsoft Word and Adobe Reader, to gain code execution as part of.
Text: APT29对常见的客户端软件，如Microsoft Word和Adobe Reader，使用了多个软件漏洞，以获得代码执行的一部分

en_text: APT29 has developed malware variants written in Python.
Text: APT29开发了用Python编写的恶意软件变种

en_text: APT29 has exploited CVE-2019-19781 for Citrix, CVE-2019-11510 for Pulse Secure VPNs, CVE-2018-13379 for FortiGate VPNs, and CVE-2019-9670 in Zimbra software to gain access.
Text: APT29利用Citrix的CVE-2019-19781、Pulse Secure VPN的CVE-2019-11510、FortiGate VPN的CVE-2018-13379以及Zimbra软件的CVE-2019-9670来获取访问权

en_text: APT29 has used the meek domain fronting plugin for Tor to hide the destination of C2 traffic.
Text: APT29利用Tor的meek domain fronting插件来隐藏C2流量的目的地

en_text: APT29 used WMI to steal credentials and execute backdoors at a future time.
Text: APT29利用WMI窃取凭证，并在将来的某个时间执行后门程序

en_text: APT29 has used spearphishing emails with an attachment to deliver files with exploits to initial victims.
Text: APT29利用带有附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件向最初的受害者传递带有漏洞的文件

en_text: APT29 has used spearphishing with a link to trick victims into clicking on a link to a zip file containing malicious files.
Text: APT29利用带有链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼，欺骗受害者点击一个包含恶意文件的压缩文件的链接

en_text: APT29 has used encoded PowerShell scripts uploaded to CozyCar installations to download and install SeaDuke. APT29 also used PowerShell scripts to evade defenses.
Text: APT29利用上传到CozyCar安装的编码PowerShell脚本来下载和安装SeaDuke。APT29还使用PowerShell脚本来逃避防御。

en_text: APT29 has used social media platforms to hide communications to C2 servers.
Text: APT29利用社交媒体平台来隐藏与C2服务器的通信

en_text: APT29 used Kerberos ticket attacks for lateral movement.
Text: APT29使用Kerberos票据攻击进行横向移动

en_text: APT29 uses PowerShell to use Base64 for obfuscation.
Text: APT29使用PowerShell来使用Base64进行混淆

en_text: APT29 has used rundll32.exe for execution.
Text: APT29使用rundll32.exe来执行。

en_text: APT29 used SDelete to remove artifacts from victims.
Text: APT29使用SDelete从受害者身上删除人工制品

en_text: APT29 uses TCP for C2 communications.
Text: APT29使用TCP进行C2通信

en_text: APT29 used UPX to pack files.
Text: APT29使用UPX来打包文件

en_text: A backdoor used by APT29 created a Tor hidden service to forward traffic from the Tor client to local ports 3389 (RDP), 139 (Netbios), and 445 (SMB) enabling full remote access from outside the network.
Text: APT29使用的一个后门创建了一个Tor隐藏服务，将流量从Tor客户端转发到本地端口3389（RDP）、139（Netbios）和445（SMB），从而实现从网络外完全远程访问

en_text: APT29 has used various forms of spearphishing attempting to get a user to open links or attachments, including, but not limited to, malicious Microsoft Word documents, .pdf, and .lnk files.
Text: APT29使用各种形式的鱼叉式钓鱼，试图让用户打开链接或附件，包括但不限于恶意的微软Word文档、.pdf和.lnk文件

en_text: APT29 has used WMI to establish persistence.
Text: APT29使用了WMI来建立持久性

en_text: APT29 used named and hijacked scheduled tasks to establish persistence.
Text: APT29使用命名和劫持的计划任务来建立持久性

en_text: APT29 has used steganography to hide C2 communications in images.
Text: APT29使用隐写术将C2通信隐藏在图像中

en_text: APT29 has used valid accounts, including administrator accounts, to help facilitate lateral movement on compromised networks.
Text: APT29使用有效的账户，包括管理员账户，以帮助促进被攻击网络的横向移动

en_text: APT29 used sticky-keys to obtain unauthenticated, privileged console access.
Text: APT29使用粘性钥匙来获得未经认证的特权控制台访问权

en_text: APT29 drops a Windows shortcut file for execution.
Text: APT29投放了一个Windows快捷方式文件供执行

en_text: APT29 has bypassed UAC.
Text: APT29已经绕过了UAC

en_text: APT29 added Registry Run keys to establish persistence.
Text: APT29增加了注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: APT30 may have used the SHIPSHAPE malware to move onto air-gapped networks. SHIPSHAPE targets removable drives to spread to other systems by modifying the drive to use Autorun to execute or by hiding legitimate document files and copying an executable to the folder with the same name as the legitimate document.
Text: APT30可能利用SHIPSHAPE恶意软件转移到有空气防护的网络。SHIPSHAPE以可移动驱动器为目标，通过修改驱动器使用Autorun执行或隐藏合法文件并将可执行文件复制到与合法文件同名的文件夹中，传播到其他系统。

en_text: APT30 has used spearphishing emails with malicious DOC attachments.
Text: APT30利用带有恶意DOC附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT30 has relied on users to execute malicious file attachments delivered via spearphishing emails.
Text: APT30依靠用户执行通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件发送的恶意文件附件

en_text: APT32 includes garbage code to mislead anti-malware software and researchers.
Text: APT32包括垃圾代码，以误导反恶意软件和研究人员

en_text: APT32 has used pass the hash for lateral movement.
Text: APT32采用了传球的方式进行横向移动

en_text: APT32 created a Scheduled Task/Job that used regsvr32.exe to execute a COM scriptlet that dynamically downloaded a backdoor and injected it into memory. The group has also used regsvr32 to run their backdoor.
Text: APT32创建了一个预定任务/工作，使用regsvr32.exe执行一个COM脚本let，动态下载一个后门并将其注入内存。该组织还使用regsvr32来运行其后门。

en_text: APT32's macOS backdoor changes the permission of the file it wants to execute to 755.
Text: APT32的macOS后门将其想要执行的文件的权限改为755

en_text: APT32's macOS backdoor can receive a "delete" command.
Text: APT32的macOS后门可以接收 "删除 "命令

en_text: APT32's macOS backdoor hides the clientID file via a chflags function.
Text: APT32的macOS后门通过一个chflags函数隐藏了clientID文件

en_text: APT32's backdoor can query the Windows Registry to gather system information.
Text: APT32的后门可以查询Windows注册表以收集系统信息

en_text: APT32's backdoor can exfiltrate data by encoding it in the subdomain field of DNS packets.
Text: APT32的后门可以通过在DNS数据包的子域字段中进行编码来渗出数据

en_text: APT32's backdoor has exfiltrated data using the already opened channel with its C&C server.
Text: APT32的后门利用已经打开的通道，以其C语言渗出数据

en_text: APT32's backdoor has used Windows services as a way to execute its malicious payload.
Text: APT32的后门使用Windows服务作为执行其恶意有效载荷的方式

en_text: APT32's backdoor has modified the Windows Registry to store the backdoor's configuration.
Text: APT32的后门已经修改了Windows注册表，以存储后门的配置

en_text: APT32's backdoor possesses the capability to list files and directories on a machine.
Text: APT32的后门拥有列出机器上的文件和目录的能力

en_text: APT32's backdoor has used LZMA compression and RC4 encryption before exfiltration.
Text: APT32的后门在渗出前已经使用了LZMA压缩和RC4加密

en_text: APT32 malware has used rundll32.exe to execute an initial infection process.
Text: APT32恶意软件使用rundll32.exe来执行初始感染过程

en_text: APT32 malware has injected a Cobalt Strike beacon into Rundll32.exe.
Text: APT32恶意软件在Rundll32.exe中注入了一个Cobalt Strike信标

en_text: APT32 has sent spearphishing emails with a malicious executable disguised as a document or spreadsheet.
Text: APT32发送了带有伪装成文档或电子表格的恶意可执行文件的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT32 has sent spearphishing emails containing malicious links.
Text: APT32发送了含有恶意链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT32 has moved and renamed pubprn.vbs to a .txt file to avoid detection.
Text: APT32将pubprn.vbs移动并重命名为一个.txt文件，以避免被发现

en_text: APT32 has disguised a Cobalt Strike beacon as a Flash Installer.
Text: APT32将一个Cobalt Strike信标伪装成一个Flash安装程序

en_text: APT32 has renamed a NetCat binary to kb-10233.exe to masquerade as a Windows update. APT32 has also renamed a Cobalt Strike beacon payload to install_flashplayers.exe.
Text: APT32将一个NetCat二进制文件重命名为kb-10233.exe，以伪装成一个Windows更新。APT32还将一个Cobalt Strike信标有效载荷重命名为install_flashplayers.exe。

en_text: APT32 has abused the PasswordChangeNotify to monitor for and capture account password changes.
Text: APT32滥用了PasswordChangeNotify来监控和捕捉账户密码的变化

en_text: APT32 has used CVE-2016-7255 to escalate privileges.
Text: APT32利用CVE-2016-7255来提升权限

en_text: APT32 has used JavaScript for drive-by downloads and C2 communications.
Text: APT32利用JavaScript进行偷渡式下载和C2通信

en_text: APT32 used Net to use Windows' hidden network shares to copy their tools to remote machines for execution.
Text: APT32利用Net来使用Windows的隐藏网络共享，将他们的工具复制到远程机器上执行

en_text: APT32 has used the WindowStyle parameter to conceal PowerShell windows.
Text: APT32利用WindowStyle参数来隐藏PowerShell窗口

en_text: APT32 has used scheduled tasks to persist on victim systems.
Text: APT32利用计划任务在受害者系统上持续存在

en_text: APT32 has used JavaScript that communicates over HTTP or HTTPS to attacker controlled domains to download additional frameworks. The group has also used downloaded encrypted payloads over HTTP.
Text: APT32利用通过HTTP或HTTPS与攻击者控制的域进行通信的JavaScript来下载额外的框架

en_text: APT32 established persistence using Registry Run keys, both to execute PowerShell and VBS scripts as well as to execute their backdoor directly.
Text: APT32利用注册表运行键建立持久性，既可以执行PowerShell和VBS脚本，也可以直接执行其后门

en_text: APT32 compromised McAfee ePO to move laterally by distributing malware as a software deployment task.
Text: APT32破坏了McAfee ePO，通过将恶意软件作为软件部署任务进行分发来进行横向移动

en_text: APT32 has used cmd.exe for execution.
Text: APT32使用cmd.exe来执行

en_text: APT32 has used COM scriptlets to download Cobalt Strike beacons.
Text: APT32使用COM小脚本下载Cobalt Strike信标

en_text: APT32 used GetPassword_x64 to harvest credentials.
Text: APT32使用GetPassword_x64来获取凭证

en_text: APT32 uses the Invoke-Obfuscation framework to obfuscate their PowerShell and also performs other code obfuscation. APT32 has also encoded payloads using Base64 and a framework called "Dont-Kill-My-Cat (DKMC). APT32 also encrypts the library used for network exfiltration with AES-256 in CBC mode in their macOS backdoor.
Text: APT32使用Invoke-Obfuscation框架来混淆他们的PowerShell，也执行其他代码混淆。APT32还使用Base64和一个名为 "Dont-Kill-My-Cat（DKMC）"的框架对有效载荷进行编码。APT32还在他们的macOS后门中用CBC模式的AES-256加密用于网络渗出的库。

en_text: APT32 used the ipconfig /all command to gather the IP address from the system.
Text: APT32使用ipconfig APT32使用了ipconfig APT32使用的是ipconfig APT32使用了ipconfig的

en_text: APT32 used Mimikatz and customized versions of Windows Credential Dumper to harvest credentials.
Text: APT32使用Mimikatz和定制版本的Windows Credential Dumper来获取凭证

en_text: APT32 has enumerated DC servers using the command net group "Domain Controllers" /domain. The group has also used the ping command.
Text: APT32使用net group "Domain Controllers" /domain命令列举了DC服务器。该组还使用了ping命令。

en_text: APT32 used the net view command to show all shares available, including the administrative shares such as C$ and ADMIN$.
Text: APT32使用net view命令来显示所有可用的共享，包括C$和ADMIN$等管理共享

en_text: APT32 used the netstat -anpo tcp command to display TCP connections on the victim's machine.
Text: APT32使用netstat -anpo tcp命令来显示受害者机器上的TCP连接

en_text: APT32 used NTFS alternate data streams to hide their payloads.
Text: APT32使用NTFS备用数据流来隐藏其有效载荷

en_text: APT32 used Outlook Credential Dumper to harvest credentials stored in Windows registry.
Text: APT32使用Outlook Credential Dumper来获取存储在Windows注册表中的凭证

en_text: APT32 has used Web shells to maintain access to victim websites.
Text: APT32使用Web shells来维持对受害者网站的访问

en_text: APT32 used WMI to deploy their tools on remote machines and to gather information about the Outlook process.
Text: APT32使用WMI在远程机器上部署他们的工具并收集有关Outlook进程的信息

en_text: APT32 has used RTF document that includes an exploit to execute malicious code. (CVE-2017-11882)
Text: APT32使用了包含漏洞的RTF文档来执行恶意代码

en_text: APT32 has used legitimate local admin account credentials.
Text: APT32使用了合法的本地管理账户凭证

en_text: APT32 has used PowerShell-based tools, PowerShell one-liners, and shellcode loaders for execution.
Text: APT32使用了基于PowerShell的工具、PowerShell单线程工具和shellcode加载器来执行

en_text: APT32 has used scheduled task raw XML with a backdated timestamp of June 2, 2016. The group has also set the creation time of the files dropped by the second stage of the exploit to match the creation time of kernel32.dll. Additionally, APT32 has used a random value to modify the timestamp of the file storing the clientID.
Text: APT32使用了预定任务的原始XML，其追溯的时间戳为2016年6月2日。该组织还设置了第二阶段利用所丢弃文件的创建时间，以匹配kernel32.dll的创建时间。此外，APT32还使用一个随机值来修改存储客户端ID的文件的时间戳。

en_text: APT32 enumerated administrative users using the commands net localgroup administrators.
Text: APT32使用命令net localgroup administrators列举了管理用户

en_text: APT32 has used hidden or non-printing characters to help masquerade service names, such as appending a Unicode no-break space character to a legitimate service name. APT32 has also impersonated the legitimate Flash installer file name "install_flashplayer.exe".
Text: APT32使用隐藏的或不打印的字符来帮助伪装服务名称，例如在合法的服务名称上附加一个Unicode无断点空格字符。APT32还冒充合法的Flash安装程序文件名 "install_flashplayer.exe"。

en_text: APT32 has attempted to lure users to execute a malicious dropper delivered via a spearphishing attachment.
Text: APT32试图引诱用户执行一个通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼附件交付的恶意投放器

en_text: APT32 collected the victim's username and executed the whoami command on the victim's machine. APT32 executed shellcode to collect the username on the victim's machine.
Text: APT32收集了受害者的用户名并在受害者的机器上执行whoami命令。APT32执行shellcode以收集受害者机器上的用户名。

en_text: APT32 successfully gained remote access by using pass the ticket.
Text: APT32通过使用pass the ticket成功获得了远程访问

en_text: APT32 has used email for C2 via an Office macro.
Text: APT32通过一个Office宏来使用电子邮件进行C2

en_text: APT32 has infected victims by tricking them into visiting compromised watering hole websites.
Text: APT32通过诱使受害者访问受影响的灌水网站而感染了他们

en_text: APT32 has lured targets to download a Cobalt Strike beacon by including a malicious link within spearphishing emails.
Text: APT32通过在鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件中加入一个恶意链接，诱使目标下载Cobalt Strike信标

en_text: APT32 modified Windows Services to ensure PowerShell scripts were loaded on the system. APT32 also creates a Windows service to establish persistence.
Text: APT32修改了Windows服务，以确保PowerShell脚本在系统中被加载

en_text: APT32 has cleared select event log entries.
Text: APT32已经清除了选定的事件日志条目

en_text: APT32 has used mshta.exe for code execution.
Text: APT32已经使用mshta.exe进行代码执行

en_text: APT32 has used macros, COM scriptlets, and VBS scripts.
Text: APT32已经使用了宏、COM小脚本和VBS脚本

en_text: APT32 has collected the OS version and computer name from victims. One of the group's backdoors can also query the Windows Registry to gather system information, and another macOS backdoor performs a fingerprint of the machine on its first connection to the C&C server. APT32 executed shellcode to identify the name of the infected host.
Text: APT32已经收集了受害者的操作系统版本和计算机名称。该组织的一个后门还可以查询Windows注册表以收集系统信息，另一个macOS后门在其首次连接到C&C服务器时执行机器的指纹识别。APT32执行shellcode以识别受感染主机的名称。

en_text: APT32 have replaced Microsoft Outlook's VbaProject.OTM file to install a backdoor macro for persistence.
Text: APT32已经替换了微软Outlook的VbaProject.OTM文件，以安装一个后门宏来实现持久化

en_text: APT32 ran legitimately-signed executables from Symantec and McAfee which load a malicious DLL. The group also side-loads its backdoor by dropping a library and a legitimate, signed executable (AcroTranscoder).
Text: APT32运行来自赛门铁克和McAfee的合法签名的可执行文件，该文件加载了一个恶意的DLL

en_text: APT32 has deployed tools after moving laterally using administrative accounts.
Text: APT32在使用管理账户横向移动后部署了工具

en_text: APT32 has added JavaScript to victim websites to download additional frameworks that profile and compromise website visitors.
Text: APT32在受害者网站上添加了JavaScript，以下载额外的框架，对网站访问者进行剖析和危害

en_text: APT32 performed network scanning on the network to search for open ports, services, OS finger-printing, and other vulnerabilities.
Text: APT32在网络上进行网络扫描，搜索开放的端口、服务、操作系统指纹和其他漏洞

en_text: APT32 has used PubPrn.vbs within execution scripts to execute malware, possibly bypassing defenses.
Text: APT32在执行脚本中使用PubPrn.vbs来执行恶意软件，可能绕过了防御措施

en_text: APT33 has created a scheduled task to execute a .vbe file multiple times a day.
Text: APT33创建了一个计划任务，每天多次执行一个.vbe文件

en_text: APT33 has sent spearphishing e-mails with archive attachments.
Text: APT33发送了带有档案附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件

en_text: APT33 has sent spearphishing emails containing links to .hta files.
Text: APT33发送了含有.hta文件链接的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件

en_text: APT33 has used a publicly available exploit for CVE-2017-0213 to escalate privileges on a local system.
Text: APT33利用CVE-2017-0213的一个公开可用的漏洞，在本地系统上提升了权限

en_text: APT33 has utilized PowerShell to download files from the C2 server and run various scripts.
Text: APT33利用PowerShell从C2服务器下载文件并运行各种脚本

en_text: APT33 has used SniffPass to collect credentials by sniffing network traffic.
Text: APT33利用SniffPass通过嗅探网络流量来收集凭证

en_text: APT33 has used malicious e-mail attachments to lure victims into executing malware.
Text: APT33利用恶意的电子邮件附件来引诱受害者执行恶意软件

en_text: APT33 has used a variety of publicly available tools like LaZagne to gather credentials.
Text: APT33利用各种公开可用的工具，如LaZagne来收集凭证

en_text: APT33 has used password spraying to gain access to target systems.
Text: APT33利用密码喷洒来获得对目标系统的访问

en_text: APT33 has used compromised Office 365 accounts in tandem with Ruler in an attempt to gain control of endpoints.
Text: APT33利用受损的Office 365账户与Ruler配合，试图获得对端点的控制

en_text: APT33 has used AES for encryption of command and control traffic.
Text: APT33使用AES对指挥和控制通信进行加密

en_text: APT33 has used base64 to encode command and control traffic.
Text: APT33使用base64对命令和控制流量进行编码

en_text: APT33 has used base64 to encode payloads.
Text: APT33使用base64来编码有效载荷

en_text: APT33 has used VBScript to initiate the delivery of payloads.
Text: APT33使用VBScript来启动有效载荷的交付

en_text: APT33 has used a variety of publicly available tools like Gpppassword to gather credentials.
Text: APT33使用了各种公开的工具，如Gpppassword来收集凭证

en_text: APT33 has used a variety of publicly available tools like LaZagne, Mimikatz, and ProcDump to dump credentials.
Text: APT33使用了各种公开可用的工具，如LaZagne、Mimikatz和ProcDump来转储凭证

en_text: APT33 has used valid accounts for initial access and privilege escalation.
Text: APT33使用有效账户进行初始访问和权限升级

en_text: APT33 has attempted to exploit a known vulnerability in WinRAR (CVE-2018-20250), and attempted to gain remote code execution via a security bypass vulnerability (CVE-2017-11774).
Text: APT33试图利用WinRAR的一个已知漏洞（CVE-2018-20250），并试图通过安全绕过漏洞（CVE-2017-11774）获得远程代码执行

en_text: APT33 has attempted to use WMI event subscriptions to establish persistence on compromised hosts.
Text: APT33试图使用WMI事件订阅来建立被攻击主机的持久性

en_text: APT33 has used HTTP over TCP ports 808 and 880 for command and control.
Text: APT33通过TCP 808和880端口使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: APT33 has downloaded additional files and programs from its C2 server.
Text: APT33已经从其C2服务器下载了更多的文件和程序

en_text: APT33 has used FTP to exfiltrate files (separately from the C2 channel).
Text: APT33已经使用FTP来渗出文件（与C2渠道分开）

en_text: APT33 has used HTTP for command and control.
Text: APT33已经使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: APT33 has used WinRAR to compress data prior to exfil.
Text: APT33已经使用WinRAR来压缩数据，然后再外流

en_text: APT33 has lured users to click links to malicious HTML applications delivered via spearphishing emails.
Text: APT33诱使用户点击通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件发送的恶意HTML应用程序的链接

en_text: APT33 has deployed a tool known as DarkComet to the Startup folder of a victim, and used Registry run keys to gain persistence.
Text: APT33在受害者的启动文件夹中部署了一个名为DarkComet的工具，并使用注册表运行键来获得持久性

en_text: APT37's Freenki malware lists running processes using the Microsoft Windows API.
Text: APT37的Freenki恶意软件列出了使用微软Windows API的运行进程

en_text: APT37's has added persistence via the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run\.
Text: APT37的通过注册表键HKCU\Software\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run\增加了持久性

en_text: APT37 has sent spearphishing attachments attempting to get a user to open them.
Text: APT37发送了鱼叉式钓鱼附件，试图让用户打开这些附件

en_text: APT37 obfuscates strings and payloads.
Text: APT37混淆了字符串和有效载荷

en_text: APT37 injects its malware variant, ROKRAT, into the cmd.exe process.
Text: APT37将其恶意软件变体ROKRAT注入cmd.exe进程中

en_text: APT37 has access to destructive malware that is capable of overwriting a machine's Master Boot Record (MBR).
Text: APT37可以获得破坏性的恶意软件，能够覆盖一台机器的主引导记录（MBR）

en_text: APT37 has used Flash Player (CVE-2016-4117, CVE-2018-4878) and Word (CVE-2017-0199) exploits for execution.
Text: APT37利用Flash Player（CVE-2016-4117，CVE-2018-4878）和Word（CVE-2017-0199）漏洞进行执行

en_text: APT37 has used Windows DDE for execution of commands and a malicious VBS.
Text: APT37利用Windows DDE来执行命令和一个恶意的VBS

en_text: APT37 delivers malware using spearphishing emails with malicious HWP attachments.
Text: APT37利用带有恶意HWP附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件来传播恶意软件

en_text: APT37 leverages the Windows API calls: VirtualAlloc(), WriteProcessMemory(), and CreateRemoteThread() for process injection.
Text: APT37利用了Windows API调用VirtualAlloc()，WriteProcessMemory()和CreateRemoteThread()来实现进程注入

en_text: APT37 leverages social networking sites and cloud platforms (AOL, Twitter, Yandex, Mediafire, pCloud, Dropbox, and Box) for C2.
Text: APT37利用社交网站和云平台（AOL、Twitter、Yandex、Mediafire、pCloud、Dropbox和Box）进行C2

en_text: APT37 has used strategic web compromises, particularly of South Korean websites, to distribute malware. The group has also used torrent file-sharing sites to more indiscriminately disseminate malware to victims. As part of their compromises, the group has used a Javascript based profiler called RICECURRY to profile a victim's web browser and deliver malicious code accordingly.
Text: APT37利用战略性的网络妥协，特别是韩国网站，来传播恶意软件。该组织还利用torrent文件共享网站向受害者更不加区分地传播恶意软件。作为他们入侵行动的一部分，该组织使用了一个名为RICECURRY的基于Javascript的剖析器来剖析受害者的网络浏览器，并相应地提供恶意代码。

en_text: APT37 identifies the victim username.
Text: APT37确定了受害者的用户名

en_text: APT37 uses HTTPS to conceal C2 communications.
Text: APT37使用HTTPS来掩盖C2通信

en_text: APT37 has used malware that will issue the command shutdown /r /t 1 to reboot a system after wiping its MBR.
Text: APT37使用的恶意软件会发出关闭的命令 APT37使用的恶意软件会发出关闭命令 APT37使用的恶意软件会发出关机命令 APT37使用的恶意软件将发出关闭命令

en_text: APT37 has used a credential stealer known as ZUMKONG that can harvest usernames and passwords stored in browsers.
Text: APT37使用了一个被称为ZUMKONG的凭证窃取器，可以收获存储在浏览器中的用户名和密码

en_text: APT37 has used an audio capturing utility known as SOUNDWAVE that captures microphone input.
Text: APT37使用了一种被称为SOUNDWAVE的音频捕捉工具，可以捕捉麦克风的输入

en_text: APT37 uses steganography to send images to users that are embedded with shellcode.
Text: APT37使用隐写术向用户发送嵌入了壳代码的图像

en_text: APT37 collects the computer name, the BIOS model, and execution path.
Text: APT37收集计算机名称、BIOS型号和执行路径

en_text: APT37 has downloaded second stage malware from compromised websites.
Text: APT37已经从被攻击的网站下载了第二阶段的恶意软件

en_text: APT37 has collected data from victims' local systems.
Text: APT37已经从受害者的本地系统中收集数据

en_text: APT37 has used the command-line interface.
Text: APT37已经使用了命令行界面

en_text: APT37 has signed its malware with an invalid digital certificates listed as "Tencent Technology (Shenzhen) Company Limited."
Text: APT37用列为 "腾讯科技（深圳）有限公司 "的无效数字证书签署其恶意软件

en_text: APT37 has a Bluetooth device harvester, which uses Windows Bluetooth APIs to find information on connected Bluetooth devices.
Text: APT37有一个蓝牙设备收割机，它使用Windows蓝牙API来寻找连接的蓝牙设备的信息

en_text: APT37 has a function in the initial dropper to bypass Windows UAC in order to execute the next payload with higher privileges.
Text: APT37在初始dropper中有一个绕过Windows UAC的功能，以便以更高的权限执行下一个有效载荷

en_text: APT37 executes shellcode and a VBA script to decode Base64 strings.
Text: APT37执行shellcode和一个VBA脚本来解码Base64字符串

en_text: APT38 installed a port monitoring tool, MAPMAKER, to print the active TCP connections on the local system.
Text: APT38安装了一个端口监控工具MAPMAKER，用于打印本地系统上的活动TCP连接

en_text: APT38 has conducted watering holes schemes to gain initial access to victims.
Text: APT38进行了灌水计划，以获得对受害者的初步接触

en_text: APT38 leveraged Sysmon to understand the processes, services in the organization.
Text: APT38利用Sysmon来了解组织中的流程和服务

en_text: APT38 clears Window Event logs and Sysmon logs from the system.
Text: APT38清除了系统中的Window事件日志和Sysmon日志

en_text: APT38 has used DYEPACK.FOX to manipulate PDF data as it is accessed to remove traces of fraudulent SWIFT transactions from the data displayed to the end user.
Text: APT38使用DYEPACK.FOX在访问PDF数据时对其进行处理，以从显示给最终用户的数据中去除欺诈性SWIFT交易的痕迹

en_text: APT38 has used DYEPACK to manipulate SWIFT messages en route to a printer.
Text: APT38使用DYEPACK来操纵运往打印机的SWIFT报文

en_text: APT38 has used DYEPACK to create, delete, and alter records in databases used for SWIFT transactions.
Text: APT38使用DYEPACK在用于SWIFT交易的数据库中创建、删除和更改记录

en_text: APT38 has used Hermes ransomware to encrypt files with AES256.
Text: APT38使用Hermes赎金软件用AES256加密文件

en_text: APT38 has used several code packing methods such as Themida, Enigma, VMProtect, and Obsidium, to pack their implants.
Text: APT38使用了几种代码打包方法，如Themida、Enigma、VMProtect和Obsidium，来打包其植入物

en_text: APT38 used a backdoor, NESTEGG, that has the capability to download and upload files to and from a victim’s machine.
Text: APT38使用了一个后门，即NESTEGG，它有能力向受害者的机器下载和上传文件

en_text: APT38 has used a custom MBR wiper named BOOTWRECK, which will initiate a system reboot after wiping the victim's MBR.
Text: APT38使用了一个名为BOOTWRECK的自定义MBR擦除器，它将在擦除受害者的MBR后启动系统重启

en_text: APT38 has used a custom MBR wiper named BOOTWRECK to render systems inoperable.
Text: APT38使用了一个名为BOOTWRECK的自定义MBR擦拭器，使系统无法运行

en_text: APT38 has used a utility called CLOSESHAVE that can securely delete a file from the system.
Text: APT38使用了一个名为CLOSESHAVE的工具，可以安全地从系统中删除一个文件

en_text: APT38 has used a command-line tunneler, NACHOCHEESE, to give them shell access to a victim’s machine.
Text: APT38使用了一个命令行隧道器，NACHOCHEESE，使他们有了进入受害者机器的外壳权限

en_text: APT38 has used a custom secure delete function to make deleted files unrecoverable.
Text: APT38使用了一个自定义的安全删除功能，使删除的文件无法恢复

en_text: APT38 used a backdoor, QUICKRIDE, to communicate to the C2 server over HTTP and HTTPS.
Text: APT38使用一个后门QUICKRIDE，通过HTTP和HTTPS与C2服务器通信

en_text: APT38 uses a tool called CLEANTOAD that has the capability to modify Registry keys.
Text: APT38使用一个名为CLEANTOAD的工具，该工具具有修改注册表键的功能

en_text: APT38 used a Trojan called KEYLIME to capture keystrokes from the victim’s machine.
Text: APT38使用一个名为KEYLIME的木马程序，从受害者的机器上捕捉键盘信息

en_text: APT38 used a Trojan called KEYLIME to collect data from the clipboard.
Text: APT38使用一个名为KEYLIME的木马程序从剪贴板上收集数据

en_text: APT39 has sent spearphishing emails in an attempt to lure users to click on a malicious link.
Text: APT39发送了鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，试图引诱用户点击一个恶意链接

en_text: APT39 has sent spearphishing emails in an attempt to lure users to click on a malicious attachment.
Text: APT39发送鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，试图引诱用户点击一个恶意附件

en_text: APT39 has packed tools with UPX, and has repacked a modified version of Mimikatz to thwart anti-virus detection.
Text: APT39将工具与UPX打包，并重新打包了一个修改版的Mimikatz，以阻挡反病毒检测

en_text: APT39 has used Ncrack to reveal credentials.
Text: APT39利用Ncrack泄露了证书

en_text: APT39 has used PowerShell to execute malicious code.
Text: APT39利用PowerShell来执行恶意代码

en_text: APT39 leveraged spearphishing emails with malicious attachments to initially compromise victims.
Text: APT39利用带有恶意附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件，最初损害了受害者

en_text: APT39 leveraged spearphishing emails with malicious links to initially compromise victims.
Text: APT39利用带有恶意链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件，最初控制了受害者

en_text: APT39 has used stolen credentials to compromise Outlook Web Access (OWA).
Text: APT39利用窃取的凭证破坏了Outlook Web Access（OWA）

en_text: APT39 utilized custom scripts to perform internal reconnaissance.
Text: APT39利用自定义脚本来进行内部侦察

en_text: APT39 has used CrackMapExec and a custom port scanner known as BLUETORCH for network scanning.
Text: APT39使用CrackMapExec和一个被称为BLUETORCH的自定义端口扫描器进行网络扫描

en_text: APT39 has used nbtscan and custom tools to discover remote systems.
Text: APT39使用nbtscan和自定义工具来发现远程系统

en_text: APT39 used Remexi to collect usernames from the system.
Text: APT39使用Remexi从系统中收集用户名

en_text: APT39 has used the Smartftp Password Decryptor tool to decrypt FTP passwords.
Text: APT39使用Smartftp Password Decryptor工具来解密FTP密码

en_text: APT39 has used WinRAR and 7-Zip to compress an archive stolen data.
Text: APT39使用WinRAR和7-Zip来压缩被盗数据的档案

en_text: APT39 used secure shell (SSH) to move laterally among their targets.
Text: APT39使用安全外壳（SSH）在其目标中横向移动

en_text: APT39 has used different versions of Mimikatz to obtain credentials.
Text: APT39使用不同版本的Mimikatz来获取证书

en_text: APT39 has used the post exploitation tool CrackMapExec to enumerate network shares.
Text: APT39使用后期开发工具CrackMapExec来列举网络共享

en_text: APT39 has used SQL injection for initial compromise.
Text: APT39使用了SQL注入技术进行初始入侵

en_text: APT39 has used post-exploitation tools including RemCom and the Non-sucking Service Manager (NSSM) to execute processes.
Text: APT39使用了包括RemCom和Non-sucking Service Manager（NSSM）在内的扩展后工具来执行进程

en_text: APT39 has used various tools to proxy C2 communications.
Text: APT39使用了各种工具来代理C2通信

en_text: APT39 has used a command line utility and a network scanner written in python.
Text: APT39使用了一个命令行工具和一个用python编写的网络扫描仪

en_text: APT39 has used a screen capture utility to take screenshots on a compromised host.
Text: APT39使用了一个屏幕捕捉工具在被攻击的主机上进行屏幕截图

en_text: APT39 has used a tool to steal files from the compromised host.
Text: APT39使用了一种工具，从被攻击的主机中窃取文件

en_text: APT39 has used remote access tools that leverage DNS in communications with C2.
Text: APT39使用了远程访问工具，在与C2的通信中利用了DNS

en_text: APT39 has maintained persistence using the startup folder.
Text: APT39使用启动文件夹保持了持久性

en_text: APT39 has used a tool named mfevtpse.exe to proxy C2 communications, closely mimicking a legitimate McAfee file mfevtps.exe.
Text: APT39使用一个名为mfevtpse.exe的工具来代理C2通信，密切模仿合法的McAfee文件mfevtps.exe

en_text: APT39 used custom tools to create SOCK5 and custom protocol proxies between infected hosts.
Text: APT39使用自定义工具在受感染的主机之间创建SOCK5和自定义协议代理

en_text: APT39 has communicated with C2 through files uploaded to DropBox.
Text: APT39通过上传到DropBox的文件与C2进行沟通

en_text: APT39 has modified LNK shortcuts.
Text: APT39修改了LNK的快捷键

en_text: APT39 has downloaded tools to compromised hosts.
Text: APT39已将工具下载到被攻击的主机

en_text: APT39 has installed ANTAK and ASPXSPY web shells.
Text: APT39已经安装了ANTAK和ASPXSPY网络外壳

en_text: APT39 has used Mimikatz, Windows Credential Editor and ProcDump to dump credentials.
Text: APT39已经使用Mimikatz、Windows凭证编辑器和ProcDump来转储凭证

en_text: APT39 has used tools for capturing keystrokes.
Text: APT39已经使用了捕捉键盘的工具

en_text: APT39 has used tools capable of stealing contents of the clipboard.
Text: APT39已经使用了能够窃取剪贴板内容的工具

en_text: APT39 has created scheduled tasks for persistence.
Text: APT39已经为持久性创建了计划任务

en_text: APT39 has used SMB for lateral movement.
Text: APT39已使用SMB进行横向移动

en_text: APT39 has created accounts on multiple compromised hosts to perform actions within the network.
Text: APT39在多个被攻击的主机上创建了账户，以在网络中执行行动

en_text: APT39 has used HTTP in communications with C2.
Text: APT39在与C2的通信中使用了HTTP

en_text: APT3 obfuscates files or information to help evade defensive measures.
Text: APT3混淆了文件或信息，以帮助逃避防御措施

en_text: APT3 will copy files over to Windows Admin Shares (like ADMIN$) as part of lateral movement.
Text: APT3将把文件复制到Windows管理共享（如ADMIN$），作为横向移动的一部分

en_text: APT3 places scripts in the startup folder for persistence.
Text: APT3将脚本放在启动文件夹中，以便持久保存

en_text: APT3 will identify Microsoft Office documents on the victim's computer.
Text: APT3将识别受害者计算机上的微软Office文档

en_text: APT3 enables the Remote Desktop Protocol for persistence. APT3 has also interacted with compromised systems to browse and copy files through RDP sessions.
Text: APT3启用了远程桌面协议的持久性

en_text: APT3 replaces the Sticky Keys binary C:\Windows\System32\sethc.exe for persistence.
Text: APT3取代了Sticky Keys二进制文件C:\Windows\System32\sethc.exe的持久性

en_text: A keylogging tool used by APT3 gathers network information from the victim, including the MAC address, IP address, WINS, DHCP server, and gateway.
Text: APT3使用的一个键盘记录工具从受害者那里收集网络信息，包括MAC地址、IP地址、WINS、DHCP服务器和网关

en_text: APT3 has used a tool to dump credentials by injecting itself into lsass.exe and triggering with the argument "dig."
Text: APT3使用了一个工具，通过将自己注入lsass.exe并触发参数 "dig "来转储凭证

en_text: APT3 has used a tool that can obtain info about local and global group users, power users, and administrators.
Text: APT3使用了一种工具，可以获得本地和全球组用户、权力用户和管理员的信息

en_text: APT3 has used a keylogging tool that records keystrokes in encrypted files.
Text: APT3使用了一种键盘记录工具，在加密文件中记录键盘点击

en_text: APT3 has used tools to dump passwords from browsers.
Text: APT3已经使用工具从浏览器中转储密码

en_text: APT3 has used tools to compress data before exfilling it.
Text: APT3已经使用工具在流出数据之前对其进行压缩

en_text: APT3 has been known to pack their tools.
Text: APT3已经知道他们的工具是打包的

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can obtain information about the local system.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以获得本地系统的信息

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can detect the existence of remote systems.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以检测到远程系统的存在

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can copy files to remote machines.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以将文件复制到远程机器上

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can list out currently running processes.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以列出当前运行的进程

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can enumerate the permissions associated with Windows groups.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以列举出与Windows组相关的权限

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can enumerate current network connections.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以列举当前的网络连接

en_text: APT3 has a tool that creates a new service for persistence.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以为持久性创建一个新的服务

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can locate credentials in files on the file system such as those from Firefox or Chrome.
Text: APT3有一个工具，可以在文件系统的文件中找到证书，如来自Firefox或Chrome的文件

en_text: APT3 has a tool that exfiltrates data over the C2 channel.
Text: APT3有一个工具可以通过C2通道渗出数据

en_text: APT3 has a tool that looks for files and directories on the local file system.
Text: APT3有一个工具可以在本地文件系统中寻找文件和目录

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can delete files.
Text: APT3有一个可以删除文件的工具

en_text: APT3 has a tool that can run DLLs.
Text: APT3有一个可以运行DLLs的工具

en_text: APT3 leverages valid accounts after gaining credentials for use within the victim domain.
Text: APT3在获得在受害者域内使用的凭证后，利用有效账户

en_text: APT3 has used PowerShell on victim systems to download and run payloads after exploitation.
Text: APT3在受害者系统上使用PowerShell，在利用后下载和运行有效载荷

en_text: APT41 created a RAR archive of targeted files for exfiltration.
Text: APT41创建了一个目标文件的RAR档案，用于渗透

en_text: APT41 created user accounts and adds them to the User and Admin groups.
Text: APT41创建了用户账户，并将其添加到用户和管理员组

en_text: APT41 deleted files from the system.
Text: APT41从系统中删除文件

en_text: APT41 performed password brute-force attacks on the local admin account.
Text: APT41对本地管理账户进行了密码暴力攻击

en_text: APT41 malware TIDYELF loaded the main WINTERLOVE component by injecting it into the iexplore.exe process.
Text: APT41恶意软件TIDYELF通过将其注入iexplore.exe进程来加载主WINTERLOVE组件

en_text: APT41 sent spearphishing emails with attachments such as compiled HTML (.chm) files to initially compromise their victims.
Text: APT41发送带有附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件，如编译过的HTML（.chm）文件，以最初损害其受害者

en_text: APT41 gained access to production environments where they could inject malicious code into legitimate, signed files and widely distribute them to end users.
Text: APT41获得了对生产环境的访问权，他们可以将恶意代码注入合法的、经过签名的文件中，并将其广泛分发给终端用户

en_text: APT41 has used DGAs to change their C2 servers monthly.
Text: APT41利用DGAs每月更换其C2服务器

en_text: APT41 leveraged PowerShell to deploy malware families in victims’ environments.
Text: APT41利用PowerShell在受害者的环境中部署恶意软件家族

en_text: APT41 used the storescyncsvc.dll BEACON backdoor to download a secondary backdoor.
Text: APT41利用storecyncsvc.dll BEACON后门下载一个二级后门

en_text: APT41 used a compromised account to create a scheduled task on a system.
Text: APT41利用一个被入侵的账户在一个系统上创建一个计划任务

en_text: APT41 leveraged sticky keys to establish persistence.
Text: APT41利用粘性键来建立持久性

en_text: APT41 exploited CVE-2020-10189 against Zoho ManageEngine Desktop Central, and CVE-2019-19781 to compromise Citrix Application Delivery Controllers (ADC) and gateway devices.
Text: APT41利用针对Zoho ManageEngine Desktop Central的CVE-2020-10189，以及CVE-2019-1978，入侵思杰应用交付控制器（ADC）和网关设备

en_text: APT41 used BITSAdmin to download and install payloads.
Text: APT41使用BITSAdmin下载和安装有效载荷

en_text: APT41 used certutil to download additional files.
Text: APT41使用certutil下载其他文件

en_text: APT41 used DNS for C2 communications.
Text: APT41使用DNS进行C2通信

en_text: APT41 used HTTP to download payloads for CVE-2019-19781 and CVE-2020-10189 exploits.
Text: APT41使用HTTP下载CVE-2019-1978和CVE-2020-10189漏洞的有效载荷

en_text: APT41 used the net share command as part of network reconnaissance.
Text: APT41使用net share命令作为网络侦查的一部分

en_text: APT41 used the netstat command as part of network reconnaissance. The group has also used a malware variant, HIGHNOON, to enumerate active RDP sessions.
Text: APT41使用netstat命令作为网络侦查的一部分。该组织还使用了一个恶意软件变体HIGHNOON，来列举活跃的RDP会话。

en_text: APT41 used Net to execute a system service installed to launch a Cobalt Strike BEACON loader.
Text: APT41使用Net来执行安装的系统服务，以启动Cobalt Strike BEACON加载器

en_text: APT41 used RDP for lateral movement.
Text: APT41使用RDP进行横向移动

en_text: APT41 used the Steam community page as a fallback mechanism for C2.
Text: APT41使用Steam社区页面作为C2的后备机制

en_text: APT41 used the Windows Credential Editor to dump password hashes from memory and authenticate to other user accounts.
Text: APT41使用Windows凭证编辑器从内存中转储密码哈希值，并对其他用户账户进行认证

en_text: APT41 used the WMIEXEC utility to execute whoami commands on remote machines.
Text: APT41使用WMIEXEC工具在远程机器上执行whoami命令

en_text: APT41 used compromised credentials to log on to other systems.
Text: APT41使用被泄露的凭证登录其他系统

en_text: APT41 used compiled HTML (.chm) files for targeting.
Text: APT41使用编译的HTML（.chm）文件作为目标

en_text: APT41 used legitimate executables to perform DLL side-loading of their malware.
Text: APT41使用合法的可执行文件来执行其恶意软件的DLL侧载

en_text: APT41 used cmd.exe /c to execute commands on remote machines.APT41 used a batch file to install persistence for the Cobalt Strike BEACON loader.
Text: APT41使用了cmd.exe APT41使用cmd.exe APT41使用 cmd.exe APT41使用的是cmd.exe

en_text: APT41 used exploit payloads that initiate download via FTP.
Text: APT41使用了通过FTP启动下载的漏洞有效载荷

en_text: APT41 has encrypted payloads using the Data Protection API (DPAPI), which relies on keys tied to specific user accounts on specific machines. APT41 has also environmentally keyed second stage malware with an RC5 key derived in part from the infected system's volume serial number.
Text: APT41使用数据保护API（DPAPI）对有效载荷进行加密，该API依赖于与特定机器上的特定用户账户相联系的密钥。APT41还用RC5密钥对第二阶段的恶意软件进行环境密钥化，该密钥部分来自受感染系统的卷宗序列号

en_text: APT41 used a tool called CLASSFON to covertly proxy network communications.
Text: APT41使用一个名为CLASSFON的工具，秘密地代理网络通信

en_text: APT41 used a ransomware called Encryptor RaaS to encrypt files on the targeted systems and provide a ransom note to the user.
Text: APT41使用一个名为Encryptor RaaS的勒索软件来加密目标系统上的文件，并向用户提供一份赎金说明

en_text: APT41 used a malware variant called GOODLUCK to modify the registry in order to steal credentials.
Text: APT41使用一个名为GOODLUCK的恶意软件变体来修改注册表，以窃取凭证

en_text: APT41 used a malware variant called WIDETONE to conduct port scans on the specified subnets.
Text: APT41使用一个名为WIDETONE的恶意软件变体对指定子网进行端口扫描

en_text: APT41 attempted to masquerade their files as popular anti-virus software.
Text: APT41试图将其文件伪装成流行的反病毒软件

en_text: APT41 attempted to remove evidence of some of its activity by clearing Windows security and system events.
Text: APT41试图通过清除Windows安全和系统事件来消除其一些活动的证据

en_text: APT41 attempted to remove evidence of some of its activity by deleting Bash histories.
Text: APT41试图通过删除巴什历史记录来消除其一些活动的证据

en_text: APT41 collected MAC addresses from victim machines.
Text: APT41收集了受害者机器的MAC地址

en_text: APT41 compromised an online billing/payment service using VPN access between a third-party service provider and the targeted payment service.
Text: APT41损毁了一个在线计费 APT41损害了一个在线计费 APT41损毁了一个在线账单 APT41损害了一个在线账单

en_text: APT41 used legitimate websites for C2 through dead drop resolvers (DDR), including GitHub, Pastebin, and Microsoft TechNet.
Text: APT41通过死锁解析器（DDR）将合法网站用于C2，包括GitHub、Pastebin和Microsoft TechNet

en_text: APT41 created and modified startup files for persistence. APT41 added a registry key in HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Svchost to establish persistence for Cobalt Strike.
Text: APT41为持久性创建并修改了启动文件。APT41在HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Svchost中添加了一个注册表键，以便为Cobalt Strike建立持久性。

en_text: APT41 modified legitimate Windows services to install malware backdoors. APT41 created the StorSyncSvc service to provide persistence for Cobalt Strike.
Text: APT41修改了合法的Windows服务以安装恶意软件后门

en_text: APT41 has executed file /bin/pwd on exploited victims, perhaps to return architecture related information.
Text: APT41已执行文件 APT41已经执行文件 APT41已经执行了文件 APT41已执行的文件

en_text: APT41 used WMI in several ways, including for execution of commands via WMIEXEC as well as for persistence via PowerSploit.
Text: APT41以多种方式使用WMI，包括通过WMIEXEC执行命令，以及通过PowerSploit进行持久化

en_text: APT41 deployed rootkits on Linux systems.
Text: APT41在Linux系统上部署了rootkits

en_text: APT41 deployed Master Boot Record bootkits on Windows systems to hide their malware and maintain persistence on victim systems.
Text: APT41在Windows系统上部署了主引导记录引导程序，以隐藏他们的恶意软件并在受害者系统上保持持久性

en_text: APT41 used VMProtected binaries in multiple intrusions.
Text: APT41在多次入侵中使用了VMP保护的二进制文件

en_text: APT41 leveraged the follow exploits in their operations: CVE-2012-0158, CVE-2015-1641, CVE-2017-0199, CVE-2017-11882, and CVE-2019-3396.
Text: APT41在其行动中利用了以下漏洞

en_text: APT41 deployed a Monero cryptocurrency mining tool in a victim’s environment.
Text: APT41在受害者的环境中部署了一个Monero加密货币挖掘工具

en_text: APT41 used a keylogger called GEARSHIFT on a target system.
Text: APT41在一个目标系统上使用一个名为GEARSHIFT的键盘记录器

en_text: APT41 leveraged code-signing certificates to sign malware when targeting both gaming and non-gaming organizations.
Text: APT41在针对游戏和非游戏组织时利用代码签名证书来签署恶意软件

en_text: APT41 executed file /bin/pwd in activity exploiting CVE-2019-19781 against Citrix devices.
Text: APT41执行文件 APT41执行的文件 APT41的执行文件 APT41被执行的文件

en_text: APT-C-36 has prompted victims to accept macros in order to execute the subsequent payload.
Text: APT-C-36促使受害者接受宏，以执行随后的有效载荷

en_text: APT-C-36 has disguised its scheduled tasks as those used by Google.
Text: APT-C-36将其计划任务伪装成谷歌使用的任务

en_text: APT-C-36 has used ConfuserEx to obfuscate its variant of Imminent Monitor, compressed payload and RAT packages, and password protected encrypted email attachments to avoid detection.
Text: APT-C-36使用ConfuserEx混淆其Imminent Monitor的变体、压缩的有效载荷和RAT包，以及受密码保护的加密电子邮件附件，以避免被发现

en_text: APT-C-36 has used spearphishing emails with password protected RAR attachment to avoid being detected by the email gateway.
Text: APT-C-36使用了带有密码保护的RAR附件的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，以避免被电子邮件网关发现

en_text: APT-C-36 has used a macro function to set scheduled tasks, disguised as those used by Google.
Text: APT-C-36使用了一个宏功能来设置计划任务，伪装成谷歌使用的任务

en_text: APT-C-36 has used port 4050 for C2 communications.
Text: APT-C-36已使用4050端口进行C2通信

en_text: APT-C-36 has downloaded binary data from a specified domain after the malicious document is opened.
Text: APT-C-36在打开恶意文件后，从指定域下载了二进制数据

en_text: APT-C-36 has embedded a VBScript within a malicious Word document which is executed upon the document opening.
Text: APT-C-36在一个恶意的Word文档中嵌入了一个VBScript，在文档打开时被执行

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to collect data from USB devices.
Text: Aria-body具有从USB设备收集数据的能力

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to launch files using ShellExecute.
Text: Aria-body具有使用ShellExecute启动文件的能力

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to gather TCP and UDP table status listings.
Text: Aria-body具有收集TCP和UDP表状态列表的能力

en_text: Aria-body has used ZIP to compress data gathered on a compromised host.
Text: Aria-body使用ZIP来压缩在被入侵主机上收集的数据

en_text: Aria-body has used an encrypted configuration file for its loader.
Text: Aria-body使用了一个加密的配置文件作为其加载器

en_text: Aria-body has established persistence via the Startup folder or Run Registry key.
Text: Aria-body已经通过启动文件夹或运行注册表键建立了持久性

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to download additional payloads from C2.
Text: Aria-body有能力从C2下载额外的有效载荷

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to duplicate a token from ntprint.exe.
Text: Aria-body有能力从ntprint.exe复制一个令牌

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to gather metadata from a file and to search for file and directory names.
Text: Aria-body有能力从文件中收集元数据，并能搜索文件和目录名称

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to inject itself into another process such as rundll32.exe and dllhost.exe.
Text: Aria-body有能力将自己注入另一个进程，如rundll32.exe和dllhost.exe

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to decrypt the loader configuration and payload DLL.
Text: Aria-body有能力解密加载器配置和有效载荷DLL

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to delete files and directories on compromised hosts.
Text: Aria-body有能力删除被攻击主机上的文件和目录

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to identify the location, public IP address, and domain name on a compromised host.
Text: Aria-body有能力识别被入侵主机的位置、公共IP地址和域名

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to identify the hostname, computer name, Windows version, processor speed, machine GUID, and disk information on a compromised host.
Text: Aria-body有能力识别被入侵主机的主机名、计算机名、Windows版本、处理器速度、机器GUID和磁盘信息

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to identify the username on a compromised host.
Text: Aria-body有能力识别被入侵主机上的用户名

en_text: Aria-body has the ability to identify the titles of running windows on a compromised host.

Text: Backdoor.Oldrea添加注册表运行键以实现持久性

en_text: Backdoor.Oldrea writes collected data to a temporary file in an encrypted form before exfiltration to a C2 server.
Text: Backdoor.Oldrea在渗出到C2服务器之前，将收集到的数据以加密形式写入一个临时文件

en_text: BACKSPACE achieves persistence by creating a shortcut to itself in the CSIDL_STARTUP directory.
Text: BACKSPACE 通过在 CSIDL_STARTUP 目录中为自己创建一个快捷方式来实现持久性

en_text: The "ZJ" variant of BACKSPACE allows "ZJ link" infections with Internet access to relay traffic from "ZJ listen" to a command server.
Text: BACKSPACE的 "ZJ "变体允许有互联网接入的 "ZJ link "感染者从 "ZJ listen "向命令服务器转发流量

en_text: The "ZR" variant of BACKSPACE will check to see if known host-based firewalls are installed on the infected systems. BACKSPACE will attempt to establish a C2 channel, then will examine open windows to identify a pop-up from the firewall software and will simulate a mouse-click to allow the connection to proceed.
Text: BACKSPACE的 "ZR "变体将检查已知的基于主机的防火墙是否安装在受感染的系统上。BACKSPACE将试图建立一个C2通道，然后将检查打开的窗口，以确定防火墙软件的弹出窗口，并模拟鼠标点击，以允许连接继续进行。

en_text: BADNEWS has a command to download an .exe and execute it via CreateProcess API. It can also run with ShellExecute.
Text: BACKSPACE的 "ZR "变体将检查已知的基于主机的防火墙是否安装在受感染的系统上。BACKSPACE将试图建立一个C2通道，然后将检查打开的窗口，以确定防火墙软件的弹出窗口，并模拟鼠标点击，以允许连接继续进行。

en_text: BACKSPACE may collect information about running processes.
Text: BACKSPACE可能会收集有关运行进程的信息

en_text: BACKSPACE is capable of enumerating and making modifications to an infected system's Registry.
Text: BACKSPACE能够列举并修改受感染系统的注册表

en_text: BACKSPACE is capable of deleting Registry keys, sub-keys, and values on a victim system.
Text: BACKSPACE能够删除受害者系统上的注册表键、子键和值

en_text: BACKSPACE uses HTTP as a transport to communicate with its command server.
Text: BACKSPACE使用HTTP作为传输方式，与它的命令服务器进行通信

en_text: BACKSPACE attempts to avoid detection by checking a first stage command and control server to determine if it should connect to the second stage server, which performs "louder" interactions with the malware.
Text: BACKSPACE试图通过检查第一阶段的命令和控制服务器来确定它是否应该连接到第二阶段的服务器，后者与恶意软件进行 "更大声 "的互动，从而避免被发现

en_text: BACKSPACE allows adversaries to search for files.
Text: BACKSPACE允许对手搜索文件

en_text: BADCALL communicates on ports 443 and 8000 with a FakeTLS method.
Text: BADCALL采用FakeTLS方式在443和8000端口进行通信

en_text: BADCALL functions as a proxy server between the victim and C2 server.
Text: BADCALL的功能是作为受害者和C2服务器之间的一个代理服务器

en_text: BADCALL encrypts C2 traffic using an XOR/ADD cipher.
Text: BADCALL使用XOR对C2流量进行加密

en_text: BADCALL collects the computer name and host name on the compromised system.
Text: BADCALL收集了被攻击系统上的计算机名称和主机名称

en_text: BADCALL collects the network adapter information.
Text: BADCALL收集网络适配器信息

en_text: BADCALL modifies the firewall Registry key SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\SharedAccess\Parameters\FirewallPolicy\StandardProfileGloballyOpenPorts\List.
Text: BADCALL修改了防火墙注册表键SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\SharedAccess\Parameters\FirewallPolicy\StandardProfileGloballyOpenPorts\List

en_text: BADCALL uses a FakeTLS method during C2.
Text: BADCALL在C2期间使用FakeTLS方法

en_text: BADCALL disables the Windows firewall before binding to a port.
Text: BADCALL在与端口绑定前禁用了Windows防火墙

en_text: BADNEWS installs a registry Run key to establish persistence.
Text: BADNEWS安装了一个注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: BADNEWS creates a scheduled task to establish by executing a malicious payload every subsequent minute.
Text: BADNEWS创建一个计划任务，通过每隔一分钟执行一个恶意的有效载荷来建立

en_text: BADNEWS identifies files with certain extensions from USB devices, then copies them to a predefined directory.
Text: BADNEWS从USB设备中识别具有某些扩展名的文件，然后将它们复制到一个预定义的目录

en_text: BADNEWS monitors USB devices and copies files with certain extensions toa predefined directory.
Text: BADNEWS监控USB设备，并将具有某些扩展名的文件复制到预定义的目录中

en_text: BADNEWS copies files with certain extensions from USB devices toa predefined directory.
Text: BADNEWS将USB设备中带有某些扩展名的文件复制到一个预定义的目录

en_text: BADNEWS copies documents under 15MB found on the victim system to is the user's %temp%\SMB\ folder. It also copies files from USB devices to a predefined directory.
Text: BADNEWS将受害者系统中发现的15MB以下的文件复制到用户的%temp%/SMB/文件夹

en_text: BADNEWS can use multiple C2 channels, including RSS feeds, Github, forums, and blogs.
Text: BADNEWS可以使用多种C2渠道，包括RSS订阅、Github、论坛和博客

en_text: BADNEWS is capable of downloading additional files through C2 channels, including a new version of itself.
Text: BADNEWS能够通过C2渠道下载更多的文件，包括自己的新版本

en_text: BADNEWS is capable of executing commands via cmd.exe.
Text: BADNEWS能够通过cmd.exe执行命令

en_text: BADNEWS attempts to hide its payloads using legitimate filenames.
Text: BADNEWS试图使用合法的文件名来隐藏其有效载荷

en_text: BADNEWS typically loads its DLL file into a legitimate signed Java or VMware executable.
Text: BADNEWS通常将其DLL文件加载到一个合法的已签名的Java或VMware可执行文件中

en_text: BADNEWS establishes a backdoor over HTTP.
Text: BADNEWS通过HTTP建立了一个后门

en_text: BADNEWS checks for new hard drives on the victim, such as USB devices, by listening for the WM_DEVICECHANGE window message.
Text: BADNEWS通过监听WM_DEVICECHANGE窗口信息，检查受害者的新硬盘，如USB设备

en_text: BADNEWS collects C2 information via a dead drop resolver.
Text: BADNEWS通过一个死循环解析器收集C2信息

en_text: BADNEWS encrypts C2 data with a ROR by 3 and an XOR by 0x23.
Text: BADNEWS用3的ROR和0x23的XOR对C2数据进行加密

en_text: BADNEWS encodes C2 traffic with base64.
Text: BADNEWS用base64对C2流量进行编码

en_text: BADNEWS is sometimes signed with an invalid Authenticode certificate in an apparent effort to make it look more legitimate.
Text: BADNEWS有时使用无效的Authenticode证书签名，显然是为了让它看起来更合法。

en_text: BADNEWS has a command to take a screenshot and send it to the C2 server.
Text: BADNEWS有一个命令，可以进行截图并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: BADNEWS has a command to download an .exe and use process hollowing to inject it into a new process.
Text: BADNEWS有一个命令，可以下载一个.exe文件，并使用进程空洞化将其注入一个新进程

en_text: BadPatch captures screenshots in .jpg format and then exfiltrates them.
Text: BadPatch捕获.jpg格式的屏幕截图，然后将其外泄

en_text: BadPatch collects files from the local system that have the following extensions, then prepares them for exfiltration: .xls, .xlsx, .pdf, .mdb, .rar, .zip, .doc, .docx.
Text: BadPatch从本地系统中收集具有以下扩展名的文件，然后准备将它们外泄：.xls, .xlsx, .pdf, .mdb, .rar, .zip, .doc, .docx

en_text: BadPatch collects the OS system, OS version, MAC address, and the computer name from the victim’s machine.
Text: BadPatch从受害者的机器上收集操作系统、操作系统版本、MAC地址和计算机名称

en_text: BadPatch can download and execute or update malware.
Text: BadPatch可以下载并执行或更新恶意软件

en_text: BadPatch uses HTTP for C2.
Text: BadPatch使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: BadPatch uses SMTP for C2.
Text: BadPatch使用SMTP进行C2

en_text: BadPatch uses WMI to enumerate installed security products in the victim’s environment.
