Text: BadPatch使用WMI来列举受害者环境中已安装的安全产品

en_text: BadPatch attempts to detect if it is being run in a Virtual Machine (VM) using a WMI query for disk drive name, BIOS, and motherboard information.
Text: BadPatch试图通过WMI查询磁盘驱动器名称、BIOS和主板信息，来检测它是否在虚拟机（VM）中运行

en_text: BadPatch searches for files with specific file extensions.
Text: BadPatch搜索具有特定文件扩展名的文件

en_text: BadPatch establishes a foothold by adding a link to the malware executable in the startup folder.
Text: BadPatch通过在启动文件夹中添加一个恶意软件可执行文件的链接来建立一个立足点

en_text: BadPatch has a keylogging capability.
Text: BadPatch有一个键盘记录功能

en_text: BadPatch stores collected data in log files before exfiltration.
Text: BadPatch在渗出前将收集到的数据存储在日志文件中

en_text: Bandook contains keylogging capabilities
Text: Bandook包含键盘记录功能 Bandook含有键盘记录功能 Bandook包含键盘记录能力 Bandook包含了键盘记录功能

en_text: Bandook is capable of spawning a Windows command shell.
Text: Bandook能够催生一个Windows命令外壳

en_text: Bandook is capable of taking an image of and uploading the current desktop.
Text: Bandook能够拍摄并上传当前桌面的图像

en_text: Bandook has been launched by starting iexplore.exe and replacing it with Bandook's payload.
Text: Bandook是通过启动iexplore.exe并将其替换为Bandook的有效载荷而启动的

en_text: Bandook has modules that are capable of capturing audio.
Text: Bandook有能够捕获音频的模块

en_text: Bandook has modules that are capable of capturing from a victim's webcam.
Text: Bandook有一些模块能够从受害者的网络摄像头中进行捕捉

en_text: Bankshot gathers domain and account names/information through process monitoring.
Text: Bankhot收集域名和账户名称 Bankhot收集域名和账户名 Bankshot收集域名和账户名称 Bankshot收集域名和账户名

en_text: Bankshot recursively generates a list of files within a directory and sends them back to the control server.
Text: Bankshot 递归地生成一个目录内的文件列表，并将它们送回控制服务器

en_text: Bankshot modifies the time of a file as specified by the control server.
Text: Bankshot按照控制服务器的指定修改文件的时间

en_text: Bankshot collects files from the local system.
Text: Bankshot从本地系统收集文件

en_text: Bankshot decodes embedded XOR strings.
Text: Bankshot对嵌入式XOR字符串进行解码

en_text: Bankshot marks files to be deleted upon the next system reboot and uninstalls and removes itself from the system.
Text: Bankshot会在下一次系统重启时标记要删除的文件，并将自己从系统中卸载和删除

en_text: Bankshot writes data into the Registry key HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Pniumj.
Text: Bankshot将数据写入注册表键HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Microsoft/Pniumj。

en_text: Bankshot uploads files and secondary payloads to the victim's machine.
Text: Bankshot将文件和次级有效载荷上传到受害者的机器上

en_text: Bankshot can terminate a specific process by its process id.
Text: Bankshot可以通过进程的ID来终止一个特定的进程

en_text: Bankshot leverages a known zero-day vulnerability in Adobe Flash to execute the implant into the victims’ machines.
Text: Bankshot利用Adobe Flash中的一个已知的零日漏洞，将其植入受害者的机器中

en_text: Bankshot deletes all artifacts associated with the malware from the infected machine.
Text: Bankshot删除了与被感染机器上的恶意软件相关的所有人工制品

en_text: Bankshot identifies processes and collects the process ids.
Text: Bankshot识别进程并收集进程的ID

en_text: Bankshot uses HTTP for command and control communication.
Text: Bankshot使用HTTP进行命令和控制通信

en_text: Bankshot creates processes using the Windows API calls: CreateProcessA() and CreateProcessAsUserA().
Text: Bankshot使用Windows API调用创建进程

en_text: Bankshot grabs a user token using WTSQueryUserToken and then creates a process by impersonating a logged-on user.
Text: Bankshot使用WTSQueryUserToken抓取一个用户令牌，然后通过冒充登录的用户创建一个进程

en_text: Bankshot generates a false TLS handshake using a public certificate to disguise C2 network communications.
Text: Bankshot使用公共证书生成一个虚假的TLS握手，以伪装C2网络通信

en_text: Bankshot uses the command-line interface to execute arbitrary commands.
Text: Bankshot使用命令行界面来执行任意命令

en_text: Bankshot encodes commands from the control server using a range of characters and gzip.
Text: Bankshot使用一系列的字符和gzip对来自控制服务器的命令进行编码

en_text: Bankshot gathers system information, network addresses, disk type, disk free space, and the operation system version.
Text: Bankshot收集系统信息、网络地址、磁盘类型、磁盘可用空间和操作系统版本

en_text: Bankshot exfiltrates data over its C2 channel.
Text: Bankshot通过其C2渠道渗出数据

en_text: Bankshot binds and listens on port 1058 for HTTP traffic while also utilizing a FakeTLS method.
Text: Bankshot在1058端口对HTTP流量进行绑定和监听，同时还利用了FakeTLS方法

en_text: Bankshot searches for files on the victim's machine.
Text: Bankshot在受害者的机器上搜索文件

en_text: BBK has the ability to download files from C2 to the infected host.
Text: BBK有能力从C2下载文件到受感染的主机

en_text: BBK has the ability to decrypt AES encrypted payloads.
Text: BBK有能力解密AES加密的有效载荷

en_text: BBK has the ability to use cmd to run a Portable Executable (PE) on the compromised host.
Text: BBK有能力使用cmd在被攻击的主机上运行一个可移植执行程序（PE）

en_text: BBK has the ability to use the CreatePipe API to add a sub-process for execution via cmd.
Text: BBK有能力使用CreatePipe API来添加一个子进程，以便通过cmd执行

en_text: BBK has the ability to inject shellcode into svchost.exe.
Text: BBK有能力向svchost.exe注入shellcode

en_text: BBSRAT uses a custom encryption algorithm on data sent back to the C2 server over HTTP.
Text: BBSRAT对通过HTTP发回C2服务器的数据使用了一种自定义的加密算法

en_text: BBSRAT can query service configuration information.
Text: BBSRAT可以查询服务配置信息

en_text: BBSRAT can list file and directory information.
Text: BBSRAT可以列出文件和目录信息

en_text: BBSRAT can list running processes.
Text: BBSRAT可以列出正在运行的进程

en_text: BBSRAT can start, stop, or delete services.
Text: BBSRAT可以启动、停止、或删除服务

en_text: BBSRAT can delete files and directories.
Text: BBSRAT可以删除文件和目录

en_text: BBSRAT can modify service configurations.
Text: BBSRAT可以修改服务配置

en_text: BBSRAT can compress data with ZLIB prior to sending it back to the C2 server.
Text: BBSRAT可以在将数据发回C2服务器之前用ZLIB进行压缩

en_text: BBSRAT uses Expand to decompress a CAB file into executable content.
Text: BBSRAT使用Expand将CAB文件解压为可执行内容

en_text: BBSRAT has been loaded through DLL side-loading of a legitimate Citrix executable that is set to persist through the Registry Run key location HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ssonsvr.exe.
Text: BBSRAT通过DLL侧面加载合法的Citrix可执行文件，该文件被设置为通过注册表运行键位置HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ssonsvr.exe持续存在

en_text: BBSRAT uses GET and POST requests over HTTP or HTTPS for command and control to obtain commands and send ZLIB compressed data back to the C2 server.
Text: BBSRAT通过HTTP或HTTPS使用GET和POST请求进行命令和控制，以获得命令并将ZLIB压缩数据发回给C2服务器

en_text: BISCUIT malware contains a secondary fallback command and control server that is contacted after the primary command and control server.
Text: BISCUIT恶意软件包含一个次要的后备命令和控制服务器，在主命令和控制服务器之后进行联系

en_text: BISCUIT can capture keystrokes.
Text: BISCUIT可以捕获按键

en_text: BISCUIT uses SSL for encrypting C2 communications.
Text: BISCUIT使用SSL对C2通信进行加密

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to download a file from the C2 server.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令，从C2服务器下载一个文件

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to gather the username from the system.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令可以从系统中收集用户名

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to periodically take screenshots of the system.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令可以定期对系统进行截图

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to enumerate running processes and identify their owners.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令可以列举正在运行的进程并识别其所有者

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to launch a command shell on the system.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令可以在系统上启动一个命令外壳

en_text: BISCUIT has a command to collect the processor type, operation system, computer name, uptime, and whether the system is a laptop or PC.
Text: BISCUIT有一个命令来收集处理器类型、操作系统、计算机名称、正常运行时间以及系统是笔记本电脑还是PC

en_text: Bisonal's DLL file and non-malicious decoy file are encrypted with RC4.
Text: Bisonal的DLL文件和非恶意的诱饵文件是用RC4加密的

en_text: Bisonal's dropper creates VBS scripts on the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal的投放器在受害者的机器上创建VBS脚本

en_text: Bisonal deletes its dropper and VBS scripts from the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal将其dropper和VBS脚本从受害者的机器上删除

en_text: Bisonal adds itself to the Registry key HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run\ for persistence.
Text: Bisonal将自己添加到注册表键HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run\中，以便持久保存

en_text: Bisonal can obtain a list of running processes on the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal可以获得受害者机器上的运行进程列表

en_text: Bisonal can launch cmd.exe to execute commands on the system.
Text: Bisonal可以启动cmd.exe，在系统上执行命令

en_text: Bisonal can execute ipconfig on the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal可以在受害者的机器上执行ipconfig

en_text: Bisonal uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: Bisonal使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: Bisonal uses rundll32.exe to execute as part of the Registry Run key it adds: HKEY_CURRENT_USER \Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\"vert" = "rundll32.exe c:\windows\temp\pvcu.dll , Qszdez".
Text: Bisonal使用rundll32.exe作为它添加的注册表运行键的一部分来执行

en_text: Bisonal decodes strings in the malware using XOR and RC4.
Text: Bisonal使用XOR和RC4对恶意软件中的字符串进行解码

en_text: Bisonal has the capability to download files to execute on the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal有能力下载文件，在受害者的机器上执行

en_text: Bisonal has a command to gather system information from the victim’s machine.
Text: Bisonal有一个命令可以从受害者的机器上收集系统信息

en_text: BITSAdmin can be used to create BITS Jobs to upload files from a compromised host.
Text: BITSAdmin可以用来创建BITS工作，从被破坏的主机上传文件

en_text: BITSAdmin can be used to create BITS Jobs to launch a malicious process.
Text: BITSAdmin可以用来创建BITS工作，以启动一个恶意的进程

en_text: BITSAdmin can be used to create BITS Jobs to upload and/or download files from SMB file servers.
Text: BITSAdmin可以用来创建BITS工作，以上传和下载

en_text: BITSAdmin can be used to create BITS Jobs to upload and/or download files.
Text: BITSAdmin可以用来创建BITS工作，以上传和下载

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE has also obfuscated its C2 traffic as normal traffic to sites such as Github.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE还将其C2流量混淆为Github等网站的正常流量

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE has the capability to enumerate files.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE具有列举文件的能力

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE uses Microsoft’s TechNet Web portal to obtain an encoded tag containing the IP address of a command and control server and then communicates separately with that IP address for C2. If the C2 server is discovered or shut down, the threat actors can update the encoded IP address on TechNet to maintain control of the victims’ machines.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE利用微软的TechNet网络门户获得一个包含指挥和控制服务器IP地址的编码标签，然后单独与该IP地址进行C2通信。如果C2服务器被发现或被关闭，威胁者可以更新TechNet上的编码IP地址，以保持对受害者机器的控制。

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE uses Microsoft’s TechNet Web portal to obtain a dead drop resolver containing an encoded tag with the IP address of a command and control server.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE使用微软的TechNet网络门户，获得一个包含有命令和控制服务器IP地址的编码标签的dead drop解析器

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE has the capability to create a reverse shell.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE有能力创建一个反向外壳

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE has the capability to discover processes.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE有能力发现进程

en_text: BLACKCOFFEE has the capability to delete files.
Text: BLACKCOFFEE有删除文件的能力

en_text: BlackEnergy 2 contains a "Destroy" plug-in that destroys data stored on victim hard drives by overwriting file contents.
Text: BlackEnergy 2包含一个 "Destroy "插件，通过覆盖文件内容破坏存储在受害者硬盘上的数据

en_text: The BlackEnergy 3 variant drops its main DLL component and then creates a .lnk shortcut to that file in the startup folder.
Text: BlackEnergy 3的变体会丢弃其主要的DLL组件，然后在启动文件夹中为该文件创建一个.lnk快捷方式

en_text: BlackEnergy gathers a list of installed apps from the uninstall program Registry. It also gathers registered mail, browser, and instant messaging clients from the Registry. BlackEnergy has searched for given file types.
Text: BlackEnergy从卸载程序注册表中收集已安装的应用程序列表。它还从注册表中收集注册的邮件、浏览器和即时通信客户端。BlackEnergy已经搜索了给定的文件类型。

en_text: One variant of BlackEnergy creates a new service using either a hard-coded or randomly generated name.
Text: BlackEnergy的一个变种使用硬编码或随机生成的名称创建一个新的服务

en_text: One variant of BlackEnergy locates existing driver services that have been disabled and drops its driver component into one of those service's paths, replacing the legitimate executable. The malware then sets the hijacked service to start automatically to establish persistence.
Text: BlackEnergy的一个变种找到了已被禁用的现有驱动服务，并将其驱动组件放入这些服务的路径之一，取代了合法的可执行文件。然后，该恶意软件将被劫持的服务设置为自动启动以建立持久性。

en_text: BlackEnergy has conducted port scans on a host.
Text: BlackEnergy对一台主机进行了端口扫描

en_text: BlackEnergy injects its DLL component into svchost.exe.
Text: BlackEnergy将其DLL组件注入svchost.exe中

en_text: BlackEnergy can gather very specific information about attached USB devices, to include device instance ID and drive geometry.
Text: BlackEnergy可以收集关于连接的USB设备的非常具体的信息，包括设备实例ID和驱动器几何形状

en_text: BlackEnergy has used a plug-in to gather credentials from web browsers including FireFox, Google Chrome, and Internet Explorer.
Text: BlackEnergy利用一个插件从包括FireFox、Google Chrome和Internet Explorer在内的网络浏览器中收集凭证

en_text: BlackEnergy is capable of taking screenshots.
Text: BlackEnergy能够进行屏幕截图

en_text: BlackEnergy has gathered information about network IP configurations using ipconfig.exe and about routing tables using route.exe.
Text: BlackEnergy使用ipconfig.exe收集了关于网络IP配置的信息，使用route.exe收集了关于路由表的信息

en_text: BlackEnergy has gathered information about local network connections using netstat.
Text: BlackEnergy使用netstat收集了有关本地网络连接的信息

en_text: BlackEnergy has used Systeminfo to gather the OS version, as well as information on the system configuration, BIOS, the motherboard, and the processor.
Text: BlackEnergy使用Systeminfo收集了操作系统版本，以及系统配置、BIOS、主板和处理器等信息

en_text: BlackEnergy has used a plug-in to gather credentials stored in files on the host by various software programs, including The Bat! email client, Outlook, and Windows Credential Store.
Text: BlackEnergy使用一个插件来收集各种软件程序存储在主机上的凭证，包括The Bat！电子邮件客户端、Outlook和Windows凭证商店

en_text: BlackEnergy attempts to bypass default User Access Control (UAC) settings by exploiting a backward-compatibility setting found in Windows 7 and later.
Text: BlackEnergy试图利用Windows 7和更高版本中的一个向后兼容的设置，绕过默认的用户访问控制（UAC）设置

en_text: BlackEnergy communicates with its C2 server over HTTP.
Text: BlackEnergy通过HTTP与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: BlackEnergy has gathered a process list by using Tasklist.exe.
Text: BlackEnergy通过使用Tasklist.exe收集了一个进程列表

en_text: BlackEnergy has the capability to communicate over a backup channel via plus.google.com.
Text: BlackEnergy有能力通过plus.google.com的备份通道进行通信

en_text: BlackEnergy has run a plug-in on a victim to spread through the local network by using PsExec and accessing admin shares.
Text: BlackEnergy在受害者身上运行了一个插件，通过使用PsExec和访问管理员共享，在本地网络中传播

en_text: BlackEnergy has run a keylogger plug-in on a victim.
Text: BlackEnergy在一个受害者身上运行了一个键盘记录器插件

en_text: The BlackEnergy component KillDisk is capable of deleting Windows Event Logs.
Text: BlackEnergy组件KillDisk能够删除Windows事件日志

en_text: BlackOasis's first stage shellcode contains a NOP sled with alternative instructions that was likely designed to bypass antivirus tools.
Text: BlackOasis的第一阶段shellcode包含一个带有替代指令的NOP橇，很可能是为了绕过反病毒工具

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used JuicyPotato to abuse the SeImpersonate token privilege to escalate from web application pool accounts to NT Authority\SYSTEM.
Text: Blue Mockingbird利用JuicyPotato滥用SeImpersonate令牌权限，从Web应用池账户升级到NT Authority/SYSTEM

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used Windows Explorer to manually copy malicious files to remote hosts over SMB.
Text: Blue Mockingbird利用Windows Explorer通过SMB手动复制恶意文件到远程主机

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used Windows Registry modifications to specify a DLL payload.
Text: Blue Mockingbird利用Windows注册表的修改来指定一个DLL有效载荷

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used wmic.exe and Windows Registry modifications to set the COR_PROFILER environment variable to execute a malicious DLL whenever a process loads the .NET CLR.
Text: Blue Mockingbird利用wmic.exe和Windows注册表的修改来设置COR_PROFILER环境变量，以便在进程加载.NET CLR时执行一个恶意的DLL

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used XMRIG to mine cryptocurrency on victim systems.
Text: Blue Mockingbird利用XMRIG在受害者系统上挖掘加密货币

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used frp, ssf, and Venom to establish SOCKS proxy connections.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用frp、ssf和Venom来建立SOCKS代理连接

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has executed custom-compiled XMRIG miner DLLs using regsvr32.exe.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用regsvr32.exe执行自定义编译的XMRIG矿工DLLs

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has executed custom-compiled XMRIG miner DLLs using rundll32.exe.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用rundll32.exe执行自定义编译的XMRIG矿工DLLs

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used mofcomp.exe to establish WMI Event Subscription persistence mechanisms configured from a *.mof file.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用了mofcomp.exe来建立从*.mof文件配置的WMI事件订阅持久化机制

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used wmic.exe to set environment variables.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用了wmic.exe来设置环境变量

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used batch script files to automate execution and deployment of payloads.
Text: Blue Mockingbird使用批处理脚本文件来自动执行和部署有效载荷

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has collected hardware details for the victim's system, including CPU and memory information.
Text: Blue Mockingbird收集了受害者系统的硬件细节，包括CPU和内存信息

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has gained initial access by exploiting CVE-2019-18935, a vulnerability within Telerik UI for ASP.NET AJAX.
Text: Blue Mockingbird通过利用CVE-2019-18935，即Telerik UI for ASP.NET AJAX中的一个漏洞，获得了初始访问权

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has executed custom-compiled XMRIG miner DLLs by configuring them to execute via the "wercplsupport" service.
Text: Blue Mockingbird通过配置自定义编译的XMRIG矿工DLLs，使其通过 "wercplsupport "服务来执行

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has made their XMRIG payloads persistent as a Windows Service.
Text: Blue Mockingbird已经将他们的XMRIG有效载荷作为一个Windows服务持续存在

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used Mimikatz to retrieve credentials from LSASS memory.
Text: Blue Mockingbird已经使用Mimikatz从LSASS内存中检索证书

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used PowerShell reverse TCP shells to issue interactive commands over a network connection.
Text: Blue Mockingbird已经使用PowerShell反向TCP shells通过网络连接发布交互式命令

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used Windows Scheduled Tasks to establish persistence on local and remote hosts.
Text: Blue Mockingbird已经使用Windows调度任务在本地和远程主机上建立了持久性

en_text: Blue Mockingbird has used Remote Desktop to log on to servers interactively and manually copy files to remote hosts.
Text: Blue Mockingbird已经使用远程桌面以交互方式登录服务器，并手动复制文件到远程主机

en_text: Bonadan has maliciously altered the OpenSSH binary on targeted systems to create a backdoor.
Text: Bonadan恶意地改变了目标系统上的OpenSSH二进制文件，以创建一个后门

en_text: Bonadan can XOR-encrypt C2 communications.
Text: Bonadan可以XOR-加密C2通信

en_text: Bonadan can download additional modules from the C2 server.
Text: Bonadan可以从C2服务器下载额外的模块

en_text: Bonadan can use the ps command to discover other cryptocurrency miners active on the system.
Text: Bonadan可以使用ps命令来发现系统上活跃的其他加密货币矿工

en_text: Bonadan can download an additional module which has a cryptocurrency mining extension.
Text: Bonadan可以下载一个额外的模块，该模块有一个加密货币挖掘扩展

en_text: Bonadan can create bind and reverse shells on the infected system.
Text: Bonadan可以在受感染的系统上创建绑定和反向壳

en_text: Bonadan can find the external IP address of the infected host.
Text: Bonadan可以找到被感染主机的外部IP地址

en_text: Bonadan has discovered the OS version, CPU model, and RAM size of the system it has been installed on.
Text: Bonadan已经发现了它所安装的系统的操作系统版本、CPU型号和内存大小

en_text: Bonadan has discovered the username of the user running the backdoor.
Text: Bonadan已经发现了运行后门的用户的用户名

en_text: BONDUPDATER can download or upload files from its C2 server.
Text: BONDUPDATER可以从其C2服务器下载或上传文件

en_text: BONDUPDATER can read batch commands in a file sent from its C2 server and execute them with cmd.exe.
Text: BONDUPDATER可以读取其C2服务器发送的文件中的批处理命令，并用cmd.exe执行这些命令

en_text: BONDUPDATER can use DNS and TXT records within its DNS tunneling protocol for command and control.
Text: BONDUPDATER可以在其DNS隧道协议中使用DNS和TXT记录进行指挥和控制

en_text: BONDUPDATER uses a DGA to communicate with command and control servers.
Text: BONDUPDATER使用DGA与指挥和控制服务器进行通信

en_text: BONDUPDATER uses -windowstyle hidden to conceal a PowerShell window that downloads a payload.
Text: BONDUPDATER使用-windowstyle hidden来隐藏一个下载有效载荷的PowerShell窗口

en_text: BONDUPDATER persists using a scheduled task that executes every minute.
Text: BONDUPDATER使用一个每分钟执行一次的计划任务来持续进行

en_text: BONDUPDATER is written in PowerShell.
Text: BONDUPDATER是用PowerShell编写的

en_text: BOOSTWRITE has encoded its payloads using a ChaCha stream cipher with a 256-bit key and 64-bit Initialization vector (IV) to evade detection.
Text: BOOSTWRITE使用具有256位密钥和64位初始化向量（IV）的ChaCha流密码对其有效载荷进行编码，以逃避检测

en_text: BOOSTWRITE has used the DWriteCreateFactory() function to load additional modules.
Text: BOOSTWRITE使用了DWriteCreateFactory()函数来加载附加模块

en_text: BOOSTWRITE has used a a 32-byte long multi-XOR key to decode data inside its payload.
Text: BOOSTWRITE使用了一个32字节长的多XOR密钥来解码其有效载荷内的数据

en_text: BOOSTWRITE has exploited the loading of the legitimate Dwrite.dll file by actually loading the gdi library, which then loads the gdiplus library and ultimately loads the local Dwrite dll.
Text: BOOSTWRITE通过实际加载gdi库，然后加载gdiplus库，最终加载本地Dwrite dll，从而利用了合法Dwrite.dll文件的加载

en_text: BOOSTWRITE has been signed by a valid CA.
Text: BOOSTWRITE已经由一个有效的CA签署

en_text: BOOTRASH has used unallocated disk space between partitions for a hidden file system that stores components of the Nemesis bootkit.
Text: BOOTRASH将分区之间未分配的磁盘空间用于存储Nemesis bootkit组件的隐藏文件系统

en_text: BOOTRASH is a Volume Boot Record (VBR) bootkit that uses the VBR to maintain persistence.
Text: BOOTRASH是一个卷引导记录（VBR）的引导工具包，使用VBR来保持持久性

en_text: Brave Prince gathers network configuration information as well as the ARP cache.
Text: Brave Prince收集了网络配置信息以及ARP缓存

en_text: Brave Prince collects hard drive content and system configuration information.
Text: Brave Prince收集硬盘内容和系统配置信息

en_text: Briba installs a service pointing to a malicious DLL dropped to disk.
Text: Briba安装了一个指向丢到磁盘上的恶意DLL的服务

en_text: Briba creates run key Registry entries pointing to malicious DLLs dropped to disk.
Text: Briba创建运行键注册表项，指向丢入磁盘的恶意DLLs

en_text: Briba downloads files onto infected hosts.
Text: Briba下载文件到受感染的主机

en_text: Briba uses rundll32 within Registry Run Keys / Startup Folder entries to execute malicious DLLs.
Text: Briba在注册表运行键中使用rundll32 Briba在注册表运行键内使用rundll32 Briba在注册表运行键中使用rundll32

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used net user /domain to identify account information.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER 已经使用了网友 BRONZE BUTLER 已经使用了网民 BRONZE BUTLER已经使用了网友 BRONZE BUTLER 已经使用过的网友

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has created forged Kerberos Ticket Granting Ticket (TGT) and Ticket Granting Service (TGS) tickets to maintain administrative access.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER创建了伪造的Kerberos票证授予票证（TGT）和票证授予服务（TGS）票证，以维持管理访问

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has collected a list of files from the victim and uploaded it to its C2 server, and then created a new list of specific files to steal.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER从受害者那里收集了一份文件清单，并将其上传到其C2服务器上，然后创建了一个新的特定文件清单来进行盗窃

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER's MSGET downloader uses a dead drop resolver to access malicious payloads.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER的MSGET下载器使用一个死掉的解析器来访问恶意的有效载荷

en_text: The BRONZE BUTLER uploader or malware the uploader uses command to delete the RAR archives after they have been exfiltrated.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER的上传者或上传者使用的恶意软件在RAR档案被渗出后命令删除它们

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER malware has used HTTP for C2.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER恶意软件使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has given malware the same name as an existing file on the file share server to cause users to unwittingly launch and install the malware on additional systems.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER给恶意软件起了与文件共享服务器上现有文件相同的名字，以使用户在不知情的情况下启动并在其他系统上安装该恶意软件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER compromised three Japanese websites using a Flash exploit to perform watering hole attacks.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用Flash漏洞对三个日本网站进行攻击，进行灌水

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used Right-to-Left Override to deceive victims into executing several strains of malware.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用从右到左的覆盖来欺骗受害者执行若干种恶意软件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER used spearphishing emails with malicious Microsoft Word attachments to infect victims.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用带有恶意的Microsoft Word附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件来感染受害者

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used legitimate applications to side-load malicious DLLs.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用合法的应用程序从侧面加载恶意的DLLs

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has made use of Python-based remote access tools.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用了基于Python的远程访问工具

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has exploited Microsoft Office vulnerabilities CVE-2014-4114, CVE-2018-0802, and CVE-2018-0798 for execution.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER利用微软Office漏洞CVE-2014-4114、CVE-2018-0802和CVE-2018-0798进行执行

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used schtasks to register a scheduled task to execute malware during lateral movement.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用schtasks注册了一个计划任务，在横向移动中执行恶意软件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used tools to enumerate software installed on an infected host.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用工具列举了安装在受感染主机上的软件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used net time to check the local time on a target system.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用净时间来检查目标系统的本地时间

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used PowerShell for execution.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了PowerShell进行执行

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used TROJ_GETVERSION to discover system services.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了TROJ_GETVERSION来发现系统服务

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used VBS and VBE scripts for execution.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了VBS和VBE脚本来执行

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used various tools (such as Mimikatz and WCE) to perform credential dumping.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了各种工具（如Mimikatz和WCE）来进行凭证转储

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used various tools to download files, including DGet (a similar tool to wget).
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了各种工具来下载文件，包括DGet（一种类似于wget的工具）

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used batch scripts and the command-line interface for execution.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了批处理脚本和命令行界面来执行

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used a Windows 10 specific tool and xxmm to bypass UAC for privilege escalation.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了一个Windows 10特定的工具和xxmm来绕过UAC进行权限升级

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used a batch script that adds a Registry Run key to establish malware persistence.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了一个批处理脚本，添加了一个注册表运行键来建立恶意软件的持久性

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used a tool to capture screenshots.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER使用了一种工具来捕捉屏幕截图

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has attempted to get users to launch malicious Microsoft Word attachments delivered via spearphishing emails.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER试图让用户启动通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件传递的恶意微软Word附件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER typically use ping and Net to enumerate systems.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER通常使用ping和Net来列举系统

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER downloads encoded payloads and decodes them on the victim.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER下载编码的有效载荷并在受害者身上解码

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER downloader code has included "0" characters at the end of the file to inflate the file size in a likely attempt to evade anti-virus detection.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER下载器代码在文件末尾包含了 "0 "字符，以扩大文件大小，这很可能是为了逃避反病毒检测

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has exfiltrated files stolen from local systems.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER已经渗出了从本地系统盗取的文件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has exfiltrated files stolen from file shares.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER已经渗出了从文件共享中窃取的文件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used RC4 encryption (for Datper malware) and AES (for xxmm malware) to obfuscate HTTP traffic. BRONZE BUTLER has also used a tool called RarStar that encodes data with a custom XOR algorithm when posting it to a C2 server.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER已经使用RC4加密（用于Datper恶意软件）和AES（用于xxmm恶意软件）来混淆HTTP流量。BRONZE BUTLER还使用了一个名为RarStar的工具，在将数据发布到C2服务器时，用自定义的XOR算法进行编码。

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used at to register a scheduled task to execute malware during lateral movement.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER用at注册了一个计划任务，在横向移动中执行恶意软件

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has masked executables with document file icons including Word and Adobe PDF.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER用文档文件图标屏蔽了可执行文件，包括Word和Adobe PDF

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has used steganography in multiple operations to conceal malicious payloads.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER在多次行动中使用隐写术来隐藏恶意的有效载荷

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has incorporated code into several tools that attempts to terminate anti-virus processes.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER在几个工具中加入了代码，试图终止反病毒进程

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has compressed data into password-protected RAR archives prior to exfiltration.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER在渗出前已将数据压缩到有密码保护的RAR档案中

en_text: BRONZE BUTLER has placed malware on file shares and given it the same name as legitimate documents on the share.
Text: BRONZE BUTLER在文件共享中放置了恶意软件，并赋予其与共享中合法文件相同的名称

en_text: BS2005 uses Base64 encoding for communication in the message body of an HTTP request.
Text: BS2005在HTTP请求的信息体中使用Base64编码进行通信

en_text: BUBBLEWRAP can communicate using HTTP or HTTPS.
Text: BUBBLEWRAP可以使用HTTP或HTTPS进行通信

en_text: BUBBLEWRAP can communicate using SOCKS.
Text: BUBBLEWRAP可以使用SOCKS进行通信

en_text: BUBBLEWRAP collects system information, including the operating system version and hostname.
Text: BUBBLEWRAP收集系统信息，包括操作系统版本和主机名

en_text: build_downer has added itself to the Registry Run key as "NVIDIA" to appear legitimate.
Text: build_downer将自己添加到注册表运行键中，成为 "NVIDIA"，以显示合法

en_text: build_downer has the ability to download files from C2 to the infected host.
Text: build_downer具有从C2下载文件到受感染主机的能力

en_text: build_downer can extract malware from a downloaded JPEG.
Text: build_downer可以从下载的JPEG中提取恶意软件

en_text: build_downer has the ability to detect if the infected host is running an anti-virus process.
Text: build_downer有能力检测被感染的主机是否正在运行一个反病毒程序

en_text: build_downer has the ability to add itself to the Registry Run key for persistence.
Text: build_downer有能力将自己添加到注册表的运行键中，以便持久化

en_text: build_downer has the ability to determine the local time to ensure malware installation only happens during the hours that the infected system is active.
Text: build_downer有能力确定当地时间，以确保恶意软件的安装只发生在受感染系统的活动时间

en_text: build_downer has the ability to use the WinExec API to execute malware on a compromised host.
Text: build_downer有能力使用WinExec API在被攻击的主机上执行恶意软件

en_text: build_downer has the ability to send system volume information to C2.
Text: build_downer有能力向C2发送系统体积信息

en_text: Bundlore will enumerate the macOS version to determine which follow-on behaviors to execute.
Text: Bundlore将列举macOS的版本，以决定执行哪些后续行为

en_text: Bundlore has disguised a malicious .app file as a Flash Player update.
Text: Bundlore将一个恶意的.app文件伪装成Flash Player更新

en_text: Bundlore can install malicious browser extensions that are used to hijack user searches.
Text: Bundlore可以安装恶意的浏览器扩展，用来劫持用户的搜索

en_text: Bundlore can change macOS security settings and browser preferences to enable follow-on behaviors.
Text: Bundlore可以改变macOS安全设置和浏览器偏好，以启用后续行为

en_text: Bundlore can use AppleScript to inject malicious JavaScript into a browser.
Text: Bundlore可以使用AppleScript将恶意的JavaScript注入到浏览器中

en_text: Bundlore can persist via a LaunchAgent.
Text: Bundlore可以通过LaunchAgent持续存在

en_text: Bundlore can persist via a LaunchDaemon.
Text: Bundlore可以通过LaunchDaemon持续存在

en_text: Bundlore can execute JavaScript by injecting it into the victim's browser.
Text: Bundlore可以通过将JavaScript注入受害者的浏览器来执行它

en_text: Bundlore can download and execute new versions of itself.
Text: Bundlore可以下载并执行自己的新版本

en_text: Bundlore has leveraged /bin/sh and /bin/bash to execute commands on the victim machine.
Text: Bundlore利用了 Bundlore借助于 Bundlore利用 Bundlore公司利用了

en_text: Bundlore uses HTTP requests for C2.
Text: Bundlore使用HTTP请求进行C2

en_text: Bundlore has used openssl to decrypt AES encrypted payload data. Bundlore has also used base64 and RC4 with a hardcoded key to deobfuscate data.
Text: Bundlore使用openssl来解密AES加密的有效载荷数据。Bundlore还使用base64和RC4与硬编码的密钥对数据进行解惑。

en_text: Bundlore has used Python scripts to execute payloads.
Text: Bundlore使用Python脚本来执行有效载荷

en_text: Bundlore has used the ps command to list processes.
Text: Bundlore使用了ps命令来列出进程

en_text: Bundlore has attempted to get users to execute a malicious .app file that looks like a Flash Player update.
Text: Bundlore试图让用户执行一个恶意的.app文件，该文件看起来像一个Flash Player更新

en_text: Bundlore has been spread through malicious advertisements on websites.
Text: Bundlore是通过网站上的恶意广告传播的

en_text: Bundlore prompts the user for their credentials.
Text: Bundlore提示用户提供他们的凭证

en_text: Bundlore has obfuscated data with base64, AES, RC4, and bz2.
Text: Bundlore用base64、AES、RC4和bz2对数据进行了混淆处理

en_text: Bundlore creates a new key pair with ssh-keygen and drops the newly created user key in authorized_keys to enable remote login.
Text: Bundlore用ssh-keygen创建一个新的密钥对，并将新创建的用户密钥放到authorized_keys中，以实现远程登录

en_text: Bundlore has the ability to enumerate what browser is being used as well as version information for Safari.
Text: Bundlore有能力列举正在使用的浏览器以及Safari的版本信息

en_text: The C2 server response to a beacon sent by a variant of Emissary contains a 36-character GUID value that is used as an encryption key for subsequent network communications. Some variants of Emissary use various XOR operations to encrypt C2 data.
Text: C2服务器对Emissary变种发送的信标的响应包含一个36字符的GUID值，该值被用作后续网络通信的加密密钥。一些变种的Emissary使用各种XOR操作来加密C2数据。

en_text: Cachedump can extract cached password hashes from cache entry information.
Text: Cachedump可以从缓存条目信息中提取缓存的密码哈希值

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to capture screenshots and webcam photos.
Text: Cadelspy具有捕获屏幕截图和网络摄像头照片的能力

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to record audio from the compromised host.
Text: Cadelspy有能力从被攻击的主机上录制音频

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to steal data from the clipboard.
Text: Cadelspy有能力从剪贴板上窃取数据

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to discover information about the compromised host.
Text: Cadelspy有能力发现被攻击主机的信息

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to log keystrokes on the compromised host.
Text: Cadelspy有能力记录被攻击主机上的击键

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to compress stolen data into a .cab file.
Text: Cadelspy有能力将被盗数据压缩成一个.cab文件

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to steal information about printers and the documents sent to printers.
Text: Cadelspy有能力窃取关于打印机和发送到打印机的文件的信息

en_text: Cadelspy has the ability to identify open windows on the compromised host.
Text: Cadelspy有能力识别被攻击主机上的开放窗口

en_text: The CALENDAR malware communicates through the use of events in Google Calendar.
Text: CALENDAR恶意软件通过使用谷歌日历中的事件进行交流

en_text: CALENDAR has a command to run cmd.exe to execute commands.
Text: CALENDAR有一个运行cmd.exe的命令，可以执行命令

en_text: Calisto's installation file is an unsigned DMG image under the guise of Intego’s security solution for mac.
Text: Calisto的安装文件是一个没有签名的DMG图像，打着Intego的Mac安全解决方案的幌子

en_text: Calisto adds a .plist file to the /Library/LaunchAgents folder to maintain persistence.
Text: Calisto将一个.plist文件添加到 Calisto将一个.plist文件加入到 Calisto将一个.plist文件添加至 Calisto将一个.plist文件添加到了

en_text: Calisto can collect data from user directories.
Text: Calisto可以从用户目录中收集数据

en_text: Calisto uses launchctl to enable screen sharing on the victim’s machine.
Text: Calisto使用launchctl来启用受害者机器上的屏幕共享

en_text: Calisto uses the zip -r command to compress the data collected on the local system.
Text: Calisto使用zip -r命令来压缩本地系统上收集的数据

en_text: Calisto uses a hidden directory named .calisto to store data from the victim’s machine before exfiltration.
Text: Calisto使用一个名为.calisto的隐藏目录来存储受害者机器上的数据，然后再渗出

en_text: Calisto collects Keychain storage data and copies those passwords/tokens to a file.
Text: Calisto收集Keychain存储数据并复制这些密码

en_text: Calisto collects information on bookmarks from Google Chrome.
Text: Calisto收集来自谷歌浏览器的书签信息

en_text: Calisto presents an input prompt asking for the user's login and password.
Text: Calisto提出一个输入提示，询问用户的登录和密码

en_text: Calisto adds permissions and remote logins to all users.
Text: Calisto为所有用户增加权限和远程登录

en_text: Calisto has the capability to use rm -rf to remove folders and files from the victim's machine.
Text: Calisto有能力使用rm -rf从受害者的机器上删除文件夹和文件

en_text: Calisto has the capability to upload and download files to the victim's machine.
Text: Calisto有能力向受害者的机器上传和下载文件

en_text: Calisto has the capability to add its own account to the victim's machine.
Text: Calisto有能力在受害者的机器上添加自己的账户

en_text: Calisto runs the ifconfig command to obtain the IP address from the victim’s machine.
Text: Calisto运行ifconfig命令，从受害者的机器上获得IP地址

en_text: CallMe uses AES to encrypt C2 traffic.
Text: CallMe使用AES来加密C2流量

en_text: CallMe exfiltrates data to its C2 server over the same protocol as C2 communications.
Text: CallMe通过与C2通信相同的协议将数据外流到其C2服务器

en_text: CallMe has the capability to download a file to the victim from the C2 server.
Text: CallMe有能力从C2服务器下载一个文件给受害者

en_text: CallMe has the capability to create a reverse shell on victims.
Text: CallMe有能力在受害者身上创建一个反向外壳

en_text: Cannon can collect the current time zone information from the victim’s machine.
Text: Cannon可以从受害者的机器上收集当前的时区信息

en_text: Cannon can gather system information from the victim’s machine such as the OS version, machine name, and drive information.
Text: Cannon可以从受害者的机器上收集系统信息，如操作系统版本、机器名称和驱动器信息

en_text: Cannon adds the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon to establish persistence.
Text: Cannon添加注册表键HKCUSoftware\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon以建立持久性

en_text: Carbanak installs VNC server software that executes through rundll32.
Text: Carbanak安装的VNC服务器软件是通过rundll32执行的

en_text: Carbanak encrypts strings to make analysis more difficult.
Text: Carbanak对字符串进行加密，使分析更加困难

en_text: Carbanak malware installs itself as a service to provide persistence and SYSTEM privileges.
Text: Carbanak恶意软件将自己安装成一个服务，以提供持久性和SYSTEM权限

en_text: The Carbanak malware communicates to its command server using HTTP with an encrypted payload.
Text: Carbanak恶意软件使用HTTP与它的命令服务器进行通信，并有一个加密的有效载荷

en_text: Carbanak has copied legitimate service names to use for malicious services.
Text: Carbanak复制了合法的服务名称，用于恶意服务

en_text: Carbanak obtains Windows logon password details.
Text: Carbanak获得了Windows登录密码的详细信息

en_text: Carbanak logs key strokes for configured processes and sends them back to the C2 server.
Text: Carbanak记录了配置进程的按键，并将其发送回C2服务器

en_text: Carbanak checks the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Internet Settings for proxy configurations information.
Text: Carbanak检查注册表键HKCUSoftware\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Internet Settings的代理配置信息

en_text: Carbanak has named malware "svchost.exe," which is the name of the Windows shared service host program.
Text: Carbanak将恶意软件命名为 "svchost.exe"，这是Windows共享服务主机程序的名称

en_text: Carbanak performs desktop video recording and captures screenshots of the desktop and sends it to the C2 server.
Text: Carbanak进行桌面视频记录，并捕获桌面的屏幕截图，并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Carbanak can create a Windows account.
Text: Carbanak可以创建一个Windows账户

en_text: Carbanak may use netsh to add local firewall rule exceptions.
Text: Carbanak可以使用netsh来添加本地防火墙规则例外

en_text: Carbanak lists running processes.
Text: Carbanak列出了正在运行的进程

en_text: Carbanak used legitimate programs such as AmmyyAdmin and Team Viewer for remote interactive C2 to target systems.
Text: Carbanak使用AmmyyAdmin和Team Viewer等合法程序对目标系统进行远程互动C2

en_text: Carbanak has used a VBScript named "ggldr" that uses Google Apps Script, Sheets, and Forms services for C2.
Text: Carbanak使用了一个名为 "ggldr "的VBScript，该VBScript使用Google Apps的脚本、表单和表格服务，用于C2

en_text: Carbanak downloads an executable and injects it directly into a new process.
Text: Carbanak下载一个可执行文件，并将其直接注入一个新进程

en_text: Carbanak actors used legitimate credentials of banking employees to perform operations that sent them millions of dollars.
Text: Carbanak行动者利用银行雇员的合法凭证进行操作，向他们发送了数百万美元

en_text: Carbanak searches recursively for Outlook personal storage tables (PST) files within user directories and sends them back to the C2 server.
Text: Carbanak以递归方式搜索用户目录内的Outlook个人存储表（PST）文件，并将其送回C2服务器

en_text: Carbanak encodes the message body of HTTP traffic with Base64.
Text: Carbanak用Base64对HTTP流量的信息体进行编码

en_text: Carbanak encrypts the message body of HTTP traffic with RC2 (in CBC mode). Carbanak also uses XOR with random keys for its communications.
Text: Carbanak用RC2（CBC模式）对HTTP通信的信息体进行加密

en_text: Carbanak has a plugin for VNC and Ammyy Admin Tool.
Text: Carbanak有一个VNC和Ammyy管理工具的插件

en_text: Carbanak has a command to create a reverse shell.
Text: Carbanak有一个命令来创建一个反向的shell

en_text: Carbanak has a command to delete files.
Text: Carbanak有一个删除文件的命令

en_text: Carbanak stores a configuration files in the startup directory to automatically execute commands in order to persist across reboots.
Text: Carbanak在启动目录中存储了一个配置文件，以自动执行命令，以便在重启后持续存在

en_text: Carbanak enables concurrent Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) sessions.
Text: Carbanak支持并发的远程桌面协议（RDP）会话

en_text: Carberp has queried the infected system's registry searching for specific registry keys associated with antivirus products.
Text: Carberp查询了被感染系统的注册表，寻找与防病毒产品相关的特定注册表键

en_text: Carberp's bootkit can inject a malicious DLL into the address space of running processes.
Text: Carberp的bootkit可以将一个恶意的DLL注入到运行进程的地址空间

en_text: Carberp's passw.plug plugin can gather account information from multiple instant messaging, email, and social media services, as well as FTP, VNC, and VPN clients.
Text: Carberp的passw.plug插件可以从多个即时通讯、电子邮件和社交媒体服务，以及FTP、VNC和VPN客户端收集账户信息

en_text: Carberp's passw.plug plugin can gather passwords saved in Opera, Internet Explorer, Safari, Firefox, and Chrome.
Text: Carberp的passw.plug插件可以收集保存在Opera、Internet Explorer、Safari、Firefox和Chrome的密码

en_text: Carberp can download and execute new plugins from the C2 server.
Text: Carberp可以从C2服务器下载并执行新的插件

en_text: Carberp can capture display screenshots with the screens_dll.dll plugin.
Text: Carberp可以通过screen_dll.dll插件捕获显示屏幕截图

en_text: Carberp can start a remote VNC session by downloading a new plugin.
Text: Carberp可以通过下载一个新的插件来启动一个远程VNC会话

en_text: Carberp has exploited multiple Windows vulnerabilities (CVE-2010-2743, CVE-2010-3338, CVE-2010-4398, CVE-2008-1084) and a .NET Runtime Optimization vulnerability for privilege escalation.
Text: Carberp利用多个Windows漏洞（CVE-2010-2743、CVE-2010-3338、CVE-2010-4398、CVE-2008-1084）和一个.NET运行时优化漏洞进行权限升级

en_text: Carberp has used the NtQueryDirectoryFile and ZwQueryDirectoryFile functions to hide files and directories.
Text: Carberp使用了NtQueryDirectoryFile和ZwQueryDirectoryFile函数来隐藏文件和目录

en_text: Carberp has used XOR-based encryption to mask C2 server locations within the trojan.
Text: Carberp使用了基于XOR的加密技术来掩盖木马中的C2服务器位置

en_text: Carberp has used user mode rootkit techniques to remain hidden on the system.
Text: Carberp使用了用户模式的rootkit技术，在系统中保持隐蔽

en_text: Carberp has attempted to disable security software by creating a suspended process for the security software and injecting code to delete antivirus core files when the process is resumed.
Text: Carberp试图通过为安全软件创建一个暂停的进程，并在进程恢复时注入代码以删除杀毒软件的核心文件，从而使安全软件失效

en_text: Carberp has collected a list of running processes.
Text: Carberp收集了一个正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Carberp has exfiltrated data via HTTP to already established C2 servers.
Text: Carberp通过HTTP将数据外流到已经建立的C2服务器

en_text: Carberp has maintained persistence by placing itself inside the current user's startup folder.
Text: Carberp通过把自己放在当前用户的启动文件夹中来保持持久性

en_text: Carberp has queued an APC routine to explorer.exe by calling ZwQueueApcThread.
Text: Carberp通过调用ZwQueueApcThread将一个APC程序排到explorer.exe

en_text: Carberp has masqueraded as Windows system file names, as well as "chkntfs.exe" and "syscron.exe".
Text: Carberp伪装成Windows系统文件名，以及 "chkntfs.exe "和 "syscron.exe"

en_text: Carberp has collected the operating system version from the infected system.
Text: Carberp已经收集了受感染系统的操作系统版本

en_text: Carberp has connected to C2 servers via HTTP.
Text: Carberp已经通过HTTP连接到C2服务器

en_text: Carberp has removed various hooks before installing the trojan or bootkit to evade sandbox analysis or other analysis software.
Text: Carberp在安装木马或bootkit之前已经删除了各种钩子，以规避沙盒分析或其他分析软件

en_text: Carberp has created a hidden file in the Startup folder of the current user.
Text: Carberp在当前用户的启动文件夹中创建了一个隐藏文件

en_text: Carberp has hooked several Windows API functions during its Man in the Browser attack to steal credentials.
Text: Carberp在其 "浏览器中的人 "的攻击过程中钩住了几个Windows API函数，以窃取凭证

en_text: Carberp has searched the Image File Execution Options registry key for "Debugger" within every subkey.
Text: Carberp在图像文件执行选项注册表的每一个子键中搜索了 "调试器"

en_text: Carberp has installed a bootkit on the system to maintain persistence.
Text: Carberp在系统上安装了一个bootkit以保持持久性

en_text: Carbon creates several tasks for later execution to continue persistence on the victim’s machine.
Text: Carbon创建了几个任务供以后执行，以继续在受害者的机器上持久存在

en_text: Carbon creates a base directory that contains the files and folders that are collected.
Text: Carbon创建了一个基础目录，其中包含被收集的文件和文件夹

en_text: Carbon decrypts task and configuration files for execution.
Text: Carbon对任务和配置文件进行解密，以便执行

en_text: Carbon can list the processes on the victim’s machine.
Text: Carbon可以列出受害者机器上的进程

en_text: Carbon can collect the IP address of the victims and other computers on the network using the commands: ipconfig -all nbtstat -n, and nbtstat -s.
Text: Carbon可以使用以下命令收集受害者和网络上其他计算机的IP地址：ipconfig -all nbtstat -n，以及nbtstat -s

en_text: Carbon encrypts configuration files and tasks for the malware to complete using CAST-128 algorithm.
Text: Carbon使用CAST-128算法对配置文件和恶意软件完成的任务进行加密

en_text: Carbon uses HTTP to send data to the C2 server.
Text: Carbon使用HTTP向C2服务器发送数据

en_text: Carbon uses the netstat -r and netstat -an commands.
Text: Carbon使用netstat -r和netstat -an命令

en_text: Carbon uses TCP and UDP for C2.
Text: Carbon使用TCP和UDP进行C2

en_text: Carbon uses the command net time \127.0.0.1 to get information the system’s time.
Text: Carbon使用命令net time\127.0.0.1来获取系统的时间信息

en_text: Carbon establishes persistence by creating a service and naming it based off the operating system version running on the current machine.
Text: Carbon通过创建一个服务并根据当前机器上运行的操作系统版本对其进行命名来建立持久性

en_text: Carbon has a command to inject code into a process.
Text: Carbon有一个向进程注入代码的命令

en_text: Carbon runs the net group command to list accounts on the system.
Text: Carbon运行net group命令来列出系统上的账户

en_text: Cardinal RAT can capture screenshots.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以捕获屏幕截图

en_text: Cardinal RAT can collect the username from a victim machine.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以从受害者的机器上收集用户名

en_text: Cardinal RAT can log keystrokes.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以记录击键

en_text: Cardinal RAT can communicate over multiple C2 host and port combinations.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以通过多个C2主机和端口组合进行通信

en_text: Cardinal RAT can download and execute additional payloads.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以下载和执行额外的有效载荷

en_text: Cardinal RAT can execute commands.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以执行命令

en_text: Cardinal RAT can uninstall itself, including deleting its executable.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以自行卸载，包括删除其可执行文件

en_text: Cardinal RAT can act as a reverse proxy.
Text: Cardinal RAT可以作为一个反向代理

en_text: Cardinal RAT sets HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows\Load to point to its executable.
Text: Cardinal RAT设置HKCUSoftware\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows\Load以指向其可执行文件

en_text: Cardinal RAT applies compression to C2 traffic using the ZLIB library.
Text: Cardinal RAT使用ZLIB库对C2流量进行压缩

en_text: Cardinal RAT uses a secret key with a series of XOR and addition operations to encrypt C2 traffic.
Text: Cardinal RAT使用带有一系列XOR和加法运算的秘密密钥来加密C2流量

en_text: Cardinal RAT establishes Persistence by setting the  HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows\Load Registry key to point to its executable.
Text: Cardinal RAT通过设置HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows\Load注册表键值指向其可执行文件来建立持久性

en_text: CARROTBALL has used a custom base64 alphabet to decode files.
Text: CARROTBALL使用了一个自定义的base64字母表来解码文件

en_text: CARROTBALL has been executed through users being lured into opening malicious e-mail attachments.
Text: CARROTBALL是通过用户被诱导打开恶意的电子邮件附件而执行的

en_text: CARROTBALL has the ability to download and install a remote payload.
Text: CARROTBALL有能力下载和安装一个远程有效载荷

en_text: CARROTBALL has the ability to use FTP in C2 communications.
Text: CARROTBALL有能力在C2通信中使用FTP

en_text: CARROTBAT has the ability to delete downloaded files from a compromised host.
Text: CARROTBAT有能力从被攻击的主机上删除下载的文件

en_text: CARROTBAT has the ability to determine the operating system of the compromised host and whether Windows is being run with x86 or x64 architecture.
Text: CARROTBAT有能力确定被攻击的主机的操作系统，以及Windows是以x86还是x64架构运行

en_text: CARROTBAT has the ability to download and execute a remote file via certutil.
Text: CARROTBAT有能力通过certutil下载和执行一个远程文件

en_text: CARROTBAT has the ability to download a base64 encoded payload and execute obfuscated commands on the infected host.
Text: CARROTBAT有能力下载一个base64编码的有效载荷，并在受感染的主机上执行混淆的命令

en_text: CARROTBAT has the ability to execute command line arguments on a compromised host.
Text: CARROTBAT有能力在被攻击的主机上执行命令行参数

en_text: Catchamas creates three Registry keys to establish persistence by adding a New Service.
Text: Catchamas创建了三个注册表键，通过添加一个新服务来建立持久性

en_text: Catchamas gathers the Mac address, IP address, and the network adapter information from the victim’s machine.
Text: Catchamas从受害者的机器上收集Mac地址、IP地址和网络适配器信息

en_text: Catchamas collects keystrokes from the victim’s machine.
Text: Catchamas从受害者的机器上收集键盘信息

en_text: Catchamas captures screenshots based on specific keywords in the window’s title.
Text: Catchamas根据窗口标题中的特定关键词来捕捉屏幕截图

en_text: Catchamas obtains application windows titles and then determines which windows to perform Screen Capture on.
Text: Catchamas获取应用程序窗口的标题，然后确定哪些窗口要进行屏幕捕捉

en_text: Catchamas stores the gathered data from the machine in .db files and .bmp files under four separate locations.
Text: Catchamas将收集到的机器数据储存在四个不同的位置下的.db文件和.bmp文件中

en_text: Catchamas steals data stored in the clipboard.
Text: Catchamas窃取存储在剪贴板上的数据

en_text: Catchamas adds a new service named NetAdapter to establish persistence.
Text: Catchamas添加了一个名为NetAdapter的新服务来建立持久性

en_text: Catchamas adds a new service named NetAdapter in an apparent attempt to masquerade as a legitimate service.
Text: Catchamas增加了一个名为NetAdapter的新服务，显然是想伪装成一个合法的服务

en_text: CCBkdr was added to a legitimate, signed version 5.33 of the CCleaner software and distributed on CCleaner's distribution site.
Text: CCBkdr被添加到合法的、有签名的5.33版CCleaner软件中，并在CCleaner的发行网站上传播

en_text: certutil has been used to decode binaries hidden inside certificate files as Base64 information.
Text: certutil被用来将隐藏在证书文件中的二进制文件解码为Base64信息

en_text: certutil can be used to install browser root certificates as a precursor to performing man-in-the-middle between connections to banking websites. Example command: certutil -addstore -f -user ROOT ProgramData\cert512121.der.
Text: certutil可以用来安装浏览器根证书，作为在连接银行网站之间进行中间人操作的前奏。命令示例： certutil -addstore -f -user ROOT ProgramData\cert512121.der.

en_text: certutil can be used to download files from a given URL.
Text: certutil可以用来从一个给定的URL下载文件

en_text: Chaos conducts brute force attacks against SSH services to gain initial access.
Text: Chaos对SSH服务进行暴力攻击以获得初始访问权

en_text: Chaos provides a reverse shell is triggered upon receipt of a packet with a special string, sent to any port.
Text: Chaos提供了一个反向外壳，当收到一个带有特殊字符串的数据包时，会被触发，发送到任何端口

en_text: Chaos provides a reverse shell connection on 8338/TCP, encrypted via AES.
Text: Chaos在8338上提供一个反向shell连接 Chaos在8338上提供一个反向的shell连接 Chaos在8338上提供了一个反向shell连接 Chaos在8338上提供一个反向shell连接

en_text: ChChes copies itself to an .exe file with a filename that is likely intended to imitate Norton Antivirus but has several letters reversed (e.g. notron.exe).
Text: ChChes将自己复制到一个.exe文件中，其文件名很可能是为了模仿诺顿杀毒软件，但有几个字母颠倒了（例如notron.exe）

en_text: ChChes can alter the victim's proxy configuration.
Text: ChChes可以改变受害者的代理配置

en_text: ChChes can encrypt C2 traffic with AES or RC4.
Text: ChChes可以用AES或RC4对C2流量进行加密

en_text: ChChes can encode C2 data with a custom technique that utilizes Base64.
Text: ChChes可以用一种利用Base64的自定义技术对C2数据进行编码

en_text: ChChes is capable of downloading files, including additional modules.
Text: ChChes能够下载文件，包括附加模块

en_text: ChChes steals credentials stored inside Internet Explorer.
Text: ChChes窃取了存储在Internet Explorer内的凭证

en_text: ChChes collects the victim's %TEMP% directory path and version of Internet Explorer.
Text: ChChes收集受害者的%TEMP%目录路径和Internet Explorer的版本

en_text: ChChes collects the victim hostname, window resolution, and Microsoft Windows version.
Text: ChChes收集受害者的主机名、窗口分辨率和微软Windows版本

en_text: ChChes communicates to its C2 server over HTTP and embeds data within the Cookie HTTP header.
Text: ChChes通过HTTP与它的C2服务器进行通信，并将数据嵌入到Cookie HTTP头中

en_text: ChChes establishes persistence by adding a Registry Run key.
Text: ChChes通过添加一个注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: ChChes samples were digitally signed with a certificate originally used by Hacking Team that was later leaked and subsequently revoked.
Text: ChChes样本是用最初由Hacking Team使用的证书进行数字签名的，该证书后来被泄露，随后被撤销

en_text: ChChes collects its process identifier (PID) on the victim.
Text: ChChes在受害者身上收集其进程标识符（PID）

en_text: Some variants of Cherry Picker use AppInit_DLLs to achieve persistence by creating the following Registry key: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows "AppInit_DLLs"="pserver32.dll"
Text: Cherry Picker的一些变种使用AppInit_DLLs来实现持久性，创建了以下注册表键： HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Windows "AppInit_DLLs"="pserver32.dll"

en_text: Cherry Picker exfiltrates files over FTP.
Text: Cherry Picker通过FTP渗出文件

en_text: Chimera's malware has altered the NTLM authentication program on domain controllers to allow Chimera to login without a valid credential.
Text: Chimera的恶意软件改变了域控制器上的NTLM认证程序，允许Chimera在没有有效凭证的情况下登录

en_text: Chimera has encoded PowerShell commands.
Text: Chimera对PowerShell命令进行了编码

en_text: Chimera has remotely copied tools and malware onto targeted systems.
Text: Chimera公司将工具和恶意软件远程复制到目标系统

en_text: Chimera has used WMIC to execute remote commands.
Text: Chimera公司利用WMIC执行了远程命令

en_text: Chimera has used Google Cloud's appspot service to host C2 servers.
Text: Chimera公司使用谷歌云的appspot服务来托管C2服务器

en_text: Chimera has used legitimate credentials to login to an external VPN.
Text: Chimera公司使用合法凭证登录到外部VPN

en_text: Chimera has renamed malware to GoogleUpdate.exe, impersonating legitimate Google filenames.
Text: Chimera将恶意软件重新命名为GoogleUpdate.exe，冒充合法的Google文件名

en_text: Chimera has used PowerShell scripts to execute malicious payloads.
Text: Chimera利用PowerShell脚本执行恶意的有效载荷

en_text: Chimera has used RDP to access targeted systems.
Text: Chimera利用RDP访问目标系统

en_text: Chimera has gathered the SYSTEM registry and ntds.dit files from target systems.
Text: Chimera收集了目标系统的SYSTEM注册表和ntds.dit文件

en_text: Chimera has used direct Windows system calls by leveraging Dumpert.
Text: Chimera通过利用Dumpert，直接使用Windows系统调用

en_text: Chimera has used Windows admin shares to move laterally.
Text: Chimera已经使用Windows管理共享来进行横向移动

en_text: Chimera has used a valid account to maintain persistence via scheduled task.
Text: Chimera已经使用了一个有效的账户，通过计划任务来维持持久性

en_text: Chimera has used scheduled tasks to invoke Cobalt Strike and maintain persistence.
Text: Chimera已经使用预定任务来调用Cobalt Strike并保持持久性

en_text: China Chopper's server component can perform brute force password guessing against authentication portals.
Text: China Chopper的服务器组件可以对认证门户进行暴力密码猜测

en_text: China Chopper's server component can change the timestamp of files.
Text: China Chopper的服务器组件可以改变文件的时间戳

en_text: China Chopper's server component can list directory contents.
Text: China Chopper的服务器组件可以列出目录内容

en_text: China Chopper's server component can upload local files.
Text: China Chopper的服务器组件可以上传本地文件

en_text: China Chopper's server component is a Web Shell payload.
Text: China Chopper的服务器组件是一个Web Shell有效载荷

en_text: China Chopper's client component is packed with UPX.
Text: China Chopper的客户端组件中装有UPX

en_text: CHOPSTICK  includes runtime checks to identify an analysis environment and prevent execution on it.
Text: CHOPSTICK包括运行时检查，以识别分析环境并防止在其上执行

en_text: Various implementations of CHOPSTICK communicate with C2 over HTTP.
Text: CHOPSTICK的各种实现通过HTTP与C2通信

en_text: Various implementations of CHOPSTICK communicate with C2 over SMTP and POP3.
Text: CHOPSTICK的各种实现通过SMTP和POP3与C2通信

en_text: An older version of CHOPSTICK has a module that monitors all mounted volumes for files with the extensions .doc, .docx, .pgp, .gpg, .m2f, or .m2o.
Text: CHOPSTICK的一个旧版本有一个模块，可以监控所有挂载的卷，以寻找扩展名为.doc、.docx、.pgp、.gpg、.m2f或.m2o的文件

en_text: CHOPSTICK checks for antivirus and forensics software.
Text: CHOPSTICK检查防病毒和取证软件

en_text: CHOPSTICK has the capability to capture screenshots.
Text: CHOPSTICK具有捕捉屏幕截图的能力。

en_text: CHOPSTICK may store RC4 encrypted configuration information in the Windows Registry.
Text: CHOPSTICK可能在Windows注册表中存储RC4加密的配置信息

en_text: CHOPSTICK can use a DGA for Fallback Channels, domains are generated by concatenating words from lists.
Text: CHOPSTICK可以使用DGA的回退通道，域是通过连接列表中的词来生成的

en_text: CHOPSTICK is capable of performing keylogging.
Text: CHOPSTICK能够进行键盘记录

en_text: CHOPSTICK is capable of performing remote command execution.
Text: CHOPSTICK能够进行远程命令执行

en_text: CHOPSTICK is capable of performing remote file transmission.
Text: CHOPSTICK能够进行远程文件传输

en_text: CHOPSTICK provides access to the Windows Registry, which can be used to gather information.
Text: CHOPSTICK提供对Windows注册表的访问，可用于收集信息

en_text: CHOPSTICK encrypts C2 communications with RC4.
Text: CHOPSTICK用RC4对C2通信进行加密

en_text: CHOPSTICK encrypts C2 communications with TLS.
Text: CHOPSTICK用TLS对C2通信进行加密

en_text: CHOPSTICK used a proxy server between victims and the C2 server.
Text: CHOPSTICK在受害者和C2服务器之间使用一个代理服务器

en_text: Cleaver has used custom tools to facilitate ARP cache poisoning.
Text: Cleaver使用了自定义工具来促进ARP缓存中毒

en_text: CloudDuke downloads and executes additional malware from either a Web address or a Microsoft OneDrive account.
Text: CloudDuke从网络地址或微软OneDrive账户下载并执行额外的恶意软件

en_text: One variant of CloudDuke uses HTTP and HTTPS for C2.
Text: CloudDuke的一个变体使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2

en_text: One variant of CloudDuke uses a Microsoft OneDrive account to exchange commands and stolen data with its operators.
Text: CloudDuke的一个变种使用微软的OneDrive账户与运营商交换命令和被盗数据

en_text: cmd can be used to find files and directories with native functionality such as dir commands.
Text: cmd可以用来查找具有本地功能的文件和目录，如dir命令

en_text: cmd can be used to find information about the operating system.
Text: cmd可以用来查找有关操作系统的信息

en_text: cmd can be used to delete files from the file system.
Text: cmd可以用来从文件系统中删除文件

en_text: cmd can be used to copy files to/from a remotely connected external system.
Text: cmd可以用来复制文件到 cmd可以用来将文件复制到 cmd可以用来把文件复制到 cmd可用于将文件复制到

en_text: cmd can be used to copy files to/from a remotely connected internal system.
Text: cmd可以用来复制文件到 cmd可以用来将文件复制到 cmd可以用来把文件复制到 cmd可用于将文件复制到

en_text: cmd is used to execute programs and other actions at the command-line interface.
Text: cmd用于在命令行界面执行程序和其他操作

en_text: Cobalt Strike includes a capability to modify the "beacon" payload to eliminate known signatures or unpacking methods.
Text: Cobalt Strike包括一种修改 "信标 "有效载荷的能力，以消除已知的签名或解包方法

en_text: Cobalt Strike's "beacon" payload can collect information on process details.
Text: Cobalt Strike的 "信标 "有效载荷可以收集有关过程细节的信息

en_text: Cobalt Strike's "beacon" payload is capable of capturing screenshots.
Text: Cobalt Strike的 "信标 "有效载荷能够捕捉屏幕截图

en_text: Cobalt Strike's "beacon" payload is capable of running shell commands without cmd.exe and PowerShell commands without powershell.exe
Text: Cobalt Strike的 "信标 "有效载荷能够在没有cmd.exe的情况下运行shell命令，在没有powershell.exe的情况下运行PowerShell命令

en_text: Cobalt Strike will timestomp any files or payloads placed on a target machine to help them blend in.
Text: Cobalt Strike将对放置在目标机器上的任何文件或有效载荷进行时间压缩，以帮助他们混入

en_text: Cobalt Strike can SSH to a remote service.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以SSH到一个远程服务

en_text: Cobalt Strike can install a new service.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以安装一个新的服务

en_text: Cobalt Strike can be configured to have commands relayed over a peer-to-peer network of infected hosts. This can be used to limit the number of egress points, or provide access to a host without direct internet access.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以被配置为通过受感染主机的点对点网络来转发命令。这可以用来限制出口点的数量，或提供对没有直接互联网接入的主机的访问。

en_text: Cobalt Strike can query shared drives on the local system.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以查询本地系统的共享驱动器

en_text: Cobalt Strike can collect data from a local system.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以从本地系统收集数据

en_text: Cobalt Strike can perform port scans from an infected host.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以从受感染的主机上进行端口扫描

en_text: Cobalt Strike can steal access tokens from exiting processes.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以从退出的进程中窃取访问令牌

en_text: Cobalt Strike can recover hashed passwords.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以恢复散列的密码

en_text: Cobalt Strike can perform browser pivoting and inject into a user's browser to inherit cookies, authenticated HTTP sessions, and client SSL certificates.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以进行浏览器透视，并注入到用户的浏览器中，以继承cookie、认证的HTTP会话和客户端SSL证书

en_text: Cobalt Strike can exploit vulnerabilities such as MS14-058.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以利用MS14-058等漏洞

en_text: Cobalt Strike can start a VNC-based remote desktop server and tunnel the connection through the already established C2 channel.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以启动一个基于VNC的远程桌面服务器，并通过已经建立的C2通道进行隧道连接

en_text: Cobalt Strike can determine if the user on an infected machine is in the admin or domain admin group.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以确定受感染机器上的用户是否在管理或域管理组中

en_text: Cobalt Strike can determine the IP addresses of domain controllers.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以确定域控制器的IP地址

en_text: Cobalt Strike can set its "beacon" payload to reach out to the C2 server on an arbitrary and random interval. In addition it will break large data sets into smaller chunks for exfiltration.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以设置其 "信标 "有效载荷，以任意和随机的时间间隔与C2服务器取得联系

en_text: Cobalt Strike can download a hosted "beacon" payload using BITSAdmin.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用BITSAdmin下载一个托管的 "信标 "有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use PsExec to execute a payload on a remote host. It can also use Service Control Manager to start new services.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用PsExec在远程主机上执行一个有效载荷。它还可以使用服务控制管理器来启动新的服务。

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use Python to perform execution.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用Python来进行执行

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use VBA to perform execution.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用VBA来进行执行

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use Window admin shares (C$ and ADMIN$) for lateral movement.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用Window管理股（C$和ADMIN$）进行横向移动

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use WinRM to execute a payload on a remote host.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用WinRM在远程主机上执行一个有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use WMI to deliver a payload to a remote host.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用WMI向远程主机提供有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use a number of known techniques to bypass Windows UAC.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用一些已知的技术来绕过Windows UAC

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use known credentials to run commands and spawn processes as a local user account.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用已知的凭证，以本地用户账户的身份运行命令和催生进程

en_text: Cobalt Strike can use known credentials to run commands and spawn processes as a domain user account.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以使用已知的凭证，以域用户账户的身份运行命令和催生进程

en_text: Cobalt Strike can execute a payload on a remote host with PowerShell. This technique does not write any data to disk. Cobalt Strike can also use PowerSploit and other scripting frameworks to perform execution.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以通过PowerShell在远程主机上执行有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can deliver "beacon" payloads for lateral movement by leveraging remote COM execution.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以通过利用远程COM执行，为横向移动提供 "信标 "有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can track key presses with a keylogger module.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以通过一个键盘记录器模块跟踪按键

en_text: Cobalt Strike can make tokens from known credentials.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以通过已知的凭证制作代币

en_text: Cobalt Strike can inject a variety of payloads into processes dynamically chosen by the adversary.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以向对手动态选择的进程注入各种有效载荷

en_text: Cobalt Strike can spawn processes with alternate PPIDs.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以用备用的PPID催生进程

en_text: Cobalt Strike can perform pass the hash.
Text: Cobalt Strike可以执行通过哈希

en_text: Cobalt Strike uses the native Windows Network Enumeration APIs to interrogate and discover targets in a Windows Active Directory network.
Text: Cobalt Strike使用本地Windows网络枚举API来询问和发现Windows Active Directory网络中的目标

en_text: Cobalt Strike uses a command-line interface to interact with systems.
Text: Cobalt Strike使用命令行界面与系统进行交互

en_text: Cobalt Strike uses a custom command and control protocol that is encapsulated in HTTP, HTTPS, or DNS. In addition, it conducts peer-to-peer communication over Windows named pipes encapsulated in the SMB protocol. All protocols use their standard assigned ports.
Text: Cobalt Strike使用一个自定义的命令和控制协议，该协议被封装在HTTP、HTTPS或DNS中。此外，它通过SMB协议封装的Windows命名管道进行点对点的通信。所有协议都使用其标准分配的端口。

en_text: Cobalt Strike uses a custom command and control protocol that can be encapsulated in HTTP or HTTPS, or DNS. All protocols use their standard assigned ports.
Text: Cobalt Strike使用自定义的命令和控制协议，可以封装在HTTP或HTTPS中，也可以封装在DNS中。所有协议都使用其标准分配的端口。

en_text: Cobalt Strike uses a custom command and control protocol that can encapsulated in DNS. All protocols use their standard assigned ports.
Text: Cobalt Strike使用自定义的命令和控制协议，可以在DNS中进行封装。所有协议都使用其标准分配的端口。

en_text: Cobalt Strike conducts peer-to-peer communication over Windows named pipes encapsulated in the SMB protocol. All protocols use their standard assigned ports.
Text: Cobalt Strike通过SMB协议封装的Windows命名管道进行点对点的通信。所有协议都使用其标准分配的端口。

en_text: Cobalt Group had exploited multiple vulnerabilities for execution, including Microsoft’s Equation Editor (CVE-2017-11882), an Internet Explorer vulnerability (CVE-2018-8174), CVE-2017-8570, CVE-2017-0199, and CVE-2017-8759.
Text: Cobalt集团曾利用多个漏洞进行执行，包括微软的方程式编辑器（CVE-2017-11882）、Internet Explorer漏洞（CVE-2018-8174）、CVE-2017-8570、CVE-2017-0199和CVE-2017-8759

en_text: Cobalt Group deleted the DLL dropper from the victim’s machine to cover their tracks.
Text: Cobalt集团从受害者的机器上删除了DLL投放器以掩盖他们的踪迹

en_text: Cobalt Group obfuscated several scriptlets and code used on the victim’s machine, including through use of XOR and RC4.
Text: Cobalt集团对受害者机器上使用的几个小脚本和代码进行了模糊处理，包括通过使用XOR和RC4

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent emails with URLs pointing to malicious documents.
Text: Cobalt集团发送了带有指向恶意文件的URL的电子邮件

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent emails containing malicious attachments that require users to execute a file or macro to infect the victim machine.
Text: Cobalt集团发送了含有恶意附件的电子邮件，要求用户执行一个文件或宏来感染受害者的机器

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent emails containing malicious links that require users to execute a file or macro to infect the victim machine.
Text: Cobalt集团发送了含有恶意链接的电子邮件，要求用户执行一个文件或宏来感染受害者的机器

en_text: Cobalt Group has used public sites such as github.com and sendspace.com to upload files and then download them to victim computers. The group's JavaScript backdoor is also capable of downloading files.
Text: Cobalt集团利用github.com和sendspace.com等公共网站上传文件，然后将其下载到受害者的电脑上

en_text: Cobalt Group has used odbcconf to proxy the execution of malicious DLL files.
Text: Cobalt集团利用odbcconf来代理执行恶意的DLL文件

en_text: Cobalt Group has used exploits to increase their levels of rights and privileges.
Text: Cobalt集团利用漏洞来增加他们的权利和特权水平

en_text: Cobalt Group leveraged an open-source tool called SoftPerfect Network Scanner to perform network scanning.
Text: Cobalt集团利用一个名为SoftPerfect Network Scanner的开源工具来进行网络扫描

en_text: Cobalt Group used the Ammyy Admin tool as well as TeamViewer for remote access, including to preserve remote access if a Cobalt Strike module was lost.
Text: Cobalt集团使用Ammyy管理工具以及TeamViewer进行远程访问，包括在Cobalt Strike模块丢失时保留远程访问

en_text: Cobalt Group used msxsl.exe to bypass AppLocker and to invoke Jscript code from an XSL file.
Text: Cobalt集团使用msxsl.exe绕过AppLocker并从XSL文件中调用Jscript代码

en_text: Cobalt Group has used the Plink utility to create SSH tunnels.
Text: Cobalt集团使用Plink工具来创建SSH隧道

en_text: Cobalt Group has used powershell.exe to download and execute scripts.
Text: Cobalt集团使用powerhell.exe下载和执行脚本

en_text: Cobalt Group has used regsvr32.exe to execute scripts.
Text: Cobalt集团使用regsvr32.exe来执行脚本

en_text: Cobalt Group has used a JavaScript backdoor that is capable of launching cmd.exe to execute shell commands. The group has used an exploit toolkit known as Threadkit that launches .bat files.
Text: Cobalt集团使用了一个JavaScript后门，能够启动cmd.exe来执行shell命令。该组织使用了一个被称为Threadkit的漏洞工具包，能够启动.bat文件。

en_text: Cobalt Group used a JavaScript backdoor that is capable of collecting a list of the security solutions installed on the victim's machine.
Text: Cobalt集团使用了一个JavaScript后门，能够收集受害者机器上安装的安全解决方案的列表

en_text: Cobalt Group has used the command cmstp.exe /s /ns C:\Users\ADMINI~W\AppData\Local\Temp\XKNqbpzl.txt to bypass AppLocker and launch a malicious script.
Text: Cobalt集团使用命令cmstp.exe /s /ns C:\Users\ADMINI~W\AppData\Local\Temp\XKNqbpzl.txt来绕过AppLocker并启动一个恶意脚本。

en_text: Cobalt Group has added persistence by registering the file name for the next stage malware under HKCU\Environment\UserInitMprLogonScript.
Text: Cobalt集团通过在HKCU/Environment/UserInitMprLogonScript下注册下一阶段的恶意软件的文件名来增加持久性

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent Word OLE compound documents with malicious obfuscated VBA macros that will run upon user execution.
Text: Cobalt集团向Word OLE复合文档发送了带有恶意混淆的VBA宏，在用户执行时将会运行

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent spearphishing emails with various attachment types to corporate and personal email accounts of victim organizations. Attachment types have included .rtf, .doc, .xls, archives containing LNK files, and password protected archives containing .exe and .scr executables.
Text: Cobalt集团向受害机构的公司和个人电子邮件账户发送了带有各种附件类型的鱼叉式钓鱼电子邮件。附件类型包括.rtf、.doc、.xls、含有LNK文件的档案，以及含有.exe和.scr可执行文件的受密码保护的档案。

en_text: Cobalt Group has sent malicious Word OLE compound documents to victims.
Text: Cobalt集团向受害者发送了恶意的Word OLE复合文档

en_text: Cobalt Group has used DNS tunneling for C2.
Text: Cobalt集团已将DNS隧道用于C2

en_text: Cobalt Group has used HTTPS for C2.
Text: Cobalt集团已将HTTPS用于C2

en_text: Cobalt Group has injected code into trusted processes.
Text: Cobalt集团已将代码注入受信任的进程

en_text: Cobalt Group has created Windows tasks to establish persistence.
Text: Cobalt集团已经创建了Windows任务来建立持久性

en_text: Cobalt Group has created new services to establish persistence.
Text: Cobalt集团已经创建了新的服务来建立持久性

en_text: Cobalt Group has bypassed UAC.
Text: Cobalt集团已经绕开了UAC

en_text: Cobalt Group has used Registry Run keys for persistence. The group has also set a Startup path to launch the PowerShell shell command and download Cobalt Strike.
Text: Cobalt集团已经使用注册表运行键来实现持久性。该集团还设置了一个启动路径来启动PowerShell shell命令并下载Cobalt Strike。

en_text: Cobalt Group has used Remote Desktop Protocol to conduct lateral movement.
Text: Cobalt集团已使用远程桌面协议进行横向移动

en_text: Cobalt Group has executed JavaScript scriptlets on the victim's machine.
Text: Cobalt集团在受害者的机器上执行了JavaScript小脚本

en_text: Cobian RAT creates an autostart Registry key to ensure persistence.
Text: Cobian RAT创建了一个自动启动注册表键以确保持久性

en_text: Cobian RAT can launch a remote command shell interface for executing commands.
Text: Cobian RAT可以启动一个远程命令shell界面来执行命令

en_text: Cobian RAT obfuscates communications with the C2 server using Base64 encoding.
Text: Cobian RAT使用Base64编码混淆了与C2服务器的通信

en_text: Cobian RAT uses DNS for C2.
Text: Cobian RAT使用DNS进行C2

en_text: Cobian RAT has a feature to perform keylogging on the victim’s machine.
Text: Cobian RAT有一个功能，可以在受害者的机器上进行键盘记录

en_text: Cobian RAT has a feature to perform voice recording on the victim’s machine.
Text: Cobian RAT有一个功能，可以在受害者的机器上进行语音录制

en_text: Cobian RAT has a feature to access the webcam on the victim’s machine.
Text: Cobian RAT有一个功能是访问受害者机器上的网络摄像头

en_text: Cobian RAT has a feature to perform screen capture.
Text: Cobian RAT有一个进行屏幕捕捉的功能

en_text: CoinTicker creates user launch agents named .espl.plist and com.apple.[random string].plist to establish persistence.
Text: CoinTicker创建了名为.espl.plist和com.apple.[随机字符串].plist的用户启动代理来建立持久性

en_text: CoinTicker downloads the EggShell mach-o binary using curl, which does not set the quarantine flag.
Text: CoinTicker使用curl下载EggShell mach-o二进制文件，它没有设置隔离标志

en_text: CoinTicker decodes the initially-downloaded hidden encoded file using OpenSSL.
Text: CoinTicker使用OpenSSL对最初下载的隐藏编码文件进行解码

en_text: CoinTicker downloads the following hidden files to evade detection and maintain persistence: /private/tmp/.info.enc, /private/tmp/.info.py, /private/tmp/.server.sh, ~/Library/LaunchAgents/.espl.plist, ~/Library/Containers/.[random string]/[random string].
Text: CoinTicker下载以下隐藏文件以逃避检测并保持持久性。/private/tmp/.info.enc, /private/tmp/.info.py, /private/tmp/.server.sh, ~/Library/LaunchAgents/.espl.plist, ~/Library/Containers/. [随机字符串]/[随机字符串] 。

en_text: CoinTicker executes a bash script to establish a reverse shell.
Text: CoinTicker执行一个bash脚本来建立一个反向的shell

en_text: CoinTicker executes a Python script to download its second stage.
Text: CoinTicker执行一个Python脚本来下载其第二阶段

en_text: CoinTicker initially downloads a hidden encoded file.
Text: CoinTicker最初下载一个隐藏的编码文件

en_text: Comnie uses HTTP for C2 communication.
Text: Comnie使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: Comnie uses ipconfig /all and route PRINT to identify network adapter and interface information.
Text: Comnie使用ipconfig 康尼使用ipconfig 康尼使用的是ipconfig 康尼使用了ipconfig

en_text: Comnie uses the net user command.
Text: Comnie使用net user命令

en_text: Comnie uses RC4 and Base64 to obfuscate strings.
Text: Comnie使用RC4和Base64来混淆字符串

en_text: Comnie uses Rundll32 to load a malicious DLL.
Text: Comnie使用Rundll32来加载一个恶意的DLL

en_text: Comnie uses the tasklist to view running processes on the victim’s machine.
Text: Comnie使用任务列表来查看受害者机器上的运行进程

en_text: Comnie attempts to detect several anti-virus products.
Text: Comnie试图检测几个反病毒产品

en_text: Comnie collects the hostname of the victim machine.
Text: Comnie收集受害者机器的主机名

en_text: Comnie establishes persistence via a .lnk file in the victim’s startup path.
Text: Comnie通过受害者的启动路径中的.lnk文件建立持久性

en_text: Comnie achieves persistence by adding a shortcut of itself to the startup path in the Registry.
Text: Comnie通过在注册表的启动路径中添加自己的快捷方式来实现持久性

en_text: Comnie encrypts command and control communications with RC4.
Text: Comnie用RC4对指挥和控制通信进行加密

en_text: Comnie runs the net view command
Text: Comnie运行net view命令 康尼运行net view命令 Comnie运行net view指令 Comnie运行了net view命令

en_text: Comnie runs the command: net start >> %TEMP%\info.dat on a victim.
Text: Comnie在一个受害者身上运行命令：net start >> %TEMP%\info.dat

en_text: Comnie appends a total of 64MB of garbage data to a file to deter any security products in place that may be scanning files on disk.
Text: Comnie在一个文件中附加了总共64MB的垃圾数据，以阻止任何可能正在扫描磁盘上的文件的安全产品

en_text: Comnie executes BAT scripts.
Text: Comnie执行BAT脚本

en_text: Comnie executes the netstat -ano command.
Text: Comnie执行netstat -ano命令

en_text: Comnie executes VBS scripts.
Text: Comnie执行VBS脚本

en_text: Comnie executes a batch script to store discovery information in %TEMP%\info.dat and then uploads the temporarily file to the remote C2 server.
Text: Comnie执行一个批处理脚本，将发现信息存储在%TEMP%\info.dat中，然后将临时文件上传到远程C2服务器

en_text: ComRAT can load a PE file from memory or the file system and execute it with CreateProcessW.
Text: ComRAT可以从内存或文件系统中加载一个PE文件，并用CreateProcessW来执行

en_text: ComRAT can check the victim's default browser to determine which process to inject its communications module into.
Text: ComRAT可以检查受害者的默认浏览器，以确定将其通信模块注入哪个进程

en_text: ComRAT can use email attachments for command and control.
Text: ComRAT可以使用电子邮件附件进行指挥和控制

en_text: ComRAT can check the default browser by querying HKCR\http\shell\open\command.
Text: ComRAT可以通过查询HKCR\http\shellopen\command来检查默认浏览器

en_text: ComRAT can use SSL/TLS encryption for its HTTP-based C2 channel. ComRAT has used public key cryptography with RSA and AES encrypted email attachments for its Gmail C2 channel.
Text: ComRAT可以为其基于HTTP的C2渠道使用SSL/TLS加密。ComRAT为其Gmail C2渠道使用了带有RSA和AES加密的电子邮件附件的公钥加密技术。

en_text: ComRAT has used HTTP requests for command and control.
Text: ComRAT利用HTTP请求进行指挥和控制

en_text: ComRAT has used cmd.exe to execute commands.
Text: ComRAT使用cmd.exe来执行命令

en_text: ComRAT has used encryption and base64 to obfuscate its orchestrator code in the Registry. ComRAT has also embedded an XOR encrypted communications module inside the orchestrator module. ComRAT has encrypted its virtual file system using AES-256 in XTS mode.
Text: ComRAT使用加密和base64来混淆其在注册中心的协调器代码。ComRAT还在协调器模块内嵌入了一个XOR加密的通信模块。ComRAT在XTS模式下使用AES-256对其虚拟文件系统进行了加密。

en_text: ComRAT has used a portable FAT16 partition image placed in %TEMP% as a hidden file system.
Text: ComRAT使用了一个放置在%TEMP%中的便携式FAT16分区映像作为隐藏的文件系统

en_text: ComRAT has used a scheduled task to launch its PowerShell loader.
Text: ComRAT使用了一个计划任务来启动其PowerShell加载器

en_text: ComRAT has used a task name associated with Windows SQM Consolidator.
Text: ComRAT使用了一个与Windows SQM Consolidator相关的任务名称

en_text: ComRAT has used unique per machine passwords to decrypt the orchestrator payload and a hardcoded XOR key to decrypt its communications module. ComRAT has also used a unique password to decrypt the file used for its hidden file system.
Text: ComRAT使用每台机器的唯一密码来解密协调器的有效载荷，并使用硬编码的XOR密钥来解密其通信模块。ComRAT还使用一个独特的密码来解密用于其隐藏文件系统的文件。

en_text: ComRAT has injected its orchestrator DLL into explorer.exe. ComRAT has also injected its communications module into the victim's default browser to make C2 connections appear less suspicious as all network connections will be initiated by the browser process.
Text: ComRAT已将其协调器DLL注入explorer.exe中。ComRAT还将其通信模块注入受害者的默认浏览器，使C2连接看起来不那么可疑，因为所有的网络连接都将由浏览器进程启动。

en_text: ComRAT has encrypted and stored its orchestrator code in the Registry.
Text: ComRAT已将其协调器代码加密并存储在注册表中

en_text: ComRAT has been programmed to sleep outside local business hours (9 to 5, Monday to Friday).
Text: ComRAT已经被设定为在当地工作时间之外睡觉（周一至周五，9点至5点）

en_text: ComRAT has used PowerShell to load itself every time a user logs in to the system. ComRAT can execute PowerShell scripts loaded into memory or from the file system.
Text: ComRAT已经使用PowerShell在每次用户登录系统时加载自己。ComRAT可以执行加载到内存或从文件系统中的PowerShell脚本。

en_text: ComRAT has the ability to use the Gmail web UI to receive commands and exfiltrate information.
Text: ComRAT有能力使用Gmail网页用户界面来接收命令和渗出信息

en_text: CookieMiner can steal Google Chrome and Apple Safari browser cookies from the victim’s machine.
Text: CookieMiner可以从受害者的机器上窃取谷歌浏览器和苹果Safari浏览器的cookies

en_text: CookieMiner can download additional scripts from a web server.
Text: CookieMiner可以从网络服务器下载额外的脚本

en_text: CookieMiner can steal saved usernames and passwords in Chrome as well as credit card credentials.
Text: CookieMiner可以窃取Chrome浏览器中保存的用户名和密码，以及信用卡凭证

en_text: CookieMiner has used base64 encoding to obfuscate scripts on the system.
Text: CookieMiner使用base64编码对系统中的脚本进行了混淆

en_text: CookieMiner has used the curl --upload-file command to exfiltrate data over HTTP.
Text: CookieMiner使用curl --upload-file命令通过HTTP渗出数据

en_text: CookieMiner has looked for files in the user's home directory with "wallet" in their name using find.
Text: CookieMiner使用查找功能在用户的主目录中寻找名称中带有 "wallet "的文件

en_text: CookieMiner has used Google Chrome's decryption and extraction operations.
Text: CookieMiner使用了谷歌浏览器的解密和提取操作

en_text: CookieMiner has used a Unix shell script to run a series of commands targeting macOS.
Text: CookieMiner使用了一个Unix shell脚本来运行一系列针对MacOS的命令

en_text: CookieMiner has loaded coinmining software onto systems to mine for Koto cryptocurrency.
Text: CookieMiner已将挖币软件加载到系统中，以挖掘Koto加密货币

en_text: CookieMiner has installed multiple new Launch Agents in order to maintain persistence for cryptocurrency mining software.
Text: CookieMiner已经安装了多个新的启动代理，以保持加密货币挖矿软件的持久性

en_text: CookieMiner has retrieved iPhone text messages from iTunes phone backup files.
Text: CookieMiner已经从iTunes手机备份文件中检索出iPhone短信

en_text: CookieMiner has checked for the presence of "Little Snitch", macOS network monitoring and application firewall software, stopping and exiting if it is found.
Text: CookieMiner已经检查了 "Little Snitch"、macOS网络监控和应用防火墙软件的存在，如果发现它，就停止并退出

en_text: CookieMiner has used python scripts on the user’s system, as well as the Python variant of the Empire agent, EmPyre.
Text: CookieMiner在用户的系统上使用了python脚本，以及帝国代理的Python变体EmPyre

en_text: CopyKittens uses rundll32 to load various tools on victims, including a lateral movement tool named Vminst, Cobalt Strike, and shellcode.
Text: CopyKittens使用rundll32在受害者身上加载各种工具，包括一个名为Vminst的横向移动工具、Cobalt Strike和shellcode

en_text: CopyKittens uses ZPP, a .NET console program, to compress files with ZIP.
Text: CopyKittens使用ZPP，一个.NET控制台程序，用ZIP来压缩文件

en_text: CopyKittens has used -w hidden and -windowstyle hidden to conceal PowerShell windows.
Text: CopyKittens使用了-w hidden和-windowstyle hidden来掩盖PowerShell窗口

en_text: CopyKittens has used PowerShell Empire.
