Text: CopyKittens已经使用了PowerShell帝国

en_text: CopyKittens digitally signed an executable with a stolen certificate from legitimate company AI Squared.
Text: CopyKittens用偷来的合法公司AI Squared的证书对一个可执行文件进行数字签名

en_text: CopyKittens encrypts data with a substitute cipher prior to exfiltration.
Text: CopyKittens在渗出前用替代密码对数据进行加密

en_text: CORALDECK has created password-protected RAR, WinImage, and zip archives to be exfiltrated.
Text: CORALDECK创建了受密码保护的RAR、WinImage和ZIP文件，以便进行外泄

en_text: CORALDECK searches for specified files.
Text: CORALDECK搜索指定的文件

en_text: CORALDECK has exfiltrated data in HTTP POST headers.
Text: CORALDECK在HTTP POST头中渗出了数据

en_text: CORESHELL C2 messages are Base64-encoded.
Text: CORESHELL C2信息是Base64编码的

en_text: CORESHELL C2 messages are encrypted with custom stream ciphers using six-byte or eight-byte keys.
Text: CORESHELL C2信息是使用六字节或八字节的密钥用自定义流密码加密的

en_text: CORESHELL contains unused machine instructions in a likely attempt to hinder analysis.
Text: CORESHELL包含未使用的机器指令，可能是为了阻碍分析

en_text: CORESHELL downloads another dropper from its C2 server.
Text: CORESHELL从其C2服务器上下载另一个dropper

en_text: CORESHELL collects hostname, volume serial number and OS version data from the victim and sends the information to its C2 server.
Text: CORESHELL从受害者那里收集主机名、卷轴序列号和操作系统版本数据，并将这些信息发送到其C2服务器

en_text: CORESHELL can communicate over HTTP for C2.
Text: CORESHELL可以通过HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: CORESHELL can communicate over SMTP and POP3 for C2.
Text: CORESHELL可以通过SMTP和POP3进行C2通信

en_text: CORESHELL obfuscates strings using a custom stream cipher.
Text: CORESHELL使用一个自定义的流密码来混淆字符串

en_text: CORESHELL is installed via execution of rundll32 with an export named "init" or "InitW."
Text: CORESHELL是通过执行rundll32与一个名为 "init "或 "InitW "的出口来安装

en_text: CORESHELL has established persistence by creating autostart extensibility point (ASEP) Registry entries in the Run key and other Registry keys, as well as by creating shortcuts in the Internet Explorer Quick Start folder.
Text: CORESHELL通过在运行键和其他注册表键中创建自动启动扩展点（ASEP）注册表项，以及在Internet Explorer快速启动文件夹中创建快捷方式，建立了持久性

en_text: CosmicDuke contains a custom version of the RC4 algorithm that includes a programming error.
Text: CosmicDuke包含一个自定义版本的RC4算法，其中包括一个编程错误

en_text: CosmicDuke steals user files from local hard drives with file extensions that match a predefined list.
Text: CosmicDuke从本地硬盘中窃取用户文件，其文件扩展名与预定义的列表相符

en_text: CosmicDuke steals user files from removable media with file extensions and keywords that match a predefined list.
Text: CosmicDuke从可移动媒体中窃取用户文件，其文件扩展名和关键词与预定义的列表相匹配

en_text: CosmicDuke steals user files from network shared drives with file extensions and keywords that match a predefined list.
Text: CosmicDuke从网络共享驱动器中窃取用户文件，其文件扩展名和关键词与预定义的列表相匹配

en_text: CosmicDuke takes periodic screenshots and exfiltrates them.
Text: CosmicDuke会定期截图，并将其外流

en_text: CosmicDuke can use HTTP or HTTPS for command and control to hard-coded C2 servers.
Text: CosmicDuke可以使用HTTP或HTTPS对硬编码的C2服务器进行命令和控制

en_text: CosmicDuke copies and exfiltrates the clipboard contents every 30 seconds.
Text: CosmicDuke每隔30秒就会复制和渗入剪贴板的内容

en_text: CosmicDuke uses scheduled tasks typically named "Watchmon Service" for persistence.
Text: CosmicDuke使用通常被命名为 "Watchmon Service "的计划任务来实现持久性

en_text: CosmicDuke uses Windows services typically named "javamtsup" for persistence.
Text: CosmicDuke使用通常名为 "javamtsup "的Windows服务作为持久性

en_text: CosmicDuke uses a keylogger.
Text: CosmicDuke使用一个键盘记录器

en_text: CosmicDuke attempts to exploit privilege escalation vulnerabilities CVE-2010-0232 or CVE-2010-4398.
Text: CosmicDuke试图利用特权升级漏洞CVE-2010-0232或CVE-2010-4398

en_text: CosmicDuke collects user credentials, including passwords, for various programs including popular instant messaging applications and email clients as well as WLAN keys.
Text: CosmicDuke收集各种程序的用户凭证，包括密码，包括流行的即时通讯应用程序和电子邮件客户端以及WLAN密钥

en_text: CosmicDuke collects Windows account hashes.
Text: CosmicDuke收集了Windows账户的哈希值

en_text: CosmicDuke collects user credentials, including passwords, for various programs including Web browsers.
Text: CosmicDuke收集用户凭证，包括密码，用于各种程序，包括网络浏览器

en_text: CosmicDuke searches for Microsoft Outlook data files with extensions .pst and .ost for collection and exfiltration.
Text: CosmicDuke搜索扩展名为.pst和.ost的微软Outlook数据文件进行收集和渗出

en_text: CosmicDuke searches attached and mounted drives for file extensions and keywords that match a predefined list.
Text: CosmicDuke搜索连接和安装的驱动器，寻找符合预定义列表的文件扩展名和关键词

en_text: CosmicDuke exfiltrates collected files over FTP or WebDAV. Exfiltration servers can be separately configured from C2 servers.
Text: CosmicDuke通过FTP或WebDAV将收集的文件外流

en_text: CosmicDuke exfiltrates collected files automatically over FTP to remote servers.
Text: CosmicDuke通过FTP将收集的文件自动外流到远程服务器

en_text: The CozyCar dropper copies the system file rundll32.exe to the install location for the malware, then uses the copy of rundll32.exe to load and execute the main CozyCar component.
Text: CozyCar dropper将系统文件rundll32.exe复制到恶意软件的安装位置，然后使用rundll32.exe的副本来加载和执行CozyCar主要组件

en_text: The payload of CozyCar is encrypted with simple XOR with a rotating key. The CozyCar configuration file has been encrypted with RC4 keys.
Text: CozyCar的有效载荷是用简单的XOR与旋转的密钥进行加密的。CozyCar的配置文件已经用RC4密钥进行了加密。

en_text: The main CozyCar dropper checks whether the victim has an anti-virus product installed. If the installed product is on a predetermined list, the dropper will exit.
Text: CozyCar的主程序会检查受害者是否安装了防病毒产品

en_text: The CozyCar dropper has masqueraded a copy of the infected system's rundll32.exe executable that was moved to the malware's install directory and renamed according to a predefined configuration file.
Text: CozyCar滴管伪装了被感染系统的rundll32.exe可执行文件的副本，该副本被移至恶意软件的安装目录，并根据预定义的配置文件重新命名

en_text: CozyCar uses Twitter as a backup C2 channel to Twitter accounts specified in its configuration file.
Text: CozyCar使用Twitter作为其配置文件中指定的Twitter账户的备份C2通道

en_text: One persistence mechanism used by CozyCar is to register itself as a Windows service.
Text: CozyCar使用的一种持久性机制是将自己注册为一个Windows服务

en_text: One persistence mechanism used by CozyCar is to register itself as a scheduled task.
Text: CozyCar使用的一种持久性机制是将自己注册为一个计划任务

en_text: One persistence mechanism used by CozyCar is to set itself to be executed at system startup by adding a Registry value under one of the following Registry keys: HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer\Run HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer\Run
Text: CozyCar使用的一种持久性机制是通过在以下注册表键下添加一个注册表值，将自己设置为在系统启动时执行。HKLM\Software\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Run HKCUSoftware\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Run HKLM\Software\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer\Run HKCUSoftware\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer/Run

en_text: CozyCar has executed Mimikatz to harvest stored credentials from the victim and further victim penetration.
Text: CozyCar已经执行了Mimikatz，以收获受害者的存储凭证并进一步渗透受害者

en_text: CozyCar's main method of communicating with its C2 servers is using HTTP or HTTPS.
Text: CozyCar与其C2服务器通信的主要方法是使用HTTP或HTTPS

en_text: Password stealer and NTLM stealer modules in CozyCar harvest stored credentials from the victim, including credentials used as part of Windows NTLM user authentication.
Text: CozyCar中的密码窃取器和NTLM窃取器模块从受害者那里获取存储的凭证，包括作为Windows NTLM用户认证一部分的凭证

en_text: A module in CozyCar allows arbitrary commands to be executed by invoking C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe.
Text: CozyCar中的一个模块允许通过调用C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe来执行任意命令

en_text: A system info module in CozyCar gathers information on the victim host’s configuration.
Text: CozyCar中的一个系统信息模块收集了受害者主机的配置信息

en_text: CrackMapExec can dump usernames and hashed passwords from the SAM.
Text: CrackMapExec可以从SAM中转储用户名和散列密码

en_text: CrackMapExec can dump hashed passwords from LSA secrets for the targeted system.
Text: CrackMapExec可以从目标系统的LSA机密中转储散列的密码。

en_text: CrackMapExec can collect DNS information from the targeted system.
Text: CrackMapExec可以从目标系统收集DNS信息

en_text: CrackMapExec can discover active sessions for a targeted system.
Text: CrackMapExec可以发现目标系统的活动会话

en_text: CrackMapExec can discover specified filetypes and log files on a targeted system.
Text: CrackMapExec可以发现目标系统上的指定文件类型和日志文件

en_text: CrackMapExec can discover the password policies applied to the target system.
Text: CrackMapExec可以发现应用于目标系统的密码策略

en_text: CrackMapExec can dump hashed passwords associated with Active Directory using Windows' Directory Replication Services API (DRSUAPI), or Volume Shadow Copy.
Text: CrackMapExec可以利用Windows的目录复制服务API（DRSUAPI）或卷影复制，转储与活动目录相关的哈希密码

en_text: CrackMapExec can enumerate the shared folders and associated permissions for a targeted network.
Text: CrackMapExec可以列举出目标网络的共享文件夹和相关权限

en_text: CrackMapExec can enumerate the domain user accounts on a targeted system.

en_text: Dark Caracal leveraged a watering hole to serve up malicious code.

en_text: Dark Caracal makes their malware look like Flash Player, Office, or PDF documents in order to entice a user to click on it.

en_text: Dark Caracal took screenshots using their Windows malware.

en_text: Dark Caracal collected file listings of all default Windows directories.

en_text: Dark Caracal has obfuscated strings in Bandook by base64 encoding, and then encrypting them.

en_text: Dark Caracal spearphished victims via Facebook and Whatsapp.

en_text: Dark Caracal has used macros in Word documents that would download a second stage if executed.

en_text: DarkComet gathers the username from the victim’s machine.

en_text: DarkComet can open an active screen of the victim’s machine and take control of the mouse and keyboard.

Text: DarkComet可以访问受害者的网络摄像头来拍照

en_text: DarkComet can load any files onto the infected machine to execute.
Text: DarkComet可以将任何文件加载到被感染的机器上执行

en_text: DarkComet can disable Security Center functions like the Windows Firewall.
Text: DarkComet可以禁用安全中心的功能，如Windows防火墙

en_text: DarkComet can disable Security Center functions like anti-virus.
Text: DarkComet可以禁用安全中心的功能，如防病毒

en_text: DarkComet can list active processes running on the victim’s machine.
Text: DarkComet可以列出受害者机器上运行的活动进程

en_text: DarkComet can launch a remote shell to execute commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: DarkComet可以启动一个远程外壳，在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: DarkComet can use HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: DarkComet可以使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: DarkComet can listen in to victims' conversations through the system’s microphone.
Text: DarkComet可以通过系统的麦克风监听受害者的谈话

en_text: DarkComet has the option to compress its payload using UPX or MPRESS.
Text: DarkComet可以选择使用UPX或MPRESS来压缩其有效载荷

en_text: DarkComet can execute various types of scripts on the victim’s machine.
Text: DarkComet可以在受害者的机器上执行各种类型的脚本

en_text: DarkComet adds several Registry entries to enable automatic execution at every system startup.
Text: DarkComet添加了几个注册表项，以便在每次系统启动时能够自动执行

en_text: DarkComet has dropped itself onto victim machines with file names such as WinDefender.Exe and winupdate.exe in an apparent attempt to masquerade as a legitimate file.
Text: DarkComet以WinDefender.Exe和winupdate.exe等文件名投放到受害者机器上，显然是想伪装成一个合法文件

en_text: DarkComet has a keylogging capability.
Text: DarkComet有一个键盘记录功能

en_text: DarkComet adds a Registry value for its installation routine to the Registry Key HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System Enable LUA="0" and HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\DC3_FEXEC.
Text: DarkComet在注册表键HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System Enable LUA="0 "和HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\DC3_FEXEC中为其安装程序添加一个注册表值

en_text: Darkhotel's selective infector modifies executables stored on removable media as a method of spreading across computers.

en_text: Darkhotel has sent spearphishing emails with malicious RAR attachments.

en_text: Darkhotel sent spearphishing emails with malicious attachments that required users to click on an image in the document to drop the malware to disk.

en_text: Darkhotel used embedded iframes on hotel login portals to redirect selected victims to download malware.
Text: Darkhotel利用酒店登录门户上的嵌入式iframe，将选定的受害者重定向到下载恶意软件

en_text: Darkhotel has obfuscated code used in an operation using RC4 and other methods.

en_text: Darkhotel has used a keylogger.
Text: Darkhotel使用了一个键盘记录器

Text: Darkhotel使用了一种通过感染存储在共享驱动器上的可执行文件进行传播的病毒

en_text: Darkhotel has collected the hostname, OS version, service pack version, and the processor architecture from the victim’s machine.
Text: Darkhotel收集了受害者机器上的主机名、操作系统版本、服务包版本和处理器架构

en_text: Darkhotel has searched for anti-malware strings and anti-virus processes running on the system.
Text: Darkhotel搜索了系统上运行的反恶意软件串和反病毒进程

Text: Darkhotel在其恶意软件上使用了代码签名证书，这些证书要么是由于弱钥匙而伪造的，要么是偷来的

en_text: Darkhotel has decrypted strings and imports using RC4 during execution.
Text: Darkhotel在执行过程中使用RC4解密了字符串和导入

en_text: DarkHydrus has sent malware that required users to hit the enable button in Microsoft Excel to allow an .iqy file to be downloaded.

Text: DarkHydrus利用PowerShell下载并执行额外的脚本来执行

Text: DarkHydrus使用了-WindowStyle Hidden来掩盖PowerShell窗口

Text: DarkHydrus使用模板注入来启动一个认证窗口，让用户输入他们的凭证

Text: DarkHydrus使用一个开源工具Phishery在微软Word文档中注入恶意的远程模板URL，然后将其发送给受害者以启用强制认证

en_text: DarkHydrus has sent spearphishing emails with password-protected RAR archives containing malicious Excel Web Query files (.iqy). The group has also sent spearphishing emails that contained malicious Microsoft Office documents that use the "attachedTemplate" technique to load a template from a remote server.
Text: DarkHydrus已经发送了带有密码保护的RAR档案的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，其中包含恶意的Excel网络查询文件（.iqy）。该组织还发送了包含恶意微软Office文档的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，这些文档使用 "附件模板 "技术从远程服务器加载模板。

en_text: Denis used the IsDebuggerPresent, OutputDebugString, and SetLastError APIs to avoid debugging. Denis used GetProcAddress and LoadLibrary to dynamically resolve APIs. Denis also used the Wow64SetThreadContext API as part of a process hollowing process.
Text: DarkHydrus已经发送了带有密码保护的RAR档案的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，其中包含恶意的Excel网络查询文件（.iqy）。该组织还发送了包含恶意微软Office文档的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，这些文档使用 "附件模板 "技术从远程服务器加载模板。

Text: DarkVishnya使用暴力攻击来获取登录数据

Text: DarkVishnya使用端口5190和7900进行shellcode监听，使用端口4444、4445、31337进行shellcode C2

Text: DarkVishnya为贝壳代码加载器的分发创造了新的服务

en_text: A version of Daserf uses the MPRESS packer.
Text: Daserf的一个版本使用MPRESS打包器

en_text: Daserf hides collected data in password-protected .rar archives.
Text: Daserf将收集的数据隐藏在有密码保护的.rar档案中

Text: Daserf可以记录击键

en_text: Daserf can take screenshots.
Text: Daserf可以进行屏幕截图

en_text: Daserf can use steganography to hide malicious code downloaded to the victim.
Text: Daserf可以使用隐写术来隐藏下载给受害者的恶意代码

en_text: Daserf can download remote files.
Text: Daserf可以下载远程文件

en_text: Daserf can execute shell commands.
Text: Daserf可以执行shell命令

en_text: Daserf leverages Mimikatz and Windows Credential Editor to steal credentials.
Text: Daserf利用Mimikatz和Windows凭证编辑器来窃取凭证

en_text: Daserf uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Daserf使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Daserf uses RC4 encryption to obfuscate HTTP traffic.
Text: Daserf使用RC4加密来混淆HTTP流量

en_text: Daserf uses encrypted Windows APIs and also encrypts data using the alternative base64+RC4 or the Caesar cipher.
Text: Daserf使用加密的Windows APIs，也使用替代的base64 RC4或凯撒密码对数据进行加密

en_text: Daserf uses file and folder names related to legitimate programs in order to blend in, such as HP, Intel, Adobe, and perflogs.
Text: Daserf使用与合法程序有关的文件和文件夹名称，以便混入其中，如惠普、英特尔、Adobe和perflogs

en_text: Daserf uses custom base64 encoding to obfuscate HTTP traffic.
Text: Daserf使用自定义base64编码来混淆HTTP流量

en_text: DDKONG lists files on the victim’s machine.
Text: DDKONG列出受害者机器上的文件

en_text: DDKONG uses Rundll32 to ensure only a single instance of itself is running at once.
Text: DDKONG使用Rundll32来确保一次只运行自己的一个实例

en_text: DDKONG decodes an embedded configuration using XOR.
Text: DDKONG使用XOR解码一个嵌入式配置

en_text: DDKONG downloads and uploads files on the victim’s machine.

en_text: Deep Panda has used ping to identify other machines of interest.

en_text: Deep Panda has used the sticky-keys technique to bypass the RDP login screen on remote systems during intrusions.

en_text: Denis queries the Registry for keys and values.
Text: Denis查询注册表的键和值

en_text: Denis collects OS information and the computer name from the victim’s machine.

en_text: Denis encodes the data sent to the server in Base64.
Text: Denis对发送到服务器的数据进行Base64编码

en_text: Denis obfuscates its code and encrypts the API names. Denis also encodes its payload in Base64.
Text: Denis混淆了它的代码并对API名称进行了加密

en_text: Denis will decrypt important strings used for C&C communication.
Text: Denis将解密用于C语言的重要字符串

en_text: Denis can launch a remote shell to execute arbitrary commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: Denis可以启动一个远程外壳，在受害者的机器上执行任意命令

en_text: Denis exploits a security vulnerability to load a fake DLL and execute its code.
Text: Denis利用一个安全漏洞，加载一个假的DLL并执行其代码

en_text: Denis uses ipconfig to gather the IP address from the system.
Text: Denis使用ipconfig从系统中收集IP地址

en_text: Denis performed process hollowing through the API calls CreateRemoteThread, ResumeThread, and Wow64SetThreadContext.
Text: Denis通过API调用CreateRemoteThread、ResumeThread和Wow64SetThreadContext进行了进程空洞化

en_text: Denis replaces the nonexistent Windows DLL "msfte.dll" with its own malicious version, which is loaded by the SearchIndexer.exe and SearchProtocolHost.exe.
Text: Denis用自己的恶意版本替换了不存在的Windows DLL "msfte.dll"，该版本被SearchIndexer.exe和SearchProtocolHost.exe加载

en_text: Denis has several commands to search directories for files.
Text: Denis有几个命令来搜索目录中的文件

en_text: Denis has a version written in PowerShell.
Text: Denis有一个用PowerShell编写的版本

en_text: The Derusbi malware supports timestomping.
Text: Derusbi恶意软件支持时间跟踪

en_text: Derusbi injects itself into the secure shell (SSH) process.
Text: Derusbi将自己注入到安全外壳（SSH）进程中

en_text: Derusbi is capable of creating a remote Bash shell and executing commands.
Text: Derusbi能够创建一个远程Bash shell并执行命令

en_text: Derusbi is capable of obtaining directory, file, and drive listings.
Text: Derusbi能够获得目录、文件和驱动器列表

en_text: Derusbi is capable of logging keystrokes.
Text: Derusbi能够记录击键

en_text: Derusbi is capable of enumerating Registry keys and values.
Text: Derusbi能够列举注册表的键和值

en_text: Derusbi is capable of deleting files. It has been observed loading a Linux Kernel Module (LKM) and then deleting it from the hard disk as well as overwriting the data with null bytes.
Text: Derusbi能够删除文件。它被观察到加载了一个Linux内核模块（LKM），然后从硬盘上删除它，并以空字节覆盖数据。

en_text: Derusbi gathers the name of the local host, version of GNU Compiler Collection (GCC), and the system information about the CPU, machine, and operating system.
Text: Derusbi收集本地主机的名称、GNU编译器集合（GCC）的版本，以及CPU、机器和操作系统的系统信息

en_text: Derusbi collects current and parent process IDs.
Text: Derusbi收集了当前和父进程的ID

en_text: Derusbi obfuscates C2 traffic with variable 4-byte XOR keys.
Text: Derusbi用可变的4字节XOR密钥混淆了C2流量

en_text: Derusbi binds to a raw socket on a random source port between 31800 and 31900 for C2.
Text: Derusbi在31800和31900之间的随机源端口上绑定了一个原始套接字，用于C2

en_text: Dipsind can be configured to only run during normal working hours, which would make its communications harder to distinguish from normal traffic.
Text: Dipsind可以被配置为只在正常工作时间内运行，这将使其通信更难与正常交通区分开

en_text: Dipsind can spawn remote shells.
Text: Dipsind可以催生远程炮弹

en_text: Dipsind can download remote files.
Text: Dipsind可以下载远程文件

en_text: Dipsind uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Dipsind使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Dipsind encodes C2 traffic with base64.
Text: Dipsind用base64对C2流量进行编码

en_text: Dipsind encrypts C2 data with AES256 in ECB mode.
Text: Dipsind在ECB模式下用AES256对C2数据进行加密

en_text: DLL side-loading has been used to execute BBSRAT through a legitimate Citrix executable, ssonsvr.exe. The Citrix executable was dropped along with BBSRAT by the dropper.
Text: DLL侧面加载被用来通过一个合法的Citrix可执行文件ssonsvr.exe来执行BBSRAT

en_text: DOGCALL can capture microphone data from the victim's machine.
Text: DOGCALL可以从受害者的机器上捕获麦克风数据

en_text: DOGCALL can download and execute additional payloads.
Text: DOGCALL可以下载和执行额外的有效载荷

en_text: DOGCALL is capable of logging keystrokes.
Text: DOGCALL能够记录击键信息

en_text: DOGCALL is capable of leveraging cloud storage APIs such as Cloud, Box, Dropbox, and Yandex for C2.
Text: DOGCALL能够利用云存储API，如Cloud、Box、Dropbox和Yandex for C2

en_text: DOGCALL is capable of capturing screenshots of the victim's machine.
Text: DOGCALL能够抓取受害者机器的屏幕截图

en_text: DOGCALL is encrypted using single-byte XOR.
Text: DOGCALL是使用单字节XOR进行加密的

en_text: Dok installs a root certificate to aid in man-in-the-middle actions.
Text: Dok安装了一个根证书以帮助中间人行动

en_text: Dok uses AppleScript to create a login item for persistence.
Text: Dok使用AppleScript来创建一个用于持久化的登录项

en_text: Dok prompts the user for credentials.
Text: Dok提示用户提供凭证

en_text: Dok persists via a Launch Agent.
Text: Dok通过启动代理持续存在

en_text: Dok persists via a plist login item.
Text: Dok通过一个plist登录项持续存在

en_text: Dok downloads and installs Tor via homebrew.
Text: Dok通过自制软件下载和安装Tor

en_text: down_new has the ability to AES encrypt C2 communications.
Text: down_new具有对C2通信进行AES加密的能力

en_text: down_new has the ability to base64 encode C2 communications.
Text: down_new具有对C2通信进行base64编码的能力

en_text: down_new has the ability to gather information on installed applications.
Text: down_new具有收集已安装的应用程序信息的能力

en_text: down_new has the ability to detect anti-virus products and processes on a compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力检测被攻击主机上的反病毒产品和进程

en_text: down_new has the ability to list running processes on a compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力列出被攻击主机上的运行进程

en_text: down_new has the ability to list the directories on a compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力列出被入侵主机上的目录

en_text: down_new has the ability to identify the MAC address of a compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力识别被攻击主机的MAC地址

en_text: down_new has the ability to identify the system volume information of a compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力识别被攻击主机的系统卷信息

en_text: down_new has the ability to download files to the compromised host.
Text: down_new有能力下载文件到被攻击的主机

en_text: down_new has the ability to use HTTP in C2 communications.
Text: down_new有能力在C2通信中使用HTTP

en_text: Downdelph uses search order hijacking of the Windows executable sysprep.exe to escalate privileges.
Text: Downdelph利用对Windows可执行文件sysprep.exe的搜索顺序劫持来提升权限

en_text: Downdelph uses RC4 to encrypt C2 responses.
Text: Downdelph使用RC4来加密C2响应

en_text: Downdelph bypasses UAC to escalate privileges by using a custom "RedirectEXE" shim database.
Text: Downdelph通过使用一个自定义的 "RedirectEXE "shim数据库绕过UAC来提升权限

en_text: DownPaper uses PowerShell for execution.
Text: DownPaper使用PowerShell来执行

en_text: DownPaper uses PowerShell to add a Registry Run key in order to establish persistence.
Text: DownPaper使用PowerShell添加一个注册表运行键，以建立持久性

en_text: DownPaper uses the command line.
Text: DownPaper使用命令行

en_text: DownPaper collects the victim username and sends it to the C2 server.
Text: DownPaper收集受害者的用户名并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: DownPaper collects the victim host name and serial number, and then sends the information to the C2 server.
Text: DownPaper收集受害者的主机名称和序列号，然后将信息发送到C2服务器

en_text: DownPaper searches and reads the value of the Windows Update Registry Run key.
Text: DownPaper搜索并读取Windows更新注册表运行键的值

en_text: DownPaper communicates to its C2 server over HTTP.
Text: DownPaper通过HTTP与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 cleared Windows event logs and other logs produced by tools they used, including system, security, terminal services, remote services, and audit logs. The actors also deleted specific Registry keys.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0清除了Windows事件日志和他们使用的工具产生的其他日志，包括系统、安全、终端服务、远程服务和审计日志

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 accessed email accounts using Outlook Web Access.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0使用Outlook Web Access访问电子邮件账户

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 used batch scripts to enumerate users on a victim domain controller.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0使用批处理脚本来列举受害者域控制器上的用户

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 used batch scripts to enumerate network information, including information about trusts, zones, and the domain.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0使用批处理脚本来列举网络信息，包括关于信任、区域和域的信息

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 used batch scripts to enumerate administrators and users in the domain.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0使用批处理脚本来列举域中的管理员和用户

en_text: Dragonfly 2.0 created a directory named "out" in the user's %AppData% folder and copied files to it.
Text: Dragonfly 2.0在用户的%AppData%文件夹中创建了一个名为 "out "的目录，并将文件复制到其中

en_text: Dridex contains a backconnect module for tunneling network traffic through a victim's computer. Infected computers become part of a P2P botnet that can relay C2 traffic to other infected peers.
Text: Dridex包含一个Backconnect模块，用于通过受害者的计算机进行网络通信隧道。受感染的计算机成为P2P僵尸网络的一部分，可以将C2流量转发给其他受感染的同伴。

en_text: Dridex contains a module for VNC.
Text: Dridex包含一个用于VNC的模块

en_text: Dridex can perform browser attacks via web injects to steal information such as credentials, certificates, and cookies.
Text: Dridex可以通过网页注入进行浏览器攻击，以窃取信息，如凭证、证书和cookies

en_text: Dridex has used HTTPS for C2 communications.
Text: Dridex已将HTTPS用于C2通信

en_text: Dridex has encrypted traffic with RSA.
Text: Dridex已经用RSA对流量进行了加密

en_text: Dridex has encrypted traffic with RC4.
Text: Dridex用RC4对流量进行了加密

en_text: Drovorub has de-obsfuscated XOR encrypted payloads in WebSocket messages.
Text: Drovorub对WebSocket消息中的XOR加密的有效载荷进行了去伪存真

en_text: Drovorub can delete specific files from a compromised host.
Text: Drovorub可以从被攻击的主机上删除特定文件

en_text: Drovorub can transfer files from the victim machine.
Text: Drovorub可以从受害者机器上传输文件

en_text: Drovorub can use TCP to communicate between its agent and client modules.
Text: Drovorub可以使用TCP在其代理和客户端模块之间进行通信

en_text: Drovorub can use the WebSocket protocol and has initiated communication with C2 servers with an HTTP Upgrade request.
Text: Drovorub可以使用WebSocket协议，并通过HTTP升级请求与C2服务器发起通信

en_text: Drovorub can use kernel modules to establish persistence.
Text: Drovorub可以使用内核模块来建立持久性

en_text: Drovorub can exfiltrate files over C2 infrastructure.
Text: Drovorub可以通过C2基础设施渗出文件

en_text: Drovorub can download files to a compromised host.
Text: Drovorub可以下载文件到被攻击的主机

en_text: Drovorub can execute arbitrary commands as root on a compromised system.
Text: Drovorub可以在被攻击的系统上以root身份执行任意命令

en_text: Drovorub can use a port forwarding rule on its agent module to relay network traffic through the client module to a remote host on the same network.
Text: Drovorub可以在其代理模块上使用端口转发规则，将网络流量通过客户端模块转发到同一网络的远程主机

en_text: Drovorub has used a kernel module rootkit to hide processes, files, executables, and network artifacts from user space view.
Text: Drovorub使用了一个内核模块rootkit来隐藏进程、文件、可执行文件和网络工件，使用户空间无法看到

en_text: Drovorub has used XOR encrypted payloads in WebSocket client to server messages.
Text: Drovorub在WebSocket客户端到服务器的信息中使用了XOR加密的有效载荷

en_text: dsquery can be used to gather information on permission groups within a domain.
Text: dsquery可以用来收集一个域内权限组的信息

en_text: dsquery can be used to gather information on user accounts within a domain.
Text: dsquery可以用来收集一个域内用户账户的信息

en_text: dsquery can be used to gather information on domain trusts with dsquery * -filter "(objectClass=trustedDomain)" -attr *.
Text: dsquery可以用来收集域信任的信息，使用dsquery * -filter "(objectClass=trustedDomain)" -attr *

en_text: Duqu creates a new service that loads a malicious driver when the system starts. When Duqu is active, the operating system believes that the driver is legitimate, as it has been signed with a valid private key.
Text: Duqu创建了一个新的服务，在系统启动时加载一个恶意的驱动程序。当Duqu处于活动状态时，操作系统认为该驱动程序是合法的，因为它已经用有效的私钥签名。

en_text: Duqu examines running system processes for tokens that have specific system privileges. If it finds one, it will copy the token and store it for later use. Eventually it will start new processes with the stored token attached. It can also steal tokens to acquire administrative privileges.
Text: Duqu检查正在运行的系统进程，寻找具有特定系统权限的令牌。如果它发现了一个，它将复制该令牌并存储起来以备后用。最终，它将用存储的令牌启动新的进程。它还可以窃取令牌以获得管理权限。

en_text: Duqu will inject itself into different processes to evade detection. The selection of the target process is influenced by the security software that is installed on the system (Duqu will inject into different processes depending on which security suite is installed on the infected host).
Text: Duqu将自己注入到不同的进程中以逃避检测。目标进程的选择受到安装在系统上的安全软件的影响（Duqu会根据被感染主机上安装的安全套件而注入不同的进程）。

en_text: Duqu can track key presses with a keylogger module.
Text: Duqu可以通过一个键盘记录器模块追踪按键

en_text: The Duqu command and control protocol's data stream can be encrypted with AES-CBC.
Text: Duqu命令和控制协议的数据流可以用AES-CBC进行加密

en_text: Duqu is capable of loading executable code via process hollowing.
Text: Duqu能够通过进程中空加载可执行代码

en_text: Duqu has used msiexec to execute malicious Windows Installer packages. Additionally, a PROPERTY=VALUE pair containing a 56-bit encryption key has been used to decrypt the main payload from the installer packages.
Text: Duqu使用msiexec来执行恶意的Windows安装程序包。此外，一个包含56位加密密钥的PROPERTY=VALUE对已被用于解密安装程序包的主要有效载荷。

en_text: Duqu uses a custom command and control protocol that communicates over commonly used ports, and is frequently encapsulated by application layer protocols.
Text: Duqu使用一个自定义的命令和控制协议，通过常用的端口进行通信，并经常被应用层协议封装起来。

en_text: The DustySky dropper uses Windows Management Instrumentation to extract information about the operating system and whether an anti-virus is active.
Text: DustySky dropper使用Windows Management Instrumentation来提取有关操作系统和反病毒是否处于活动状态的信息

en_text: The DustySky dropper uses a function to obfuscate the name of functions and other parts of the malware.
Text: DustySky dropper使用一个函数来混淆函数的名称和恶意软件的其他部分

en_text: DustySky contains a keylogger.
Text: DustySky包含一个键盘记录器

en_text: DustySky captures PNG screenshots of the main screen.
Text: DustySky捕捉主屏幕的PNG屏幕截图

en_text: DustySky scans the victim for files that contain certain keywords and document types including PDF, DOC, DOCX, XLS, and XLSX, from a list that is obtained from the C2 as a text file. It can also identify logical drives for the infected machine.
Text: DustySky从C2获得的文本文件列表中扫描受害者包含某些关键词和文件类型的文件，包括PDF、DOC、DOCX、XLS和XLSX。它还可以识别受感染机器的逻辑驱动器。

en_text: DustySky collects information about running processes from victims.
Text: DustySky从受害者那里收集有关运行进程的信息

en_text: DustySky checks for the existence of anti-virus.
Text: DustySky检查是否存在反病毒

en_text: DustySky can shutdown the infected machine.
Text: DustySky可以关闭被感染的机器

en_text: DustySky can detect connected USB devices.
Text: DustySky可以检测连接的USB设备

en_text: DustySky can delete files it creates from the infected system.
Text: DustySky可以删除它在受感染系统中创建的文件

en_text: DustySky can compress files via RAR while staging data to be exfiltrated.
Text: DustySky可以通过RAR压缩文件，同时将数据分期外泄

en_text: DustySky lists all installed software for the infected machine.
Text: DustySky列出了受感染机器的所有已安装软件

en_text: DustySky searches for removable media and duplicates itself onto it.
Text: DustySky搜索可移动媒体并将自己复制到上面

en_text: DustySky searches for network drives and removable media and duplicates itself onto them.
Text: DustySky搜索网络驱动器和可移动媒体，并将自己复制到它们上面

en_text: DustySky extracts basic information about the operating system.
Text: DustySky提取有关操作系统的基本信息

en_text: DustySky achieves persistence by creating a Registry entry in HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run.
Text: DustySky通过在HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run中创建一个注册表项来实现持久性

en_text: DustySky has exfiltrated data to the C2 server.
Text: DustySky已经将数据外流到C2服务器

en_text: DustySky has two hard-coded domains for C2 servers; if the first does not respond, it will try the second.
Text: DustySky有两个硬编码的C2服务器域；如果第一个没有响应，它将尝试第二个

en_text: DustySky has used both HTTP and HTTPS for C2.
Text: DustySky在C2中同时使用了HTTP和HTTPS

en_text: DustySky created folders in temp directories to host collected files before exfiltration.
Text: DustySky在临时目录中创建了文件夹，以便在渗出前存放收集的文件

en_text: Dyre decrypts resources needed for targeting the victim.
Text: Dyre解密了针对受害者的所需资源

en_text: Dyre can detect sandbox analysis environments by inspecting the process list and Registry.
Text: Dyre可以通过检查进程列表和注册表来检测沙盒分析环境

en_text: Dyre uses HTTPS for C2 communications.
Text: Dyre使用HTTPS进行C2通信

en_text: Dyre has been delivered with encrypted resources and must be unpacked for execution.
Text: Dyre是以加密的资源交付的，必须解压后才能执行

en_text: Dyre registers itself as a service by adding several Registry keys.
Text: Dyre通过添加几个注册表键将自己注册为一项服务

en_text: Dyre has the ability to send information staged on a compromised host externally to C2.
Text: Dyre有能力将被攻击的主机上的信息从外部发送到C2

en_text: Dyre has the ability to identify installed programs on a compromised host.
Text: Dyre有能力识别被破坏的主机上安装的程序

en_text: Dyre has the ability to identify network settings on a compromised host.
Text: Dyre有能力识别被破坏的主机上的网络设置

en_text: Dyre has the ability to identify running services on a compromised host.
Text: Dyre有能力识别被破坏的主机上正在运行的服务

en_text: Dyre has the ability to identify the computer name, OS version, and hardware configuration on a compromised host.
Text: Dyre有能力识别被入侵主机上的计算机名称、操作系统版本和硬件配置

en_text: Dyre has the ability to identify the users on a compromised host.
Text: Dyre有能力识别被入侵主机上的用户

en_text: Dyre has the ability to achieve persistence by adding a new task in the task scheduler to run every minute.
Text: Dyre有能力通过在任务调度器中添加一个新任务来实现持久性，每分钟运行一次

en_text: Dyre has the ability to create files in a TEMP folder to act as a database to store information.
Text: Dyre有能力在TEMP文件夹中创建文件，作为数据库来存储信息

en_text: Dyre has the ability to directly inject its code into the web browser process.
Text: Dyre有能力直接将其代码注入网络浏览器进程中

en_text: Dyre has a command to download and executes additional files.
Text: Dyre有一个下载和执行额外文件的命令

en_text: Dyre injects into other processes to load modules.
Text: Dyre注入到其他进程中以加载模块

en_text: Ebury can intercept private keys using a trojanized ssh-add function.
Text: Ebury可以使用木马化的ssh-add功能拦截私钥

en_text: Ebury has used a DGA to generate a domain name for C2.
Text: Ebury使用DGA为C2生成了一个域名

en_text: Ebury has encrypted C2 traffic using the client IP address, then encoded it as a hexadecimal string.
Text: Ebury使用客户的IP地址对C2流量进行了加密，然后将其编码为十六进制的字符串

en_text: Ebury has used DNS requests over UDP port 53 for C2.
Text: Ebury通过UDP端口53使用DNS请求进行C2

en_text: Ebury has been embedded into modified OpenSSH binaries to gain persistent access to SSH credential information.
Text: Ebury已经被嵌入到修改过的OpenSSH二进制文件中，以获得对SSH凭证信息的持久性访问

en_text: Ebury has intercepted unencrypted private keys as well as private key pass-phrases.
Text: Ebury已经截获了未加密的私钥以及私钥密码

en_text: Ebury has encoded C2 traffic in hexadecimal format.
Text: Ebury以十六进制格式对C2流量进行了编码

en_text: Ebury has obfuscated its strings with a simple XOR encryption with a static key.
Text: Ebury用静态密钥的简单XOR加密来混淆其字符串

en_text: Ebury has installed a self-signed RPM package mimicking the original system package on RPM based systems.
Text: Ebury在基于RPM的系统上安装了一个模仿原始系统包的自签名RPM包

en_text: Elderwood has delivered zero-day exploits and malware to victims via targeted emails containing a link to malicious content hosted on an uncommon Web server.
Text: Elderwood公司通过目标邮件向受害者提供零日漏洞和恶意软件，邮件中包含一个指向不常见的网络服务器上托管的恶意内容的链接

en_text: Elderwood has targeted manufacturers in the supply chain for the defense industry.
Text: Elderwood将目标锁定在国防工业供应链的制造商上

en_text: Elderwood has used exploitation of endpoint software, including Microsoft Internet Explorer Adobe Flash vulnerabilities, to gain execution. They have also used zero-day exploits.
Text: Elderwood利用端点软件，包括微软Internet Explorer Adobe Flash漏洞，来获得执行。他们同时使用零日漏洞

en_text: Elderwood has leveraged multiple types of spearphishing in order to attempt to get a user to open attachments.
Text: Elderwood利用多种类型的鱼叉式钓鱼，试图让用户打开附件

en_text: Elderwood has leveraged multiple types of spearphishing in order to attempt to get a user to open links.
Text: Elderwood利用多种类型的鱼叉式网络钓鱼，以试图让用户打开链接

en_text: The Ritsol backdoor trojan used by Elderwood can download files onto a compromised host from a remote location.
Text: Elderwood使用的Ritsol后门木马可以从远程位置将文件下载到被攻击的主机上

en_text: Elderwood has delivered zero-day exploits and malware to victims via targeted emails containing malicious attachments.
Text: Elderwood通过含有恶意附件的目标邮件向受害者提供零日漏洞和恶意软件

en_text: Elderwood has delivered zero-day exploits and malware to victims by injecting malicious code into specific public Web pages visited by targets within a particular sector.
Text: Elderwood通过将恶意代码注入特定部门内目标访问的特定公共网页，向受害者提供零日漏洞和恶意软件

en_text: Elderwood has encrypted documents and malicious executables.
Text: Elderwood有加密的文件和恶意的可执行文件

en_text: Elderwood has packed malware payloads before delivery to victims.
Text: Elderwood在交付给受害者之前已经将恶意软件的有效载荷打包

en_text: A variant of Elise executes dir C:\progra~1 when initially run.
Text: Elise的一个变体在最初运行时执行dir C:\progra~1

en_text: Elise performs timestomping of a CAB file it creates.
Text: Elise对其创建的CAB文件进行时间分解

en_text: Elise encrypts several of its files, including configuration files.
Text: Elise对其几个文件进行加密，包括配置文件

en_text: Elise injects DLL files into iexplore.exe.
Text: Elise将DLL文件注入iexplore.exe中

en_text: Elise configures itself as a service.
Text: Elise将自己配置为一个服务

en_text: Elise can download additional files from the C2 server for execution.
Text: Elise可以从C2服务器下载更多的文件来执行

en_text: Elise is capable of launching a remote shell on the host to delete itself.
Text: Elise能够在主机上启动一个远程外壳来删除自己

en_text: Elise exfiltrates data using cookie values that are Base64-encoded.
Text: Elise使用Base64编码的cookie值来渗出数据

en_text: Elise communicates over HTTP or HTTPS for C2.
Text: Elise通过HTTP或HTTPS进行C2通信

en_text: Elise enumerates processes via the tasklist command.
Text: Elise通过任务列表命令列举进程

en_text: Elise encrypts exfiltrated data with RC4.
Text: Elise用RC4加密渗出的数据

en_text: Elise creates a file in AppData\Local\Microsoft\Windows\Explorer and stores all harvested data in that file.
Text: Elise在AppData\Local\Microsoft\Windows\Explorer中创建一个文件，并将所有收获的数据存储在该文件中

en_text: Elise executes net start after initial communication is made to the remote server.
Text: Elise在与远程服务器进行初始通信后执行net start

en_text: Elise executes net user after initial communication is made to the remote server.
Text: Elise在与远程服务器进行初始通信后执行net用户

en_text: Elise executes systeminfo after initial communication is made to the remote server.
Text: Elise在与远程服务器进行初始通信后执行systeminfo

en_text: Elise executes ipconfig /all after initial communication is made to the remote server.
Text: Elise执行了ipconfig Elise执行ipconfig Elise执行了ipconfig

en_text: ELMER is capable of performing process listings.
Text: ELMER能够执行过程列表

en_text: ELMER is capable of performing directory listings.
Text: ELMER能够执行目录列表

en_text: ELMER uses HTTP for command and control.
Text: ELMER使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: Variants of Emissary encrypt payloads using various XOR ciphers, as well as a custom algorithm that uses the "srand" and "rand" functions.
Text: Emissary的变种使用各种XOR密码以及一种使用 "srand "和 "rand "函数的自定义算法来加密有效载荷

en_text: Variants of Emissary have used rundll32.exe in Registry values added to establish persistence.
Text: Emissary的变种在注册表值中使用了rundll32.exe，以建立持久性

en_text: Variants of Emissary have added Run Registry keys to establish persistence.
Text: Emissary的变种增加了运行注册表键来建立持久性

en_text: A variant of Emissary appends junk data to the end of its DLL file to create a large file that may exceed the maximum size that anti-virus programs can scan.
Text: Emissary的一个变种将垃圾数据附加到其DLL文件的末尾，形成一个大文件，可能超过反病毒程序可以扫描的最大尺寸

en_text: Emissary injects its DLL file into a newly spawned Internet Explorer process.
Text: Emissary将其DLL文件注入一个新生成的Internet Explorer进程中

en_text: Emissary is capable of configuring itself as a service.
Text: Emissary能够将自己配置成一种服务

en_text: Emissary uses HTTP or HTTPS for C2.
Text: Emissary使用HTTP或HTTPS进行C2

en_text: Emissary has the capability to create a remote shell and execute specified commands.
Text: Emissary有能力创建一个远程shell并执行指定的命令

en_text: Emissary has the capability to download files from the C2 server.
Text: Emissary有能力从C2服务器下载文件

en_text: Emissary has the capability to execute the command ipconfig /all.
Text: Emissary有能力执行ipconfig命令 Emissary具有执行ipconfig命令的能力

en_text: Emissary has the capability to execute the command net localgroup administrators.
Text: Emissary有能力执行net localgroup administrators的命令

en_text: Emissary has the capability to execute the command net start to interact with services.
Text: Emissary有能力执行net start命令，与服务进行交互

en_text: Emissary has the capability to execute ver, systeminfo, and gpresult commands.
Text: Emissary有能力执行ver、systeminfo和gpresult命令

en_text: Emotet has sent Microsoft Word documents with embedded macros that will invoke scripts to download additional payloads.
Text: Emotet发送了带有嵌入式宏的微软Word文件，这些文件将调用脚本下载额外的有效载荷

en_text: Emotet can brute force a local admin password, then use it to facilitate lateral movement.
Text: Emotet可以暴力破解本地管理员密码，然后用它来促进横向移动

en_text: Emotet has used cmd.exe to run a PowerShell script.
Text: Emotet使用cmd.exe来运行PowerShell脚本

en_text: Emotet has used HTTP over ports such as 20, 22, 7080, and 50000, in addition to using ports commonly associated with HTTP/S.
Text: Emotet使用了HTTP的端口，如20、22、7080和50000，此外还使用了通常与HTTP有关的端口

en_text: Emotet has used Powershell to retrieve the malicious payload and download additional resources like Mimikatz.
Text: Emotet使用了Powershell来检索恶意的有效载荷并下载额外的资源，如Mimikatz

en_text: Emotet has used WMI to execute powershell.exe.
Text: Emotet使用了WMI来执行powerhell.exe

en_text: Emotet has used custom packers to protect its payloads.
Text: Emotet使用了定制的打包器来保护其有效载荷

en_text: Emotet has been delivered by phishing emails containing attachments.
Text: Emotet是通过含有附件的钓鱼邮件传递的

en_text: Emotet has been delivered by phishing emails containing links.
Text: Emotet是由含有链接的钓鱼邮件传递的

en_text: Emotet has maintained persistence through a scheduled task.
Text: Emotet通过一个预定任务保持了持久性

en_text: Emotet has relied upon users clicking on a malicious attachment delivered through spearphishing.
Text: Emotet依靠的是用户点击通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼传递的恶意附件

en_text: Emotet has relied upon users clicking on a malicious link delivered through spearphishing.
Text: Emotet依靠的是用户点击通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼提供的恶意链接

en_text: Emotet has been observed dropping password grabber modules including Mimikatz.
Text: Emotet已经被观察到丢弃了包括Mimikatz在内的密码抓取模块

en_text: Emotet has been observed dropping browser password grabber modules.
Text: Emotet已经被观察到丢弃了浏览器密码抓取模块

en_text: Emotet has obfuscated macros within malicious documents to hide the URLs hosting the malware,  CMD.exe arguments, and PowerShell scripts.
Text: Emotet在恶意文件中混淆了宏，以隐藏承载恶意软件的URL、CMD.exe参数和PowerShell脚本

en_text: Empire contains modules that can discover and exploit path interception opportunities in the PATH environment variable.
Text: Empire包含的模块可以发现并利用PATH环境变量中的路径拦截机会

en_text: Empire contains multiple modules for injecting into processes, such as Invoke-PSInject.
Text: Empire包含多个用于注入进程的模块，如Invoke-PSInject

en_text: Empire contains modules that can discover and exploit unquoted path vulnerabilities.
Text: Empire包含可以发现和利用非引用路径漏洞的模块

en_text: Empire contains modules for executing commands over SSH as well as in-memory VNC agent injection.
Text: Empire包含通过SSH执行命令的模块，以及内存中的VNC代理注入

en_text: Empire contains some modules that leverage API hooking to carry out tasks, such as netripper.
Text: Empire包含一些利用API挂钩来执行任务的模块，如netripper

en_text: Empire includes various modules for finding files of interest on hosts and network shares.
Text: Empire包括各种模块，用于在主机和网络共享上寻找感兴趣的文件

en_text: Empire can acquire local and domain user account information.
Text: Empire可以获得本地和域的用户账户信息

en_text: Empire can acquire network configuration information like DNS servers and network proxies used by a host.
Text: Empire可以获得网络配置信息，如主机使用的DNS服务器和网络代理

en_text: Empire can enumerate Security Support Providers (SSPs) as well as utilize PowerSploit's Install-SSP and Invoke-Mimikatz to install malicious SSPs and log authentication events.
Text: Empire可以列举安全支持供应商（SSP），以及利用PowerSploit的Install-SSP和Invoke-Mimikatz来安装恶意的SSP并记录认证事件

en_text: Empire can use modules like Invoke-SessionGopher to extract private key and session information.
Text: Empire可以使用Invoke-SessionGopher等模块来提取私钥和会话信息

en_text: Empire can use WMI to deliver a payload to a remote host.
Text: Empire可以使用WMI向远程主机传递有效载荷

en_text: Empire leverages PowerShell for the majority of its client-side agent tasks. Empire also contains the ability to conduct PowerShell remoting with the Invoke-PSRemoting module.
Text: Empire利用PowerShell完成了大部分的客户端代理任务

en_text: Empire uses PowerSploit's Invoke-Kerberoast to request service tickets and return crackable ticket hashes.
Text: Empire使用PowerSploit的Invoke-Kerberoast来请求服务票据并返回可破解的票据哈希值

en_text: Epic collects the user name from the victim’s machine.
Text: Epic从受害者的机器上收集用户名

en_text: Epic recursively searches for all .doc files on the system and collects a directory listing of the Desktop, %TEMP%, and %WINDOWS%\Temp directories.
Text: Epic递归搜索系统中的所有.doc文件，并收集桌面、%TEMP%和%WINDOWS%/Temp目录的目录清单

en_text: Epic uses HTTP and HTTPS for C2 communications.
Text: Epic使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2通信

en_text: Epic uses the net time command  to get the system time from the machine and collect the current date and time zone information.
Text: Epic使用net time命令从机器上获取系统时间，并收集当前日期和时区信息

en_text: Epic uses the net use, net session, and netstat commands to gather information on network connections.
Text: Epic使用net use、net session和netstat命令来收集网络连接的信息

en_text: Epic uses the rem reg query command to obtain values from Registry keys.
Text: Epic使用rem reg query命令从注册表键中获取数值

en_text: Epic uses the tasklist /svc command to list the services on the system.
Text: Epic使用任务列表 Epic使用的是任务列表 Epic使用任务清单 Epic使用了任务列表

en_text: Epic uses the tasklist /v command to obtain a list of processes.
Text: Epic使用任务列表 Epic使用的是任务列表 Epic使用任务清单 Epic使用了任务列表

en_text: Epic encrypts commands from the C2 server using a hardcoded key.
Text: Epic使用一个硬编码的密钥对来自C2服务器的命令进行加密

en_text: Epic collects the OS version, hardware information, computer name, available system memory status, disk space information, and system and user language settings.
Text: Epic收集操作系统版本、硬件信息、计算机名称、可用系统内存状态、磁盘空间信息以及系统和用户语言设置

en_text: Epic gathers information on local group names.
Text: Epic收集了关于本地组名的信息

en_text: Epic gathers a list of all user accounts, privilege classes, and time of last logon.
Text: Epic收集了所有用户账户、权限等级和最后登录时间的列表

en_text: Epic searches for anti-malware services running on the victim’s machine and terminates itself if it finds them.
Text: Epic搜索受害者机器上运行的反恶意软件服务，如果发现这些服务，就会自行终止

en_text: Epic heavily obfuscates its code to make analysis more difficult.
Text: Epic严重混淆了其代码，使分析更加困难

en_text: Epic has a command to delete a file from the machine.
Text: Epic有一个命令，可以从机器上删除一个文件

en_text: Epic uses the nbtstat -n and nbtstat -s commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: Epic在受害者的机器上使用nbtstat -n和nbtstat -s命令

en_text: Epic encrypts collected data using a public key framework before sending it over the C2 channel. Some variants encrypt the collected data with AES and encode it with base64 before transmitting it to the C2 server.
Text: Epic在通过C2通道发送之前，使用公钥框架对收集的数据进行加密

en_text: Epic compresses the collected data with bzip2 before sending it to the C2 server.
Text: Epic在向C2服务器发送之前用bzip2压缩了收集的数据

en_text: Epic has overwritten the function pointer in the extra window memory of Explorer's Shell_TrayWnd in order to execute malicious code in the context of the explorer.exe process.
Text: Epic重写了Explorer的Shell_TrayWnd的额外窗口内存中的函数指针，以便在explorer.exe进程的上下文中执行恶意代码

en_text: esentutl can use Volume Shadow Copy to copy locked files such as ntds.dit.
Text: esentutl可以使用卷影复制来复制锁定的文件，如ntds.dit

en_text: esentutl can be used to read and write alternate data streams.
Text: esentutl可以用来读取和写入备用数据流

en_text: esentutl can be used to copy files to/from a given URL.
Text: esentutl可以用来复制文件到/从一个给定的URL。

en_text: esentutl can be used to copy files to/from a remote share.
Text: esentutl可以用来复制文件到/来自一个远程共享。

en_text: EvilBunny has downloaded additional Lua scripts from the C2.
Text: EvilBunny从C2下载了额外的Lua脚本

en_text: EvilBunny has exploited CVE-2011-4369, a vulnerability in the PRC component in Adobe Reader.
Text: EvilBunny利用了CVE-2011-4369，Adobe Reader中的PRC组件存在漏洞

en_text: EvilBunny has used the API calls NtQuerySystemTime, GetSystemTimeAsFileTime, and GetTickCount to check to see if the malware is running in a sandbox.
Text: EvilBunny使用API调用NtQuerySystemTime、GetSystemTimeAsFileTime和GetTickCount来检查恶意软件是否在沙盒中运行

en_text: EvilBunny has used EnumProcesses() to identify how many process are running in the environment.
Text: EvilBunny使用EnumProcesses()来识别环境中运行着多少个进程

en_text: EvilBunny has used WMI to gather information about the system.
Text: EvilBunny使用WMI来收集系统的信息

en_text: EvilBunny for a number of specific processes and the length of its own name to identify if the malware is in a sandbox environment.
Text: EvilBunny为一些特定的进程和自己的名字的长度，以识别恶意软件是否在沙盒环境中

en_text: EvilBunny has executed commands via scheduled tasks.
Text: EvilBunny已通过计划任务执行命令

en_text: EvilBunny has an integrated scripting engine to download and execute Lua scripts.
Text: EvilBunny有一个集成的脚本引擎来下载和执行Lua脚本

en_text: EvilBunny has deleted the initial dropper after running through the environment checks.
Text: EvilBunny在通过环境检查后，已经删除了最初的dropper

en_text: EvilBunny has executed C2 commands directly via HTTP.
Text: EvilBunny直接通过HTTP执行C2命令

en_text: EvilGrab has the capability to capture keystrokes.
Text: EvilGrab具有捕捉键盘的能力

en_text: EvilGrab has the capability to capture screenshots.
Text: EvilGrab具有捕捉屏幕截图的能力

en_text: EvilGrab adds a Registry Run key for ctfmon.exe to establish persistence.
Text: EvilGrab为ctfmon.exe添加了一个注册表运行键以建立持久性

en_text: EvilGrab has the capability to capture audio from a victim machine.
Text: EvilGrab有能力从受害者的机器上捕获音频

en_text: EvilGrab has the capability to capture video from a victim machine.
Text: EvilGrab有能力从受害者的机器上捕捉视频

en_text: Exaramel for Linux uses HTTPS for C2 communications.
Text: Exaramel for Linux使用HTTPS进行C2通信

en_text: Exaramel for Linux uses RC4 for encrypting the configuration.
Text: Exaramel for Linux使用RC4对配置进行加密

en_text: Exaramel for Linux has a command to download a file from a remote server.
Text: Exaramel for Linux有一个命令可以从远程服务器下载文件

en_text: The Exaramel for Windows dropper creates and starts a Windows service named wsmprovav with the description "Windows Check AV" in an apparent attempt to masquerade as a legitimate service.
Text: Exaramel for Windows的下载程序创建并启动了一个名为wsmprovav的Windows服务，描述为 "Windows Check AV"，显然试图伪装成一个合法服务

en_text: The Exaramel for Windows dropper creates and starts a Windows service named wsmprovav with the description "Windows Check AV."
Text: Exaramel for Windows的下载程序创建并启动一个名为wsmprovav的Windows服务，描述为 "Windows Check AV"

en_text: Exaramel for Windows adds the configuration to the Registry in XML format.
Text: Exaramel for Windows将配置以XML格式添加到注册表

en_text: Exaramel for Windows automatically encrypts files before sending them to the C2 server.
Text: Exaramel for Windows在将文件发送到C2服务器之前会自动加密

en_text: Exaramel for Windows specifies a path to store files scheduled for exfiltration.
Text: Exaramel for Windows指定了一个路径来存储计划渗出的文件

en_text: Expand can be used to decompress a local or remote CAB file into an executable.
Text: Expand可以用来将本地或远程的CAB文件解压成一个可执行文件

en_text: FakeM contains a keylogger module.
Text: FakeM包含一个键盘记录器模块

en_text: FakeM C2 traffic attempts to evade detection by resembling data generated by legitimate messenger applications, such as MSN and Yahoo! messengers. Additionally, some variants of FakeM use modified SSL code for communications back to C2 servers, making SSL decryption ineffective.
Text: FakeM的C2流量试图通过类似于合法信使应用程序（如MSN和雅虎信使）产生的数据来逃避检测。此外，FakeM的一些变种使用修改过的SSL代码进行通信，回到C2服务器，使SSL解密失效。

en_text: Some variants of FakeM use SSL to communicate with C2 servers.
Text: FakeM的一些变种使用SSL与C2服务器通信

en_text: The original variant of FakeM encrypts C2 traffic using a custom encryption cipher that uses an XOR key of "YHCRA" and bit rotation between each XOR operation. Some variants of FakeM use RC4 to encrypt C2 traffic.
Text: FakeM的原始变体使用自定义的加密密码对C2流量进行加密，该密码使用 "YHCRA "的XOR密钥和每个XOR操作之间的比特旋转

en_text: FALLCHILL can collect operating system (OS) version information, processor information, system name, and information about installed disks from the victim.
Text: FALLCHILL可以从受害者那里收集操作系统（OS）版本信息、处理器信息、系统名称和已安装磁盘的信息

en_text: FALLCHILL can delete malware and associated artifacts from the victim.
Text: FALLCHILL可以从受害者身上删除恶意软件和相关工件

en_text: FALLCHILL can search files on a victim.
Text: FALLCHILL可以搜索受害者的文件

en_text: FALLCHILL can modify file or directory timestamps.
Text: FALLCHILL可以修改文件或目录的时间戳

en_text: FALLCHILL uses fake Transport Layer Security (TLS) to communicate with its C2 server.
Text: FALLCHILL使用假的传输层安全（TLS）来与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: FALLCHILL collects MAC address and local IP address information from the victim.
Text: FALLCHILL收集受害者的MAC地址和本地IP地址信息

en_text: FALLCHILL encrypts C2 data with RC4 encryption.
Text: FALLCHILL用RC4加密法对C2数据进行加密

en_text: FatDuke has the ability to execute PowerShell scripts.
Text: FatDuke具有执行PowerShell脚本的能力

en_text: FatDuke can secure delete its DLL.
Text: FatDuke可以安全地删除其DLL

en_text: FatDuke can get user agent strings for the default browser from HKCU\Software\Classes\http\shell\open\command.
Text: FatDuke可以从HKCU\Software\Classes\httpshell\open\command获得默认浏览器的用户代理字符串

en_text: FatDuke can copy files and directories from a compromised host.
Text: FatDuke可以从被攻击的主机上复制文件和目录

en_text: FatDuke can call ShellExecuteW to open the default browser on the URL localhost.
Text: FatDuke可以调用ShellExecuteW来打开URL localhost上的默认浏览器

en_text: FatDuke can AES encrypt C2 communications.
Text: FatDuke可以对C2通信进行AES加密

en_text: FatDuke can decrypt AES encrypted C2 communications.
Text: FatDuke可以解密AES加密的C2通信

en_text: FatDuke can list running processes on the localhost.
Text: FatDuke可以列出本地主机上正在运行的进程

en_text: FatDuke can enumerate directories on target machines.
Text: FatDuke可以列举目标机器上的目录

en_text: FatDuke can identify the MAC address on the target computer.
Text: FatDuke可以识别目标计算机上的MAC地址

en_text: FatDuke can use base64 encoding, string stacking, and opaque predicates for obfuscation.
Text: FatDuke可以使用base64编码、字符串堆叠和不透明的谓词进行混淆。

en_text: FatDuke can used pipes to connect machines with restricted internet access to remote machines via other infected hosts.
Text: FatDuke可以使用管道将互联网访问受限的机器通过其他受感染的主机连接到远程机器。

en_text: FatDuke can collect the user name, Windows version, computer name, and available space on discs from a compromised host.
Text: FatDuke可以收集用户名、Windows版本、计算机名称和被攻击主机上的磁盘可用空间

en_text: FatDuke can be controlled via a custom C2 protocol over HTTP.
Text: FatDuke可以通过HTTP的自定义C2协议进行控制

en_text: FatDuke can execute via rundll32.
Text: FatDuke可以通过rundll32执行

en_text: FatDuke can turn itself on or off at random intervals.
Text: FatDuke可以在随机的时间间隔内开启或关闭自己

en_text: FatDuke has used HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run to establish persistence.
Text: FatDuke使用HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run来建立持久性

en_text: FatDuke has attempted to mimic a compromised user's traffic by using the same user agent as the installed browser.
Text: FatDuke试图通过使用与所安装的浏览器相同的用户代理来模仿被入侵用户的流量

en_text: FatDuke has used several C2 servers per targeted organization.
Text: FatDuke为每个目标组织使用了几个C2服务器

en_text: FatDuke has been regularly repacked by its operators to create large binaries and evade detection.
Text: FatDuke已被其操作者定期重新打包，以创建大型二进制文件并逃避检测

en_text: FatDuke has been packed with junk code and strings.
Text: FatDuke已经被包装成垃圾代码和字符串

en_text: FatDuke has the ability to create a process.
Text: FatDuke有能力创建一个流程

en_text: Felismus checks for processes associated with anti-virus vendors.
Text: Felismus检查与反病毒供应商有关的进程

en_text: Felismus can download files from remote servers.
Text: Felismus可以从远程服务器下载文件

en_text: Felismus uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Felismus使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Felismus uses command line for execution.
Text: Felismus使用命令行来执行

en_text: Felismus collects the current username and sends it to the C2 server.
Text: Felismus收集当前的用户名并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Felismus collects the victim LAN IP address and sends it to the C2 server.
Text: Felismus收集受害者局域网的IP地址并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Felismus collects the system information, including hostname and OS version, and sends it to the C2 server.
Text: Felismus收集系统信息，包括主机名和操作系统版本，并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Felismus has masqueraded as legitimate Adobe Content Management System files.
Text: Felismus已伪装成合法的Adobe内容管理系统文件

en_text: FELIXROOT queries the Registry for specific keys for potential privilege escalation and proxy information. FELIXROOT has also used WMI to query the Windows Registry.
Text: FELIXROOT查询注册表的特定键，以获取潜在的特权升级和代理信息

en_text: FELIXROOT creates a .LNK file for persistence.
Text: FELIXROOT创建了一个.LNK文件用于持久化

en_text: FELIXROOT gathers the time zone information from the victim’s machine.
Text: FELIXROOT从受害者的机器上收集时区信息

en_text: FELIXROOT collects the username from the victim’s machine.
Text: FELIXROOT从受害者的机器上收集用户名

en_text: FELIXROOT checks for installed security software like antivirus and firewall.
Text: FELIXROOT检查已安装的安全软件，如防病毒和防火墙

en_text: FELIXROOT deletes the .LNK file from the startup directory as well as the dropper components.
Text: FELIXROOT删除了启动目录中的.LNK文件以及dropper组件

en_text: FELIXROOT deletes the Registry key HKCU\Software\Classes\Applications\rundll32.exe\shell\open.
Text: FELIXROOT删除了注册表键HKCU\Software\Classes\Applications\rundll32.exe\shell\open

en_text: FELIXROOT uses HTTP and HTTPS to communicate with the C2 server.
Text: FELIXROOT使用HTTP和HTTPS与C2服务器通信

en_text: FELIXROOT uses Rundll32 for executing the dropper program.
Text: FELIXROOT使用Rundll32来执行dropper程序

en_text: FELIXROOT uses WMI to query the Windows Registry.
Text: FELIXROOT使用WMI来查询Windows注册表

en_text: FELIXROOT encrypts strings in the backdoor using a custom XOR algorithm.
Text: FELIXROOT使用一种自定义的XOR算法对后门中的字符串进行加密

en_text: FELIXROOT collects the victim’s computer name, processor architecture, OS version, volume serial number, and system type.
Text: FELIXROOT收集了受害者的计算机名称、处理器架构、操作系统版本、卷轴序列号和系统类型

en_text: FELIXROOT collects a list of running processes.
Text: FELIXROOT收集了一个正在运行的进程列表

en_text: FELIXROOT collects information about the network including the IP address and DHCP server.
Text: FELIXROOT收集有关网络的信息，包括IP地址和DHCP服务器

en_text: FELIXROOT encrypts collected data with AES and Base64 and then sends it to the C2 server.
Text: FELIXROOT用AES和Base64对收集的数据进行加密，然后将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: FELIXROOT adds a shortcut file to the startup folder for persistence.
Text: FELIXROOT在启动文件夹中添加了一个快捷方式文件，以便持久保存

en_text: FELIXROOT downloads and uploads files to and from the victim’s machine.
Text: FELIXROOT在受害者的机器上下载和上传文件

en_text: FELIXROOT executes batch scripts on the victim’s machine, and can launch a reverse shell for command execution.
Text: FELIXROOT在受害者的机器上执行批处理脚本，并可以启动一个反向外壳来执行命令

en_text: Fgdump can dump Windows password hashes.
Text: Fgdump可以转储Windows密码哈希值

en_text: FIN10 has used RDP to move laterally to systems in the victim environment.
Text: FIN10利用RDP横向移动到受害者环境中的系统

en_text: FIN10 has used stolen credentials to connect remotely to victim networks using VPNs protected with only a single factor.
Text: FIN10利用窃取的凭证，使用仅有单因素保护的VPN远程连接到受害者网络

en_text: FIN10 uses PowerShell for execution as well as PowerShell Empire to establish persistence.
Text: FIN10使用PowerShell来执行以及PowerShell Empire来建立持久性

en_text: FIN10 has moved laterally using the Local Administrator account.
Text: FIN10使用本地管理员账户进行了横向移动

en_text: FIN10 has used batch scripts and scheduled tasks to delete critical system files.
Text: FIN10使用批处理脚本和计划任务来删除关键的系统文件

en_text: FIN10 has established persistence by using the Registry option in PowerShell Empire to add a Run key.
Text: FIN10通过使用PowerShell Empire中的注册表选项来添加一个运行键，建立了持久性

en_text: FIN10 has established persistence by using S4U tasks as well as the Scheduled Task option in PowerShell Empire.
Text: FIN10通过使用S4U任务以及PowerShell Empire的Scheduled Task选项建立了持久性

en_text: FIN10 has used Meterpreter to enumerate users on remote systems.
Text: FIN10已经使用Meterpreter来列举远程系统上的用户

en_text: FIN10 has executed malicious .bat files containing PowerShell commands.
Text: FIN10已经执行了包含PowerShell命令的恶意.bat文件

en_text: FIN10 has deployed Meterpreter stagers and SplinterRAT instances in the victim network after moving laterally.
Text: FIN10在横向移动后在受害者网络中部署了Meterpreter stagers和SplinterRAT实例

en_text: FIN4 has used Tor to log in to victims' email accounts.
Text: FIN4利用Tor登录了受害者的电子邮件账户

en_text: FIN4 has used legitimate credentials to hijack email communications.
Text: FIN4利用合法凭证劫持了电子邮件通信

en_text: FIN4 has accessed and hijacked online email communications using stolen credentials.
Text: FIN4利用窃取的凭证访问并劫持了在线电子邮件通信

en_text: FIN4 has used VBA macros to display a dialog box and collect victim credentials.
Text: FIN4使用VBA宏来显示一个对话框并收集受害者的证书

en_text: FIN4 has used spearphishing emails containing attachments (which are often stolen, legitimate documents sent from compromised accounts) with embedded malicious macros.
Text: FIN4使用了包含附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件（这些附件通常是被盗的合法文件，由被攻击的账户发送），其中嵌入了恶意的宏程序

en_text: FIN4 has used spearphishing emails (often sent from compromised accounts) containing malicious links.
Text: FIN4使用了含有恶意链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件（经常从被攻击的账户中发送）

en_text: FIN4 has captured credentials via fake Outlook Web App (OWA) login pages and has also used a .NET based keylogger.
Text: FIN4通过伪造的Outlook Web App (OWA)登录页面抓取凭证，还使用了一个基于.NET的键盘记录器

en_text: FIN4 has presented victims with spoofed Windows Authentication prompts to collect their credentials.
Text: FIN4向受害者展示了欺骗性的Windows认证提示，以收集他们的凭据

en_text: FIN4 has used HTTP POST requests to transmit data.
Text: FIN4已经使用HTTP POST请求来传输数据

en_text: FIN4 has lured victims to click malicious links delivered via spearphishing emails (often sent from compromised accounts).
Text: FIN4诱使受害者点击通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件（通常由被攻击的账户发送）传递的恶意链接

en_text: FIN4 has lured victims to launch malicious attachments delivered via spearphishing emails (often sent from compromised accounts).
Text: FIN4诱使受害者启动通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件（通常从被攻击的账户发送）传递的恶意附件

en_text: FIN4 has created rules in victims' Microsoft Outlook accounts to automatically delete emails containing words such as "hacked," "phish," and "malware" in a likely attempt to prevent organizations from communicating about their activities.
Text: FIN4在受害者的微软Outlook账户中创建了规则，自动删除含有 "黑客"、"网络钓鱼 "和 "恶意软件 "等字眼的邮件，这很可能是为了防止各组织对其活动进行交流

en_text: FIN5 scripts save memory dump data into a specific directory on hosts in the victim environment.
Text: FIN5脚本将内存转储数据保存到受害者环境中的主机上的一个特定目录

en_text: FIN5 scans processes on all victim systems in the environment and uses automated scripts to pull back the results.
Text: FIN5扫描环境中所有受害系统的进程，并使用自动脚本拉回结果

en_text: FIN5 uses SDelete to clean up the environment and attempt to prevent detection.
Text: FIN5使用SDelete来清理环境并试图防止被发现

en_text: FIN5 has used legitimate VPN, Citrix, or VNC credentials to maintain access to a victim environment.
Text: FIN5使用合法的VPN、Citrix或VNC凭证来维持对受害者环境的访问

en_text: FIN5 has used legitimate VPN, RDP, Citrix, or VNC credentials to maintain access to a victim environment.
Text: FIN5使用合法的VPN、RDP、Citrix或VNC凭证来维持对受害者环境的访问

en_text: FIN5 has used the open source tool Essential NetTools to map the network and build a list of targets.
Text: FIN5使用了开源工具Essential NetTools来绘制网络地图，并建立了一个目标清单

en_text: FIN5 maintains access to victim environments by using FLIPSIDE to create a proxy for a backup RDP tunnel.
Text: FIN5通过使用FLIPSIDE为备份的RDP隧道创建一个代理来保持对受害者环境的访问

en_text: FIN5 has cleared event logs from victims.
Text: FIN5已经清除了受害者的事件日志

en_text: FIN5 has has used the tool GET5 Penetrator to look for remote login and hard-coded credentials.
Text: FIN5已经使用GET5 Penetrator工具寻找远程登录和硬编码的凭证

en_text: FIN6 has extracted password hashes from ntds.dit to crack offline.
Text: FIN6从ntds.dit中提取了密码哈希值进行离线破解

en_text: FIN6 has renamed the "psexec" service name to "mstdc" to masquerade as a legitimate Windows service.
Text: FIN6将 "psexec "服务名称重命名为 "mstdc"，以伪装成合法的Windows服务

en_text: FIN6 has used PowerShell to gain access to merchant's networks, and a Metasploit PowerShell module to download and execute shellcode and to set up a local listener.
Text: FIN6利用PowerShell获得了对商家网络的访问权，并利用Metasploit PowerShell模块下载和执行shellcode，并设置了一个本地监听器

en_text: FIN6 used RDP to move laterally in victim networks.
Text: FIN6利用RDP在受害者网络中横向移动

en_text: FIN6 has used the Stealer One credential stealer to target e-mail and file transfer utilities including FTP.
Text: FIN6利用Stealer One凭证窃取器，以电子邮件和包括FTP在内的文件传输工具为目标

en_text: FIN6 has used malicious JavaScript to steal payment card data from e-commerce sites.
Text: FIN6利用恶意的JavaScript从电子商务网站窃取支付卡数据

en_text: FIN6 has used malicious documents to lure victims into allowing execution of PowerShell scripts.
Text: FIN6利用恶意文件引诱受害者允许执行PowerShell脚本

en_text: FIN6 has used scripting to iterate through a list of compromised PoS systems, copy data to a log file, and remove the original data files.
Text: FIN6利用脚本在被攻击的PoS系统列表中进行迭代，将数据复制到日志文件中，并删除原始数据文件

en_text: FIN6 has used fake job advertisements sent via LinkedIn to spearphish targets.
Text: FIN6利用通过LinkedIn发送的虚假招聘广告对目标进行鱼叉式攻击

en_text: FIN6 has used kill.bat script to disable security tools.
Text: FIN6使用kill.bat脚本来禁用安全工具

en_text: FIN6 has used Metasploit’s PsExec NTDSGRAB module to obtain a copy of the victim's Active Directory database.
Text: FIN6使用Metasploit的PsExec NTDSGRAB模块来获取受害者的活动目录数据库的副本

en_text: FIN6 used the Plink command-line utility to create SSH tunnels to C2 servers.
Text: FIN6使用Plink命令行工具来创建通往C2服务器的SSH隧道

en_text: FIN6 has used the Stealer One credential stealer to target web browsers.
Text: FIN6使用Stealer One凭证窃取器来攻击网络浏览器

en_text: FIN6 has used tools to exploit Windows vulnerabilities in order to escalate privileges. The tools targeted CVE-2013-3660, CVE-2011-2005, and CVE-2010-4398, all of which could allow local users to access kernel-level privileges.
Text: FIN6使用工具来利用Windows漏洞，以提升权限。这些工具针对的是CVE-2013-3660、CVE-2011-2005和CVE-2010-4398，这些漏洞都可能允许本地用户访问内核级权限。

en_text: FIN6 used publicly available tools (including Microsoft's built-in SQL querying tool, osql.exe) to map the internal network and conduct reconnaissance against Active Directory, Structured Query Language (SQL) servers, and NetBIOS.
Text: FIN6使用公开的工具（包括微软内置的SQL查询工具osql.exe）来映射内部网络，并对活动目录、结构化查询语言（SQL）服务器和NetBIOS进行侦查

en_text: FIN6 has used scheduled tasks to establish persistence for various malware it uses, including downloaders known as HARDTACK and SHIPBREAD and FrameworkPOS.
Text: FIN6使用计划任务为其使用的各种恶意软件建立持久性，包括称为HARDTACK和SHIPBREAD的下载器和FrameworkPOS

en_text: FIN6 has used has used Metasploit’s named-pipe impersonation technique to escalate privileges.
Text: FIN6使用了Metasploit的命名管道冒充技术来提升权限

en_text: FIN6 has used Windows Credential Editor for credential dumping.
Text: FIN6使用了Windows凭证编辑器进行凭证转储

en_text: FIN6 has used a script to iterate through a list of compromised PoS systems, copy and remove data to a log file, and to bind to events from the submit payment button.
Text: FIN6使用了一个脚本来迭代被攻击的PoS系统的列表，复制和删除数据到一个日志文件，并与提交支付按钮的事件绑定

en_text: FIN6 has used Registry Run keys to establish persistence for its downloader tools known as HARDTACK and SHIPBREAD.
Text: FIN6使用注册表运行键为其称为HARDTACK和SHIPBREAD的下载器工具建立持久性

en_text: FIN6 has sent stolen payment card data to remote servers via HTTP POSTs.
Text: FIN6通过HTTP POSTs将盗取的支付卡数据发送到远程服务器

en_text: FIN6 actors have compressed data from remote systems and moved it to another staging system before exfiltration.
Text: FIN6行动者从远程系统中压缩数据，并在外泄前将其转移到另一个暂存系统

en_text: FIN6 has deployed a utility script named kill.bat to disable anti-virus.
Text: FIN6已经部署了一个名为kill.bat的实用脚本来禁用防病毒

en_text: FIN6 has created Windows services to execute encoded PowerShell commands.
Text: FIN6已经创建了Windows服务来执行编码的PowerShell命令

en_text: FIN6 has removed files from victim machines.
Text: FIN6已经从受害者机器上删除了文件

en_text: FIN6 has collected schemas and user accounts from systems running SQL Server.
Text: FIN6已经从运行SQL Server的系统中收集了模式和用户账户

en_text: FIN6 has used tools like Adfind to query users, groups, organizational units, and trusts.
Text: FIN6已经使用Adfind等工具来查询用户、组、组织单位和信托

en_text: FIN6 has used Pastebin and Google Storage to host content for their operations.
Text: FIN6已经使用Pastebin和谷歌存储来托管其业务内容

en_text: FIN6 has used WMI to automate the remote execution of PowerShell scripts.
Text: FIN6已经使用WMI来实现PowerShell脚本的远程执行的自动化

en_text: FIN6 has used Comodo code-signing certificates.
Text: FIN6已经使用了Comodo代码签名证书

en_text: FIN6 has used Metasploit Bind and Reverse TCP stagers.
Text: FIN6已经使用了Metasploit Bind和Reverse TCP stagers

en_text: FIN6 has used encoded PowerShell commands.
Text: FIN6已经使用了编码的PowerShell命令

en_text: FIN6 has collected and exfiltrated payment card data from compromised systems.
Text: FIN6已经收集并从被破坏的系统中渗出了支付卡数据

en_text: FIN6 has targeted victims with e-mails containing malicious attachments.
Text: FIN6以含有恶意附件的电子邮件为目标

en_text: FIN6 has encoded data gathered from the victim with a simple substitution cipher and single-byte XOR using the 0xAA key, and Base64 with character permutation.
Text: FIN6用简单的替换密码和单字节XOR对从受害者那里收集的数据进行了编码，使用的是0xAA密钥，以及带有字符置换的Base64

en_text: FIN7 captured screenshots and desktop video recordings.
Text: FIN7捕获的屏幕截图和桌面视频记录

en_text: FIN7 created new Windows services and added them to the startup directories for persistence.
Text: FIN7创建了新的Windows服务，并将其添加到启动目录中，以便持久使用

en_text: FIN7 created a custom video recording capability that could be used to monitor operations in the victim's environment.
Text: FIN7创建了一个定制的视频记录功能，可以用来监控受害者环境中的操作

en_text: FIN7 has created a scheduled task named "AdobeFlashSync" to establish persistence.
Text: FIN7创建了一个名为 "AdobeFlashSync "的计划任务来建立持久性

en_text: FIN7 malware has created Registry Run and RunOnce keys to establish persistence, and has also added items to the Startup folder.
Text: FIN7恶意软件创建了注册表 "运行 "和 "一次运行 "键，以建立持久性，还在 "启动 "文件夹中添加了项目

en_text: FIN7 malware has created scheduled tasks to establish persistence.
Text: FIN7恶意软件已经创建了预定任务，以建立持久性

en_text: FIN7 sent spearphishing emails with either malicious Microsoft Documents or RTF files attached.
Text: FIN7发送的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件中附有恶意的微软文档或RTF文件

en_text: FIN7 has used mshta.exe to execute VBScript to execute malicious code on victim systems.
Text: FIN7利用mshta.exe执行VBScript，在受害者系统上执行恶意代码

en_text: FIN7 used JavaScript scripts to help perform tasks on the victim's machine.
Text: FIN7使用JavaScript脚本来帮助在受害者的机器上执行任务

en_text: FIN7 used SQL scripts to help perform tasks on the victim's machine.
Text: FIN7使用SQL脚本来帮助在受害者的机器上执行任务

en_text: FIN7 used VBS scripts to help perform tasks on the victim's machine.
Text: FIN7使用VBS脚本来帮助在受害者的机器上执行任务

en_text: FIN7 used legitimate services like Google Docs, Google Scripts, and Pastebin for C2.
Text: FIN7使用谷歌文档、谷歌脚本和Pastebin等合法服务进行C2

en_text: FIN7 used the command prompt to launch commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: FIN7使用命令提示符在受害者的机器上启动命令

en_text: FIN7 used images embedded into document lures that only activate the payload when a user double clicks to avoid sandboxes.
Text: FIN7使用嵌入到文档诱饵中的图像，只有在用户双击时才激活有效载荷，以避免沙箱

en_text: FIN7 has used fragmented strings, environment variables, standard input (stdin), and native character-replacement functionalities to obfuscate commands.
Text: FIN7使用碎片化的字符串、环境变量、标准输入（stdin）和本地字符替换功能来混淆命令

en_text: FIN7 used a PowerShell script to launch shellcode that retrieved an additional payload.
Text: FIN7使用一个PowerShell脚本启动shellcode，检索出一个额外的有效载荷

en_text: FIN7 has performed C2 using DNS via A, OPT, and TXT records.
Text: FIN7通过A、OPT和TXT记录使用DNS执行C2

en_text: FIN7 has downloaded additional malware to execute on the victim's machine, including by using a PowerShell script to launch shellcode that retrieves an additional payload.
Text: FIN7下载了额外的恶意软件在受害者的机器上执行，包括通过使用PowerShell脚本来启动检索额外有效载荷的shellcode

en_text: FIN7 has used application shim databases for persistence.
Text: FIN7已经使用了应用程序shim数据库来实现持久性

en_text: FIN7 has signed Carbanak payloads with legally purchased code signing certificates. FIN7 has also digitally signed their phishing documents, backdoors and other staging tools to bypass security controls.
Text: FIN7用合法购买的代码签名证书签署了Carbanak的有效载荷

en_text: FIN7 lured victims to double-click on images in the attachments they sent which would then execute the hidden LNK file.
Text: FIN7诱使受害者双击他们发送的附件中的图像，然后执行隐藏的LNK文件

en_text: FIN7 spear phishing campaigns have included malicious Word documents with DDE execution.
Text: FIN7鱼叉式网络钓鱼活动包括带有DDE执行的恶意Word文档

en_text: FIN7 has used port-protocol mismatches on ports such as 53, 80, 443, and 8080 during C2.
Text: FIN7在C2期间在53、80、443和8080等端口上使用了端口协议错配

en_text: FIN8's malicious spearphishing payloads use WMI to launch malware and spawn cmd.exe execution. FIN8 has also used WMIC during and post compromise cleanup activities.
Text: FIN8的恶意网络钓鱼有效载荷使用WMI来启动恶意软件并催生cmd.exe执行。FIN8还在入侵后的清理活动中使用WMIC。

en_text: FIN8's malicious spearphishing payloads are executed as PowerShell. FIN8 has also used PowerShell during Lateral Movement and Credential Access.
Text: FIN8的恶意鱼叉式钓鱼有效载荷是以PowerShell的形式执行的。FIN8还在横向移动和凭证访问中使用PowerShell。

en_text: FIN8 has distributed targeted emails containing links to malicious documents with embedded macros.
Text: FIN8发布的目标邮件中含有嵌入宏的恶意文件的链接

en_text: FIN8 has distributed targeted emails containing Word documents with embedded malicious macros.
Text: FIN8发布了含有Word文档的目标邮件，其中嵌入了恶意的宏程序

en_text: FIN8 aggregates staged data from a network into a single location.
Text: FIN8将网络中的阶段性数据汇总到一个地方

en_text: FIN8 has leveraged Spearphishing Attachments attempting to gain User Execution.
Text: FIN8利用 "网络钓鱼 "附件，试图获得用户执行力

en_text: FIN8 has used environment variables and standard input (stdin) to obfuscate command-line arguments. FIN8 also obfuscates malicious macros delivered as payloads.
Text: FIN8利用环境变量和标准输入（stdin）来混淆命令行参数。FIN8还对作为有效载荷传递的恶意宏进行混淆。

en_text: FIN8 has leveraged Spearphishing Links attempting to gain User Execution.
Text: FIN8利用鱼叉式链接试图获得用户执行

en_text: FIN8 has used remote code execution to download subsequent payloads.
Text: FIN8利用远程代码执行来下载后续的有效载荷

en_text: FIN8 uses dsquery and other Active Directory utilities to enumerate hosts.
Text: FIN8使用dsquery和其他Active Directory工具来列举主机

en_text: FIN8 has used FTP to exfiltrate collected data.
Text: FIN8使用FTP来渗出收集的数据

en_text: FIN8 harvests credentials using Invoke-Mimikatz or Windows Credentials Editor (WCE).
Text: FIN8使用Invoke-Mimikatz或Windows Credentials Editor（WCE）收获证书

en_text: FIN8 has used a Batch file to automate frequently executed post compromise cleanup activities. FIN8 executes commands remotely via cmd.exe.
Text: FIN8使用了一个批处理文件来自动执行经常执行的妥协后清理活动。FIN8通过cmd.exe远程执行命令。

en_text: FIN8 has used RDP for Lateral Movement.
Text: FIN8已将RDP用于横向移动

en_text: FIN8 has attempted to map to C$ on enumerated hosts to test the scope of their current credentials/context.
Text: FIN8已经尝试在列举的主机上映射到C$，以测试其当前凭证的范围

en_text: FIN8 has exploited the CVE-2016-0167 local vulnerability.
Text: FIN8已经利用了CVE-2016-0167局部漏洞

en_text: FIN8 has used the Plink utility to tunnel RDP back to C2 infrastructure.
Text: FIN8已经使用Plink工具将RDP以隧道方式返回到C2基础设施

en_text: FIN8 has used scheduled tasks to maintain RDP backdoors.
Text: FIN8已经使用计划任务来维护RDP后门

en_text: FIN8 has used Registry keys to detect and avoid executing in potential sandboxes.
Text: FIN8已经使用注册表键来检测和避免在潜在的沙盒中执行

en_text: FIN8 has utilized Valid Accounts during and Persistence and Lateral Movement.
Text: FIN8在和持久性和横向移动期间利用了有效账户

en_text: FIN8 has used RAR to compress collected data before Exfiltration.
Text: FIN8在渗出前使用RAR压缩收集的数据

en_text: FIN8 has cleared logs during post compromise cleanup activities.
Text: FIN8在妥协后的清理活动中清除了日志

en_text: FIN8 has deleted tmp and prefetch files during post compromise cleanup activities.
Text: FIN8在妥协后的清理活动中删除了临时文件和预取文件

en_text: FIN8 has deleted Registry keys during post compromise cleanup activities.
Text: FIN8在妥协后的清理活动中删除了注册表键

en_text: Final1stspy creates a Registry Run key to establish persistence.
Text: Final1stspy创建了一个注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: Final1stspy obtains victim Microsoft Windows version information and CPU architecture.
Text: Final1stspy获得受害者的微软Windows版本信息和CPU架构

en_text: Final1stspy obtains a list of running processes.
Text: Final1stspy获得一个正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Final1stspy uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Final1stspy使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Final1stspy uses Python code to deobfuscate base64-encoded strings.
Text: Final1stspy使用Python代码来解密base64编码的字符串

en_text: Final1stspy obfuscates strings with base64 encoding.
Text: Final1stspy用base64编码来混淆字符串

en_text: FinFisher queries Registry values as part of its anti-sandbox checks.
Text: FinFisher查询注册表的值，作为其反沙盒检查的一部分

en_text: FinFisher takes a screenshot of the screen and displays it on top of all other windows for few seconds in an apparent attempt to hide some messages showed by the system during the setup process.
Text: FinFisher对屏幕进行截图，并在所有其他窗口上方显示几秒钟，显然是为了隐藏系统在安装过程中显示的一些信息

en_text: FinFisher injects itself into various processes depending on whether it is low integrity or high integrity.
Text: FinFisher根据它是低完整性还是高完整性，将自己注入各种流程

en_text: FinFisher obtains the hardware device list and checks if the MD5 of the vendor ID is equal to a predefined list in order to check for sandbox/virtualized environments.
Text: FinFisher获得硬件设备列表，并检查供应商ID的MD5是否等于一个预定义的列表，以便检查沙箱

en_text: FinFisher checks its parent process for indications that it is running in a sandbox setup.
Text: FinFisher检查其父进程是否有迹象表明它在沙盒设置中运行

en_text: FinFisher checks if the victim OS is 32 or 64-bit.
Text: FinFisher检查受害者的操作系统是32位还是64位

en_text: FinFisher renames one of its .dll files to uxtheme.dll in an apparent attempt to masquerade as a legitimate file.
Text: FinFisher将其一个.dll文件重命名为uxtheme.dll，显然是想伪装成一个合法文件

en_text: FinFisher enumerates directories and scans for certain files.
Text: FinFisher列举目录并扫描某些文件

en_text: FinFisher uses DLL side-loading to load malicious programs.
Text: FinFisher使用DLL侧面加载来加载恶意程序

en_text: FinFisher uses token manipulation with NtFilterToken as part of UAC bypass.
Text: FinFisher使用NtFilterToken的令牌操作作为UAC绕过的一部分

en_text: FinFisher clears the system event logs using  OpenEventLog/ClearEventLog APIs .
Text: FinFisher使用OpenEventLog清除了系统事件日志

en_text: FinFisher probes the system to check for antimalware processes.
Text: FinFisher探测系统，检查反恶意软件进程

en_text: FinFisher extracts and decrypts stage 3 malware, which is stored in encrypted resources.
Text: FinFisher提取并解密第三阶段的恶意软件，这些恶意软件存储在加密资源中

en_text: FinFisher establishes persistence by creating the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\Run.
Text: FinFisher通过创建注册表键HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\Run建立了持久性

en_text: FinFisher hooks processes by modifying IAT pointers to CreateWindowEx.
Text: FinFisher通过修改CreateWindowEx的IAT指针来钩住进程

en_text: FinFisher creates a new Windows service with the malicious executable for persistence.
Text: FinFisher用恶意的可执行文件创建了一个新的Windows服务，用于持久化

en_text: FinFisher contains junk code in its functions in an effort to confuse disassembly programs.
Text: FinFisher在其功能中包含垃圾代码，以努力混淆反汇编程序

en_text: FinFisher is heavily obfuscated in many ways, including through the use of spaghetti code in its functions in an effort to confuse disassembly programs. It also uses a custom XOR algorithm to obfuscate code.
Text: FinFisher在许多方面进行了严重的混淆，包括在其功能中使用意大利语代码，以努力混淆反汇编程序。它还使用一个自定义的XOR算法来混淆代码。

en_text: FinFisher performs UAC bypass.
Text: FinFisher执行UAC绕过

en_text: Flame contains modules to infect USB sticks and spread laterally to other Windows systems the stick is plugged into using Autorun functionality.
Text: Flame包含感染U盘的模块，并利用自动运行功能横向传播到U盘所插入的其他Windows系统

en_text: Flame can use Windows Authentication Packages for persistence.
Text: Flame可以使用Windows认证包进行持久化

en_text: Flame can record audio using any existing hardware recording devices.
Text: Flame可以使用任何现有的硬件录音设备录制音频

en_text: Flame identifies security software such as antivirus through the Security module.
Text: Flame通过安全模块识别防病毒等安全软件

en_text: Flame has a module named BeetleJuice that contains Bluetooth functionality that may be used in different ways, including transmitting encoded information from the infected system over the Bluetooth protocol, acting as a Bluetooth beacon, and identifying other Bluetooth devices in the vicinity.
Text: Flame有一个名为BeetleJuice的模块，包含蓝牙功能，可用于不同的方式，包括通过蓝牙协议传输受感染系统的编码信息，充当蓝牙信标，并识别附近的其他蓝牙设备

en_text: FLASHFLOOD employs the same encoding scheme as SPACESHIP for data it stages. Data is compressed with zlib, and bytes are rotated four times before being XOR'ed with 0x23.
