en_text: LaZagne can obtain credential information from /etc/shadow using the shadow.py module.
Text: LaZagne可以从以下方面获得凭证信息 LaZagne可以从以下方面获得证书信息 LaZagne可以从以下方面获取证书信息 LaZagne可以从以下途径获得证书信息

en_text: LaZagne can obtain credential information running Linux processes.
Text: LaZagne可以获得运行Linux进程的凭证信息

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia obtains and sends to its C2 server information about the first network interface card’s configuration, including IP address, gateways, subnet mask, DHCP information, and whether WINS is available.
Text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia获取并向其C2服务器发送关于第一个网络接口卡的配置信息，包括IP地址、网关、子网掩码、DHCP信息以及WINS是否可用

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia checks Registry keys within HKCU and HKLM to determine if certain applications are present, including SecureCRT, Terminal Services, RealVNC, TightVNC, UltraVNC, Radmin, mRemote, TeamViewer, FileZilla, pcAnyware, and Remote Desktop. Another Lazarus Group malware sample checks for the presence of the following Registry key:HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Bitcoin\Bitcoin-Qt.
Text: Lazarus Group恶意软件India检查HKCU和HKLM内的注册表键，以确定是否存在某些应用程序，包括SecureCRT、终端服务、RealVNC、TightVNC、UltraVNC、Radmin、mRemote、TeamViewer、FileZilla、pcAnyware和远程桌面。另一个Lazarus集团的恶意软件样本检查是否存在以下注册表键：HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Bitcoin\Bitcoin-Qt.

en_text: Lazarus Group malware uses cmd.exe to execute commands on victims. A Destover-like variant used by Lazarus Group uses a batch file mechanism to delete its binaries from the system.
Text: Lazarus Group恶意软件使用cmd.exe对受害者执行命令。Lazarus Group使用的一个类似Destover的变体使用批处理文件机制，从系统中删除其二进制文件。

en_text: Lazarus Group malware attempts to connect to Windows shares for lateral movement by using a generated list of usernames, which center around permutations of the username Administrator, and weak passwords.
Text: Lazarus Group恶意软件试图通过使用生成的用户名列表连接到Windows共享来进行横向移动，这些用户名以Administrator的排列组合为中心，并使用弱密码

en_text: Lazarus Group malware uses multiple types of encryption and encoding in its malware files, including AES, Caracachs, RC4, basic XOR with constant 0xA7, and other techniques.
Text: Lazarus Group恶意软件在其恶意软件文件中使用了多种类型的加密和编码，包括AES、Caracachs、RC4、带有常数0xA7的基本XOR以及其他技术

en_text: Lazarus Group has exploited Adobe Flash vulnerability CVE-2018-4878 for execution.
Text: Lazarus Group利用Adobe Flash漏洞CVE-2018-4878进行执行

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia obtains and sends to its C2 server the title of the window for each running process. The KilaAlfa keylogger also reports the title of the window in the foreground.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件IndiaIndia获取并向其C2服务器发送每个运行进程的窗口标题

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia saves information gathered about the victim to a file that is uploaded to one of its 10 C2 servers. Another Lazarus Group malware sample also performs exfiltration over the C2 channel.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件IndiaIndia将收集到的有关受害者的信息保存到一个文件中，并上传到其10个C2服务器之一

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia saves information gathered about the victim to a file that is uploaded to one of its 10 C2 servers. Lazarus Group malware RomeoDelta copies specified directories from the victim's machine, then archives and encrypts the directories before uploading to its C2 server. Lazarus Group has used wevtutil to export Window security event logs.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件IndiaIndia将收集到的有关受害者的信息保存到一个文件中，并上传到其10个C2服务器之一。Lazarus集团的恶意软件RomeoDelta从受害者的机器上复制指定的目录，然后在上传到其C2服务器之前对这些目录进行归档和加密。Lazarus集团利用wevtutil导出Window安全事件日志。

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia saves information gathered about the victim to a file that is compressed with Zlib, encrypted, and uploaded to a C2 server.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件IndiaIndia将收集到的有关受害者的信息保存在一个文件中，该文件用Zlib压缩，经过加密，并上传到C2服务器

en_text: Lazarus Group malware IndiaIndia saves information gathered about the victim to a file that is saved in the %TEMP% directory, then compressed, encrypted, and uploaded to a C2 server.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件India将收集到的有关受害者的信息保存在%TEMP%目录下的文件中，然后进行压缩、加密，并上传到C2服务器

en_text: Lazarus Group malware KiloAlfa contains keylogging functionality.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件KiloAlfa包含键盘记录功能

en_text: Lazarus Group malware RomeoDelta archives specified directories in .zip format, encrypts the .zip file, and uploads it to its C2 server.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件RomeoDelta将指定的目录以.zip格式存档，对.zip文件进行加密，并将其上传到其C2服务器

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SHARPKNOT overwrites and deletes the Master Boot Record (MBR) on the victim's machine and has possessed MBR wiper malware since at least 2009.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SHARPKNOT覆盖并删除了受害者机器上的主引导记录（MBR），至少从2009年起就拥有了MBR擦除器恶意软件

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SierraAlfa accesses the ADMIN$ share via SMB to conduct lateral movement.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SierraAlfa通过SMB访问ADMIN$共享，进行横向移动

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SierraAlfa sends data to one of the hard-coded C2 servers chosen at random, and if the transmission fails, chooses a new C2 server to attempt the transmission again.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SierraAlfa向随机选择的一个硬编码C2服务器发送数据，如果传输失败，则选择一个新的C2服务器再次尝试传输

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SierraAlfa uses the Windows Management Instrumentation Command-line application wmic to start itself on a target system during lateral movement.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SierraAlfa在横向移动过程中使用Windows管理仪表命令行应用程序wmic在目标系统上启动自己

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SierraBravo-Two generates an email message via SMTP containing information about newly infected victims.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SierraBravo-Two会通过SMTP生成一封电子邮件，其中包含新感染受害者的信息

en_text: Lazarus Group malware SierraCharlie uses RDP for propagation.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件SierraCharlie使用RDP进行传播

en_text: Lazarus Group malware TangoDelta attempts to terminate various processes associated with McAfee. Additionally, Lazarus Group malware SHARPKNOT disables the Microsoft Windows System Event Notification and Alerter services.. During a 2019 intrusion, Lazarus Group disabled Windows Defender and Credential Guard as some of their first actions on host.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件TangoDelta试图终止与McAfee相关的各种进程。此外，Lazarus集团的恶意软件SHARPKNOT禁用了微软Windows系统事件通知和警报器服务。在2019年的一次入侵中，Lazarus集团禁用了Windows Defender和Credential Guard，作为他们在主机上的一些首要行动。

en_text: Lazarus Group malware WhiskeyAlfa-Three modifies sector 0 of the Master Boot Record (MBR) to ensure that the malware will persist even if a victim machine shuts down.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件WhiskeyAlfa-Three修改了主引导记录（MBR）的0扇区，以确保即使受害者的机器关闭，恶意软件也会持续存在

en_text: Lazarus Group malware WhiskeyDelta-Two contains a function that attempts to rename the administrator’s account.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件WhiskeyDelta-Two包含一个试图重命名管理员账户的功能

en_text: Lazarus Group malware also uses a unique form of communication encryption known as FakeTLS that mimics TLS but uses a different encryption method, evading SSL man-in-the-middle decryption attacks.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件还使用一种被称为FakeTLS的独特通信加密形式，模仿TLS，但使用不同的加密方法，逃避SSL中间人解密攻击

en_text: Lazarus Group malware has conducted C2 over HTTP and HTTPS.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件已经通过HTTP和HTTPS进行了C2

en_text: Lazarus Group malware deletes files in various ways, including "suicide scripts" to delete malware binaries from the victim. Lazarus Group also uses secure file deletion to delete files from the victim.
Text: Lazarus集团的恶意软件以各种方式删除文件，包括以 "自杀脚本 "从受害者身上删除恶意软件二进制文件

en_text: Several Lazarus Group malware families are capable of downloading and executing binaries from its C2 server.
Text: Lazarus集团的几个恶意软件系列能够从其C2服务器下载和执行二进制文件

en_text: Lazarus Group keylogger KiloAlfa obtains user tokens from interactive sessions to execute itself with API call CreateProcessAsUserA under that user's context.
Text: Lazarus集团的键盘记录器KiloAlfa从交互式会话中获取用户令牌，并通过API调用CreateProcessAsUserA在该用户的上下文中执行自己

en_text: A Lazarus Group custom backdoor implant included a custom PE loader named "Security Package" that was added into the lsass.exe process via registry key.
Text: Lazarus集团的一个定制后门植入物包括一个名为 "安全包 "的定制PE加载器，该加载器通过注册表密钥被添加到lsass.exe进程中

en_text: A Lazarus Group malware sample encodes data with base64.
Text: Lazarus集团的一个恶意软件样本用base64进行数据编码

en_text: A Lazarus Group malware sample encrypts data using a simple byte based XOR operation prior to exfiltration.
Text: Lazarus集团的一个恶意软件样本在渗出前使用一个简单的基于字节的XOR操作对数据进行加密

en_text: A Lazarus Group malware sample performs reflective DLL injection.
Text: Lazarus集团的一个恶意软件样本执行了反射性DLL注入

en_text: Lazarus Group has used CHM files to move concealed payloads.
Text: Lazarus集团利用CHM文件来转移隐蔽的有效载荷

en_text: Lazarus Group leveraged Mimikatz to extract Windows Credentials of currently logged-in users and steals passwords stored in browsers. Lazarus Group has also used a custom version Mimikatz to capture credentials.
Text: Lazarus集团利用Mimikatz提取当前登录用户的Windows凭证，并窃取浏览器中存储的密码。Lazarus Group还使用了自定义版本的Mimikatz来捕获凭证。

en_text: Lazarus Group has used mshta.exe to run malicious scripts and download programs.
Text: Lazarus集团利用mshta.exe来运行恶意脚本和下载程序

en_text: Lazarus Group has used Powershell to download malicious payloads.
Text: Lazarus集团利用Powershell下载恶意的有效载荷

en_text: Lazarus Group has used fake job advertisements sent via LinkedIn to spearphish victims.
Text: Lazarus集团利用通过LinkedIn发送的虚假招聘广告对受害者进行鱼叉式攻击

en_text: Lazarus Group has modified registry keys using the reg windows utility for its custom backdoor implants.
Text: Lazarus集团使用reg windows工具修改了注册表的键值，用于其定制的后门植入

en_text: Lazarus Group has used a VBA Macro to set its file attributes to System and Hidden and has named files with a dot prefix to hide them from the Finder application.
Text: Lazarus集团使用VBA宏将其文件属性设置为系统和隐藏，并以点为前缀来命名文件，以便从Finder应用程序中隐藏它们

en_text: Lazarus Group has used VBScript to gather information about a victim machine.
Text: Lazarus集团使用VBScript来收集受害者机器的信息

en_text: A Destover-like implant used by Lazarus Group can obtain the current system time and send it to the C2 server.
Text: Lazarus集团使用的类似Destover的植入物可以获得当前的系统时间并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Lazarus Group uses multiple proxies to obfuscate network traffic from victims.
Text: Lazarus集团使用多个代理服务器来混淆受害者的网络流量

en_text: Lazarus Group has used a custom secure delete function to overwrite file contents with data from heap memory.
Text: Lazarus集团使用了一个自定义的安全删除功能，用堆内存的数据覆盖文件内容

en_text: Lazarus Group has used malware like WhiskeyAlfa to overwrite the first 64MB of every drive with a mix of static and random buffers. A similar process is then used to wipe content in logical drives and, finally, attempt to wipe every byte of every sector on every drive. WhiskeyBravo can be used to overwrite the first 4.9MB of physical drives. WhiskeyDelta can overwrite the first 132MB or 1.5MB of each drive with random data from heap memory.
Text: Lazarus集团使用像WhiskeyAlfa这样的恶意软件，用静态和随机缓冲区的混合物覆盖每个驱动器的前64MB。然后，一个类似的过程被用来擦除逻辑驱动器中的内容，最后，试图擦除每个驱动器上每个扇区的每一个字节。WhiskeyBravo可以用来覆盖物理驱动器的前4.9MB。WhiskeyDelta可以用堆内存的随机数据覆盖每个驱动器的前132MB或1.5MB

en_text: Lazarus Group has attempted to get users to launch a malicious Microsoft Word attachment delivered via a spearphishing email.
Text: Lazarus集团试图让用户启动一个通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件传递的恶意微软Word附件

en_text: Lazarus Group has rebooted victim machines to establish persistence by installing a SSP DLL.
Text: Lazarus集团通过安装SSP DLL，重启了受害者的机器以建立持久性

en_text: Lazarus Group delivered RATANKBA to victims via a compromised legitimate website.
Text: Lazarus集团通过一个被破坏的合法网站向受害者提供RATANKBA

en_text: Lazarus Group has used Themida to pack at least two separate backdoor implants.
Text: Lazarus集团已经使用Themida打包了至少两个独立的后门植入物

en_text: Lazarus Group has stopped the MSExchangeIS service to render Exchange contents inaccessible to users.
Text: Lazarus集团已经停止了MSExchangeIS服务，使用户无法访问Exchange内容

en_text: Lazarus Group has targeted victims with spearphishing emails containing malicious Microsoft Word documents.
Text: Lazarus集团以含有恶意微软Word文档的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件为目标

en_text: Lazarus Group has subset groups like Bluenoroff who have used cryptocurrency mining software on victim machines.
Text: Lazarus集团有像Bluenoroff这样的子集团，他们在受害者机器上使用加密货币挖矿软件

en_text: Lazarus Group has rebooted systems after destroying files and wiping the MBR on infected systems.
Text: Lazarus集团在销毁文件和擦除受感染系统的MBR后重新启动了系统

en_text: Lazarus Group replaced the background wallpaper of systems with a threatening image after rendering the system unbootable with a Disk Structure Wipe
Text: Lazarus集团在用磁盘结构清除法使系统无法启动后，用威胁性的图像替换了系统的背景墙纸

en_text: Leafminer obfuscated scripts that were used on victim machines.
Text: Leafminer混淆了受害者机器上使用的脚本

en_text: Leafminer has used Process Doppelg?nging to evade security software while deploying tools on compromised systems.
Text: Leafminer利用 "进程二重奏"（Process Doppelg?nging）来规避安全软件，同时在被攻击的系统上部署工具

en_text: Leafminer scanned network services to search for vulnerabilities in the victim system.
Text: Leafminer扫描网络服务，搜索受害者系统中的漏洞

en_text: Leafminer infected victims using JavaScript code.
Text: Leafminer使用JavaScript代码感染了受害者

en_text: Leafminer used several tools for retrieving login and password information, including LaZagne.
Text: Leafminer使用几个工具来检索登录和密码信息，包括LaZagne

en_text: Leafminer used several tools for retrieving login and password information, including LaZagne and Mimikatz.
Text: Leafminer使用几个工具来检索登录和密码信息，包括LaZagne和Mimikatz

en_text: Leafminer used Microsoft’s Sysinternals tools to gather detailed information about remote systems.
Text: Leafminer使用微软的Sysinternals工具来收集远程系统的详细信息

en_text: Leafminer used a tool called Imecab to set up a persistent remote access account on the victim machine.
Text: Leafminer使用一个名为Imecab的工具，在受害者机器上建立了一个持久的远程访问账户

en_text: Leafminer used a tool called MailSniper to search through the Exchange server mailboxes for keywords.
Text: Leafminer使用一个名为MailSniper的工具，在Exchange服务器的邮箱中搜索关键词

en_text: Leafminer used a tool called MailSniper to search for files on the desktop and another utility called Sobolsoft to extract attachments from EML files.
Text: Leafminer使用一个名为MailSniper的工具来搜索桌面上的文件，并使用另一个名为Sobolsoft的工具来从EML文件中提取附件

en_text: Leafminer used a tool called Total SMB BruteForcer to perform internal password spraying.
Text: Leafminer使用一个名为Total SMB BruteForcer的工具来进行内部密码喷涂

en_text: Leviathan has used C:\Windows\Debug and C:\Perflogs as staging directories.
Text: Leviathan使用C:\Windows\Debug和C:\Perflogs作为暂存目录

en_text: Leviathan has used WMI for persistence.
Text: Leviathan使用了WMI来实现持久性

en_text: Leviathan has used WMI for execution.
Text: Leviathan使用了WMI来执行

en_text: LightNeuron contains a function to encrypt and store emails that it collects.
Text: LightNeuron包含一个对其收集的电子邮件进行加密和存储的功能

en_text: LightNeuron has used filenames associated with Exchange and Outlook for binary and configuration files, such as winmail.dat.
Text: LightNeuron将与Exchange和Outlook相关的文件名用于二进制和配置文件，如winmail.dat

en_text: LightNeuron can be configured to exfiltrate data during nighttime or working hours.
Text: LightNeuron可以被配置为在夜间或工作时间渗出数据

en_text: LightNeuron can be configured to automatically exfiltrate files under a specified directory.
Text: LightNeuron可以被配置为自动渗出指定目录下的文件

en_text: LightNeuron can be configured to automatically collect files under a specified directory.
Text: LightNeuron可以被配置为自动收集指定目录下的文件

en_text: LightNeuron can collect files from a local system.
Text: LightNeuron可以从本地系统收集文件

en_text: LightNeuron can store email data in files and directories specified in its configuration, such as C:\Windows\ServiceProfiles\NetworkService\appdata\Local\Temp\.
Text: LightNeuron可以在其配置中指定的文件和目录中存储电子邮件数据，如C:\Windows\ServiceProfiles\NetworkService\appdata\Local\Temp\

en_text: LightNeuron is capable of starting a process using CreateProcess.
Text: LightNeuron能够使用CreateProcess启动一个进程

en_text: LightNeuron is capable of executing commands via cmd.exe.
Text: LightNeuron能够通过cmd.exe执行命令

en_text: LightNeuron is capable of modifying email content, headers, and attachments during transit.
Text: LightNeuron能够在传输过程中修改电子邮件内容、标题和附件

en_text: LightNeuron has used AES and XOR to decrypt configuration files and commands.
Text: LightNeuron使用AES和XOR来解密配置文件和命令

en_text: LightNeuron uses AES to encrypt C2 traffic.
Text: LightNeuron使用AES来加密C2流量

en_text: LightNeuron uses SMTP for C2.
Text: LightNeuron使用SMTP进行C2

en_text: LightNeuron gathers information about network adapters using the Win32 API call GetAdaptersInfo.
Text: LightNeuron使用Win32 API调用GetAdaptersInfo来收集网络适配器的信息

en_text: LightNeuron gathers the victim computer name using the Win32 API call GetComputerName.
Text: LightNeuron使用Win32 API调用GetComputerName来收集受害者的计算机名称

en_text: LightNeuron has used a malicious Microsoft Exchange transport agent for persistence.
Text: LightNeuron使用了一个恶意的微软Exchange传输代理进行持久化

en_text: LightNeuron is controlled via commands that are embedded into PDFs and JPGs using steganographic methods.
Text: LightNeuron是通过使用隐写方法嵌入到PDF和JPG中的命令来控制的

en_text: LightNeuron collects Exchange emails matching rules specified in its configuration.
Text: LightNeuron收集符合其配置中指定规则的Exchange电子邮件

en_text: LightNeuron exfiltrates data over its email C2 channel.
Text: LightNeuron通过其电子邮件C2渠道渗出数据

en_text: LightNeuron encrypts its configuration files with AES-256.
Text: LightNeuron用AES-256对其配置文件进行加密

en_text: LightNeuron has the ability to download and execute additional files.
Text: LightNeuron有能力下载和执行其他文件

en_text: LightNeuron has a function to delete files.
Text: LightNeuron有一个删除文件的功能

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can obtain data from local systems.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它从本地系统获取数据

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can change C2 servers.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它改变C2服务器

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve system information.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它检索系统信息

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve a list of running processes.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它检索正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can download files onto compromised hosts.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它将文件下载到被攻击的主机上

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can list contents of drives and search for files.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它列出驱动器的内容并搜索文件

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can delete files.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它删除文件

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can change the frequency at which compromised hosts contact remote C2 infrastructure.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过这个后门改变被攻击主机与远程C2基础设施联系的频率

en_text: Linfo creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can start a remote shell.
Text: Linfo创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过这个后门启动一个远程外壳

en_text: Linux Rabbit brute forces SSH passwords in order to attempt to gain access and install its malware onto the server.
Text: Linux Rabbit对SSH密码进行暴力破解，以试图获得访问权并将其恶意软件安装到服务器上

en_text: Linux Rabbit sends the payload from the C2 server as an encoded URL parameter.
Text: Linux Rabbit将C2服务器的有效载荷作为一个编码的URL参数发送

en_text: Linux Rabbit attempts to gain access to the server via SSH.
Text: Linux Rabbit试图通过SSH获得对服务器的访问

en_text: Linux Rabbit maintains persistence on an infected machine through rc.local and .bashrc files.
Text: Linux Rabbit通过rc.local和.bashrc文件在被感染的机器上保持持久性

en_text: Linux Rabbit acquires valid SSH accounts through brute force.
Text: Linux Rabbit通过暴力手段获取有效的SSH账户

en_text: Linux Rabbit opens a socket on port 22 and if it receives a response it attempts to obtain the machine's hostname and Top-Level Domain.
Text: Linux Rabbit在22号端口打开一个套接字，如果它收到一个响应，它就会试图获得机器的主机名和顶级域

en_text: Exaramel for Linux has a hardcoded location under systemd that it uses to achieve persistence if it is running as root.
Text: Linux的Exaramel在systemd下有一个硬编码的位置，如果它以root身份运行，它就用这个位置来实现持久性

en_text: LockerGoga installation has been immediately preceded by a "task kill" command in order to disable anti-virus.
Text: LockerGoga安装前已立即使用 "任务杀 "命令，以禁用防病毒

en_text: LockerGoga has encrypted files, including core Windows OS files, using RSA-OAEP MGF1 and then demanded Bitcoin be paid for the decryption key.
Text: LockerGoga使用RSA-OAEP MGF1加密了文件，包括核心的Windows操作系统文件，然后要求用比特币支付解密密钥

en_text: LockerGoga has been signed with stolen certificates in order to make it look more legitimate.
Text: LockerGoga已经用偷来的证书签名，以使它看起来更合法

en_text: LoJax is a UEFI BIOS rootkit deployed to persist remote access software on some targeted systems.
Text: LoJax是一个UEFI BIOS rootkit，部署在一些目标系统上用于坚持远程访问软件

en_text: LoJax has modified the Registry key ‘HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\BootExecute’ from ‘autocheck autochk ’ to ‘autocheck autoche ’ in order to execute its payload during Windows startup.
Text: LoJax修改了注册表键 "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\BootExecute"，从 "autocheck autochk "改为 "autocheck autoche"，以便在Windows启动期间执行其有效载荷

en_text: LoJax has modified the Registry key ‘HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\BootExecute’ from ‘autocheck autochk ’ to ‘autocheck autoche ’.
Text: LoJax修改了注册表键 "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\BootExecute"，将 "autocheck autochk "改为 "autocheck autoche"

en_text: LoJax has loaded an embedded NTFS DXE driver to be able to access and write to NTFS partitions.
Text: LoJax已经加载了一个嵌入式NTFS DXE驱动，能够访问和写入NTFS分区

en_text: Lokibot has used process hollowing to inject into legitimate Windows process vbc.exe.
Text: Lokibot利用进程空洞化，将其注入合法的Windows进程vbc.exe

en_text: Lokibot has used several packing methods for obfuscation.
Text: Lokibot使用了几种包装方法来混淆视听

en_text: Lokibot has been executed through malicious documents contained in spearphishing e-mails.
Text: Lokibot是通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件中的恶意文件执行的

en_text: Lokibot has stolen credentials from multiple applications and data sources including Windows OS credentials, email clients, FTP, and SFTP clients.
Text: Lokibot已经从多个应用程序和数据源窃取了凭证，包括Windows操作系统凭证、电子邮件客户端、FTP和SFTP客户端

en_text: Lokibot has demonstrated the ability to steal credentials from multiple applications and data sources including Safari and the Chromium and Mozilla Firefox-based web browsers.
Text: Lokibot已经证明有能力从多个应用程序和数据源窃取凭证，包括Safari和基于Chromium和Mozilla Firefox的网络浏览器

en_text: Lokibot has used HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: Lokibot已使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: Lokibot has obfuscated strings with base64 encoding.
Text: Lokibot用base64编码对字符串进行了混淆处理

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to discover the domain name of the infected host.
Text: Lokibot有能力发现被感染主机的域名

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to discover the computer name and Windows product name/version.
Text: Lokibot有能力发现计算机名称和Windows产品名称

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to discover the username on the infected host.
Text: Lokibot有能力发现受感染主机上的用户名

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to copy itself to a hidden file and directory.
Text: Lokibot有能力将自己复制到一个隐藏的文件和目录

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to initiate contact with command and control (C2) to exfiltrate stolen data.
Text: Lokibot有能力启动与指挥和控制（C2）的联系，以渗出被盗数据

en_text: Lokibot has the ability to capture input on the compromised host via keylogging.
Text: Lokibot有能力通过键盘记录捕捉被攻击主机上的输入

en_text: LoudMiner has obfuscated various scripts and encrypted DMG files.
Text: LoudMiner混淆了各种脚本和加密的DMG文件

en_text: LoudMiner added plist files in /Library/LaunchDaemons with RunAtLoad set to true.
Text: LoudMiner将plist文件添加到 LoudMiner添加了plist文件在 LoudMiner将plist文件加入到 LoudMiner将plist文件添加到了

en_text: LoudMiner started the cryptomining virtual machine as a service on the infected machine.
Text: LoudMiner将加密虚拟机作为一项服务在受感染的机器上启动

en_text: LoudMiner used shell scripts to launch various services and to start/stop the QEMU virtualization.
Text: LoudMiner使用 shell 脚本来启动各种服务，并启动

en_text: LoudMiner used an MSI installer to install the virtualization software.
Text: LoudMiner使用MSI安装程序来安装虚拟化软件

en_text: LoudMiner used plists to execute shell scripts and maintain persistence on boot. LoudMiner also added plist files in /Library/LaunchDaemons with KeepAlive set to true, which would restart the process if stopped.
Text: LoudMiner使用plist来执行shell脚本并在启动时保持持久性

en_text: LoudMiner used the ps command to monitor the running processes on the system.
Text: LoudMiner使用ps命令来监控系统中的运行进程

en_text: LoudMiner has used QEMU and VirtualBox to run a Tiny Core Linux virtual machine, which runs XMRig and makes connections to the C2 server for updates.
Text: LoudMiner使用QEMU和VirtualBox来运行Tiny Core Linux虚拟机，该虚拟机运行XMRig并与C2服务器建立连接以进行更新

en_text: LoudMiner used SCP to update the miner from the C2.
Text: LoudMiner使用SCP从C2更新矿工

en_text: LoudMiner used a batch script to run the Linux virtual machine as a service.
Text: LoudMiner使用批处理脚本将Linux虚拟机作为一项服务来运行

en_text: LoudMiner used a script to gather the IP address of the infected machine before sending to the C2.
Text: LoudMiner使用一个脚本来收集受感染机器的IP地址，然后发送给C2

en_text: LoudMiner harvested system resources to mine cryptocurrency, using XMRig to mine Monero.
Text: LoudMiner收割系统资源来挖掘加密货币，使用XMRig来挖掘Monero

en_text: LoudMiner is typically bundled with pirated copies of Virtual Studio Technology (VST) for Windows and macOS.
Text: LoudMiner通常与Windows和macOS的虚拟工作室技术（VST）的盗版捆绑在一起

en_text: LoudMiner launched the QEMU services in the /Library/LaunchDaemons/ folder using launchctl.
Text: LoudMiner推出的QEMU服务在 LoudMiner推出了QEMU服务

en_text: LoudMiner deleted installation files after completion.
Text: LoudMiner完成后删除了安装文件

en_text: LoudMiner has monitored CPU usage.
Text: LoudMiner已监测到CPU的使用

en_text: LoudMiner has set the attributes of the VirtualBox directory and VBoxVmService parent directory to "hidden".
Text: LoudMiner已经将VirtualBox目录和VBoxVmService父目录的属性设置为 "隐藏"

en_text: LOWBALL command and control occurs via HTTPS over port 443.
Text: LOWBALL的命令和控制通过443端口的HTTPS进行

en_text: LOWBALL uses the Dropbox API to request two files, one of which is the same file as the one dropped by the malicious email attachment. This is most likely meant to be a mechanism to update the compromised host with a new version of the LOWBALL malware.
Text: LOWBALL使用Dropbox API请求两个文件，其中一个是与恶意电子邮件附件所投放的文件相同的文件。这很可能是为了用新版本的LOWBALL恶意软件更新被攻击的主机的机制。

en_text: LOWBALL uses the Dropbox cloud storage service for command and control.
Text: LOWBALL使用Dropbox云存储服务进行指挥和控制

en_text: Lslsass can dump active logon session password hashes from the lsass process.
Text: Lslsass可以从lsass进程中转储活动登录会话密码哈希值

en_text: Lurid can compress data before sending it.
Text: Lurid可以在发送数据之前对其进行压缩

en_text: Lurid performs XOR encryption.
Text: Lurid执行XOR加密

en_text: Machete uses the netsh wlan show networks mode=bssid and netsh wlan show interfaces commands to list all nearby WiFi networks and connected interfaces.
Text: Machete 使用 netsh wlan show networks mode=bssid 和 netsh wlan show interfaces 命令来列出所有附近的 WiFi 网络和连接的接口

en_text: Machete saves the window names.
Text: Machete保存了窗口名称

en_text: Machete employed some visual obfuscation techniques by naming variables as combinations of letters to hinder analysis.
Text: Machete采用了一些视觉混淆技术，将变量命名为字母组合，以阻碍分析

en_text: Machete produces file listings in order to search for files to be exfiltrated.
Text: Machete产生文件列表，以便搜索要外流的文件

en_text: Machete created their own directories to drop files into.
Text: Machete创建了他们自己的目录，将文件放入其中

en_text: Machete retrieves the user profile data (e.g., browsers) from Chrome and Firefox browsers.
Text: Machete从Chrome和Firefox浏览器中检索用户档案数据（如浏览器）

en_text: Machete captures audio from the computer’s microphone.
Text: Machete从计算机的麦克风中捕捉音频

en_text: Machete copies files from newly inserted drives.
Text: Machete从新插入的驱动器中复制文件

en_text: Machete stores zipped files with profile data from installed web browsers.
Text: Machete存储有来自已安装的网络浏览器的配置文件数据的压缩文件

en_text: The different components of Machete are executed by Windows Task Scheduler.
Text: Machete的不同组件是由Windows任务调度器执行的

en_text: Machete malware used FTP for C2.
Text: Machete恶意软件使用FTP进行C2

en_text: Machete malware used Python’s urllib library to make HTTP requests to the C2 server.
Text: Machete恶意软件使用Python的urllib库，向C2服务器发出HTTP请求

en_text: Machete has sent phishing emails that contain a link to an external server with ZIP and RAR archives.
Text: Machete发送的钓鱼邮件包含一个指向外部服务器的ZIP和RAR档案的链接

en_text: Machete has delivered spearphishing emails that contain a zipped file with malicious contents.
Text: Machete发送的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件包含一个带有恶意内容的压缩文件

en_text: Machete stores files and logs in a folder on the local drive.
Text: Machete将文件和日志存储在本地驱动器的一个文件夹中

en_text: Machete can download additional files for execution on the victim’s machine.
Text: Machete可以下载额外的文件在受害者的机器上执行

en_text: Machete sends stolen data to the C2 server every 10 minutes.
Text: Machete每10分钟向C2服务器发送被盗数据

en_text: Machete has used AES to exfiltrate documents.
Text: Machete使用AES来渗出文件

en_text: Machete uses FTP for Command & Control.
Text: Machete使用FTP进行指挥 弯刀使用FTP进行指挥 弯刀使用FTP来指挥 弯刀使用FTP进行命令

en_text: Machete uses Python scripts.
Text: Machete使用Python脚本

en_text: Machete has used TLS-encrypted FTP to exfiltrate data.
Text: Machete使用TLS加密的FTP来渗出数据

en_text: Machete used scheduled tasks for persistence.
Text: Machete使用计划任务来实现持久性

en_text: Machete has used pyobfuscate, zlib compression, and base64 encoding for obfuscation.
Text: Machete使用了pyobfuscate、zlib压缩和base64编码进行混淆处理

en_text: Machete's collected data is exfiltrated over the same channel used for C2.
Text: Machete收集的数据通过用于C2的同一渠道流出

en_text: Machete's collected data is encrypted with AES before exfiltration.
Text: Machete收集的数据在渗出前用AES进行了加密

en_text: Machete’s collected files are exfiltrated automatically to remote servers.
Text: Machete收集的文件会自动渗出到远程服务器

en_text: Machete collects stored credentials from several web browsers.
Text: Machete收集来自几个网络浏览器的存储凭证

en_text: Machete collects the MAC address of the target computer.
Text: Machete收集目标计算机的MAC地址

en_text: Machete collects the hostname of the target computer.
Text: Machete收集目标计算机的主机名

en_text: Machete hijacks the clipboard data by creating an overlapped window that listens to keyboard events.
Text: Machete通过创建一个监听键盘事件的重叠窗口来劫持剪贴板数据

en_text: Machete detects the insertion of new devices by listening for the WM_DEVICECHANGE window message.
Text: Machete通过监听WM_DEVICECHANGE窗口消息来检测新设备的插入

en_text: Machete has used free dynamic DNS domains for C2.
Text: Machete为C2使用了免费的动态DNS域

en_text: Machete’s downloaded data is decrypted using AES.
Text: Machete下载的数据使用AES进行解密

en_text: Machete has has relied on users opening malicious attachments delivered through spearphishing to execute malware.
Text: Machete依靠用户打开通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼提供的恶意附件来执行恶意软件

en_text: Machete has has relied on users opening malicious links delivered through spearphishing to execute malware.
Text: Machete依靠用户打开通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼提供的恶意链接来执行恶意软件

en_text: Machete has scanned and looked for cryptographic keys and certificate file extensions.
Text: Machete已经扫描并查找了加密密钥和证书文件扩展名

en_text: Machete has the capability to exfiltrate stolen data to a hidden folder on a removable drive.
Text: Machete有能力将被盗数据渗透到可移动驱动器上的一个隐藏文件夹

en_text: Machete has a feature to copy files from every drive onto a removable drive in a hidden folder.
Text: Machete有一个功能，可以将每个驱动器中的文件复制到一个隐藏文件夹中的可移动驱动器上

en_text: Machete has a component to check for running processes to look for web browsers.
Text: Machete有一个组件可以检查正在运行的进程以寻找网络浏览器

en_text: Machete had a module in its malware to find, encrypt, and upload files from fixed and removable drives.
Text: Machete在其恶意软件中有一个模块，可以从固定和可移动驱动器中查找、加密和上传文件

en_text: Machete used multiple compiled Python scripts on the victim’s system.
Text: Machete在受害者的系统上使用了多个编译的Python脚本

en_text: Machete searches the File system for files of interest.
Text: Machete在文件系统中搜索感兴趣的文件

en_text: Machete renamed payloads to masquerade as legitimate Google Chrome, Java, Dropbox, Adobe Reader and Python executables.
Text: Machete重命名的有效载荷伪装成合法的谷歌浏览器、Java、Dropbox、Adobe Reader和Python可执行文件

en_text: MacSpy stores itself in ~/Library/.DS_Stores/
Text: MacSpy将自己存储在~中 MacSpy将自己存储在~中

en_text: MacSpy can record the sounds from microphones on a computer.
Text: MacSpy可以记录计算机上麦克风的声音

en_text: MacSpy can steal clipboard contents.
Text: MacSpy可以窃取剪贴板内容

en_text: MacSpy can capture screenshots of the desktop over multiple monitors.
Text: MacSpy可以通过多个显示器捕获桌面的截图

en_text: MacSpy captures keystrokes.
Text: MacSpy能捕捉到键盘信息

en_text: MacSpy deletes any temporary files it creates
Text: MacSpy删除了它所创建的任何临时文件 MacSpy会删除其创建的任何临时文件 MacSpy会删除它所创建的任何临时文件 MacSpy删除它所创建的任何临时文件

en_text: MacSpy uses HTTP for command and control.
Text: MacSpy使用HTTP进行指挥和控制

en_text: MacSpy uses Tor for command and control.
Text: MacSpy使用Tor进行指挥和控制

en_text: MacSpy persists via a Launch Agent.
Text: MacSpy通过一个启动代理持续存在

en_text: Magic Hound malware can take a screenshot and upload the file to its C2 server.
Text: Magic Hound 恶意软件可以进行截图，并将文件上传到其C2服务器

en_text: Magic Hound has downloaded additional code and files from servers onto victims. Magic Hound used Wrapper/Gholee, custom-developed malware, which downloaded additional malware to the infected system.
Text: Magic Hound从服务器上下载了额外的代码和文件到受害者身上。Magic Hound使用了Wrapper/Gholee这个定制开发的恶意软件，它将额外的恶意软件下载到受感染的系统中。

en_text: Magic Hound stole domain credentials from Microsoft Active Directory Domain Controller and leveraged Mimikatz.
Text: Magic Hound从微软活动目录域控制器中窃取域凭证，并利用Mimikatz

en_text: Magic Hound malware can list a victim's logical drives and the type, as well the total/free space of the fixed devices. Other malware can list a directory's contents.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件可以列出受害者的逻辑驱动器和类型，以及固定设备的总/可用空间。其他恶意软件可以列出一个目录的内容。

en_text: Magic Hound malware can list running processes.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件可以列出正在运行的进程

en_text: Magic Hound malware can use a SOAP Web service to communicate with its C2 server.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件可以使用SOAP网络服务与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: Magic Hound malware is capable of keylogging. Magic Hound used CWoolger and MPK, custom-developed malware, which recorded all keystrokes on an infected system.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件能够进行键盘记录。Magic Hound使用了CWoolger和MPK，这是定制开发的恶意软件，记录了受感染系统的所有按键。

en_text: Magic Hound malware has used a PowerShell command to check the victim system architecture to determine if it is an x64 machine. Other malware has obtained the OS version, UUID, and computer/host name to send to the C2 server.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件使用PowerShell命令来检查受害者的系统架构，以确定它是否是一台x64机器。其他恶意软件已经获得了操作系统版本、UUID和计算机/主机名称，以发送至C2服务器。

en_text: Magic Hound malware has used base64-encoded commands and files, and has also encrypted embedded strings with AES.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件使用了base64编码的命令和文件，还用AES对嵌入式字符串进行了加密

en_text: Magic Hound malware has used HTTP for C2.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件使用了HTTP进行C2

en_text: Magic Hound malware has used VBS scripts for execution.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件使用了VBS脚本来执行

en_text: Magic Hound malware has used Registry Run keys to establish persistence.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件使用了注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: Magic Hound malware gathers the victim's local IP address, MAC address, and external IP address.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件收集了受害者的本地IP地址、MAC地址和外部IP地址

en_text: Magic Hound malware has communicated with its C2 server over TCP port 4443 using HTTP.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件通过TCP 4443端口使用HTTP与它的C2服务器进行了通信

en_text: Magic Hound malware has obtained the victim username and sent it to the C2 server.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件已经获得了受害者的用户名并将其发送到C2服务器

en_text: Magic Hound malware has a function to determine whether the C2 server wishes to execute the newly dropped file in a hidden window.
Text: Magic Hound恶意软件有一个功能，可以确定C2服务器是否希望在一个隐藏窗口中执行新投放的文件

en_text: Magic Hound used various social media channels to spearphish victims.
Text: Magic Hound利用各种社交媒体渠道对受害者进行鱼叉式攻击

en_text: Magic Hound has used PowerShell for execution and privilege escalation.
Text: Magic Hound使用了PowerShell进行执行和权限升级

en_text: Magic Hound used FireMalv, custom-developed malware, which collected passwords from the Firefox browser storage.
Text: Magic Hound使用了定制开发的恶意软件FireMalv，它从Firefox浏览器的存储中收集密码

en_text: Magic Hound has used the command-line interface.
Text: Magic Hound使用了命令行界面

en_text: Magic Hound has collected .PST archives.
Text: Magic Hound收集了.PST档案

en_text: Magic Hound granted compromised email accounts read access to the email boxes of additional targeted accounts. The group then was able to authenticate to the intended victim's OWA (Outlook Web Access) portal and read hundreds of email communications for information on Middle East organizations.
Text: Magic Hound授予被攻击的电子邮件账户对其他目标账户的电子邮件箱的读取权限。然后，该组织能够验证目标受害者的OWA（Outlook Web Access）门户，并读取数百封电子邮件通信，以获取有关中东组织的信息。

en_text: Magic Hound sent shortened URL links over email to victims. The URLs linked to Word documents with malicious macros that execute PowerShells scripts to download Pupy.
Text: Magic Hound通过电子邮件向受害者发送缩短的URL链接。这些URL链接到带有恶意宏的Word文档，执行PowerShells脚本以下载Pupy。

en_text: Magic Hound has used RAR to stage and compress local folders.
Text: Magic Hound已经使用RAR对本地文件夹进行分期和压缩

en_text: Magic Hound has used personalized spearphishing attachments.
Text: Magic Hound已经使用了个性化的鱼叉式钓鱼附件

en_text: Magic Hound has lured victims into executing malicious files.
Text: Magic Hound诱使受害者执行恶意文件

en_text: MailSniper can be used to obtain account names from Exchange and Office 365 using the Get-GlobalAddressList cmdlet.
Text: MailSniper可使用Get-GlobalAddressList cmdlet从Exchange和Office 365获取账户名称

en_text: MailSniper can be used for password spraying against Exchange and Office 365.
Text: MailSniper可用于对Exchange和Office 365进行密码喷洒

en_text: MailSniper can be used for searching through email in Exchange and Office 365 environments.
Text: MailSniper可用于在Exchange和Office 365环境中搜索电子邮件

en_text: Matroyshka can establish persistence by adding a Scheduled Task named "Microsoft Boost Kernel Optimization".
Text: Matroyshka可以通过添加一个名为 "Microsoft Boost Kernel Optimization "的预定任务来建立持久性

en_text: Matroyshka can establish persistence by adding Registry Run keys.
Text: Matroyshka可以通过添加注册表运行键来建立持久性

en_text: Matroyshka is capable of keylogging.
Text: Matroyshka能够进行键盘记录

en_text: Matroyshka is capable of performing screen captures.
Text: Matroyshka能够进行屏幕抓取

en_text: Matroyshka is capable of stealing Outlook passwords.
Text: Matroyshka能够窃取Outlook密码

en_text: Matroyshka is capable of providing Meterpreter shell access.
Text: Matroyshka能够提供Meterpreter shell访问

en_text: Matroyshka uses reflective DLL injection to inject the malicious library and execute the RAT.
Text: Matroyshka使用反射式DLL注入来注入恶意库并执行RAT

en_text: Matroyshka obfuscates API function names using a substitute cipher combined with Base64 encoding.
Text: Matroyshka使用替代密码结合Base64编码对API函数名称进行混淆

en_text: Matroyshka uses rundll32.exe in a Registry Run key value for execution as part of its persistence mechanism.
Text: Matroyshka在注册表运行键值中使用rundll32.exe来执行，作为其持久性机制的一部分

en_text: Maze operators have used VirtualBox and a Windows 7 virtual machine to run the ransomware; the virtual machine's configuration file mapped the shared network drives of the target company, presumably so Maze can encrypt files on the shared drives as well as the local machine.
Text: Maze操作员使用VirtualBox和Windows 7虚拟机来运行勒索软件；虚拟机的配置文件映射了目标公司的共享网络驱动器，据推测，Maze可以加密共享驱动器上的文件以及本地机器

en_text: Maze has attempted to delete the shadow volumes of infected machines, once before and once after the encryption process.
Text: Maze曾试图删除被感染机器的影子卷，在加密过程之前和之后各一次

en_text: Maze has inserted large blocks of junk code, including some components to decrypt strings and other important information for later in the encryption process.
Text: Maze插入了大块的垃圾代码，包括一些用于解密字符串和其他重要信息的组件，供以后的加密过程使用

en_text: Maze has created scheduled tasks using name variants such as "Windows Update Security", "Windows Update Security Patches", and "Google Chrome Security Update", to launch Maze at a specific time.
Text: Maze创建了计划任务，使用的名称变体包括 "Windows Update Security"、"Windows Update Security Patches "和 "Google Chrome Security Update"，以便在特定时间启动Maze

en_text: The Maze encryption process has used batch scripts with various commands.
Text: Maze加密过程使用了带有各种命令的批处理脚本

en_text: Maze has used WMI to attempt to delete the shadow volumes on a machine, and to connect a virtual machine to the network domain of the victim organization's network.
Text: Maze利用WMI试图删除一台机器上的影子卷，并将一台虚拟机连接到受害者组织网络的网域

en_text: Maze has checked the language of the infected system using the "GetUSerDefaultUILanguage" function.
Text: Maze使用 "GetUSerDefaultUILanguage "函数检查了被感染系统的语言

en_text: Maze has used the "WNetOpenEnumW", "WNetEnumResourceW", "WNetCloseEnum" and "WNetAddConnection2W" functions to enumerate the network resources on the infected machine.
Text: Maze使用 "WNetOpenEnumW"、"WNetEnumResourceW"、"WNetCloseEnum "和 "WNetAddConnection2W "函数来列举被感染机器上的网络资源

en_text: Maze has delivered components for its ransomware attacks using MSI files, some of which have been executed from the command-line using msiexec.
Text: Maze使用MSI文件为其勒索软件攻击提供组件，其中一些是使用msiexec从命令行执行

en_text: Maze has disrupted systems by encrypting files on targeted machines, claiming to decrypt files if a ransom payment is made. Maze has used the ChaCha algorithm, based on Salsa20, and an RSA algorithm to encrypt files.
Text: Maze通过对目标机器上的文件进行加密来破坏系统，并声称如果支付赎金就会解密文件。Maze使用基于Salsa20的ChaCha算法和RSA算法来加密文件。

en_text: Maze has forged POST strings with a random choice from a list of possibilities including "forum", "php", "view", etc. while making connection with the C2, hindering detection efforts.
Text: Maze伪造了POST字符串，从包括 "forum"、"php"、"view "等一系列可能性中随机选择，同时与C2进行连接，阻碍了检测工作

en_text: Maze has injected the malware DLL into a target process.
Text: Maze已将恶意软件DLL注入目标进程中

en_text: Maze has disabled dynamic analysis and other security tools including IDA debugger, x32dbg, and OllyDbg. It has also disabled Windows Defender's Real-Time Monitoring feature and attempted to disable endpoint protection services.
Text: Maze已禁用动态分析和其他安全工具，包括IDA调试器、x32dbg和OllyDbg。它还禁用了Windows Defender的实时监控功能，并试图禁用端点保护服务。

en_text: Maze has gathered all of the running system processes.
Text: Maze已经收集了所有正在运行的系统进程

en_text: Maze has stopped SQL services to ensure it can encrypt any database.
Text: Maze已经停止了SQL服务，以确保它能对任何数据库进行加密

en_text: Maze has communicated to hard-coded IP addresses via HTTP.
Text: Maze已经通过HTTP与硬编码的IP地址进行沟通

en_text: Maze has decrypted strings and other important information during the encryption process. Maze also calls certain functions dynamically to hinder analysis.
Text: Maze在加密过程中已经解密了字符串和其他重要信息

en_text: Maze has issued a shutdown command on a victim machine that, upon reboot, will run the ransomware within a VM.
Text: Maze在受害者机器上发布了一个关机命令，重启后将在一个虚拟机内运行勒索软件

en_text: Maze has created a file named "startup_vrun.bat" in the Startup folder of a virtual machine to establish persistence.
Text: Maze在虚拟机的启动文件夹中创建了一个名为 "startup_vrun.bat "的文件以建立持久性

en_text: Maze has used several Windows API functions throughout the encryption process including IsDebuggerPresent, TerminateProcess, Process32FirstW, among others.
Text: Maze在整个加密过程中使用了几个Windows API函数，包括IsDebuggerPresent、TerminateProcess、Process32FirstW，等等

en_text: MCMD has been named Readme.txt to appear legitimate.
Text: MCMD被命名为Readme.txt，以显得合法

en_text: MCMD can launch a console process (cmd.exe) with redirected standard input and output.
Text: MCMD可以启动一个带有重定向标准输入和输出的控制台进程（cmd.exe）

en_text: MCMD can use scheduled tasks for persistence.
Text: MCMD可以使用计划任务来实现持久性

en_text: MCMD can use Registry Run Keys for persistence.
Text: MCMD可以使用注册表运行键进行持久化

en_text: MCMD can upload additional files to a compromised host.
Text: MCMD可以向被攻击的主机上传额外的文件

en_text: MCMD can modify processes to prevent them from being visible on the desktop.
Text: MCMD可以修改进程，防止它们在桌面上可见

en_text: MCMD can Base64 encode output strings prior to sending to C2.
Text: MCMD可以在发送至C2之前对输出字符串进行Base64编码

en_text: MCMD can use HTTPS in communication with C2 web servers.
Text: MCMD可以在与C2网络服务器的通信中使用HTTPS

en_text: MCMD has the ability to upload files from an infected device.
Text: MCMD有能力从受感染的设备上传文件

en_text: MCMD has the ability to remove set Registry Keys.
Text: MCMD有能力删除设定的注册表键

en_text: MechaFlounder has been downloaded as a file named lsass.exe, which matches the legitimate Windows file.
Text: MechaFlounder被下载为一个名为lsass.exe的文件，这与合法的Windows文件相符

en_text: MechaFlounder uses a python-based payload.
Text: MechaFlounder使用一个基于python的有效载荷

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to send the compromised user's account name and hostname within a URL to C2.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力将被入侵用户的账户名和主机名在一个URL中发送到C2

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to upload and download files to and from a compromised host.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力上传和下载文件，并从被破坏的主机上下载

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to identify the username and hostname on a compromised host.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力识别被入侵主机上的用户名和主机名

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to use base16 encoded strings in C2.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力在C2中使用base16编码的字符串

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to run commands on a compromised host.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力在被入侵的主机上运行命令

en_text: MechaFlounder has the ability to use HTTP in communication with C2.
Text: MechaFlounder有能力在与C2的通信中使用HTTP

en_text: meek uses Domain Fronting to disguise the destination of network traffic as another server that is hosted in the same Content Delivery Network (CDN) as the intended desitnation.
Text: meek使用 "域名前置"（Domain Fronting）将网络流量的目的地伪装成另一台服务器，该服务器与预期的目的地托管在同一内容交付网络（CDN）中

en_text: menuPass has renamed certutil and moved it to a different location on the system to avoid detection based on use of the tool.
Text: menuPass对certutil进行了重新命名，并将其移至系统中的不同位置，以避免根据使用该工具进行检测

en_text: A menuPass macro deletes files after it has decoded and decompressed them.
Text: menuPass宏在对文件进行解码和解压后，会将其删除

en_text: menuPass has used process hollowing in iexplore.exe to load the RedLeaves implant.
Text: menuPass利用iexplore.exe中的进程空洞化来加载RedLeaves的植入物

en_text: menuPass has used DLL side-loading to launch versions of Mimikatz and PwDump6 as well as UPPERCUT.
Text: menuPass使用DLL侧面加载来启动Mimikatz和PwDump6以及UPPERCUT版本

en_text: menuPass has used esentutl to change file extensions to their true type that were masquerading as .txt files.
Text: menuPass使用esentutl将伪装成.txt文件的文件扩展名改为其真实类型

en_text: menuPass has used InstallUtil.exe to execute malicious software.
Text: menuPass使用InstallUtil.exe来执行恶意软件

en_text: menuPass uses PowerSploit to inject shellcode into PowerShell.
Text: menuPass使用PowerSploit向PowerShell注入shellcode

en_text: menuPass has used RDP connections to move across the victim network.
Text: menuPass使用RDP连接在受害者网络中移动

en_text: menuPass has used key loggers to steal usernames and passwords.
Text: menuPass使用键盘记录器来窃取用户名和密码

en_text: menuPass uses scripts to enumerate IP ranges on the victim network. menuPass has also issued the command net view /domain to a PlugX implant to gather information about remote systems on the network.
Text: menuPass使用脚本来列举受害者网络上的IP范围。menuPass还向PlugX植入物发出net view /domain命令，收集网络上远程系统的信息。

en_text: menuPass has used DLL search order hijacking.
Text: menuPass使用了DLL搜索顺序劫持

en_text: menuPass has used Putty Secure Copy Client (PSCP) to transfer data.
Text: menuPass使用了Putty安全拷贝客户端（PSCP）来传输数据

en_text: menuPass has used valid accounts shared between Managed Service Providers and clients to move between the two environments.
Text: menuPass使用了管理服务提供商和客户之间共享的有效账户，在两个环境之间移动

en_text: menuPass has used legitimate access granted to Managed Service Providers in order to access victims of interest.
Text: menuPass使用了授予管理服务提供商的合法访问权，以便访问感兴趣的受害者

en_text: menuPass has used the Microsoft administration tool csvde.exe to export Active Directory data.
Text: menuPass使用了微软的管理工具csvde.exe来导出活动目录数据

en_text: menuPass has used a modified version of pentesting tools wmiexec.vbs and secretsdump.py to dump credentials.
Text: menuPass使用了修改后的pentesting工具wmiexec.vbs和secretsdump.py来转储凭证

en_text: menuPass has used a script (atexec.py) to execute a command on a target machine via Task Scheduler.
Text: menuPass使用了一个脚本（atexec.py），通过任务调度器在目标机上执行一个命令

en_text: menuPass has used a global service provider's IP as a proxy for C2 traffic from a victim.
Text: menuPass使用了一个全球服务提供商的IP作为受害者的C2流量的代理。

en_text: menuPass has used several tools to scan for open NetBIOS nameservers and enumerate NetBIOS sessions.
Text: menuPass使用了一些工具来扫描开放的NetBIOS名称服务器和列举NetBIOS会话

en_text: menuPass executes commands using a command-line interface and reverse shell. The group has used a modified version of pentesting script wmiexec.vbs to execute commands. menuPass has used malicious macros embedded inside Office documents to execute files.
Text: menuPass使用命令行界面和反向外壳执行命令。该组织使用修改过的pentesting脚本wmiexec.vbs来执行命令。menuPass使用嵌入Office文档内的恶意宏来执行文件。

en_text: menuPass uses a modified version of pentesting script wmiexec.vbs, which logs into a remote machine using WMI.
Text: menuPass使用一个修改过的pentesting脚本wmiexec.vbs，它使用WMI登录到远程机器

en_text: menuPass has used tcping.exe, similar to Ping, to probe port status on systems of interest.
Text: menuPass使用与Ping类似的tcping.exe来探测感兴趣的系统的端口状态

en_text: menuPass has attempted to get victims to open malicious files such as Windows Shortcuts (.lnk) and/or Microsoft Office documents, sent via email as part of spearphishing campaigns.
Text: menuPass试图让受害者打开恶意文件，如Windows Shortcuts（.lnk）和/或Microsoft Office文档，通过电子邮件发送，作为鱼叉式钓鱼活动的一部分。

en_text: menuPass has sent malicious Office documents via email as part of spearphishing campaigns as well as executables disguised as documents.
Text: menuPass通过电子邮件发送恶意的Office文档，作为鱼叉式钓鱼活动的一部分，以及伪装成文档的可执行文件

en_text: menuPass has collected data from remote systems by mounting network shares with net use and using Robocopy to transfer data.
Text: menuPass通过挂载有网用的网络共享和使用Robocopy传输数据，从远程系统收集数据

en_text: menuPass has been seen changing malicious files to appear legitimate.
Text: menuPass已被视为改变了恶意文件，使其看起来合法

en_text: menuPass has collected various files from the compromised computers.
Text: menuPass已经从被攻击的电脑中收集了各种文件

en_text: menuPass has used net use to conduct connectivity checks to machines.
Text: menuPass已使用net使用对机器进行连接检查

en_text: menuPass has encoded strings in its malware with base64 as well as with a simple, single-byte XOR obfuscation using key 0x40.
Text: menuPass在其恶意软件中使用base64以及使用密钥0x40的简单单字节XOR混淆法对字符串进行编码

en_text: menuPass has staged data on remote MSP systems or other victim networks prior to exfiltration.
Text: menuPass在渗出前将数据存放在远程MSP系统或其他受害者网络中

en_text: menuPass stages data prior to exfiltration in multi-part archives, often saved in the Recycle Bin.
Text: menuPass在渗出前将数据分为多个部分的档案，通常保存在回收站中

en_text: menuPass has compressed files before exfiltration using TAR and RAR.
Text: menuPass在渗出前使用TAR和RAR对文件进行了压缩

en_text: menuPass has encrypted files and information before exfiltration.
Text: menuPass在渗出前已经对文件和信息进行了加密

en_text: menuPass has installed updates and new malware on victims.
Text: menuPass在受害者身上安装了更新和新的恶意软件

en_text: menuPass has used certutil in a macro to decode base64-encoded content contained in a dropper document attached to an email. The group has also used certutil -decode to decode files on the victim’s machine when dropping UPPERCUT.
Text: menuPass在一个宏中使用了certutil来解码附在电子邮件中的dropper文件中的base64编码内容。该组织还使用 certutil -decode 在投放 UPPERCUT 时对受害者机器上的文件进行解码。

en_text: MESSAGETAP checks for the existence of two configuration files (keyword_parm.txt and parm.txt) and attempts to read the files every 30 seconds.
Text: MESSAGETAP 检查两个配置文件（keyword_parm.txt 和 parm.txt）是否存在，并尝试每 30 秒读取一次文件

en_text: MESSAGETAP has XOR-encrypted and stored contents of SMS messages that matched its target list.
Text: MESSAGETAP对符合其目标列表的短信内容进行了XOR加密和存储

en_text: MESSAGETAP checks two files, keyword_parm.txt and parm.txt, for instructions on how to target and save data parsed and extracted from SMS message data from the network traffic. If an SMS message contained either a phone number, IMSI number, or keyword that matched the predefined list, it is saved to a CSV file for later theft by the threat actor.
Text: MESSAGETAP检查两个文件，keyword_parm.txt和parm.txt，以了解如何针对和保存从网络流量中的短信数据解析和提取的数据的指示。如果一条短信包含电话号码、IMSI号码或与预定义列表相匹配的关键词，它就会被保存到CSV文件中，供威胁行为者以后盗用。

en_text: MESSAGETAP stored targeted SMS messages that matched its target list in CSV files on the compromised system.
Text: MESSAGETAP将符合其目标列表的目标短信存储在被入侵系统的CSV文件中

en_text: MESSAGETAP uses the libpcap library to listen to all traffic and parses network protocols starting with Ethernet and IP layers. It continues parsing protocol layers including SCTP, SCCP, and TCAP and finally extracts SMS message data and routing metadata.
Text: MESSAGETAP使用libpcap库来监听所有流量，并从以太网和IP层开始解析网络协议。它继续解析协议层，包括SCTP、SCCP和TCAP，最后提取SMS消息数据和路由元数据。

en_text: Metamorfo includes payloads written in JavaScript.
Text: Metamorfo包括用JavaScript编写的有效载荷

en_text: Metamorfo collects a list of installed antivirus software from the victim’s system.
Text: Metamorfo从受害者的系统中收集已安装的防病毒软件列表

en_text: Metamorfo's C2 communication has been encrypted using OpenSSL.
Text: Metamorfo的C2通信已经使用OpenSSL进行了加密

en_text: Metamorfo has obfuscated and encrypted some payloads.
Text: Metamorfo对一些有效载荷进行了混淆和加密

en_text: Metamorfo has written process names to the Registry, disabled IE browser features, deleted Registry keys, and changed the ExtendedUIHoverTime key.
Text: Metamorfo将进程名称写入注册表，禁用IE浏览器功能，删除注册表键，并改变了ExtendedUIHoverTime键

en_text: Metamorfo has disguised an MSI file as the Adobe Acrobat Reader Installer.
Text: Metamorfo将一个MSI文件伪装成Adobe Acrobat Reader安装程序

en_text: Metamorfo can enumerate all windows on the victim’s machine.
Text: Metamorfo可以列举出受害者机器上的所有窗口

en_text: Metamorfo can collect screenshots of the victim’s machine.
Text: Metamorfo可以收集受害者机器的屏幕截图

en_text: Metamorfo had used AutoIt to load and execute the DLL payload.
Text: Metamorfo使用AutoIt来加载和执行DLL有效载荷

en_text: Metamorfo uses JavaScript to get the system time.
Text: Metamorfo使用JavaScript来获取系统时间

en_text: Metamorfo has used mshta.exe to execute a HTA payload.
Text: Metamorfo使用mshta.exe来执行一个HTA有效载荷

en_text: Metamorfo has hidden its GUI using the ShowWindow() WINAPI call.
Text: Metamorfo使用ShowWindow()WINAPI调用隐藏了其GUI

en_text: Metamorfo has used VMProtect to pack and protect files.
Text: Metamorfo使用VMProtect来打包和保护文件

en_text: Metamorfo has used MsiExec.exe to automatically execute files.
Text: Metamorfo使用了MsiExec.exe来自动执行文件

en_text: Metamorfo has used native WINAPI calls.
Text: Metamorfo使用了本地WINAPI调用

en_text: Metamorfo has been delivered to victims via emails containing malicious HTML attachments.
Text: Metamorfo是通过含有恶意HTML附件的电子邮件传递给受害者的

en_text: Metamorfo has communicated with hosts over raw TCP on port 9999.
Text: Metamorfo通过端口9999的原始TCP与主机进行通信

en_text: Metamorfo has injected a malicious DLL into the Windows Media Player process (wmplayer.exe).
Text: Metamorfo向Windows媒体播放器进程（wmplayer.exe）注入了一个恶意的DLL

en_text: Metamorfo requires the user to double-click the executable to run the malicious HTA file.
Text: Metamorfo要求用户双击可执行文件来运行恶意的HTA文件

en_text: Metamorfo has written its executable path to a Registry Run key and used .LNK files in the startup folder to achieve persistence.
Text: Metamorfo已将其可执行路径写入注册表运行键，并在启动文件夹中使用.LNK文件来实现持久性

en_text: Metamorfo has used raw TCP for C2.
Text: Metamorfo已将原始TCP用于C2

en_text: Metamorfo has side-loaded its malicious DLL file.
Text: Metamorfo已经从侧面加载了其恶意的DLL文件

en_text: Metamorfo has collected the hostname and Operating System version from the system.
Text: Metamorfo已经从系统中收集了主机名和操作系统版本

en_text: Metamorfo has performed process name checks and has monitored applications.
Text: Metamorfo已经进行了进程名称检查，并对应用程序进行了监控

en_text: Metamorfo has embedded a "vmdetect.exe" executable to identify virtual machines at the beginning of execution.
Text: Metamorfo已经嵌入了一个 "vmdetect.exe "可执行文件，以便在执行之初识别虚拟机

en_text: Metamorfo has digitally signed executables using AVAST Software certificates.
Text: Metamorfo已经使用AVAST软件证书对可执行文件进行了数字签名

en_text: Metamorfo has used MSI to download files for execution.
Text: Metamorfo已经使用MSI下载文件进行执行

en_text: Metamorfo has used cmd.exe /c to execute files.
Text: Metamorfo已经使用了cmd.exe Metamorfo曾使用cmd.exe Metamorfo使用过cmd.exe Metamorfo使用了cmd.exe

en_text: Metamorfo has searched the Program Files directories for specific folders and has searched for strings related to its mutexes.
Text: Metamorfo已经搜索了Program Files目录中的特定文件夹，并搜索了与它的mutexes有关的字符串

en_text: Metamorfo has downloaded a zip file for execution on the system.
Text: Metamorfo已经下载了一个zip文件，在系统上执行

en_text: Metamorfo has searched the system for an extensive list of Brazilian banking software.
Text: Metamorfo已经在系统中搜索了大量的巴西银行软件

en_text: Metamorfo has automatically collected mouse clicks, continuous screenshots on the machine, and set timers to collect the contents of the clipboard and website browsing.
Text: Metamorfo已经自动收集了鼠标点击，在机器上连续截图，并设置定时器收集剪贴板和网站浏览的内容

en_text: Metamorfo has used HTTP for downloading items.
Text: Metamorfo已使用HTTP下载项目

en_text: Metamorfo has a function to receive data from the system clipboard.
Text: Metamorfo有一个从系统剪贴板接收数据的功能

en_text: Metamorfo has a function that can watch the contents of the system clipboard for valid bitcoin addresses, which it then overwrites with the attacker's address.
Text: Metamorfo有一个功能，可以观察系统剪贴板的内容，寻找有效的比特币地址，然后用攻击者的地址覆盖

en_text: Metamorfo has a command to delete a Registry key it uses, \Software\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\notes.
Text: Metamorfo有一个命令，可以删除它使用的注册表键，\Software\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\notes

en_text: Metamorfo has a command to launch a keylogger on the victim’s machine.
Text: Metamorfo有一个命令可以在受害者的机器上启动一个键盘记录器

en_text: Metamorfo has a function to kill processes associated with defenses and can prevent certain processes from launching.
Text: Metamorfo有一个杀死与防御有关的进程的功能，可以防止某些进程的启动

en_text: Metamorfo has used VBS code on victims’ systems.
Text: Metamorfo在受害者的系统上使用了VBS代码

en_text: Metamorfo has displayed fake forms on top of banking sites to intercept credentials from victims.
Text: Metamorfo在银行网站上面显示假的表格，以拦截受害者的凭证

en_text: Metamorfo has deleted itself from the system after execution.
Text: Metamorfo在执行后已从系统中删除

en_text: Micropsia creates a new hidden directory to store all components' outputs in a dedicated sub-folder for each.
Text: Micropsia创建了一个新的隐藏目录，将所有组件的输出存储在一个专门的子文件夹中

en_text: Micropsia gathers the hostname and OS version from the victim’s machine.
Text: Micropsia从受害者的机器上收集了主机名和操作系统版本

en_text: Micropsia collects the username from the victim’s machine.
Text: Micropsia从受害者的机器上收集用户名

en_text: Micropsia creates a RAR archive based on collected files on the victim's machine.
Text: Micropsia根据收集到的受害者机器上的文件创建一个RAR档案

en_text: Micropsia has keylogging capabilities.
Text: Micropsia具有键盘记录功能

en_text: Micropsia can download and execute an executable from the C2 server.
Text: Micropsia可以从C2服务器下载并执行一个可执行文件

en_text: Micropsia can perform a recursive directory listing for all volume drives available on the victim's machine and can also fetch specific files by their paths.
Text: Micropsia可以对受害者机器上的所有卷轴驱动器进行递归目录列表，也可以通过路径获取特定文件

en_text: Micropsia can perform microphone recording.
Text: Micropsia可以进行麦克风录音

en_text: Micropsia creates a command-line shell using cmd.exe.
Text: Micropsia使用cmd.exe创建一个命令行外壳

en_text: Micropsia uses HTTP and HTTPS for C2 network communications.
Text: Micropsia使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2网络通信

en_text: Micropsia searches for anti-virus software and firewall products installed on the victim’s machine using WMI.
Text: Micropsia使用WMI搜索受害者机器上安装的防病毒软件和防火墙产品

en_text: Micropsia takes screenshots every 90 seconds by calling the Gdi32.BitBlt API.
Text: Micropsia通过调用Gdi32.BitBlt API每90秒进行一次截图

en_text: Micropsia obfuscates the configuration with a custom Base64 and XOR.
Text: Micropsia用自定义的Base64和XOR来混淆配置

Text: Mis-Type首先尝试在原始TCP套接字上使用Base64编码的网络协议进行C2，如果该方法失败，则退回到一个基于HTTP的二级协议，与另一个C2服务器进行通信

en_text: Mosquito executes cmd.exe and uses a pipe to read the results and send back the output to the C2 server.

en_text: MuddyWater has controlled POWERSTATS from behind a proxy network to obfuscate the C2 location. MuddyWater has used a series of compromised websites that victims connected to randomly to relay information to command and control (C2).
Text: MuddyWater从代理网络后面控制POWERSTATS，以混淆MuddyWater从代理网络后面控制POWERSTATS，以混淆C2的位置。MuddyWater利用受害者随机连接到的一系列被破坏的网站，将信息传递给指挥和控制（C2）。

en_text: MuddyWater has stored obfuscated JavaScript code in an image file named temp.jpg.
Text: MuddyWater将混淆的JavaScript代码存储在一个名为temp.jpg的图像文件中

en_text: MuddyWater has performed credential dumping with LaZagne and other tools, including by dumping passwords saved in victim email.
Text: MuddyWater利用LaZagne和其他工具进行了凭证倾销，包括倾销保存在受害者电子邮件中的密码

en_text: MuddyWater has used CMSTP.exe and a malicious INF to execute its POWERSTATS payload.
Text: MuddyWater使用CMSTP.exe和一个恶意的INF来执行其POWERSTATS有效载荷

en_text: MuddyWater has used mshta.exe to execute its POWERSTATS payload and to pass a PowerShell one-liner for execution.
Text: MuddyWater使用mshta.exe来执行其POWERSTATS有效载荷，并传递一个PowerShell单行程序供执行

en_text: MuddyWater has used VBScript files to execute its POWERSTATS payload, as well as macros.
Text: MuddyWater使用VBScript文件来执行其POWERSTATS有效载荷，以及宏

en_text: MuddyWater decoded base64-encoded PowerShell commands using a VBS file.
Text: MuddyWater使用VBS文件解码了base64编码的PowerShell命令

en_text: MuddyWater has used malware that has the capability to execute malicious code via COM, DCOM, and Outlook.
Text: MuddyWater使用的恶意软件有能力通过COM、DCOM和Outlook执行恶意代码

en_text: MuddyWater has used Daniel Bohannon’s Invoke-Obfuscation framework. The group has also used other obfuscation methods, including Base64 obfuscation of VBScripts and PowerShell commands.

en_text: MuddyWater has used malware that leveraged rundll32.exe in a Registry Run key to execute a .dll.
Text: MuddyWater使用了恶意软件，利用注册表运行键中的rundll32.exe来执行一个.dll

en_text: MuddyWater has used malware that can execute PowerShell scripts via DDE.

en_text: MuddyWater has used malware that leveraged WMI for execution and querying host information.
Text: MuddyWater使用了利用WMI来执行和查询主机信息的恶意软件

en_text: MuddyWater has used a custom tool for creating reverse shells. MuddyWater has used JavaScript files to execute its POWERSTATS payload.
Text: MuddyWater使用了一个自定义工具来创建反向外壳

en_text: MuddyWater has used filenames and Registry key names associated with Windows Defender.
Text: MuddyWater使用了与Windows Defender有关的文件名和注册表键名

en_text: MuddyWater has added Registry Run key KCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\SystemTextEncoding to establish persistence.
Text: MuddyWater添加了注册表运行键KCU\Software\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Run\SystemTextEncoding来建立持久性

en_text: The "SCOUT" variant of NETEAGLE achieves persistence by adding itself to the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run Registry key.
Text: NETEAGLE的 "SCOUT "变体通过将自己添加到HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Run注册表键中而实现持久性

en_text: NETEAGLE will attempt to detect if the infected host is configured to a proxy. If so, NETEAGLE will send beacons via an HTTP POST request; otherwise it will send beacons via UDP/6000.
Text: NETEAGLE将尝试检测被感染的主机是否被配置为代理。如果是，NETEAGLE将通过HTTP POST请求发送信标；否则，它将通过UDP/6000发送信标。

en_text: NETEAGLE will attempt to detect if the infected host is configured to a proxy. If so, NETEAGLE will send beacons via an HTTP POST request. NETEAGLE will also use HTTP to download resources that contain an IP address and Port Number pair to connect to for further C2.
Text: NETEAGLE将尝试检测被感染的主机是否被配置为代理。如果是这样，NETEAGLE将通过一个HTTP POST请求发送信标。NETEAGLE还将使用HTTP下载包含IP地址和端口号对的资源，以便进一步连接到C2。

en_text: NETEAGLE will decrypt resources it downloads with HTTP requests by using RC4 with the key "ScoutEagle."
Text: NETEAGLE将通过使用RC4与密钥 "ScoutEagle "来解密它用HTTP请求下载的资源

en_text: NETEAGLE can use HTTP to download resources that contain an IP address and port number pair to connect to for C2.

en_text: NETEAGLE can send process listings over the C2 channel.

Text: NETEAGLE能够通过C2通道读取文件

Text: NETEAGLE允许对手在被感染的主机上执行shell命令

en_text: NETEAGLE allows adversaries to enumerate and modify the infected host's file system. It supports searching for directories, creating directories, listing directory contents, reading and writing to files, retrieving file attributes, and retrieving volume information.
Text: NETEAGLE允许攻击者列举和修改被感染主机的文件系统。它支持搜索目录、创建目录、列出目录内容、读写文件、检索文件属性和检索卷信息。

en_text: njRAT has executed PowerShell commands via auto-run registry key persistence.

en_text: njRAT enumerates the victim operating system and computer name during the initial infection.

en_text: NOKKI has used rundll32 for execution.

en_text: NotPetya contains a modified version of Mimikatz to help gather credentials that are later used for lateral movement.
Text: NotPetya包含一个修改过的Mimikatz版本，以帮助收集凭证，随后用于横向移动

en_text: NotPetya creates a task to reboot the system one hour after infection.
Text: NotPetya创建了一个任务，在感染后一小时重新启动系统

en_text: NotPetya will reboot the system one hour after infection.
Text: NotPetya会在感染后一小时内重新启动系统

en_text: NotPetya can use two exploits in SMBv1, EternalBlue and EternalRomance, to spread itself to other remote systems on the network.
Text: NotPetya可以利用SMBv1中的两个漏洞，即EternalBlue和EternalRomance，将自己传播到网络上的其他远程系统

en_text: NotPetya can use PsExec, which interacts with the ADMIN$ network share to execute commands on remote systems.
Text: NotPetya可以使用PsExec，它与ADMIN$网络共享互动，在远程系统上执行命令

en_text: NotPetya can use valid credentials with PsExec or wmic to spread itself to remote systems.
Text: NotPetya可以使用PsExec或wmic的有效凭证将自己传播到远程系统

en_text: NotPetya can use PsExec to help propagate itself across a network.
Text: NotPetya可以使用PsExec来帮助自己在网络中传播

en_text: NotPetya can use wmic to help propagate itself across a network.
Text: NotPetya可以使用wmic来帮助自己在网络上传播

en_text: NotPetya uses wevtutil to clear the Windows event logs.
Text: NotPetya使用wevtutil来清除Windows事件日志

en_text: NotPetya drops PsExec with the filename dllhost.dat.
Text: NotPetya以文件名dllhost.dat丢弃了PsExec

en_text: NotPetya encrypts user files and disk structures like the MBR with 2048-bit RSA.
Text: NotPetya用2048位RSA对用户文件和MBR等磁盘结构进行加密

en_text: Impacket modules like ntlmrelayx and smbrelayx can be used in conjunction with Network Sniffing and LLMNR/NBT-NS Poisoning and SMB Relay to gather NetNTLM credentials for Brute Force or relay attacks that can gain code execution.
Text: ntlmrelayx和smbrelayx等Impacket模块可与网络嗅探和LLMNR/NBT-NS中毒以及SMB中继结合使用，以收集NetNTLM凭证，进行暴力攻击或中继攻击，从而获得代码执行。

en_text: OceanSalt can extract drive information from the endpoint and search files on the system.
Text: OceanSalt可以从端点提取驱动器信息，并搜索系统中的文件

Text: OceanSalt可以从系统中删除文件

en_text: OceanSalt can collect the computer name from the system.
Text: OceanSalt可以从系统中收集计算机名称

en_text: OilRig has used Remote Desktop Protocol for lateral movement. The group has also used tunneling tools to tunnel RDP into the environment.

Text: OilRig在一个受害者身上使用sc查询来收集有关服务的信息

Text: OilRig在一个有net账户的脚本中使用了net.exe

Text: OilRig在执行后删除了与他们的有效载荷相关的文件

en_text: Okrum's installer can attempt to achieve persistence by creating a scheduled task.
Text: Okrum的安装程序可以尝试通过创建一个计划任务来实现持久性

en_text: Okrum's backdoor has used cmd.exe to execute arbitrary commands as well as batch scripts to update itself to a newer version.
Text: Okrum的后门使用cmd.exe执行任意命令以及批处理脚本，将自己更新到一个较新的版本

en_text: Okrum's backdoor deletes files after they have been successfully uploaded to C2 servers.
Text: Okrum的后门在文件被成功上传到C2服务器后，会删除这些文件

en_text: Okrum's loader can create a new service named NtmsSvc to execute the payload.
Text: Okrum的加载器可以创建一个名为NtmsSvc的新服务来执行有效载荷

en_text: Okrum's loader can check the amount of physical memory and terminates itself if the host has less than 1.5 Gigabytes of physical memory in total.
Text: Okrum的加载器可以检查物理内存的数量，如果主机的物理内存总量少于1.5G，就会自行终止

en_text: Okrum's loader can decrypt the backdoor code, embedded within the loader or within a legitimate PNG file. A custom XOR cipher or RC4 is used for decryption.
Text: Okrum的加载器可以解密后门代码，嵌入加载器内或合法的PNG文件内

en_text: Okrum's loader can detect presence of an emulator by using two calls to GetTickCount API, and checking whether the time has been accelerated.
Text: Okrum的加载器可以通过两次调用GetTickCount API来检测仿真器的存在，并检查时间是否被加速了

Text: Okrum的有效载荷被加密并嵌入其加载器中，或嵌入一个合法的PNG文件中

en_text: Okrum loader only executes the payload after the left mouse button has been pressed at least three times, in order to avoid being executed within virtualized or emulated environments.
Text: Okrum加载器只在鼠标左键被按下至少三次后才执行有效载荷，以避免在虚拟化或仿真环境中被执行

en_text: Okrum can obtain the date and time of the compromised system.

en_text: Okrum can identify proxy servers configured and used by the victim, and use it to make HTTP requests to C2 its server.

en_text: Okrum can collect computer name, locale information, and information about the OS and architecture.
Text: Okrum可以收集计算机名称、地域信息以及关于操作系统和架构的信息

en_text: Okrum can collect the victim username.
Text: Okrum可以收集受害者的用户名

en_text: Okrum can collect network information, including the host IP address, DNS, and proxy information.

en_text: Okrum can impersonate a logged-on user's security context using a call to the ImpersonateLoggedOnUser API.
Text: Okrum可以通过调用ImpersonateLoggedOnUser API来冒充登录用户的安全环境

en_text: Okrum can establish persistence by adding a new service NtmsSvc with the display name Removable Storage to masquerade as a legitimate Removable Storage Manager.

en_text: Okrum uses AES to encrypt network traffic. The key can be hardcoded or negotiated with the C2 server in the registration phase.

en_text: Okrum has used base64 to encode C2 communication.
Text: Okrum使用base64对C2通信进行了编码

en_text: Okrum has used DriveLetterView to enumerate drive information.
Text: Okrum使用DriveLetterView来列举驱动器信息

en_text: Okrum uses HTTP for communication with its C2.
Text: Okrum使用HTTP与它的C2进行通信

en_text: Okrum has used a custom implementation of AES encryption to encrypt collected data.
Text: Okrum使用了一个自定义的AES加密实现来加密收集的数据

en_text: Okrum establishes persistence by creating a .lnk shortcut to itself in the Startup folder.
Text: Okrum通过在启动文件夹中为自己创建一个.lnk快捷方式来建立持久性

en_text: Okrum has built-in commands for uploading, downloading, and executing files to the system.
Text: Okrum有内置的命令，用于向系统上传、下载和执行文件

en_text: OLDBAIT collects credentials from Internet Explorer, Mozilla Firefox, and Eudora.
Text: OLDBAIT从Internet Explorer、Mozilla Firefox和Eudora收集凭证

en_text: OLDBAIT collects credentials from several email clients.
Text: OLDBAIT从几个电子邮件客户端收集凭证

en_text: OLDBAIT obfuscates internal strings and unpacks them at startup.
Text: OLDBAIT混淆了内部字符串，并在启动时解压

en_text: OLDBAIT installs itself in %ALLUSERPROFILE%\Application Data\Microsoft\MediaPlayer\updatewindws.exe; the directory name is missing a space and the file name is missing the letter "o."
Text: OLDBAIT将自己安装在%ALLUSERPROFILE%\Application Data\Microsoft\MediaPlayer\updatewindws.exe中；目录名缺少一个空格，文件名缺少字母 "o"
