en_text: OLDBAIT can use SMTP for C2.
Text: OLDBAIT可以使用SMTP进行C2

en_text: Olympic Destroyer contains a module that tries to obtain credentials from LSASS, similar to Mimikatz. These credentials are used with PsExec and Windows Management Instrumentation to help the malware propagate itself across a network.
Text: Olympic Destroyer包含一个模块，试图从LSASS获得凭证，与Mimikatz类似。这些凭证与PsExec和Windows Management Instrumentation一起使用，以帮助恶意软件在网络上传播自己。

en_text: Olympic Destroyer contains a module that tries to obtain stored credentials from web browsers.
Text: Olympic Destroyer包含一个模块，试图从网络浏览器中获取存储的凭证

en_text: Olympic Destroyer overwrites files locally and on remote shares.
Text: Olympic Destroyer会覆盖本地和远程共享上的文件

en_text: Olympic Destroyer will attempt to enumerate mapped network shares to later attempt to wipe all files on those shares.
Text: Olympic Destroyer将尝试列举映射的网络共享，以便以后尝试擦除这些共享上的所有文件

en_text: Olympic Destroyer will attempt to clear the System and Security event logs using wevtutil.
Text: Olympic Destroyer将尝试使用wevtutil清除系统和安全事件日志

en_text: Olympic Destroyer utilizes PsExec to help propagate itself across a network.
Text: Olympic Destroyer利用PsExec来帮助自己在网络上传播

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses the API call ChangeServiceConfigW to disable all services on the affected system.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用API调用ChangeServiceConfigW来停用受影响系统上的所有服务

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses API calls to enumerate the infected system's ARP table.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用API调用来列举被感染系统的ARP表

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses PsExec to interact with the ADMIN$ network share to execute commands on remote systems.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用PsExec与ADMIN$网络共享互动，在远程系统上执行命令

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses Windows Management Instrumentation to enumerate all systems in the network.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用Windows Management Instrumentation来列举网络中的所有系统

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses WMI to help propagate itself across a network.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用WMI来帮助自己在网络上传播

en_text: Olympic Destroyer uses the native Windows utilities vssadmin, wbadmin, and bcdedit to delete and disable operating system recovery features such as the Windows backup catalog and Windows Automatic Repair.
Text: Olympic Destroyer使用本地Windows工具vssadmin、wbadmin和bcdedit来删除和禁用操作系统恢复功能，如Windows备份目录和Windows自动修复

en_text: Olympic Destroyer attempts to copy itself to remote machines on the network.
Text: Olympic Destroyer试图将自己复制到网络上的远程机器

en_text: Olympic Destroyer will shut down the compromised system after it is done modifying system configuration settings.
Text: Olympic Destroyer在完成对系统配置设置的修改后，将关闭被破坏的系统

en_text: OnionDuke steals credentials from its victims.
Text: OnionDuke从其受害者那里窃取证书

en_text: OnionDuke can use a custom decryption algorithm to decrypt strings.
Text: OnionDuke可以使用一个自定义的解密算法来解密字符串

en_text: OnionDuke uses HTTP and HTTPS for C2.
Text: OnionDuke使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2

en_text: OnionDuke uses Twitter as a backup C2.
Text: OnionDuke使用Twitter作为备份C2

en_text: OnionDuke has the capability to use a Denial of Service module.
Text: OnionDuke有能力使用拒绝服务模块

en_text: OopsIE creates and uses a VBScript as part of its persistent execution.
Text: OopsIE创建并使用一个VBScript作为其持续执行的一部分

en_text: OopsIE creates a scheduled task to run itself every three minutes.
Text: OopsIE创建了一个计划任务，每三分钟自己运行一次

en_text: OopsIE performs several anti-VM and sandbox checks on the victim's machine. One technique the group has used was to perform a WMI query SELECT * FROM MSAcpi_ThermalZoneTemperature to check the temperature to see if it’s running in a virtual environment.
Text: OopsIE对受害者的机器进行了几次反虚拟和沙盒检查。该组织使用的一项技术是执行WMI查询SELECT * FROM MSAcpi_ThermalZoneTemperature，以检查温度，看它是否在虚拟环境中运行。

en_text: OopsIE checks for information on the CPU fan, temperature, mouse, hard disk, and motherboard as part of its anti-VM checks.
Text: OopsIE检查CPU风扇、温度、鼠标、硬盘和主板的信息，作为其反病毒检查的一部分

en_text: OopsIE checks to see if the system is configured with "Daylight" time and checks for a specific region to be set for the timezone.
Text: OopsIE检查系统是否被配置为 "日光 "时间，并检查是否有一个特定的地区被设置为时区

en_text: OopsIE exfiltrates command output and collected files to its C2 server in 1500-byte blocks.
Text: OopsIE将命令输出和收集的文件以1500字节的块形式外流到其C2服务器

en_text: OopsIE can download files from its C2 server to the victim's machine.
Text: OopsIE可以从其C2服务器下载文件到受害者的机器上

en_text: OopsIE can upload files from the victim's machine to its C2 server.
Text: OopsIE可以将文件从受害者的机器上传到其C2服务器

en_text: OopsIE concatenates then decompresses multiple resources to load an embedded .Net Framework assembly.
Text: OopsIE连接然后解压多个资源以加载一个嵌入式.Net框架程序集

en_text: OopsIE uses the Confuser protector to obfuscate an embedded .Net Framework assembly used for C2. OopsIE also encodes collected data in hexadecimal format before writing to files on disk and obfuscates strings.
Text: OopsIE使用Confuser保护器来混淆用于C2的嵌入式.Net框架汇编。OopsIE还在向磁盘上的文件写入前将收集的数据编码为十六进制格式，并对字符串进行混淆。

en_text: OopsIE uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: OopsIE使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: OopsIE uses the SmartAssembly obfuscator to pack an embedded .Net Framework assembly used for C2.
Text: OopsIE使用SmartAssembly混淆器来打包一个用于C2的嵌入式.Net框架程序集

en_text: OopsIE uses WMI to perform discovery techniques.
Text: OopsIE使用WMI来执行发现技术

en_text: OopsIE uses the command prompt to execute commands on the victim's machine.
Text: OopsIE使用命令提示符在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: OopsIE encodes data in hexadecimal format over the C2 channel.
Text: OopsIE通过C2通道以十六进制格式编码数据

en_text: OopsIE has the capability to delete files and scripts from the victim's machine.
Text: OopsIE有能力从受害者的机器上删除文件和脚本

en_text: OopsIE compresses collected files with GZipStream before sending them to its C2 server.
Text: OopsIE在将收集到的文件发送到其C2服务器之前用GZipStream进行压缩

en_text: OopsIE compresses collected files with a simple character replacement scheme before sending them to its C2 server.
Text: OopsIE在将收集的文件发送到其C2服务器之前，用一个简单的字符替换方案进行压缩

en_text: OopsIE stages the output from command execution and collected files in specific folders before exfiltration.
Text: OopsIE在渗出前将命令执行的输出和收集的文件放在特定的文件夹中

en_text: Orangeworm has copied its backdoor across open network shares, including ADMIN$, C$WINDOWS, D$WINDOWS, and E$WINDOWS.
Text: Orangeworm在开放的网络共享中复制了其后门，包括ADMIN$、C$WINDOWS、D$WINDOWS和E$WINDOWS

en_text: Orz can gather a process list from the victim.
Text: Orz可以从受害者那里收集一个进程列表

en_text: Orz can overwrite Registry settings to reduce its visibility on the victim.
Text: Orz可以覆盖注册表设置，以减少其在受害者身上的可见性

en_text: Orz can download files onto the victim.
Text: Orz可以将文件下载到受害者身上

en_text: Orz can gather the victim's Internet Explorer version.
Text: Orz可以收集受害者的Internet Explorer版本

en_text: Orz can gather the victim OS version and whether it is 64 or 32 bit.
Text: Orz可以收集受害者的操作系统版本以及它是64位还是32位

en_text: Orz can gather victim proxy information.
Text: Orz可以收集受害者的代理信息

en_text: Orz can gather victim drive information.
Text: Orz可以收集受害者的驾驶信息

en_text: Orz can execute shell commands. Orz can execute commands with JavaScript.
Text: Orz可以执行shell命令

en_text: OSInfo queries the registry to look for information about Terminal Services.
Text: OSInfo查询注册表，寻找有关终端服务的信息

en_text: OSInfo discovers the current domain information.
Text: OSInfo发现了当前的域名信息

en_text: OSInfo discovers information about the infected machine.
Text: OSInfo发现了关于被感染机器的信息

en_text: OSInfo discovers shares on the network
Text: OSInfo发现了网络上的股份 OSInfo发现了网络上的股票 OSInfo发现网络上的股份 OSInfo发现了网络上的共享信息

en_text: OSInfo performs a connection test to discover remote systems in the network
Text: OSInfo进行连接测试以发现网络中的远程系统

en_text: OSInfo enumerates local and domain users
Text: OSInfo列举了本地和域的用户 OSInfo列举了本地和域用户 OSInfo列举了本地和域内的用户 OSInfo列举了本地和域的用户

en_text: OSInfo enumerates the current network connections similar to  net use .
Text: OSInfo列举了当前的网络连接，类似于net use

en_text: OSInfo has enumerated the local administrators group.
Text: OSInfo已经列举了本地管理员组

en_text: OSInfo specifically looks for Domain Admins and power users within the domain.
Text: OSInfo专门寻找域内的域管理员和权力用户

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D sets the main loader file’s attributes to hidden.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D将主加载器文件的属性设置为隐藏

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D can create a persistence file in the folder /Library/LaunchAgents.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D可以在/Library/LaunchAgents文件夹中创建一个持久性文件。

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D can create a persistence file in the folder /Library/LaunchDaemons.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D可以在/Library/LaunchDaemons文件夹中创建一个持久性文件。

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D uses PowerShell scripts.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D使用PowerShell脚本

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D uses Word macros for execution.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D使用Word宏来执行

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D collects the MAC address, computer name, hardware UUID, serial number, and operating system version.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D收集了MAC地址、计算机名称、硬件UUID、序列号和操作系统版本

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D encrypts its strings in RSA256 and encodes them in a custom base64 scheme and XOR.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D以RSA256加密其字符串，并以自定义的base64方案和XOR对其进行编码

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D has a variant that is packed with UPX.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D有一个变体，里面装有UPX

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D has a variant that checks a number of system parameters to see if it is being run on real hardware or in a virtual machine environment.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D有一个变体，它检查一些系统参数，以确定它是在真实的硬件上还是在虚拟机环境中运行

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D has a command to download and execute a file on the victim’s machine.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D有一个命令，可以在受害者的机器上下载和执行一个文件

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D has a command to delete a file from the system.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D有一条从系统中删除一个文件的命令

en_text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D scrambles and encrypts data using AES256 before sending it to the C2 server.
Text: OSX_OCEANLOTUS.D在向C2服务器发送数据之前，使用AES256对数据进行加扰和加密

en_text: OwaAuth uses incoming HTTP requests with a username keyword and commands and handles them as instructions to perform actions.
Text: OwaAuth使用传入的带有用户名关键字和命令的HTTP请求，并将其作为执行行动的指令来处理

en_text: OwaAuth DES-encrypts captured credentials using the key 12345678 before writing the credentials to a log file.
Text: OwaAuth使用密钥12345678对捕获的凭证进行DES加密，然后将凭证写入日志文件

en_text: OwaAuth uses the filename owaauth.dll, which is a legitimate file that normally resides in %ProgramFiles%\Microsoft\Exchange Server\ClientAccess\Owa\Auth\; the malicious file by the same name is saved in %ProgramFiles%\Microsoft\Exchange Server\ClientAccess\Owa\bin\.
Text: OwaAuth使用文件名owaauth.dll，这是一个合法的文件，通常位于%ProgramFiles%\Microsoft\Exchange Server\ClientAccess\Owa\Auth\；同名的恶意文件则保存在%ProgramFiles%\Microsoft\Exchange Server\ClientAccess\Owa\bin\

en_text: OwaAuth is a Web shell that appears to be exclusively used by Threat Group-3390. It is installed as an ISAPI filter on Exchange servers and shares characteristics with the China Chopper Web shell.
Text: OwaAuth是一个网络外壳，似乎是由威胁集团-3390专门使用的。它作为ISAPI过滤器安装在Exchange服务器上，并与China Chopper Web shell具有相同的特征。

en_text: OwaAuth has been loaded onto Exchange servers and disguised as an ISAPI filter (DLL file). The IIS w3wp.exe process then loads the malicious DLL.
Text: OwaAuth已经被加载到Exchange服务器，并伪装成一个ISAPI过滤器（DLL文件）。IIS的w3wp.exe进程然后加载恶意的DLL文件。

en_text: OwaAuth has a command to list its directory and logical drives.
Text: OwaAuth有一个命令可以列出其目录和逻辑驱动器

en_text: OwaAuth has a command to timestop a file or directory.
Text: OwaAuth有一条命令可以对文件或目录进行时间停止

en_text: OwaAuth captures and DES-encrypts credentials before writing the username and password to a log file, C:\log.txt.
Text: OwaAuth在将用户名和密码写入日志文件C:\log.txt之前，会捕捉和DES加密凭证

en_text: P2P ZeuS added junk data to outgoing UDP packets to peer implants.
Text: P2P ZeuS将垃圾数据添加到传出的UDP数据包中，以对等植入

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve information such as hostname and free disk space.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过该后门检索主机名和可用磁盘空间等信息

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve files.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它检索文件

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve lists of files.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它检索文件列表

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can retrieve lists of running processes.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它检索正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can delete files.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它删除文件

en_text: Pasam creates a backdoor through which remote attackers can upload files.
Text: Pasam创建了一个后门，远程攻击者可以通过它上传文件

en_text: Pasam establishes by infecting the Security Accounts Manager (SAM) DLL to load a malicious DLL dropped to disk.
Text: Pasam通过感染安全账户管理器（SAM）DLL来建立，将一个恶意的DLL下载到磁盘

en_text: Pass-The-Hash Toolkit can perform pass the hash.
Text: Pass-The-Hash Toolkit可以执行pass the hash

en_text: Patchwork dumped the login data database from \AppData\Local\Google\Chrome\User Data\Default\Login Data.
Text: Patchwork从AppData\Local\Google\Chrome\User Data\Default\Login Data转储了登录数据数据库

en_text: Patchwork collected and exfiltrated files from the infected system.
Text: Patchwork从受感染的系统中收集和渗出文件

en_text: Patchwork has used spearphishing with links to deliver files with exploits to initial victims. The group has also used embedded image tags (known as web bugs) with unique, per-recipient tracking links in their emails for the purpose of identifying which recipients opened messages.
Text: Patchwork公司利用带有链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼，向最初的受害者提供带有漏洞的文件。该组织还在他们的电子邮件中使用嵌入的图像标签（称为网络虫子），并带有独特的、针对每个收件人的跟踪链接，目的是识别哪些收件人打开了邮件。

en_text: Patchwork has added the path of its second-stage malware to the startup folder to achieve persistence. One of its file stealers has also persisted by adding a Registry Run key.
Text: Patchwork将其第二阶段的恶意软件的路径添加到启动文件夹，以实现持久性

en_text: Patchwork installed its payload in the startup programs folder as "Baidu Software Update." The group also adds its second stage payload to the startup programs as "Net Monitor." They have also dropped QuasarRAT binaries as files named microsoft_network.exe and crome.exe.
Text: Patchwork将其有效载荷作为 "百度软件更新 "安装在启动程序文件夹中。该组织还将其第二阶段的有效载荷作为 "Net Monitor "添加到启动程序中。他们还将QuasarRAT二进制文件作为名为microsoft_network.exe和crome.exe的文件投放。

en_text: Patchwork copied all targeted files to a directory called index that was eventually uploaded to the C&C server.
Text: Patchwork将所有目标文件复制到一个名为index的目录中，最终被上传到C

en_text: Patchwork developed a file stealer to search C:\ and collect files with certain extensions. Patchwork also executed a script to enumerate all drives, store them as a list, and upload generated files to the C2 server.
Text: Patchwork开发了一个文件窃取器来搜索C:\并收集具有某些扩展名的文件。Patchwork还执行了一个脚本来列举所有的驱动器，将它们存储为一个列表，并将生成的文件上传到C2服务器。

en_text: Patchwork has used BITS jobs to download malicious payloads.
Text: Patchwork利用BITS作业来下载恶意的有效载荷

en_text: Patchwork leveraged the DDE protocol to deliver their malware.
Text: Patchwork利用DDE协议来提供他们的恶意软件

en_text: Patchwork has used watering holes to deliver files with exploits to initial victims.
Text: Patchwork利用浇水孔向最初的受害者传递带有漏洞的文件

en_text: Patchwork bypassed User Access Control (UAC).
Text: Patchwork绕过了用户访问控制（UAC）

en_text: Patchwork scanned the "Program Files" directories for a directory with the string "Total Security" (the installation path of the "360 Total Security" antivirus tool).
Text: Patchwork扫描了 "Program Files "目录中带有 "Total Security "字符串的目录（"360 Total Security "杀毒工具的安装路径）。

en_text: Patchwork removed certain files and replaced them so they could not be retrieved.
Text: Patchwork删除了某些文件并替换了它们，因此它们无法被检索

en_text: Patchwork used Base64 to encode C2 traffic.
Text: Patchwork使用Base64对C2流量进行编码

en_text: Patchwork ran a reverse shell with Meterpreter. Patchwork used JavaScript code and .SCT files on victim machines.
Text: Patchwork使用Meterpreter运行一个反向外壳。Patchwork使用受害者机器上的JavaScript代码和.SCT文件。

en_text: Patchwork used PowerSploit to download payloads, run a reverse shell, and execute malware on the victim's machine.
Text: Patchwork使用PowerSploit下载有效载荷，运行反向外壳，并在受害者的机器上执行恶意软件

en_text: Patchwork uses malicious documents to deliver remote execution exploits as part of. The group has previously exploited CVE-2017-8570, CVE-2012-1856, CVE-2014-4114, CVE-2017-0199, CVE-2017-11882, and CVE-2015-1641.
Text: Patchwork使用恶意文件来传递远程执行漏洞，作为其中的一部分。该组织此前曾利用CVE-2017-8570、CVE-2012-1856、CVE-2014-4114、CVE-2017-0199、CVE-2017-11882和CVE-2015-1641。

en_text: Patchwork has used spearphishing with an attachment to deliver files with exploits to initial victims.
Text: Patchwork使用了带有附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼，向最初的受害者传递带有漏洞的文件

en_text: Patchwork has used spearphishing with links to try to get users to click, download and open malicious files.
Text: Patchwork使用了带有链接的鱼叉式钓鱼，试图让用户点击、下载和打开恶意文件

en_text: Patchwork attempted to use RDP to move laterally.
Text: Patchwork试图使用RDP来进行横向移动

en_text: Patchwork collected the victim computer name, OS version, and architecture type and sent the information to its C2 server. Patchwork also enumerated all available drives on the victim's machine.
Text: Patchwork收集了受害者的计算机名称、操作系统版本和架构类型，并将这些信息发送到其C2服务器。Patchwork还列举了受害者机器上的所有可用驱动器。

en_text: Patchwork collected the victim username and whether it was running as admin, then sent the information to its C2 server.
Text: Patchwork收集了受害者的用户名以及是否以管理员身份运行，然后将这些信息发送到其C2服务器

en_text: A Patchwork file stealer can run a TaskScheduler DLL to add persistence.
Text: Patchwork文件窃取者可以运行一个TaskScheduler DLL来增加持久性

en_text: Patchwork apparently altered NDiskMonitor samples by adding four bytes of random letters in a likely attempt to change the file hashes.
Text: Patchwork显然改变了NDiskMonitor的样本，增加了四个字节的随机字母，可能是试图改变文件的哈希值

en_text: Patchwork encrypted the collected files' path with AES and then encoded them with base64.
Text: Patchwork用AES对收集到的文件的路径进行加密，然后用base64编码

en_text: Patchwork has obfuscated a script with Crypto Obfuscator.
Text: Patchwork用Crypto Obfuscator混淆了一个脚本

en_text: Patchwork has signed malware with self-signed certificates from fictitious and spoofed legitimate software companies.
Text: Patchwork用虚构和欺骗的合法软件公司的自签名证书签署了恶意软件

en_text: Patchwork embedded a malicious macro in a Word document and lured the victim to click on an icon to execute the malware.
Text: Patchwork在Word文档中嵌入了一个恶意宏，并诱使受害者点击一个图标来执行该恶意软件

en_text: Patchwork hides base64-encoded and encrypted C2 server locations in comments on legitimate websites.
Text: Patchwork在合法网站的评论中隐藏了base64编码和加密的C2服务器位置

en_text: Patchwork used Visual Basic Scripts (VBS) on victim machines.
Text: Patchwork在受害者机器上使用Visual Basic Scripts（VBS）

en_text: PHOREAL is capable of manipulating the Registry.
Text: PHOREAL能够操纵注册表

en_text: PHOREAL is capable of creating reverse shell.
Text: PHOREAL能够创建反向外壳

en_text: PHOREAL communicates via ICMP for C2.
Text: PHOREAL通过ICMP进行C2通信

en_text: Pillowmint has stored its malicious payload in the registry key HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\DRM.
Text: Pillowmint将其恶意的有效载荷存储在注册表键HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\DRM中

en_text: Pillowmint can uninstall the malicious service from an infected machine.
Text: Pillowmint可以从受感染的机器上卸载恶意服务

en_text: Pillowmint can iterate through running processes every six seconds collecting a list of processes to capture from later.
Text: Pillowmint可以每六秒钟迭代一次正在运行的进程，收集一个进程列表，以便以后捕捉

en_text: Pillowmint has used the NtQueueApcThread syscall to inject code into svchost.exe.
Text: Pillowmint使用NtQueueApcThread系统调用，将代码注入svchost.exe

en_text: Pillowmint has used shellcode which reads code stored in the registry keys \REGISTRY\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\DRM using the native Windows API as well as read HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\Tcpip\Parameters\Interfaces as part of its C2.
Text: Pillowmint使用的shellcode读取了存储在注册表键\REGISTRY\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\DRM中的代码，使用了本地Windows API以及读取HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\Tcpip\Parameters\Interfaces作为其C2的一部分

en_text: Pillowmint has used multiple native Windows APIs to execute and conduct process injections.
Text: Pillowmint使用了多个本地Windows APIs来执行和进行进程注入

en_text: Pillowmint has used a PowerShell script to install a shim database.
Text: Pillowmint使用了一个PowerShell脚本来安装shim数据库

en_text: Pillowmint has used a malicious shim database to maintain persistence.
Text: Pillowmint使用了一个恶意的shim数据库来维持持久性

en_text: Pillowmint has been compressed and stored within a registry key. Pillowmint has also obfuscated the AES key used for encryption.
Text: Pillowmint已经被压缩并存储在一个注册表密钥中

en_text: Pillowmint has deleted the filepath %APPDATA%\Intel\devmonsrv.exe.
Text: Pillowmint已经删除了文件路径%APPDATA%\Intel\devmonsrv.exe

en_text: Pillowmint has collected credit card data using native API functions.
Text: Pillowmint已经使用本地API功能收集了信用卡数据

en_text: Pillowmint has encrypted stolen credit card information with AES and further encoded it with Base64.
Text: Pillowmint用AES加密了被盗的信用卡信息，并进一步用Base64进行编码

en_text: Pillowmint has been decompressed by included shellcode prior to being launched.
Text: Pillowmint在启动前已经被包含的shellcode解压

en_text: PinchDuke steals credentials from compromised hosts. PinchDuke's credential stealing functionality is believed to be based on the source code of the Pinch credential stealing malware (also known as LdPinch). Credentials targeted by PinchDuke include ones associated with many sources such as Netscape Navigator, Mozilla Firefox, Mozilla Thunderbird, and Internet Explorer.
Text: PinchDuke从被攻击的主机中窃取凭证。PinchDuke的凭证窃取功能被认为是基于Pinch凭证窃取恶意软件（也被称为LdPinch）的源代码。PinchDuke的目标凭证包括与Netscape Navigator、Mozilla Firefox、Mozilla Thunderbird和Internet Explorer等许多来源相关的凭证。

en_text: PinchDuke steals credentials from compromised hosts. PinchDuke's credential stealing functionality is believed to be based on the source code of the Pinch credential stealing malware (also known as LdPinch). Credentials targeted by PinchDuke include ones associated many sources such as WinInet Credential Cache, and Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP).
Text: PinchDuke从被攻击的主机中窃取凭证。PinchDuke的凭证窃取功能被认为是基于Pinch凭证窃取恶意软件（也被称为LdPinch）的源代码。PinchDuke的目标凭证包括与WinInet凭证缓存和轻量级目录访问协议（LDAP）等许多来源有关的凭证。

en_text: PinchDuke steals credentials from compromised hosts. PinchDuke's credential stealing functionality is believed to be based on the source code of the Pinch credential stealing malware (also known as LdPinch). Credentials targeted by PinchDuke include ones associated with many sources such as The Bat!, Yahoo!, Mail.ru, Passport.Net, Google Talk, and Microsoft Outlook.
Text: PinchDuke从被攻击的主机中窃取凭证。PinchDuke的凭证窃取功能被认为是基于Pinch凭证窃取恶意软件（也被称为LdPinch）的源代码。PinchDuke的目标凭证包括与许多来源有关的凭证，如The Bat！、Yahoo！、Mail.ru、Passport.Net、Google Talk和Microsoft Outlook。

en_text: PinchDuke collects user files from the compromised host based on predefined file extensions.
Text: PinchDuke根据预定义的文件扩展名从被攻击的主机收集用户文件

en_text: PinchDuke gathers system configuration information.
Text: PinchDuke会收集系统配置信息

en_text: PinchDuke searches for files created within a certain timeframe and whose file extension matches a predefined list.
Text: PinchDuke搜索在一定时间范围内创建的文件，并且其文件扩展名符合预定义的列表

en_text: PinchDuke transfers files from the compromised host via HTTP or HTTPS to a C2 server.
Text: PinchDuke通过HTTP或HTTPS将文件从被攻击的主机传输到C2服务器

en_text: Ping can be used to identify remote systems within a network.
Text: Ping可以用来识别网络中的远程系统

en_text: PipeMon, its installer, and tools are signed with stolen code-signing certificates.
Text: PipeMon、其安装程序和工具都是用偷来的代码签名证书签名的

en_text: PipeMon installer can use UAC bypass techniques to install the payload.
Text: PipeMon安装程序可以使用UAC绕过技术来安装有效载荷

en_text: The PipeMon installer has modified the Registry key HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Print\Environments\Windows x64\Print Processors to install PipeMon as a Print Processor.
Text: PipeMon安装程序修改了注册表键HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Print\Environments\Windows x64\Print Processors，将PipeMon安装为一个打印处理器

en_text: PipeMon's first stage has been executed by a call to CreateProcess with the decryption password in an argument. PipeMon has used a call to LoadLibrary to load its installer.
Text: PipeMon的第一阶段是通过调用CreateProcess来执行的，参数是解密密码

en_text: PipeMon has stored its encrypted payload in the Registry.
Text: PipeMon将其加密的有效载荷存储在注册表中

en_text: PipeMon can attempt to gain administrative privileges using token impersonation.
Text: PipeMon可以尝试使用令牌冒充来获得管理权限

en_text: PipeMon can iterate over the running processes to find a suitable injection target.
Text: PipeMon可以对正在运行的进程进行迭代，找到合适的注入目标

en_text: PipeMon can check for the presence of ESET and Kaspersky security software.
Text: PipeMon可以检查是否存在ESET和卡巴斯基安全软件

en_text: PipeMon can send time zone information from a compromised host to C2.
Text: PipeMon可以将时区信息从被攻击的主机发送到C2

en_text: PipeMon can decrypt password-protected executables.
Text: PipeMon可以解密受密码保护的可执行文件

en_text: PipeMon can use parent PID spoofing to elevate privileges.
Text: PipeMon可以利用父母的PID欺骗来提升权限

en_text: PipeMon can collect and send the local IP address, RDP information, and the network adapter physical address as a part of its C2 beacon.
Text: PipeMon可以收集并发送本地IP地址、RDP信息和网络适配器物理地址，作为其C2信标的一部分

en_text: PipeMon can collect and send OS version and computer name as a part of its C2 beacon.
Text: PipeMon可以收集并发送操作系统版本和计算机名称，作为其C2信标的一部分

en_text: PipeMon can install additional modules via C2 commands.
Text: PipeMon可以通过C2命令安装其他模块

en_text: PipeMon can inject its modules into various processes using reflective DLL loading.
Text: PipeMon可以通过反射式DLL加载将其模块注入各种进程中

en_text: PipeMon can establish persistence by registering a malicious DLL as an alternative Print Processor which is loaded when the print spooler service starts.
Text: PipeMon可以通过注册一个恶意的DLL作为替代的打印处理器来建立持久性，该处理器在打印轮转机服务启动时被加载

en_text: PipeMon modules are stored on disk with seemingly benign names including use of a file extension associated with a popular word processor.
Text: PipeMon模块被存储在磁盘上，其名称看似无害，包括使用一个与流行的文字处理器相关的文件扩展名

en_text: PipeMon modules are stored encrypted on disk.
Text: PipeMon模块是加密存储在磁盘上的

en_text: PipeMon has used call to LoadLibrary to load its installer. PipeMon loads its modules using reflective loading or custom shellcode.
Text: PipeMon使用了对LoadLibrary的调用来加载其安装程序

en_text: The PipeMon communication module can use a custom protocol based on TLS over TCP.
Text: PipeMon通信模块可以使用基于TCP的TLS的自定义协议

en_text: PipeMon communications are RC4 encrypted.
Text: PipeMon通信是RC4加密的

en_text: Pisloader uses cmd.exe to set the Registry Run key value. It also has a command to spawn a command shell.
Text: Pisloader使用cmd.exe来设置注册表的运行键值

en_text: Pisloader uses DNS as its C2 protocol.
Text: Pisloader使用DNS作为其C2协议

en_text: Pisloader obfuscates files by splitting strings into smaller sub-strings and including "garbage" strings that are never used. The malware also uses return-oriented programming (ROP) technique and single-byte XOR to obfuscate data.
Text: Pisloader通过将字符串分割成更小的子字符串并包括从未使用的 "垃圾 "字符串来混淆文件。该恶意软件还使用面向返回的编程（ROP）技术和单字节的XOR来混淆数据。

en_text: Pisloader establishes persistence via a Registry Run key.
Text: Pisloader通过注册表运行键建立了持久性

en_text: Pisloader has commands to list drives on the victim machine and to list file information for a given directory.
Text: Pisloader有列出受害者机器上的驱动器和列出特定目录的文件信息的命令

en_text: Pisloader has a command to collect the victim's IP address.
Text: Pisloader有一个命令来收集受害者的IP地址

en_text: Pisloader has a command to upload a file to the victim machine.
Text: Pisloader有一个上传文件到受害者机器的命令

en_text: Pisloader has a command to collect victim system information, including the system name and OS version.
Text: Pisloader有一个收集受害者系统信息的命令，包括系统名称和操作系统版本

en_text: PittyTiger attempts to obtain legitimate credentials during operations.
Text: PittyTiger试图在操作过程中获得合法的凭证

en_text: An older variant of PLAINTEE performs UAC bypass.
Text: PLAINTEE的一个较早的变体可以执行UAC绕过

en_text: PLAINTEE uses cmd.exe to execute commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: PLAINTEE使用cmd.exe在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: PLAINTEE uses the ipconfig /all command to gather the victim’s IP address.
Text: PLAINTEE使用ipconfig PLAINTEE使用了ipconfig PLAINTEE使用的是ipconfig

en_text: PLAINTEE uses reg add to add a Registry Run key for persistence.
Text: PLAINTEE使用reg add来添加一个注册表运行键来实现持久化

en_text: PLAINTEE encodes C2 beacons using XOR.
Text: PLAINTEE使用XOR对C2信标进行编码

en_text: PLAINTEE collects general system enumeration data about the infected machine and checks the OS version.
Text: PLAINTEE收集被感染机器的一般系统枚举数据，并检查操作系统版本

en_text: PLAINTEE gains persistence by adding the Registry key HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnce.
Text: PLAINTEE通过添加注册表键HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunOnce获得持久性

en_text: PLAINTEE has downloaded and executed additional plugins.
Text: PLAINTEE已经下载并执行了额外的插件

en_text: PLAINTEE performs the tasklist command to list running processes.
Text: PLAINTEE执行tasklist命令，列出正在运行的进程

en_text: PLATINUM has leveraged a zero-day vulnerability to escalate privileges.
Text: PLATINUM利用了一个零日漏洞来升级权限

en_text: PLATINUM is capable of using Windows hook interfaces for information gathering such as credential access.
Text: PLATINUM能够使用Windows钩子接口进行信息收集，如凭证访问

en_text: PLATINUM has used keyloggers that are also capable of dumping credentials.
Text: PLATINUM使用了同样能够倾倒证书的键盘记录器

en_text: PLATINUM has used the Intel? Active Management Technology (AMT) Serial-over-LAN (SOL) channel for command and control.
Text: PLATINUM使用了英特尔?主动管理技术（AMT）的Serial-over-LAN（SOL）通道进行指挥和控制

en_text: PLATINUM has transferred files using the Intel? Active Management Technology (AMT) Serial-over-LAN (SOL) channel.
Text: PLATINUM使用英特尔?主动管理技术（AMT）的Serial-over-LAN（SOL）通道传输文件

en_text: PLATINUM has attempted to get users to open malicious files by sending spearphishing emails with attachments to victims.
Text: PLATINUM试图通过向受害者发送带有附件的鱼叉式钓鱼邮件，让用户打开恶意文件

en_text: PLATINUM has sent spearphishing emails with attachments to victims as its primary initial access vector.
Text: PLATINUM向受害者发送带有附件的鱼叉式钓鱼电子邮件，作为其主要的初始访问载体

en_text: PLATINUM has used various methods of process injection including hot patching.
Text: PLATINUM已经使用了包括热补在内的各种工艺注入方法

en_text: PLATINUM has used several different keyloggers.
Text: PLATINUM已经使用了几种不同的键盘记录器

en_text: PLATINUM has renamed rar.exe to avoid detection.
Text: PLATINUM已经重新命名了rar.exe，以避免被发现

en_text: PLATINUM has sometimes used drive-by attacks against vulnerable browser plugins.
Text: PLATINUM有时会对易受攻击的浏览器插件使用偷渡式攻击

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to proxy network communications.
Text: PLEAD具有代理网络通信的能力

en_text: PLEAD samples were found to be highly obfuscated with junk code.
Text: PLEAD样本被发现是用垃圾代码高度混淆的

en_text: PLEAD has used RC4 encryption to download modules.
Text: PLEAD已经使用RC4加密来下载模块

en_text: PLEAD has used HTTP for communications with command and control (C2) servers.
Text: PLEAD已使用HTTP与指挥和控制（C2）服务器进行通信

en_text: PLEAD has been executed via malicious links in e-mails.
Text: PLEAD已通过电子邮件中的恶意链接执行

en_text: PLEAD has been executed via malicious e-mail attachments.
Text: PLEAD已通过恶意的电子邮件附件执行

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to steal saved credentials from web browsers.
Text: PLEAD有能力从网络浏览器中窃取保存的凭证

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to steal saved passwords from Microsoft Outlook.
Text: PLEAD有能力从微软Outlook窃取保存的密码

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to list processes on the compromised host.
Text: PLEAD有能力列出被攻击主机上的进程

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to list drives and files on the compromised host.
Text: PLEAD有能力列出被攻击主机上的驱动器和文件

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to list open windows on the compromised host.
Text: PLEAD有能力列出被入侵主机上的开放窗口

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to delete files on the compromised host.
Text: PLEAD有能力删除被攻击主机上的文件

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to upload and download files to and from an infected host.
Text: PLEAD有能力向受感染的主机上传和下载文件

en_text: PLEAD has the ability to execute shell commands on the compromised host.
Text: PLEAD有能力在被攻击的主机上执行shell命令

en_text: A version of PlugX loads as shellcode within a .NET Framework project using msbuild.exe, presumably to bypass application control techniques.
Text: PlugX的一个版本在一个使用msbuild.exe的.NET框架项目中作为shellcode加载，据推测是为了绕过应用控制技术

en_text: PlugX can be configured to use DNS for command and control.
Text: PlugX可以被配置为使用DNS进行命令和控制

en_text: PlugX can be configured to use HTTP for command and control.
Text: PlugX可以被配置为使用HTTP进行命令和控制

en_text: PlugX can be configured to use raw TCP or UDP for command and control.
Text: PlugX可以被配置为使用原始TCP或UDP进行命令和控制

en_text: PlugX can enumerate and query for information contained within the Windows Registry.
Text: PlugX可以列举和查询Windows注册表中包含的信息

en_text: PlugX can use the Windows API function CreateProcess to execute another process.
Text: PlugX可以使用Windows API函数CreateProcess来执行另一个进程

en_text: PlugX can be added as a service to establish persistence. PlugX also has a module to change service configurations as well as start, control, and delete services.
Text: PlugX可以作为一个服务被添加，以建立持久性

en_text: PlugX has used DLL side-loading to evade anti-virus.
Text: PlugX利用DLL侧面加载来躲避反病毒

en_text: PlugX uses Pastebin to store C2 addresses.
Text: PlugX使用Pastebin来存储C2地址

en_text: PlugX decompresses and decrypts itself using the Microsoft API call RtlDecompressBuffer.
Text: PlugX使用微软的API调用RtlDecompressBuffer对自己进行解压和解密

en_text: PlugX checks if VMware tools is running in the background by searching for any process named "vmtoolsd".
Text: PlugX通过搜索任何名为 "vmtoolsd "的进程来检查VMware工具是否在后台运行

en_text: PlugX has a module to create, delete, or modify Registry keys.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以创建、删除或修改注册表键

en_text: PlugX has a module to list the processes running on a machine.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以列出机器上运行的进程

en_text: PlugX has a module to enumerate drives and find files recursively.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以列举驱动器并递归地查找文件

en_text: PlugX has a module to enumerate network shares.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以列举网络共享

en_text: PlugX has a module for enumerating TCP and UDP network connections and associated processes using the netstat command.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以使用netstat命令列举TCP和UDP网络连接和相关进程

en_text: PlugX has a module to download and execute files on the compromised machine.
Text: PlugX有一个模块可以在被攻击的机器上下载和执行文件

en_text: PlugX has a module for capturing keystrokes per process including window titles.
Text: PlugX有一个模块用于捕捉每个进程的击键，包括窗口标题

en_text: PlugX allows the operator to capture screenshots.
Text: PlugX允许操作员捕捉屏幕截图

en_text: PlugX allows actors to spawn a reverse shell on a victim.
Text: PlugX允许行动者在受害者身上生成一个反向外壳

en_text: PlugX adds Run key entries in the Registry to establish persistence.
Text: PlugX在注册表中添加了Run key条目以建立持久性

en_text: pngdowner deletes content from C2 communications that was saved to the user's temporary directory.
Text: pngdowner删除了C2通信中保存在用户临时目录中的内容

en_text: pngdowner uses HTTP for command and control.
Text: pngdowner使用HTTP进行命令和控制

en_text: PoetRAT has made registry modifications to alter its behavior upon execution.
Text: PoetRAT对注册表进行了修改，以改变其执行时的行为

en_text: PoetRAT checked the size of the hard drive to determine if it was being run in a sandbox environment. In the event of sandbox detection, it would delete itself by overwriting the malware scripts with the contents of "License.txt" and exiting.
Text: PoetRAT检查硬盘驱动器的大小，以确定它是否在沙盒环境中运行。在沙盒检测的情况下，它将通过用 "License.txt "的内容覆盖恶意软件脚本并退出来删除自己。

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to take screen captures.
Text: PoetRAT具有拍摄屏幕截图的能力

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to hide and unhide files.
Text: PoetRAT具有隐藏和取消隐藏文件的能力

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to compress files with zip.
Text: PoetRAT具有用zip压缩文件的能力

en_text: PoetRAT has used spearphishing attachments to infect victims.
Text: PoetRAT利用鱼叉式钓鱼附件来感染受害者

en_text: PoetRAT used Nmap for remote system discovery.
Text: PoetRAT使用Nmap进行远程系统发现

en_text: PoetRAT used TLS to encrypt communications over port 143
Text: PoetRAT使用TLS对143端口的通信进行加密 PoetRAT使用TLS对143端口的通信进行加密

en_text: PoetRAT used TLS to encrypt command and control (C2) communications.
Text: PoetRAT使用TLS对指挥和控制（C2）通信进行加密

en_text: PoetRAT used voStro.exe, a compiled pypykatz (Python version of Mimikatz), to steal credentials.
Text: PoetRAT使用voStro.exe，一个编译的pypykatz（Mimikatz的Python版本）来窃取证书

en_text: PoetRAT has used Word documents with VBScripts to execute malicious activities.
Text: PoetRAT使用带有VBScripts的Word文档来执行恶意活动

en_text: PoetRAT has used FTP for exfiltration.
Text: PoetRAT使用了FTP进行渗出

en_text: PoetRAT has used a Python tool named Bewmac to record the webcam on compromised hosts.
Text: PoetRAT使用了一个名为Bewmac的Python工具来记录被入侵主机的网络摄像头

en_text: PoetRAT has used a Python tool named Browdec.exe to steal browser credentials.
Text: PoetRAT使用了一个名为Browdec.exe的Python工具来窃取浏览器凭证

en_text: PoetRAT has used a .NET tool named dog.exe to exiltrate information over an e-mail account.
Text: PoetRAT使用了一个名为dog.exe的.NET工具，通过电子邮件账户渗入信息

en_text: PoetRAT has used a Python tool named klog.exe for keylogging.
Text: PoetRAT使用了一个名为klog.exe的Python工具进行键盘记录

en_text: PoetRAT has used a custom encryption scheme for communication between scripts.
Text: PoetRAT使用了一个自定义的加密方案，用于脚本之间的通信

en_text: PoetRAT used file system monitoring to track modification and enable automatic exfiltration.
Text: PoetRAT使用文件系统监控来跟踪修改并实现自动渗出

en_text: PoetRAT was distributed via malicious Word documents.
Text: PoetRAT是通过恶意的Word文档传播的

en_text: PoetRAT was delivered with documents using DDE to execute malicious code.
Text: PoetRAT是通过使用DDE执行恶意代码的文件来传递的

en_text: PoetRAT was executed with a Python script and worked in conjunction with additional Python-based post-exploitation tools.
Text: PoetRAT是用Python脚本执行的，并与其他基于Python的后期开发工具一起工作

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to copy files and download/upload files into command and control channels (C2) using FTP.
Text: PoetRAT有能力复制文件和下载 PoetRAT具有复制文件和下载的能力

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to list all running processes.
Text: PoetRAT有能力列出所有正在运行的进程

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to gather information about the compromised host.
Text: PoetRAT有能力收集被攻击主机的信息

en_text: PoetRAT has the ability to list files upon receiving the ls command from C2.
Text: PoetRAT有能力在收到C2的ls命令后列出文件

en_text: PoetRAT has added a registry key in the  hive for persistence.
Text: PoetRAT在蜂巢中添加了一个注册表键，用于持久性

en_text: PoetRAT sent username, computer name, and the previously generated UUID in reply to a "who" command from C2.

Text: RATANKBA使用命令注册查询 "HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\InternetSettings"

en_text: RATANKBA uses tasklist /svc to display running tasks.
Text: RATANKBA使用任务列表 RATANKBA使用任务清单 RATANKBA使用任务表 RATANKBA使用的是任务列表

en_text: RATANKBA performs a reflective DLL injection using a given pid.

en_text: RATANKBA gathers information about the OS architecture, OS name, and OS version/Service pack.

en_text: RATANKBA gathers the victim’s IP address via the ipconfig -all command.

en_text: RATANKBA runs the whoami and query user commands.

en_text: RATANKBA runs the net view /domain and net view commands.
Text: RATANKBA运行网观点 RATANKBA运行的网络视图 RATANKBA运行网的观点 RATANKBA运行的网状视图

en_text: RawDisk has been used to directly access the hard disk to help overwrite arbitrarily sized portions of disk content.
Text: RawDisk已经被用来直接访问硬盘，以帮助覆盖任意大小的磁盘内容部分

en_text: RawDisk was used in Shamoon to help overwrite components of disk structure like the MBR and disk partitions.
Text: RawDisk在Shamoon中被用来帮助覆盖磁盘结构的组成部分，如MBR和磁盘分区

en_text: RawDisk was used in Shamoon to write to protected system locations such as the MBR and disk partitions in an effort to destroy data.
Text: RawDisk在Shamoon中被用来写入受保护的系统位置，如MBR和磁盘分区，以努力破坏数据

en_text: Data captured by RawPOS is placed in a temporary file under a directory named "memdump".
Text: RawPOS捕获的数据被放置在一个名为 "memdump "目录下的临时文件中

en_text: New services created by RawPOS are made to appear like legitimate Windows services, with names such as "Windows Management Help Service", "Microsoft Support", and "Windows Advanced Task Manager".
Text: RawPOS创建的新服务看起来像合法的Windows服务，名称是 "Windows管理帮助服务"、"微软支持"、"Windows高级任务管理器"

en_text: RawPOS dumps memory from specific processes on a victim system, parses the dumped files, and scrapes them for credit card data.
Text: RawPOS从受害者系统的特定进程中转储内存，解析转储的文件，并刮取其中的信用卡数据

en_text: RawPOS installs itself as a service to maintain persistence.
Text: RawPOS将自己安装成一个服务以保持持久性

en_text: RawPOS encodes credit card data it collected from the victim with XOR.
Text: RawPOS用XOR对它从受害者那里收集的信用卡数据进行编码

en_text: RDAT can also embed data within a BMP image prior to exfiltration.
Text: RDAT还可以在渗出前将数据嵌入BMP图像中

en_text: RDAT has used Windows Video Service as a name for malicious services.
Text: RDAT将Windows视频服务作为恶意服务的名称

en_text: RDAT can process steganographic images attached to email messages to send and receive C2 commands. RDAT can also embed additional messages within BMP images to communicate with the RDAT operator.
Text: RDAT可以处理附在电子邮件中的隐蔽图像，以发送和接收C2命令

en_text: RDAT can deobfuscate the base64-encoded and AES-encrypted files downloaded from the C2 server.
Text: RDAT可以对从C2服务器下载的base64编码和AES加密的文件进行解密

en_text: RDAT can take a screenshot on the infected system.
Text: RDAT可以对受感染的系统进行截图

en_text: RDAT can issue SOAP requests to delete already processed C2 emails. RDAT can also delete itself from the infected system.
Text: RDAT可以发出SOAP请求，删除已经处理的C2邮件。RDAT还可以从受感染的系统中删除自己。

en_text: RDAT can use HTTP communications for C2, as well as using the WinHTTP library to make requests to the Exchange Web Services API.
Text: RDAT可以使用HTTP通信进行C2，也可以使用WinHTTP库向Exchange网络服务API提出请求

en_text: RDAT can use email attachments for C2 communications.
Text: RDAT可以使用电子邮件附件进行C2通信

en_text: RDAT can communicate with the C2 via base32-encoded subdomains.
Text: RDAT可以通过base32编码的子域与C2通信

en_text: RDAT can download files via DNS.
Text: RDAT可以通过DNS下载文件

en_text: RDAT can upload a file via HTTP POST response to the C2 split into 102,400-byte portions. RDAT can also download data from the C2 which is split into 81,920-byte portions.
Text: RDAT可以通过HTTP POST响应向C2上传文件，该文件分为102,400字节的部分

en_text: RDAT can communicate with the C2 via subdomains that utilize base64 with character substitutions.
Text: RDAT可以通过利用base64与字符替换的子域与C2通信

en_text: RDAT can exfiltrate data gathered from the infected system via the established Exchange Web Services API C2 channel.
Text: RDAT可以通过已建立的Exchange Web Services API C2渠道，渗出从受感染系统收集的数据

en_text: RDAT has executed commands using cmd.exe /c.
Text: RDAT使用cmd.exe执行了命令 RDAT已经使用cmd.exe执行了命令 RDAT已使用cmd.exe执行命令 RDAT使用cmd.exe执行命令

en_text: RDAT has used encoded data within subdomains as AES ciphertext to communicate from the host to the C2.
Text: RDAT使用子域内的编码数据作为AES密码文本，从主机到C2进行通信

en_text: RDAT has masqueraded as VMware.exe.
Text: RDAT伪装成了VMware.exe

en_text: RDAT has used AES ciphertext to encode C2 communications.
Text: RDAT已经使用AES密码文本对C2通信进行编码

en_text: RDAT has used DNS to communicate with the C2.
Text: RDAT已经使用DNS与C2通信

en_text: RDAT has created a service when it is installed on the victim machine.
Text: RDAT在受害者机器上安装时已经创建了一个服务

en_text: RDFSNIFFER hooks several Win32 API functions to hijack elements of the remote system management user-interface.
Text: RDFSNIFFER钩住几个Win32 API函数来劫持远程系统管理用户界面的元素

en_text: RDFSNIFFER has the capability of deleting local files.
Text: RDFSNIFFER具有删除本地文件的能力

en_text: RDFSNIFFER has used several Win32 API functions to interact with the victim machine.
Text: RDFSNIFFER使用了几个Win32 API函数与受害者机器进行交互

en_text: Reaver queries the Registry to determine the correct Startup path to use for persistence.
Text: Reaver查询注册表以确定用于持久化的正确启动路径

en_text: Reaver creates a shortcut file and saves it in a Startup folder to establish persistence.
Text: Reaver创建了一个快捷方式文件，并将其保存在启动文件夹中以建立持久性

en_text: Reaver installs itself as a new service.
Text: Reaver将自己安装成一个新的服务

en_text: Reaver deletes the original dropped file from the victim.
Text: Reaver删除了受害者的原始投放文件

en_text: Reaver collects the victim's IP address.
Text: Reaver收集了受害者的IP地址

en_text: Reaver collects the victim's username.
Text: Reaver收集了受害者的用户名

en_text: Reaver collects system information from the victim, including CPU speed, computer name, volume serial number, ANSI code page, OEM code page identifier for the OS, Microsoft Windows version, and memory information.
Text: Reaver收集受害者的系统信息，包括CPU速度、计算机名称、卷轴序列号、ANSI代码页、操作系统的OEM代码页标识符、微软Windows版本和内存信息

en_text: Reaver drops and executes a malicious CPL file as its payload.
Text: Reaver投放并执行一个恶意的CPL文件作为其有效载荷

en_text: Reaver encrypts some of its files with XOR.
Text: Reaver用XOR对其部分文件进行加密

en_text: Reaver encrypts collected data with an incremental XOR key prior to exfiltration.
Text: Reaver在渗出前用增量XOR密钥对收集的数据进行加密

en_text: A RedLeaves configuration file is encrypted with a simple XOR key, 0x53.
Text: RedLeaves的配置文件是用一个简单的XOR密钥加密的，0x53

en_text: RedLeaves can capture screenshots.
Text: RedLeaves可以捕获屏幕截图

en_text: RedLeaves can obtain information about the logged on user both locally and for Remote Desktop sessions.
Text: RedLeaves可以获得本地和远程桌面会话的登录用户的信息

en_text: RedLeaves can obtain information about network parameters.
Text: RedLeaves可以获得有关网络参数的信息

en_text: RedLeaves can receive and execute commands with cmd.exe. It can also provide a reverse shell.
Text: RedLeaves可以接收和执行cmd.exe的命令

en_text: RedLeaves can enumerate and search for files and directories.
Text: RedLeaves可以列举和搜索文件和目录

en_text: RedLeaves can enumerate drives and Remote Desktop sessions.
Text: RedLeaves可以列举驱动器和远程桌面会话

en_text: RedLeaves can delete specified files.
Text: RedLeaves可以删除指定的文件

en_text: RedLeaves can gather extended system information including the hostname, OS version number, platform, memory information, time elapsed since system startup, and CPU information.
Text: RedLeaves可以收集扩展的系统信息，包括主机名、操作系统版本号、平台、内存信息、系统启动后经过的时间和CPU信息

en_text: RedLeaves can gather browser usernames and passwords.
Text: RedLeaves可以收集浏览器用户名和密码

en_text: RedLeaves can use HTTP over non-standard ports, such as 995, for C2.
Text: RedLeaves可以通过非标准端口使用HTTP，如995，用于C2

en_text: RedLeaves is capable of downloading a file from a specified URL.
Text: RedLeaves能够从一个指定的URL下载文件

en_text: RedLeaves attempts to add a shortcut file in the Startup folder to achieve persistence.
Text: RedLeaves试图在启动文件夹中添加一个快捷方式文件，以实现持久性

en_text: RedLeaves attempts to add a shortcut file in the Startup folder to achieve persistence. If this fails, it attempts to add Registry Run keys.
Text: RedLeaves试图在启动文件夹中添加一个快捷方式文件以实现持久性

en_text: RedLeaves is launched through use of DLL search order hijacking to load a malicious dll.
Text: RedLeaves是通过使用DLL搜索顺序劫持来加载一个恶意的dll而启动的

en_text: RedLeaves has encrypted C2 traffic with RC4, previously using keys of 88888888 and babybear.
Text: RedLeaves用RC4对C2流量进行了加密，以前使用的密钥是8888888和babybear

en_text: RegDuke can extract and execute PowerShell scripts from C2 communications.
Text: RegDuke可以从C2通信中提取并执行PowerShell脚本

en_text: RegDuke can download files from C2.
Text: RegDuke可以从C2下载文件

en_text: RegDuke can use Dropbox as its C2 server.
Text: RegDuke可以使用Dropbox作为其C2服务器

en_text: RegDuke can use control-flow flattening or the commercially available .NET Reactor for obfuscation.
Text: RegDuke可以使用控制流扁平化或商业上可用的.NET Reactor进行混淆

en_text: RegDuke can persist using a WMI consumer that is launched every time a process named WINWORD.EXE is started.
Text: RegDuke可以使用一个WMI消费者，在每次启动名为WINWORD.EXE的进程时启动该消费者

en_text: RegDuke can decrypt strings with a key either stored in the Registry or hardcoded in the code.
Text: RegDuke可以用存储在注册表中或在代码中硬编码的密钥解密字符串

en_text: RegDuke can hide data in images, including use of the Least Significant Bit (LSB).
Text: RegDuke可以在图像中隐藏数据，包括使用最小有效位（LSB）

en_text: RegDuke can store its encryption key in the Registry.
Text: RegDuke可以在注册表中存储其加密密钥

en_text: Regin contains a keylogger.
Text: Regin包含一个键盘记录器

en_text: The Regin malware platform can use ICMP to communicate between infected computers.
Text: Regin恶意软件平台可以使用ICMP在受感染的计算机之间进行通信

en_text: The Regin malware platform can use Windows admin shares to move laterally.
Text: Regin恶意软件平台可以使用Windows管理员共享来横向移动

en_text: The Regin malware platform uses Extended Attributes to store encrypted executables.
Text: Regin恶意软件平台使用扩展属性来存储加密的可执行文件

en_text: The Regin malware platform supports many standard protocols, including HTTP and HTTPS.
Text: Regin恶意软件平台支持许多标准协议，包括HTTP和HTTPS

en_text: The Regin malware platform supports many standard protocols, including SMB.
Text: Regin恶意软件平台支持许多标准协议，包括SMB

en_text: Regin leveraged several compromised universities as proxies to obscure its origin.
Text: Regin利用几所被破坏的大学作为代理机构，以掩盖其来源

en_text: Regin has used a hidden file system to store some of its components.
Text: Regin使用了一个隐藏的文件系统来存储它的一些组件

en_text: Regin appears to have functionality to modify remote Registry information.
Text: Regin似乎具有修改远程注册表信息的功能

en_text: Regin appears to have functionality to sniff for credentials passed over HTTP, SMTP, and SMB.
Text: Regin似乎具有嗅探通过HTTP、SMTP和SMB传递的凭证的功能

en_text: Reg may be used to gather details from the Windows Registry of a local or remote system at the command-line interface.
Text: Reg可以用来在命令行界面上收集本地或远程系统的Windows注册表的详细信息

Text: Reg可以用来在命令行界面与本地或远程系统的Windows注册表进行交互和修改

en_text: Reg may be used to find credentials in the Windows Registry.
Text: Reg可用于查找Windows注册表中的凭证

en_text: Remcos takes automated screenshots of the infected machine.
Text: Remcos对被感染的机器进行自动截图

en_text: Remcos can capture data from the system’s microphone.
Text: Remcos可以从系统的麦克风捕捉数据

en_text: Remcos can access a system’s webcam and take pictures.
Text: Remcos可以访问一个系统的网络摄像头并进行拍照

en_text: Remcos can add itself to the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run for persistence.
Text: Remcos可以将自己添加到注册表的HKCU\Software\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Run键中，以实现持久性

en_text: Remcos can launch a remote command line to execute commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: Remcos可以启动一个远程命令行，在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: Remcos can search for files on the infected machine.
Text: Remcos可以搜索被感染机器上的文件

en_text: Remcos can upload and download files to and from the victim’s machine.
Text: Remcos可以向受害者的机器上传和下载文件

en_text: Remcos steals and modifies data from the clipboard.
Text: Remcos窃取并修改剪贴板上的数据

en_text: Remcos uses Python scripts.
Text: Remcos使用Python脚本

en_text: Remcos uses RC4 and base64 to obfuscate data, including Registry entries and file paths.
Text: Remcos使用RC4和base64来混淆数据，包括注册表项和文件路径

en_text: Remcos uses the infected hosts as SOCKS5 proxies to allow for tunneling and proxying.
Text: Remcos使用被感染的主机作为SOCKS5代理，以实现隧道和代理

en_text: Remcos searches for Sandboxie and VMware on the system.
Text: Remcos搜索系统中的Sandboxie和VMware

en_text: Remcos has full control of the Registry, including the ability to modify it.
Text: Remcos拥有对注册表的完全控制权，包括修改注册表的能力

en_text: Remcos has a command for keylogging.
Text: Remcos有一个键盘记录的命令

en_text: Remcos has a command to hide itself through injecting into another process.
Text: Remcos有一个命令，通过注入另一个进程来隐藏自己

en_text: Remcos has a command for UAC bypassing.
Text: Remcos有一个绕过UAC的命令

en_text: Remexi collects text from the clipboard.
Text: Remexi从剪贴板上收集文本

en_text: Remexi takes screenshots of windows of interest.
Text: Remexi对感兴趣的窗口进行截图

en_text: Remexi encrypts and adds all gathered browser data into files for upload to C2.
Text: Remexi对所有收集的浏览器数据进行加密并添加到文件中，以便上传到C2

en_text: Remexi utilizes Run Registry keys in the HKLM hive as a persistence mechanism.
Text: Remexi利用HKLM蜂巢中的运行注册表键作为一种持久性机制

en_text: Remexi utilizes scheduled tasks as a persistence mechanism.
Text: Remexi利用计划任务作为一种持久性机制

en_text: Remexi silently executes received commands with cmd.exe.
Text: Remexi默默地用cmd.exe执行收到的命令

en_text: Remexi decrypts the configuration data using XOR with 25-character keys.
Text: Remexi使用25个字符的密钥进行XOR解密配置数据

en_text: Remexi uses BITSAdmin to communicate with the C2 server over HTTP.
Text: Remexi使用BITSAdmin通过HTTP与C2服务器通信

en_text: Remexi gathers and exfiltrates keystrokes from the machine.
Text: Remexi收集并渗入机器上的键盘信息

en_text: Remexi searches for files on the system.
Text: Remexi搜索系统中的文件

en_text: Remexi performs exfiltration over BITSAdmin, which is also used for the C2 channel.
Text: Remexi通过BITSAdmin进行渗透，这也被用于C2渠道

en_text: Remexi achieves persistence using Userinit by adding the Registry key HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Userinit.
Text: Remexi通过添加注册表键HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Userinit来实现持久性

en_text: Remexi executes received commands with wmic.exe (for WMI commands).
Text: Remexi用wmic.exe执行收到的命令（对于WMI命令）

en_text: Remexi obfuscates its configuration data with XOR.
Text: Remexi用XOR混淆其配置数据

en_text: Remexi has a command to capture active windows on the machine and retrieve window titles.
Text: Remexi有一个命令可以捕获机器上的活动窗口并检索窗口标题

en_text: Remexi uses AutoIt and VBS scripts throughout its execution process.
Text: Remexi在其整个执行过程中使用AutoIt和VBS脚本

en_text: RemoteCMD can execute commands remotely by creating a new service on the remote system.
Text: RemoteCMD可以通过在远程系统上创建一个新的服务来远程执行命令

en_text: RemoteCMD can execute commands remotely by creating a new schedule task on the remote system
Text: RemoteCMD可以通过在远程系统上创建一个新的计划任务来远程执行命令

en_text: RemoteCMD copies a file over to the remote system before execution.
Text: RemoteCMD在执行前将一个文件复制到远程系统上

en_text: Remsec contains a keylogger component.
Text: Remsec包含一个键盘记录器组件

en_text: Remsec contains a module to move data from airgapped networks to Internet-connected systems by using a removable USB device.
Text: Remsec包含一个模块，通过使用一个可移动的USB设备，将数据从空中覆盖的网络转移到互联网连接的系统

en_text: Remsec contains a network loader to receive executable modules from remote attackers and run them on the local victim. It can also upload and download files over HTTP and HTTPS.
Text: Remsec包含一个网络加载器，用于接收来自远程攻击者的可执行模块并在本地受害者身上运行

en_text: The Remsec loader implements itself with the name Security Support Provider, a legitimate Windows function. Various Remsec .exe files mimic legitimate file names used by Microsoft, Symantec, Kaspersky, Hewlett-Packard, and VMWare. Remsec also disguised malicious modules using similar filenames as custom network encryption software on victims.
Text: Remsec加载器以安全支持提供者的名义实现自己，这是一个合法的Windows功能。各种Remsec .exe文件模仿微软、赛门铁克、卡巴斯基、惠普和VMWare使用的合法文件名。Remsec还使用类似的文件名将恶意模块伪装成受害者的定制网络加密软件。

en_text: Remsec harvests plain-text credentials as a password filter registered on domain controllers.
Text: Remsec将纯文本凭证作为在域控制器上注册的密码过滤器来收割

en_text: Remsec can ping or traceroute a remote host.
Text: Remsec可以ping或traceroute一个远程主机

en_text: Remsec can obtain a process list from the victim.
Text: Remsec可以从受害者那里获得一个进程列表

en_text: Remsec can obtain the OS version information, computer name, processor architecture, machine role, and OS edition.
Text: Remsec可以获得操作系统版本信息、计算机名称、处理器架构、机器角色和操作系统版本

en_text: Remsec can obtain information about the current user.
Text: Remsec可以获得关于当前用户的信息

en_text: Remsec can obtain a list of active connections and open ports.
Text: Remsec可以获得一个活动连接和开放端口的列表

en_text: Remsec can obtain a list of users.
Text: Remsec可以获得一个用户列表

en_text: Remsec can obtain information about network configuration, including the routing table, ARP cache, and DNS cache.
Text: Remsec可以获得有关网络配置的信息，包括路由表、ARP缓存和DNS缓存

en_text: Remsec can perform DLL injection.
Text: Remsec可以进行DLL注入

en_text: Remsec can add or remove applications or ports on the Windows firewall or disable it entirely.
Text: Remsec可以添加或删除Windows防火墙上的应用程序或端口，或完全禁用它

en_text: Remsec can exfiltrate data via a DNS tunnel or email, separately from its C2 channel.
Text: Remsec可以通过DNS隧道或电子邮件渗出数据，与C2渠道分开

en_text: Remsec can dump the SAM database.
Text: Remsec可以转储SAM数据库

en_text: Remsec is capable of listing contents of folders on the victim. Remsec also searches for custom network encryption software on victims.
Text: Remsec能够列出受害者身上的文件夹内容。Remsec还能搜索受害者身上的自定义网络加密软件。

en_text: Remsec is capable of deleting files on the victim. It also securely removes itself after collecting and exfiltrating data.
Text: Remsec能够删除受害者的文件。它还能在收集和渗出数据后安全地删除自己。

en_text: Remsec is capable of using DNS for C2.
Text: Remsec能够使用DNS进行C2

en_text: Remsec is capable of using HTTP and HTTPS for C2.
Text: Remsec能够使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2

en_text: Remsec is capable of using ICMP, TCP, and UDP for C2.
Text: Remsec能够使用ICMP、TCP和UDP进行C2

en_text: Remsec is capable of using SMTP for C2.
Text: Remsec能够使用SMTP进行C2

en_text: Remsec schedules the execution one of its modules by creating a new scheduler task.
Text: Remsec通过创建一个新的调度器任务来安排其一个模块的执行

en_text: Remsec has a plugin to drop and execute vulnerable Outpost Sandbox or avast! Virtualization drivers in order to gain kernel mode privileges.
Text: Remsec有一个插件，可以丢弃和执行脆弱的Outpost Sandbox或avast! 虚拟化驱动程序，以获得内核模式的权限

en_text: Remsec has a plugin that can perform ARP scanning as well as port scanning.
Text: Remsec有一个插件，可以进行ARP扫描以及端口扫描

en_text: Remsec has a plugin to detect active drivers of some security products.
Text: Remsec有一个插件可以检测一些安全产品的活动驱动

en_text: Remsec has a package that collects documents from any inserted USB sticks.
Text: Remsec有一个软件包可以从任何插入的U盘中收集文件

en_text: Some data in Remsec is encrypted using RC5 in CBC mode, AES-CBC with a hardcoded key, RC4, or Salsa20. Some data is also base64-encoded.
Text: Remsec中的一些数据是使用CBC模式的RC5、带有硬编码密钥的AES-CBC、RC4或Salsa20加密的

en_text: Responder is used to poison name services to gather hashes and credentials from systems within a local network.
Text: Responder用于毒化名称服务，从本地网络内的系统中收集哈希值和凭证

en_text: Revenge RAT gathers the username from the system.
Text: Revenge RAT从系统中收集用户名

en_text: Revenge RAT schedules tasks to run malicious scripts at different intervals.
Text: Revenge RAT会安排任务，在不同时间段运行恶意脚本

en_text: Revenge RAT collects the CPU information, OS information, and system language.
Text: Revenge RAT会收集CPU信息、操作系统信息和系统语言

en_text: Revenge RAT has the ability to upload and download files.
Text: Revenge RAT具有上传和下载文件的能力

en_text: Revenge RAT uses Base64 to encode information sent to the C2 server.
Text: Revenge RAT使用Base64对发送到C2服务器的信息进行编码

en_text: Revenge RAT uses cmd.exe to execute commands and run scripts on the victim's machine.
Text: Revenge RAT使用cmd.exe来执行命令并在受害者的机器上运行脚本

en_text: Revenge RAT uses the Forfiles utility to execute commands on the system.
Text: Revenge RAT使用Forfiles工具在系统上执行命令

en_text: Revenge RAT uses mshta.exe to run malicious scripts on the system.
Text: Revenge RAT使用mshta.exe在系统中运行恶意脚本

en_text: Revenge RAT uses the PowerShell command Reflection.Assembly to load itself into memory to aid in execution.
Text: Revenge RAT使用PowerShell命令Reflection.Assembly将自己加载到内存中以帮助执行

en_text: Revenge RAT collects the IP address and MAC address from the system.
Text: Revenge RAT收集系统的IP地址和MAC地址

en_text: Revenge RAT has the ability to access the webcam.
Text: Revenge RAT有能力访问网络摄像头

en_text: Revenge RAT has a plugin to perform RDP access.
Text: Revenge RAT有一个插件可以进行RDP访问

en_text: Revenge RAT has a plugin for microphone interception.
Text: Revenge RAT有一个麦克风拦截的插件

en_text: Revenge RAT has a plugin for keylogging.
Text: Revenge RAT有一个用于键盘记录的插件

en_text: Revenge RAT has a plugin for screen capture.
Text: Revenge RAT有一个用于屏幕捕捉的插件

en_text: Revenge RAT has a plugin for credential harvesting.
Text: Revenge RAT有一个用于收集证书的插件

en_text: Revenge RAT creates a Registry key at HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Shell to survive a system reboot.
Text: Revenge RAT在HKCU\Software\MicrosoftWindows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\Shell创建了一个注册表键，以便在系统重启后生存

en_text: Revenge RAT used blogpost.com as its primary command and control server during a campaign.
Text: Revenge RAT在一次活动中使用blogpost.com作为其主要命令和控制服务器

en_text: REvil can query the Registry to get random file extensions to append to encrypted files.
Text: REvil可以查询注册表以获得随机的文件扩展名来追加到加密的文件中

en_text: REvil can download a copy of itself from an attacker controlled IP address to the victim machine.
Text: REvil可以从攻击者控制的IP地址下载一个自身的副本到受害者的机器上

en_text: REvil can obtain the token from the user that launched the explorer.exe process to avoid affecting the desktop of the SYSTEM user.
Text: REvil可以从启动explorer.exe进程的用户那里获得令牌，以避免影响SYSTEM用户的桌面

en_text: REvil can encrypt files on victim systems and demands a ransom to decrypt the files.
Text: REvil可以加密受害者系统上的文件，并要求支付赎金以解密文件

en_text: REvil can save encryption parameters and system information to the Registry.
Text: REvil可以将加密参数和系统信息保存到注册表

en_text: REvil can exfiltrate host and malware information to C2 servers.
Text: REvil可以将主机和恶意软件的信息外泄到C2服务器

en_text: REvil can inject itself into running processes on a compromised host.
Text: REvil可以将自己注入到被攻击主机上的运行进程中

en_text: REvil can decode encrypted strings to enable execution of commands and payloads.
Text: REvil可以解码加密的字符串，以便执行命令和有效载荷

en_text: REvil can connect to and disable the Symantec server on the victim's network.
Text: REvil可以连接到受害者网络上的赛门铁克服务器并使其失效

en_text: REvil can enumerate active services.
Text: REvil可以列举活动服务

en_text: REvil can mimic the names of known executables.
Text: REvil可以模仿已知可执行文件的名称

en_text: REvil can identify the domain membership of a compromised host.
Text: REvil可以识别被攻击主机的域名成员

en_text: REvil can identify the username, machine name, system language, keyboard layout, OS version, and system drive information on a compromised host.
Text: REvil可以识别被攻击主机上的用户名、机器名称、系统语言、键盘布局、操作系统版本和系统驱动器信息

en_text: REvil can use Native API for execution and to retrieve active services.
Text: REvil可以使用Native API来执行和检索活动服务

en_text: REvil can launch an instance of itself with administrative rights using runas.
Text: REvil可以使用runas启动一个具有管理权限的自身实例

en_text: REvil can use vssadmin to delete volume shadow copies and bcdedit to disable recovery features.
Text: REvil可以使用vssadmin来删除卷影复制，使用bcdedit来禁用恢复功能

en_text: REvil can use the Windows command line to delete volume shadow copies and disable recovery.
Text: REvil可以使用Windows命令行来删除卷影复制并禁用恢复功能

en_text: REvil can use WMI to monitor for and kill specific processes listed in its configuration file.
Text: REvil可以使用WMI来监控和杀死其配置文件中列出的特定进程

en_text: REvil can mark its binary code for deletion after reboot.
Text: REvil可以在重启后标记其二进制代码进行删除

en_text: REvil has used PowerShell to delete volume shadow copies and download files.
Text: REvil使用PowerShell删除卷影复制和下载文件

en_text: REvil has used obfuscated VBA macros for execution.
Text: REvil使用了混淆的VBA宏来执行

en_text: REvil has infected victim machines through compromised websites and exploit kits.
Text: REvil通过被攻击的网站和漏洞工具包感染了受害者的机器

en_text: REvil has been distributed via malicious e-mail attachments including MS Word Documents.
Text: REvil通过恶意的电子邮件附件（包括MS Word文档）传播

en_text: REvil has used encrypted strings and configuration files.
Text: REvil已经使用了加密的字符串和配置文件

en_text: REvil has encrypted C2 communications with the ECIES algorithm.
Text: REvil已经用ECIES算法对C2通信进行了加密

en_text: REvil has been executed via malicious MS Word e-mail attachments.
Text: REvil已通过恶意的MS Word电子邮件附件执行

en_text: REvil has the capability to destroy files and folders.
Text: REvil有能力破坏文件和文件夹

en_text: REvil has the ability to identify specific files and directories that are not to be encrypted.
Text: REvil有能力识别不被加密的特定文件和目录

en_text: REvil has the capability to stop services and kill processes.
Text: REvil有能力停止服务和杀死进程

en_text: REvil has used HTTP and HTTPS in communication with C2.
Text: REvil在与C2的通信中使用了HTTP和HTTPS

en_text: RGDoor decodes Base64 strings and decrypts strings using a custom XOR algorithm.
Text: RGDoor对Base64字符串进行解码，并使用自定义XOR算法对字符串进行解密

en_text: RGDoor uses cmd.exe to execute commands on the victim’s machine.
Text: RGDoor使用cmd.exe在受害者的机器上执行命令

en_text: RGDoor uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: RGDoor使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: RGDoor uploads and downloads files to and from the victim’s machine.
Text: RGDoor向受害者的机器上传和下载文件

en_text: RGDoor encrypts files with XOR before sending them back to the C2 server.
Text: RGDoor在将文件发回C2服务器之前，用XOR对文件进行加密

en_text: RGDoor executes the whoami on the victim’s machine.
Text: RGDoor在受害者的机器上执行whoami程序

en_text: Rifdoor has been executed from malicious Excel or Word documents containing macros.
Text: Rifdoor已从含有宏的恶意Excel或Word文件中执行

en_text: Rifdoor has been distributed in e-mails with malicious Excel or Word documents.
Text: Rifdoor已通过电子邮件与恶意的Excel或Word文档一起分发

en_text: Rifdoor has encrypted strings with a single byte XOR algorithm.
Text: Rifdoor用单字节的XOR算法对字符串进行了加密

en_text: Rifdoor has encrypted command and control (C2) communications with a stream cipher.
Text: Rifdoor用流密码对指挥和控制（C2）通信进行了加密

en_text: Rifdoor has the ability to identify the IP address of the compromised host.
Text: Rifdoor有能力识别被入侵主机的IP地址

en_text: Rifdoor has the ability to identify the Windows version on the compromised host.
Text: Rifdoor有能力识别被入侵主机上的Windows版本

en_text: Rifdoor has the ability to identify the username on the compromised host.
Text: Rifdoor有能力识别被入侵主机上的用户名

en_text: Rifdoor has created a new registry entry at HKEY_CURRENT_USERS\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\Graphics with a value of C:\ProgramData\Initech\Initech.exe /run.
Text: Rifdoor在HKEY_CURRENT_USERS\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\RunGraphics创建了一个新的注册表项，其值为C:\ProgramData\Initech\Initech.exe

en_text: Rifdoor has added four additional bytes of data upon launching, then saved the changed version as C:\ProgramData\Initech\Initech.exe.
Text: Rifdoor在启动时增加了四个额外的数据字节，然后将改变后的版本保存为C:\ProgramData\Initech\Initech.exe

en_text: Rising Sun can delete files specified by the C2.
Text: Rising Sun可以删除C2指定的文件

en_text: Rising Sun can send data gathered from the infected machine via HTTP POST request to the C2.
Text: Rising Sun可以通过HTTP POST请求将从受感染机器上收集的数据发送到C2

en_text: Rising Sun can clear process memory by overwriting it with junk bytes.
Text: Rising Sun可以通过用垃圾字节覆盖来清除进程内存

en_text: Rising Sun can archive data using RC4 encryption and Base64 encoding prior to exfiltration.
Text: Rising Sun可以在渗透前使用RC4加密和Base64编码对数据进行存档

en_text: Rising Sun decrypted itself using a single-byte XOR scheme. Additionally, Rising Sun can decrypt its configuration data at runtime.
Text: Rising Sun使用一个单字节的XOR方案对自己进行解密。此外，Rising Sun可以在运行时解密其配置数据。

en_text: RobbinHood will search for Windows services that are associated with antivirus software on the system and kill the process.
Text: RobbinHood将搜索系统中与杀毒软件相关的Windows服务并杀死该进程

en_text: RobbinHood will search for an RSA encryption key and then perform its encryption process on the system files.
Text: RobbinHood将搜索一个RSA加密密钥，然后对系统文件执行其加密过程

en_text: RobbinHood deletes shadow copies to ensure that all the data cannot be restored easily.
Text: RobbinHood删除了影子副本，以确保所有数据不能轻易恢复

en_text: RobbinHood disconnects all network shares from the computer with the command net use * /DELETE /Y.
Text: RobbinHood用命令net use *断开所有网络共享与计算机的连接

en_text: RobbinHood stops 181 Windows services on the system before beginning the encryption process.
Text: RobbinHood在开始加密过程前会停止系统上的181个Windows服务

en_text: RobbinHood uses cmd.exe on the victim's computer.
Text: RobbinHood在受害者的电脑上使用cmd.exe

en_text: ROCKBOOT is a Master Boot Record (MBR) bootkit that uses the MBR to establish persistence.
Text: ROCKBOOT是一个主引导记录（MBR）引导工具包，它使用MBR来建立持久性

en_text: Rocke has installed an "init.d" startup script to maintain persistence.
Text: Rocke安装了一个 "init.d "启动脚本以保持持久性

en_text: Rocke installed a cron job that downloaded and executed files from the C2.
Text: Rocke安装了一个cron job，从C2下载和执行文件

en_text: Rocke has installed a systemd service script to maintain persistence.
Text: Rocke安装了一个systemd服务脚本来维护持久性

en_text: Rocke has used Pastebin, Gitee, and GitLab for Command and Control.
Text: Rocke曾使用Pastebin、Gitee和GitLab进行指挥和控制

en_text: Rocke issued wget requests from infected systems to the C2.
Text: Rocke从受感染的系统向C2发出wget请求

en_text: Rocke's miner connects to a C2 server using port 51640.
Text: Rocke的矿工使用51640端口连接到一个C2服务器

en_text: Rocke's miner has created UPX-packed files in the Windows Start Menu Folder.
Text: Rocke的矿工在Windows开始菜单文件夹中创建了UPX包装的文件

en_text: Rocke conducted scanning for exposed TCP port 7001 as well as SSH and Redis servers.
Text: Rocke对暴露的TCP 7001端口以及SSH和Redis服务器进行了扫描

en_text: Rocke has changed the time stamp of certain files.
Text: Rocke改变了某些文件的时间戳

en_text: Rocke has changed file permissions of files so they could not be modified.
Text: Rocke改变了文件的权限，使它们无法被修改

en_text: Rocke can detect a running process's PID on the infected machine.
Text: Rocke可以检测到被感染机器上正在运行的进程的PID

en_text: Rocke exploited Apache Struts, Oracle WebLogic (CVE-2017-10271), and Adobe ColdFusion (CVE-2017-3066) vulnerabilities to deliver malware.
Text: Rocke利用Apache Struts、Oracle WebLogic（CVE-2017-10271）和Adobe ColdFusion（CVE-2017-3066）的漏洞来传递恶意软件

en_text: Rocke has used Pastebin to check the version of beaconing malware and redirect to another Pastebin hosting updated malware.
Text: Rocke利用Pastebin来检查信标恶意软件的版本，并重定向到另一个承载更新恶意软件的Pastebin

en_text: Rocke used malware to download additional malicious files to the target system.
Text: Rocke利用恶意软件向目标系统下载更多的恶意文件

en_text: Rocke used shell scripts to run commands which would obtain persistence and execute the cryptocurrency mining malware.
Text: Rocke使用shell脚本来运行命令，这些命令将获得持久性并执行加密货币挖掘恶意软件

en_text: Rocke has used uname -m to collect the name and information about the infected system's kernel.
Text: Rocke使用uname -m来收集被感染系统的内核名称和信息

en_text: Rocke has used Python-based malware to install and spread their coinminer.
Text: Rocke使用基于Python的恶意软件来安装和传播他们的硬币挖掘机

en_text: Rocke used scripts which detected and uninstalled antivirus software.
Text: Rocke使用了检测和卸载杀毒软件的脚本

en_text: Rocke used scripts which killed processes and added firewall rules to block traffic related to other cryptominers.
Text: Rocke使用了杀死进程的脚本，并添加了防火墙规则来阻止与其他加密者有关的流量

en_text: Rocke has used shell scripts which download mining executables and saves them with the filename "java".
Text: Rocke使用了下载采矿可执行文件并以 "java "文件名保存的shell脚本

en_text: Rocke has executed wget and curl commands to Pastebin over the HTTPS protocol.
Text: Rocke通过HTTPS协议对Pastebin执行了wget和curl命令

en_text: Rocke has spread its coinminer via SSH.
Text: Rocke通过SSH传播其硬币挖掘机

en_text: Rocke downloaded a file "libprocesshider", which could hide files on the target system.
Text: Rocke下载了一个文件 "libprocesshider"，它可以隐藏目标系统上的文件

en_text: Rocke has distributed cryptomining malware.
Text: Rocke已经分发了加密开采的恶意软件

en_text: Rocke has deleted files on infected machines.
Text: Rocke已经删除了被感染机器上的文件

en_text: Rocke has modified /etc/ld.so.preload to hook libc functions in order to hide the installed dropper and mining software in process lists.
Text: Rocke已经修改了 Rocke已修改了 Rocke已修改 Rocke修改了

en_text: Rocke has cleared log files within the /var/log/ folder.
Text: Rocke已清除日志文件中的 Rocke已清除日志文件内的 Rocke已清除日志文件，在 Rocke已清除日志文件内的内容

en_text: Rocke has compiled malware, delivered to victims as .c files, with the GNU Compiler Collection (GCC).
Text: Rocke用GNU编译器集（GCC）编译了恶意软件，以.c文件的形式交付给受害者

en_text: Rocke has extracted tar.gz files after downloading them from a C2 server.
Text: Rocke在从C2服务器下载tar.gz文件后提取了它们

en_text: Rocke has modified UPX headers after packing files to break unpackers.
Text: Rocke在打包文件后修改了UPX头文件，以破坏解包程序

en_text: Rocke has used SSH private keys on the infected machine to spread its coinminer throughout a network.
Text: Rocke在受感染的机器上使用SSH私钥，在整个网络中传播其硬币挖掘机

en_text: Rocke has looked for IP addresses in the known_hosts file on the infected system and attempted to SSH into them.
Text: Rocke在受感染系统的know_hosts文件中寻找IP地址，并试图通过SSH进入这些地址

en_text: RogueRobin gathers the IP address and domain from the victim’s machine.
Text: RogueRobin从受害者的机器上收集IP地址和域名

en_text: RogueRobin base64 encodes strings that are sent to the C2 over its DNS tunnel.
Text: RogueRobin对通过其DNS隧道发送到C2的字符串进行base64编码

en_text: RogueRobin checks the running processes for evidence it may be running in a sandbox environment. It specifically enumerates processes for Wireshark and Sysinternals.
Text: RogueRobin检查运行中的进程，以寻找它可能在沙盒环境中运行的证据

en_text: RogueRobin has used Google Drive as a Command and Control channel.
Text: RogueRobin将Google Drive作为一个指挥和控制渠道

en_text: RogueRobin can save a new file to the system from the C2 server.
Text: RogueRobin可以从C2服务器保存一个新文件到系统中

en_text: RogueRobin enumerates running processes to search for Wireshark and Windows Sysinternals suite.
Text: RogueRobin列举了正在运行的进程来搜索Wireshark和Windows Sysinternals套件

en_text: RogueRobin decodes an embedded executable using base64 and decompresses it.
Text: RogueRobin使用base64对嵌入式可执行文件进行解码，并对其进行解压

en_text: RogueRobin uses regsvr32.exe to run a .sct file for execution.
Text: RogueRobin使用regsvr32.exe来运行一个.sct文件进行执行

en_text: RogueRobin uses Windows Script Components.
Text: RogueRobin使用Windows脚本组件

en_text: RogueRobin uses WMI to check BIOS version for VBOX, bochs, qemu, virtualbox, and vm to check for evidence that the script might be executing within an analysis environment.
Text: RogueRobin使用WMI来检查VBOX、bochs、qemu、virtualbox和vm的BIOS版本，以检查脚本可能在分析环境中执行的证据

en_text: RogueRobin uses various WMI queries to check if the sample is running in a sandbox.
Text: RogueRobin使用各种WMI查询来检查样本是否在沙盒中运行

en_text: RogueRobin uses a command prompt to run a PowerShell script from Excel. To assist in establishing persistence, RogueRobin creates %APPDATA%\OneDrive.bat and saves the following string to it:powershell.exe -WindowStyle Hidden -exec bypass -File "%APPDATA%\OneDrive.ps1".
Text: RogueRobin使用命令提示符从Excel运行一个PowerShell脚本。为了协助建立持久性，RogueRobin创建了%APPDATA%\OneDrive.bat并将以下字符串保存到其中：powerhell.exe -WindowStyle Hidden -exec bypass -File "%APPDATA%\OneDrive.ps1"。

en_text: RogueRobin gathers BIOS versions and manufacturers, the number of CPU cores, the total physical memory, and the computer name.
Text: RogueRobin收集了BIOS版本和制造商、CPU核心数量、总物理内存和计算机名称

en_text: RogueRobin collects the victim’s username and whether that user is an admin.
Text: RogueRobin收集受害者的用户名以及该用户是否是管理员

en_text: RogueRobin establishes persistence by creating a shortcut (.LNK file) in the Windows startup folder to run a script each time the user logs in.
Text: RogueRobin通过在Windows启动文件夹中创建一个快捷方式（.LNK文件），在用户每次登录时运行一个脚本来建立持久性

en_text: RogueRobin has a command named $screenshot that may be responsible for taking screenshots of the victim machine.
Text: RogueRobin有一个名为$screenshot的命令，可能负责对受害者机器进行截图

en_text: RogueRobin created a shortcut in the Windows startup folder to launch a PowerShell script each time the user logs in to establish persistence.
Text: RogueRobin在Windows启动文件夹中创建了一个快捷方式，在用户每次登录时启动PowerShell脚本，以建立持久性

en_text: ROKRAT retrieves additional malicious payloads from the C2 server.
Text: ROKRAT从C2服务器检索额外的恶意有效载荷

en_text: ROKRAT accesses the HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\mssmbios\Data\SMBiosData Registry key to obtain the System manufacturer value to identify the machine type.
Text: ROKRAT访问HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Services\mssmbios\Data\SMBiosData注册表键，以获得系统制造商的值来识别机器类型

en_text: ROKRAT checks for debugging tools.
Text: ROKRAT检查调试工具

en_text: ROKRAT checks for sandboxing libraries.
Text: ROKRAT检查沙盒库的情况

en_text: ROKRAT can request to delete files.
Text: ROKRAT可以请求删除文件

en_text: ROKRAT can request to upload collected host data and additional files.
Text: ROKRAT可以要求上传收集的主机数据和其他文件

en_text: ROKRAT leverages legitimate social networking sites and cloud platforms (Twitter, Yandex, and Mediafire) for C2 communications.
Text: ROKRAT利用合法的社交网站和云平台（Twitter、Yandex和Mediafire）进行C2通信

en_text: ROKRAT lists the current running processes on the system.
Text: ROKRAT列出了系统上当前运行的进程

en_text: ROKRAT captures screenshots of the infected system using the gdi32 library.
Text: ROKRAT使用gdi32库抓取被感染系统的屏幕截图

en_text: ROKRAT use HTTPS for all command and control communication methods.
Text: ROKRAT使用HTTPS进行所有的指挥和控制通信方式

en_text: ROKRAT uses a keylogger to capture keystrokes and location of where the user is typing.
Text: ROKRAT使用键盘记录器来捕捉键盘输入和用户输入的位置

en_text: ROKRAT gathers the computer name and checks the OS version to ensure it doesn’t run on a Windows XP or Windows Server 2003 systems.
Text: ROKRAT收集计算机名称并检查操作系统版本，以确保它不在Windows XP或Windows Server 2003系统上运行

en_text: ROKRAT steals credentials stored in Web browsers by querying the sqlite database.
Text: ROKRAT通过查询sqlite数据库窃取存储在网络浏览器中的凭证

en_text: ROKRAT steals credentials by leveraging the Windows Vault mechanism.
Text: ROKRAT通过利用Windows Vault机制窃取凭证

en_text: ROKRAT sends collected files back over same C2 channel.
Text: ROKRAT通过相同的C2通道将收集的文件发送回来

en_text: ROKRAT has the ability to gather a list of files and directories on the infected system.
Text: ROKRAT有能力收集受感染系统中的文件和目录清单

en_text: ROKRAT has a audio capture and eavesdropping module.
Text: ROKRAT有一个音频捕获和窃听模块

en_text: Rover takes screenshots of the compromised system's desktop and saves them to C:\system\screenshot.bmp for exfiltration every 60 minutes.
Text: Rover对被攻击系统的桌面进行截图，并将其保存到C:\system\screenshot.bmp中，以便每60分钟进行外泄

en_text: Rover automatically collects files from the local system and removable drives based on a predefined list of file extensions on a regular timeframe.
Text: Rover根据预定义的文件扩展名列表，定期从本地系统和可移动驱动器中自动收集文件

en_text: Rover automatically searches for files on local drives based on a predefined list of file extensions.
Text: Rover根据预定义的文件扩展名列表，自动搜索本地驱动器上的文件

en_text: Rover searches for files on local drives based on a predefined list of file extensions.
Text: Rover根据预定义的文件扩展名列表在本地驱动器上搜索文件

en_text: Rover automatically searches for files on local drives based on a predefined list of file extensions and sends them to the command and control server every 60 minutes. Rover also automatically sends keylogger files and screenshots to the C2 server on a regular timeframe.
Text: Rover根据预定义的文件扩展名列表自动搜索本地驱动器上的文件，并每隔60分钟将其发送到命令和控制服务器。Rover还自动在一个固定的时间框架内向C2服务器发送键盘记录文件和屏幕截图。

en_text: Rover copies files from removable drives to C:\system.
Text: Rover将文件从可移动驱动器复制到C:/system

en_text: Rover has functionality to remove Registry Run key persistence as a cleanup procedure.
Text: Rover具有删除注册表运行键持久性的功能，作为一个清理程序

en_text: Rover searches for files on attached removable drives based on a predefined list of file extensions every five seconds.
Text: Rover每五秒钟根据预定义的文件扩展名列表搜索所附可移动驱动器上的文件

en_text: Rover persists by creating a Registry entry in HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\.
Text: Rover通过在HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\中创建一个注册表项而持续存在

en_text: Rover has keylogging functionality.
Text: Rover有键盘记录功能

en_text: RTM runs its core DLL file using rundll32.exe.
Text: RTM 使用 rundll32.exe 运行其核心 DLL 文件

en_text: RTM used Port 44443 for its VNC module.
Text: RTM 为其 VNC 模块使用了 44443 端口

en_text: RTM collects data from the clipboard.
Text: RTM从剪贴板上收集数据

en_text: RTM strings, network data, configuration, and modules are encrypted with a modified RC4 algorithm. RTM has also been delivered to targets as various archive files including ZIP, 7-ZIP, and RAR.
Text: RTM的字符串、网络数据、配置和模块是用修改过的RC4算法加密的。RTM还以各种档案文件的形式传递给目标，包括ZIP、7-ZIP和RAR。

en_text: RTM monitors browsing activity and automatically captures screenshots if a victim browses to a URL matching one of a list of strings.
Text: RTM监控浏览活动，如果受害者浏览的URL与一个字符串列表相匹配，则自动抓取屏幕截图

en_text: RTM has named the scheduled task it creates "Windows Update".
Text: RTM将其创建的计划任务命名为 "Windows Update"

en_text: RTM can capture screenshots.
Text: RTM可以捕获屏幕截图

en_text: RTM can attempt to run the program as admin, then show a fake error message and a legitimate UAC bypass prompt to the user in an attempt to socially engineer the user into escalating privileges.
Text: RTM可以尝试以管理员身份运行程序，然后向用户显示一个假的错误信息和一个合法的UAC绕过提示，试图通过社交工程使用户升级权限

en_text: RTM can obtain a list of smart card readers attached to the victim.
Text: RTM可以获得附在受害者身上的智能卡读卡器的列表

en_text: RTM can obtain the computer name, OS version, and default language identifier.
Text: RTM可以获得计算机名称、操作系统版本和默认语言标识符

en_text: RTM can obtain the victim time zone.
Text: RTM可以获得受害者的时区

en_text: RTM can obtain the victim username and permissions.
Text: RTM可以获得受害者的用户名和权限

en_text: RTM can obtain information about security software on the victim.
Text: RTM可以获得受害者身上安全软件的信息

en_text: RTM can obtain information about process integrity levels.
Text: RTM可以获得有关过程完整性水平的信息

en_text: RTM can record keystrokes from both the keyboard and virtual keyboard.
Text: RTM可以记录键盘和虚拟键盘的击键

en_text: RTM can detect if it is running within a sandbox or other virtualized analysis environment.
Text: RTM可以检测它是否在沙盒或其他虚拟化分析环境中运行

en_text: RTM can check for specific files and directories associated with virtualization and malware analysis.
Text: RTM可以检查与虚拟化和恶意软件分析相关的特定文件和目录

en_text: RTM can scan victim drives to look for specific banking software on the machine to determine next actions.
Text: RTM可以扫描受害者的驱动器，寻找机器上的特定银行软件，以确定下一步行动

en_text: RTM can delete all files created during its execution.
Text: RTM可以删除其执行过程中创建的所有文件

en_text: RTM can delete all Registry entries created during its execution.
Text: RTM可以删除其执行过程中创建的所有注册表项

en_text: RTM can use the FindNextUrlCacheEntryA and FindFirstUrlCacheEntryA functions to search for specific strings within browser history.
Text: RTM可以使用FindNextUrlCacheEntryA和FindFirstUrlCacheEntryA函数来搜索浏览器历史中的特定字符串
