en_text: RTM can search for specific strings within browser tabs using a Dynamic Data Exchange mechanism.
Text: RTM可以使用动态数据交换机制在浏览器标签中搜索特定字符串

en_text: RTM can download additional files.
Text: RTM可以下载额外的文件

en_text: RTM can add a certificate to the Windows store.
Text: RTM可以向Windows商店添加证书

en_text: RTM has used an RSS feed on Livejournal to update a list of encrypted C2 server names. RTM has also hidden Pony C2 server IP addresses within transactions on the Bitcoin and Namecoin blockchain.
Text: RTM利用Livejournal上的RSS订阅来更新加密的C2服务器名称列表。RTM还在比特币和Namecoin区块链的交易中隐藏了Pony C2服务器的IP地址。

en_text: RTM has used an RSS feed on Livejournal to update a list of encrypted C2 server names.
Text: RTM利用Livejournal上的RSS订阅来更新一个加密的C2服务器名称的列表

en_text: RTM has used search order hijacking to force TeamViewer to load a malicious DLL.
Text: RTM利用搜索顺序劫持，迫使TeamViewer加载一个恶意的DLL

en_text: RTM has used spearphishing attachments to distribute its malware.
Text: RTM利用鱼叉式钓鱼附件来传播其恶意软件

en_text: RTM has used Registry run keys to establish persistence for the RTM Trojan and other tools, such as a modified version of TeamViewer remote desktop software.
Text: RTM利用注册表运行键为RTM木马和其他工具建立持久性，如修改过的TeamViewer远程桌面软件

en_text: RTM has used a modified version of TeamViewer and Remote Utilities for remote access.
Text: RTM使用了TeamViewer和Remote Utilities的修改版进行远程访问

en_text: RTM uses the command line and rundll32.exe to execute.
Text: RTM使用命令行和rundll32.exe来执行

en_text: RTM tries to add a scheduled task to establish persistence.
Text: RTM试图添加一个计划任务来建立持久性

en_text: RTM has attempted to lure victims into opening e-mail attachments to execute malicious code.
Text: RTM试图引诱受害者打开电子邮件附件以执行恶意代码

en_text: RTM tries to add a Registry Run key under the name "Windows Update" to establish persistence.
Text: RTM试图在 "Windows Update "名称下添加一个注册表运行键，以建立持久性

en_text: RTM has been delivered via spearphishing attachments disguised as PDF documents.
Text: RTM是通过伪装成PDF文件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼附件进行的

en_text: RTM has distributed its malware via the RIG and SUNDOWN exploit kits, as well as online advertising network Yandex.Direct.
Text: RTM通过RIG和SUNDOWN漏洞工具包以及在线广告网络Yandex.Direct传播其恶意软件。

en_text: RTM has resolved Pony C2 server IP addresses by either converting Bitcoin blockchain transaction data to specific octets, or accessing IP addresses directly within the Namecoin blockchain.
Text: RTM通过将比特币区块链交易数据转换为特定的八位数，或直接在Namecoin区块链中访问IP地址，解决了Pony C2服务器的IP地址

en_text: RTM samples have been signed with a code-signing certificates.
Text: RTM样品已经用代码签名证书进行了签名

en_text: RTM has relied on users opening malicious email attachments, decompressing the attached archive, and double-clicking the executable within.
Text: RTM依靠用户打开恶意的电子邮件附件，解压所附档案，并双击其中的可执行文件

en_text: RTM has initiated connections to external domains using HTTPS.
Text: RTM已经开始使用HTTPS连接到外部域

en_text: RTM has been delivered as archived Windows executable files masquerading as PDF documents.
Text: RTM已经以归档的Windows可执行文件的形式交付，并伪装成PDF文档

en_text: RTM encrypts C2 traffic with a custom RC4 variant.
Text: RTM用一个自定义的RC4变体对C2流量进行加密

en_text: RTM has the capability to download a VNC module from command and control (C2).
Text: RTM有能力从指挥和控制（C2）下载一个VNC模块

en_text: RTM has the ability to remove Registry entries that it created during execution.
Text: RTM有能力删除它在执行期间创建的注册表项

en_text: Ruler can be used to enumerate Exchange users and dump the GAL.
Text: Ruler可以用来列举Exchange用户并转储GAL

en_text: Ruler can be used to automate the abuse of Outlook Forms to establish persistence.
Text: Ruler可以用来自动滥用Outlook表格来建立持久性

en_text: Ruler can be used to automate the abuse of Outlook Rules to establish persistence.
Text: Ruler可以用来自动滥用Outlook规则来建立持久性

en_text: Ruler can be used to automate the abuse of Outlook Home Pages to establish persistence.
Text: Ruler可以用来自动滥用Outlook主页来建立持久性

en_text: Rundll32.exe is used as a way of executing Flame at the command-line.
Text: Rundll32.exe被用作在命令行执行Flame的方式。

en_text: RunningRAT contains code to delete files from the victim’s machine.
Text: RunningRAT包含从受害者的机器上删除文件的代码

en_text: RunningRAT contains code to open and copy data from the clipboard.
Text: RunningRAT包含打开和复制剪贴板上的数据的代码

en_text: RunningRAT contains code to clear event logs.
Text: RunningRAT包含清除事件记录的代码

en_text: RunningRAT contains code to compress files.
Text: RunningRAT包含压缩文件的代码

en_text: RunningRAT captures keystrokes and sends them back to the C2 server.
Text: RunningRAT捕获按键并将其发回给C2服务器

en_text: RunningRAT adds itself to the Registry key Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run to establish persistence upon reboot.
Text: RunningRAT将自己添加到注册表键Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run中，以便在重新启动时建立持久性

en_text: RunningRAT kills antimalware running process.
Text: RunningRAT杀死了反恶意软件的运行进程

en_text: RunningRAT uses a batch file to kill a security program task and then attempts to remove itself.
Text: RunningRAT使用批处理文件来杀死一个安全程序任务，然后试图删除自己

en_text: RunningRAT gathers the OS version, logical drives information, processor information, and volume information.
Text: RunningRAT收集操作系统版本、逻辑驱动器信息、处理器信息和卷信息

en_text: Ryuk has called CreateToolhelp32Snapshot to enumerate all running processes.
Text: Ryuk调用了CreateToolhelp32Snapshot来列举所有正在运行的进程

en_text: Ryuk has called GetIpNetTable in attempt to identify all mounted drives and hosts that have Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) entries.
Text: Ryuk调用了GetIpNetTable，试图识别所有安装的驱动器和拥有地址解析协议（ARP）条目的主机

en_text: Ryuk has called GetLogicalDrives to emumerate all mounted drives, and GetDriveTypeW to determine the drive type.
Text: Ryuk调用了GetLogicalDrives来列举所有安装的驱动器，并调用GetDriveTypeW来确定驱动器类型

en_text: Ryuk has called kill.bat for stopping services, disabling services and killing processes.
Text: Ryuk调用了kill.bat来停止服务、禁用服务和杀死进程

en_text: Ryuk has injected itself into remote processes to encrypt files using a combination of VirtualAlloc, WriteProcessMemory, and CreateRemoteThread.
Text: Ryuk将自己注入远程进程，利用VirtualAlloc、WriteProcessMemory和CreateRemoteThread的组合来加密文件

en_text: Ryuk has used the Windows command line to create a Registry entry under HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run to establish persistence.
Text: Ryuk使用Windows命令行在HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run下创建了一个注册表项以建立持久性

en_text: Ryuk has used a combination of symmetric (AES) and asymmetric (RSA) encryption to encrypt files. Files have been encrypted with their own AES key and given a file extension of .RYK. Encrypted directories have had a ransom note of RyukReadMe.txt written to the directory.
Text: Ryuk使用对称（AES）和非对称（RSA）加密的组合来加密文件。文件已经用他们自己的AES密钥进行了加密，文件扩展名为.RYK。被加密的目录有一个RyukReadMe.txt的赎金字条写在目录中。

en_text: Ryuk has used multiple native APIs including ShellExecuteW to run executables,GetWindowsDirectoryW to create folders, and VirtualAlloc, WriteProcessMemory, and CreateRemoteThread for process injection.
Text: Ryuk使用了多个本地API，包括ShellExecuteW来运行可执行文件，GetWindowsDirectoryW来创建文件夹，以及VirtualAlloc、WriteProcessMemory和CreateRemoteThread来注入进程

en_text: Ryuk has attempted to adjust its token privileges to have the SeDebugPrivilege.
Text: Ryuk试图调整其令牌权限，以拥有SeDebugPrivilege

en_text: Ryuk has constructed legitimate appearing installation folder paths by calling GetWindowsDirectoryW and then inserting a null byte at the fourth character of the path. For Windows Vista or higher, the path would appear as C:\Users\Public.
Text: Ryuk通过调用GetWindowsDirectoryW，然后在路径的第四个字符处插入一个空字节来构建合法出现的安装文件夹路径。对于Windows Vista或更高版本，该路径将显示为C:\Users\Public。

en_text: Ryuk has stopped services related to anti-virus.
Text: Ryuk已经停止了与反病毒有关的服务

en_text: Ryuk has used vssadmin Delete Shadows /all /quiet to to delete volume shadow copies and vssadmin resize shadowstorage to force deletion of shadow copies created by third-party applications.
Text: Ryuk已使用vssadmin删除阴影 Ryuk已经使用vssadmin删除阴影 Ryuk已经使用vssadmin删除了影子 Ryuk已经使用vssadmin删除了阴影

en_text: Ryuk has used cmd.exe to create a Registry entry to establish persistence.
Text: Ryuk用cmd.exe创建了一个注册表项来建立持久性

en_text: Sakula contains UAC bypass code for both 32- and 64-bit systems.
Text: Sakula包含用于32位和64位系统的UAC绕过代码

en_text: Sakula has the capability to download files.
Text: Sakula具有下载文件的能力

en_text: Sakula uses DLL side-loading, typically using a digitally signed sample of Kaspersky Anti-Virus (AV) 6.0 for Windows Workstations or McAfee's Outlook Scan About Box to load malicious DLL files.
Text: Sakula使用DLL侧面加载，通常使用卡巴斯基反病毒（AV）6.0 for Windows工作站或McAfee的Outlook Scan About Box的数字签名样本来加载恶意的DLL文件

en_text: Sakula uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Sakula使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Sakula uses single-byte XOR obfuscation to obfuscate many of its files.
Text: Sakula使用单字节的XOR混淆法来混淆许多文件

en_text: Sakula calls cmd.exe to run various DLL files via rundll32.
Text: Sakula通过rundll32调用cmd.exe来运行各种DLL文件

en_text: Sakula calls cmd.exe to run various DLL files via rundll32 and also to perform file cleanup. Sakula also has the capability to invoke a reverse shell.
Text: Sakula通过rundll32调用cmd.exe来运行各种DLL文件，还可以执行文件清理

en_text: Sakula encodes C2 traffic with single-byte XOR keys.
Text: Sakula用单字节的XOR密钥对C2流量进行编码

en_text: SamSam encrypts victim files using RSA-2048 encryption and demands a ransom be paid in Bitcoin to decrypt those files.
Text: SamSam使用RSA-2048加密法对受害者的文件进行加密，并要求以比特币支付赎金来解密这些文件

en_text: SamSam has used garbage code to pad some of its malware components.
Text: SamSam使用垃圾代码来填充其一些恶意软件组件

en_text: SamSam uses custom batch scripts to execute some of its components.
Text: SamSam使用自定义批处理脚本来执行它的一些组件

en_text: Sandworm Team's CredRaptor tool can collect saved passwords from various internet browsers.
Text: Sandworm Team的CredRaptor工具可以从各种互联网浏览器收集保存的密码

en_text: Sandworm Team's plainpwd tool is a modified version of Mimikatz and dumps Windows credentials from system memory.
Text: Sandworm Team的plainpwd工具是Mimikatz的修改版，从系统内存中转储Windows凭证

en_text: Sandworm Team's Python backdoor can push additional malicious tools to an infected system.
Text: Sandworm Team的Python后门可以向受感染的系统推送额外的恶意工具

en_text: Sandworm Team's VBS backdoor can decode Base64-encoded data and save it to the %TEMP% folder. The group also decrypted received information using the Triple DES algorithm and decompresses it using GZip.
Text: Sandworm Team的VBS后门可以解码Base64编码的数据并将其保存到%TEMP%文件夹中。该小组还使用三重DES算法对收到的信息进行解密，并使用GZip进行解压。

en_text: Sandworm Team has used the Telegram Bot API from Telegram Messenger to send and receive commands to its Python backdoor. Sandworm Team also used legitimate M.E.Doc software update check requests for sending and receiving commands and hosted malicious payloads on putdrive.com.
Text: Sandworm Team利用Telegram Messenger的Telegram Bot API向其Python后门发送和接收命令。Sandworm Team还利用合法的M.E.Doc软件更新检查请求来发送和接收命令，并在putdrive.com上托管恶意的有效载荷。

en_text: Sandworm Team has used the BlackEnergy KillDisk component to overwrite files on Windows-based Human-Machine Interfaces.
Text: Sandworm Team使用BlackEnergy KillDisk组件来覆盖基于Windows的人机界面上的文件

en_text: Sandworm Team has used the BlackEnergy KillDisk component to corrupt the infected system's master boot record.
Text: Sandworm Team使用BlackEnergy KillDisk组件来破坏受感染系统的主引导记录

en_text: Sandworm Team used malware to enumerate email settings, including usernames and passwords, from the M.E.Doc application.
Text: Sandworm Team使用恶意软件从M.E.Doc应用程序中列举电子邮件设置，包括用户名和密码

en_text: Sandworm Team used malware to enumerate proxy settings from the M.E.Doc application.
Text: Sandworm Team使用恶意软件列举了M.E.Doc应用程序的代理设置

en_text: Sandworm Team has used a keylogger to capture keystrokes by using the SetWindowsHookEx function.
Text: Sandworm Team使用键盘记录器通过SetWindowsHookEx函数来捕获按键

en_text: Sandworm Team has used backdoors that can delete files used in an attack from an infected system.
Text: Sandworm Team使用了后门，可以从受感染的系统中删除用于攻击的文件

en_text: Sandworm Team used a backdoor which could execute a supplied DLL using rundll32.exe.
Text: Sandworm Team使用了一个后门，可以使用rundll32.exe执行一个提供的DLL

en_text: Sandworm Team has delivered spearphishing attachments with malicious macros embedded within files.
Text: Sandworm Team提供了嵌入文件中的恶意宏的鱼叉式攻击附件

en_text: Sandworm Team has avoided detection by naming a malicious binary explorer.exe.
Text: Sandworm Team通过命名一个恶意的二进制文件explorer.exe来逃避检测

en_text: Sandworm Team has distributed NotPetya by compromising the legitimate Ukrainian accounting software M.E.Doc and replacing a legitimate software update with a malicious one.
Text: Sandworm Team通过破坏乌克兰合法的会计软件M.E.Doc并将合法的软件更新替换成恶意的软件来传播NotPetya

en_text: Sandworm Team has delivered malicious Microsoft Office attachments via spearphishing emails.
Text: Sandworm Team通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件提供了恶意的微软Office附件

en_text: Sandworm Team has used Base64 encoding within malware variants. Sandworm Team has also used ROT13 encoding, AES encryption and compression with the zlib library for their Python-based backdoor.
Text: Sandworm Team在恶意软件变体中使用了Base64编码。Sandworm Team还使用ROT13编码、AES加密和压缩，并将zlib库用于其基于Python的后门。

en_text: Sandworm Team's BCS-server tool uses base64 encoding and HTML tags for the communication traffic between the C2 server.
Text: Sandworm团队的BCS-服务器工具使用base64编码和HTML标签，用于C2服务器之间的通信流量

en_text: Sandworm Team's BCS-server tool connects to the designated C2 server via HTTP.
Text: Sandworm团队的BCS-服务器工具通过HTTP连接到指定的C2服务器

en_text: Sandworm Team has used Dropbear SSH with a hardcoded backdoor password to maintain persistence within the target network. Sandworm Team has also used VPN tunnels established in legitimate software company infrastructure to gain access to internal networks of that software company's users.
Text: Sandworm团队使用Dropbear SSH与硬编码的后门密码来保持目标网络内的持久性。沙虫团队还使用在合法的软件公司基础设施中建立的VPN隧道，以获得对该软件公司用户的内部网络的访问。

en_text: Sandworm Team has used a tool to query Active Directory using LDAP, discovering information about computers listed in AD.
Text: Sandworm团队使用一个工具，使用LDAP查询活动目录，发现AD中列出的计算机信息

en_text: Sandworm Team has used a tool to query Active Directory using LDAP, discovering information about usernames listed in AD.
Text: Sandworm团队使用一个工具，使用LDAP查询活动目录，发现AD中列出的用户名信息

en_text: Scarlet Mimic has used the left-to-right override character in self-extracting RAR archive spearphishing attachment file names.
Text: Scarlet Mimic在自解压RAR档案的鱼叉式钓鱼附件文件名中使用了从左到右的覆盖字符

en_text: schtasks is used to schedule tasks on a Windows system to run at a specific date and time.
Text: schtasks用于安排Windows系统上的任务，在特定的日期和时间运行

en_text: SDBot has used a packed installer file.
Text: SDBot使用了一个打包的安装文件

en_text: SDBot has the ability to download a DLL from C2 to a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力从C2下载一个DLL到被攻击的主机

en_text: SDBot has the ability to delete files from a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力从被攻击的主机上删除文件

en_text: SDBot has the ability to decrypt and decompress its payload to enable code execution.
Text: SDBot有能力对其有效载荷进行解密和解压，以实现代码执行

en_text: SDBot has the ability to access the file system on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力访问被攻击主机上的文件系统

en_text: SDBot has the ability to get directory listings or drive information on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力获得被攻击主机上的目录列表或驱动器信息

en_text: SDBot has the ability to inject a downloaded DLL into a newly created rundll32.exe process.
Text: SDBot有能力将下载的DLL注入一个新创建的rundll32.exe进程

en_text: SDBot has the ability to clean up and remove data structures from a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力清理和删除被入侵主机的数据结构

en_text: SDBot has the ability to determine the domain name and whether a proxy is configured on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力确定域名以及在被攻击的主机上是否配置了代理

en_text: SDBot has the ability to identify the user on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力识别被入侵主机上的用户

en_text: SDBot has the ability to identify the OS version, country code, and computer name.
Text: SDBot有能力识别操作系统版本、国家代码和计算机名称

en_text: SDBot has the ability to use RDP to connect to victim's machines.
Text: SDBot有能力使用RDP连接到受害者的机器

en_text: SDBot has the ability to use port forwarding to establish a proxy between a target host and C2.
Text: SDBot有能力使用端口转发，在目标主机和C2之间建立一个代理

en_text: SDBot has the ability to use the command shell to execute commands on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力使用命令外壳在被攻击的主机上执行命令

en_text: SDBot has the ability to communicate with C2 with TCP over port 443.
Text: SDBot有能力通过443端口与C2进行TCP通信

en_text: SDBot has the ability to XOR the strings for its installer component with a hardcoded 128 byte key.
Text: SDBot有能力用一个硬编码的128字节的密钥来XOR其安装程序组件的字符串

en_text: SDBot has the ability to record video on a compromised host.
Text: SDBot有能力在被破坏的主机上录制视频

en_text: SDelete deletes data in a way that makes it unrecoverable.
Text: SDelete删除数据的方式，使其无法恢复

en_text: SeaDuke C2 traffic is base64-encoded.
Text: SeaDuke C2流量是base64编码的

en_text: SeaDuke C2 traffic has been encrypted with RC4 and AES.
Text: SeaDuke的C2流量已经用RC4和AES进行了加密

en_text: SeaDuke can securely delete files, including deleting itself from the victim.
Text: SeaDuke可以安全地删除文件，包括从受害者身上删除自己

en_text: SeaDuke is capable of uploading and downloading files.
Text: SeaDuke能够上传和下载文件

en_text: SeaDuke is capable of persisting via a .lnk file stored in the Startup directory.
Text: SeaDuke能够通过存储在Startup目录中的.lnk文件持续存在

en_text: SeaDuke is capable of persisting via the Registry Run key or a .lnk file stored in the Startup directory.
Text: SeaDuke能够通过注册表运行键或存储在启动目录中的.lnk文件持续存在

en_text: SeaDuke is capable of executing commands.
Text: SeaDuke能够执行命令

en_text: SeaDuke uses HTTP and HTTPS for C2.
Text: SeaDuke使用HTTP和HTTPS进行C2

en_text: SeaDuke uses an event filter in WMI code to execute a previously dropped executable shortly after system startup.
Text: SeaDuke使用WMI代码中的一个事件过滤器，在系统启动后不久就执行一个先前放弃的可执行文件

en_text: SeaDuke uses a module to execute Mimikatz with PowerShell to perform Pass the Ticket.
Text: SeaDuke使用一个模块来执行Mimikatz与PowerShell来执行Pass the Ticket

en_text: SeaDuke has been packed with the UPX packer.
Text: SeaDuke已经用UPX打包器进行了打包

en_text: SeaDuke compressed data with zlib prior to sending it over C2.
Text: SeaDuke在通过C2发送数据之前，用zlib压缩了数据

en_text: Seasalt obfuscates configuration data.
Text: Seasalt混淆了配置数据

en_text: Seasalt is capable of installing itself as a service.
Text: Seasalt能够将自己安装成一种服务

en_text: Seasalt uses cmd.exe to create a reverse shell on the infected endpoint.
Text: Seasalt使用cmd.exe在受感染的端点上创建一个反向外壳

en_text: Seasalt uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: Seasalt使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: Seasalt has masqueraded as a service called "SaSaut" with a display name of "System Authorization Service" in an apparent attempt to masquerade as a legitimate service.
Text: Seasalt伪装成一个名为 "SaSaut "的服务，显示名称为 "系统授权服务"，显然是想伪装成一个合法的服务

en_text: Seasalt has the capability to identify the drive type on a victim.
Text: Seasalt有能力识别受害者的驱动器类型

en_text: Seasalt has a command to download additional files.
Text: Seasalt有一个命令可以下载额外的文件

en_text: Seasalt has a command to perform a process listing.
Text: Seasalt有一个命令可以执行进程列表

en_text: Seasalt has a command to delete a specified file.
Text: Seasalt有一个删除指定文件的命令

en_text: Seasalt creates a Registry entry to ensure infection after reboot under HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\currentVersion\Run.
Text: Seasalt在HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\currentVersion\Run下创建一个注册表项，以确保重启后的感染

en_text: SEASHARPEE can execute commands on victims.
Text: SEASHARPEE可以对受害者执行命令

en_text: SEASHARPEE can timestomp files on victims using a Web shell.
Text: SEASHARPEE可以使用网络外壳对受害者的文件进行定时处理

en_text: SEASHARPEE can download remote files onto victims.
Text: SEASHARPEE可以向受害者下载远程文件

en_text: SEASHARPEE is a Web shell.
Text: SEASHARPEE是一个网络外壳

en_text: ServHelper contains modules that will use schtasks to carry out malicious operations.
Text: ServHelper包含的模块将使用schtasks来进行恶意操作

en_text: ServHelper contains a module for downloading and executing DLLs that leverages rundll32.exe.
Text: ServHelper包含一个下载和执行DLLs的模块，利用rundll32.exe

en_text: ServHelper will attempt to enumerate Windows version and system architecture.
Text: ServHelper将尝试列举Windows版本和系统架构

en_text: ServHelper will attempt to enumerate the username of the victim.
Text: ServHelper将试图列举出受害者的用户名

en_text: ServHelper may set up a reverse SSH tunnel to give the attacker access to services running on the victim, such as RDP.
Text: ServHelper可能会建立一个反向的SSH隧道，让攻击者访问受害者上运行的服务，如RDP

en_text: ServHelper may download additional files to execute.
Text: ServHelper可能会下载额外的文件来执行

en_text: ServHelper may attempt to establish persistence via the HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ run key.
Text: ServHelper可能试图通过HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run运行键来建立持久性

en_text: ServHelper can execute shell commands against cmd.
Text: ServHelper可以针对cmd执行shell命令

en_text: ServHelper uses HTTP for C2.
Text: ServHelper使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: ServHelper has created a new user and added it to the "Remote Desktop Users" and "Administrators" groups.
Text: ServHelper已经创建了一个新的用户，并将其添加到 "远程桌面用户 "和 "管理员 "组

en_text: ServHelper has the ability to execute a PowerShell script to get information from the infected host.
Text: ServHelper有能力执行PowerShell脚本，从受感染的主机上获取信息

en_text: ServHelper has commands for adding a remote desktop user and sending RDP traffic to the attacker through a reverse SSH tunnel.
Text: ServHelper有添加远程桌面用户的命令，并通过反向SSH隧道向攻击者发送RDP流量

en_text: ServHelper has a module to delete itself from the infected machine.
Text: ServHelper有一个模块可以从被感染的机器上删除自己

en_text: Shamoon contains base64-encoded strings.
Text: Shamoon包含base64编码的字符串

en_text: Shamoon queries several Registry keys to identify hard disk partitions to overwrite.
Text: Shamoon查询几个注册表键来确定要覆盖的硬盘分区

en_text: Shamoon creates a new service named "ntssrv" that attempts to appear legitimate; the service's display name is "Microsoft Network Realtime Inspection Service" and its description is "Helps guard against time change attempts targeting known and newly discovered vulnerabilities in network time protocols." Newer versions create the "MaintenaceSrv" service, which misspells the word "maintenance."
Text: Shamoon创建了一个名为 "ntssrv "的新服务，试图显得合法；该服务的显示名称是 "微软网络实时检查服务"，其描述是 "帮助防范针对网络时间协议中已知和新发现的漏洞的时间变更企图"。较新的版本创建了 "MaintenaceSrv "服务，它将 "维护 "一词拼错了。

en_text: Shamoon creates a new service named "ntssrv" to execute the payload. Shamoon can also spread via PsExec.
Text: Shamoon创建了一个名为 "ntssrv "的新服务来执行有效载荷。Shamoon也可以通过PsExec传播。

en_text: Shamoon creates a new service named "ntssrv" to execute the payload. Newer versions create the "MaintenaceSrv" and "hdv_725x" services.
Text: Shamoon创建了一个名为 "ntssrv "的新服务来执行有效载荷。较新的版本创建了 "MaintenaceSrv "和 "hdv_725x "服务。

en_text: Shamoon accesses network share(s), enables share access to the target device, copies an executable payload to the target system, and uses a Scheduled Task/Job to execute the malware.
Text: Shamoon访问网络共享，启用对目标设备的共享访问，复制一个可执行的有效载荷到目标系统，并使用一个预定任务

en_text: Shamoon obtains the victim's operating system version and keyboard layout and sends the information to the C2 server.
Text: Shamoon获得了受害者的操作系统版本和键盘布局，并将这些信息发送到C2服务器

en_text: Shamoon obtains the target's IP address and local network segment.
Text: Shamoon获取目标的IP地址和本地网段

en_text: Shamoon obtains the system time and will only activate if it is greater than a preset date.
Text: Shamoon获取系统时间，只有当它大于预设日期时才会激活

en_text: Shamoon can change the modified time for files to evade forensic detection.
Text: Shamoon可以改变文件的修改时间以逃避取证检测

en_text: Shamoon can impersonate tokens using LogonUser, ImpersonateLoggedOnUser, and ImpersonateNamedPipeClient.
Text: Shamoon可以使用LogonUser、ImpersonateLoggedOnUser和ImpersonateNamedPipeClient来假冒令牌

en_text: Shamoon can download an executable to run on the victim.
Text: Shamoon可以下载一个可执行文件，在受害者身上运行

en_text: Shamoon scans the C-class subnet of the IPs on the victim's interfaces.
Text: Shamoon扫描受害者接口上的IP的C类子网

en_text: Shamoon decrypts ciphertext using an XOR cipher and a base64-encoded string.
Text: Shamoon使用一个XOR密码和一个base64编码的字符串来解密密码文本

en_text: Shamoon attempts to copy itself to remote machines on the network.
Text: Shamoon试图将自己复制到网络上的远程机器

en_text: Shamoon attempts to disable UAC remote restrictions by modifying the Registry.
Text: Shamoon试图通过修改注册表来禁用UAC远程限制

en_text: Shamoon attempts to overwrite operating system files and disk structures with image files. In a later variant, randomly generated data was used for data overwrites.
Text: Shamoon试图用图像文件覆盖操作系统文件和磁盘结构。在后来的一个变种中，随机生成的数据被用于数据覆盖。

en_text: Shamoon copies an executable payload to the target system by using Windows Admin Shares and then scheduling an unnamed task to execute the malware.
Text: Shamoon通过使用Windows Admin Shares将一个可执行的有效载荷复制到目标系统，然后调度一个未命名的任务来执行该恶意软件

en_text: Shamoon has used HTTP for C2.
Text: Shamoon已经将HTTP用于C2

en_text: Shamoon has an operational mode for encrypting data instead of overwriting it.
Text: Shamoon有一种操作模式，用于加密数据而不是覆盖数据

en_text: Sharpshooter's first-stage downloader installed Rising Sun to the startup folder %Startup%\mssync.exe.
Text: Sharpshooter的第一阶段下载程序将Rising Sun安装到启动文件夹%Startup%\mssync.exe

en_text: Sharpshooter's first-stage downloader resolved various Windows libraries and APIs, including LoadLibraryA(), GetProcAddress(), and CreateProcessA().
Text: Sharpshooter的第一阶段下载器解决了各种Windows库和API，包括LoadLibraryA()、GetProcAddress()和CreateProcessA()

en_text: Sharpshooter's first-stage downloader was a VBA macro.
Text: Sharpshooter的第一阶段下载器是一个VBA宏

en_text: Sharpshooter has leveraged embedded shellcode to inject a downloader into the memory of Word.
Text: Sharpshooter利用嵌入式shellcode将下载器注入Word的内存中

en_text: Sharpshooter has sent malicious attachments via emails to targets.
Text: Sharpshooter通过电子邮件向目标发送了恶意附件

en_text: Sharpshooter has sent malicious DOC and PDF files to targets so that they can be opened by a user.
Text: Sharpshooter向目标发送了恶意的DOC和PDF文件，以便用户可以打开这些文件

en_text: Sharpshooter has sent malicious Word OLE documents to victims.
Text: Sharpshooter向受害者发送了恶意的Word OLE文档

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to upload and download files.
Text: SHARPSTATS具有上传和下载文件的能力

en_text: SHARPSTATS has used base64 encoding and XOR to obfuscate PowerShell scripts.
Text: SHARPSTATS使用base64编码和XOR来混淆PowerShell脚本

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to employ a custom PowerShell script.
Text: SHARPSTATS有能力采用自定义PowerShell脚本

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to identify the IP address, machine name, and OS of the compromised host.
Text: SHARPSTATS有能力识别被攻击主机的IP地址、机器名称和操作系统

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to identify the current date and time on the compromised host.
Text: SHARPSTATS有能力识别被攻击主机的当前日期和时间

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to identify the domain of the compromised host.
Text: SHARPSTATS有能力识别被攻击主机的域名

en_text: SHARPSTATS has the ability to identify the username on the compromised host.
Text: SHARPSTATS有能力识别被攻击主机上的用户名

en_text: ShimRatReporter sent collected system and network information compiled into a report to an adversary-controlled C2.
Text: ShimRatReporter将收集到的系统和网络信息汇编成一份报告发送给敌方控制的C2

en_text: ShimRatReporter spoofed itself as AlphaZawgyl_font.exe, a specialized Unicode font.
Text: ShimRatReporter将自己伪装成AlphaZawgyl_font.exe，这是一种专门的Unicode字体

en_text: ShimRatReporter listed all non-privileged and privileged accounts available on the machine.
Text: ShimRatReporter列出了机器上所有可用的非特权和特权账户

en_text: ShimRatReporter listed all running processes on the machine.
Text: ShimRatReporter列出了机器上所有正在运行的进程

en_text: ShimRatReporter used LZ compression to compress initial reconnaissance reports before sending to the C2.
Text: ShimRatReporter使用LZ压缩来压缩初始侦察报告，然后发送给C2

en_text: ShimRatReporter used the Windows function GetExtendedUdpTable to detect connected UDP endpoints.
Text: ShimRatReporter使用Windows函数GetExtendedUdpTable来检测连接的UDP端点

en_text: ShimRatReporter used several Windows API functions to gather information from the infected system.
Text: ShimRatReporter使用几个Windows API函数来收集受感染系统的信息

en_text: ShimRatReporter encrypted gathered information with a combination of shifting and XOR using a static key.
Text: ShimRatReporter使用静态密钥，用移位和XOR的组合对收集的信息进行加密

en_text: ShimRatReporter gathered the local privileges for the infected host.
Text: ShimRatReporter收集了被感染主机的本地权限

en_text: ShimRatReporter gathered a list of installed software on the infected host.
Text: ShimRatReporter收集了被感染主机上已安装的软件列表

en_text: ShimRatReporter gathered the operating system name and specific Windows version of an infected machine.
Text: ShimRatReporter收集了受感染机器的操作系统名称和具体的Windows版本

en_text: ShimRatReporter gathered the local proxy, domain, IP, routing tables, mac address, gateway, DNS servers, and DHCP status information from an infected host.
Text: ShimRatReporter收集了受感染主机的本地代理、域名、IP、路由表、Mac地址、网关、DNS服务器和DHCP状态信息

en_text: ShimRatReporter sent generated reports to the C2 via HTTP POST requests.
Text: ShimRatReporter通过HTTP POST请求将生成的报告发送到C2

en_text: ShimRatReporter communicated over HTTP with preconfigured C2 servers.
Text: ShimRatReporter通过HTTP与预先配置的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: ShimRatReporter had the ability to download additional payloads.
Text: ShimRatReporter有能力下载额外的有效载荷

en_text: ShimRatReporter gathered information automatically, without instruction from a C2, related to the user and host machine that is compiled into a report and sent to the operators.
Text: ShimRatReporter自动收集与用户和主机有关的信息，无需C2指令，这些信息被编入报告并发送给操作人员

en_text: ShimRat's loader has been packed with the compressed ShimRat core DLL and the legitimate DLL for it to hijack.
Text: ShimRat的加载器已经装入了压缩的ShimRat核心DLL和合法的DLL，以便它劫持

en_text: ShimRat has hijacked the cryptbase.dll within migwiz.exe to escalate privileges. This prevented the User Access Control window from appearing.
Text: ShimRat劫持了migwiz.exe中的cryptbase.dll以提升权限

en_text: ShimRat can be issued a command shell function from the C2.
Text: ShimRat可以从C2发出一个命令壳功能

en_text: ShimRat can uninstall itself from compromised hosts, as well create and modify directories, delete, move, copy, and rename files.
Text: ShimRat可以从被攻击的主机上卸载自己，还可以创建和修改目录，删除、移动、复制和重命名文件

en_text: ShimRat can hijack the cryptbase.dll within migwiz.exe to escalate privileges and bypass UAC controls.
Text: ShimRat可以劫持migwiz.exe中的cryptbase.dll以提升权限并绕过UAC控制

en_text: ShimRat can list directories.
Text: ShimRat可以列出目录

en_text: ShimRat can enumerate connected drives for infected host machines.
Text: ShimRat可以列举受感染主机的连接驱动器

en_text: ShimRat can impersonate Windows services and antivirus products to avoid detection on compromised systems.
Text: ShimRat可以冒充Windows服务和防病毒产品，以避免在被攻击的系统中被发现

en_text: ShimRat can use pre-configured HTTP proxies.
Text: ShimRat可以使用预先配置的HTTP代理

en_text: ShimRat can download additional files.
Text: ShimRat可以下载额外的文件

en_text: ShimRat communicated over HTTP and HTTPS with C2 servers.
Text: ShimRat通过HTTP和HTTPS与C2服务器进行通信

en_text: ShimRat has registered two registry keys for shim databases.
Text: ShimRat为shim数据库注册了两个注册表键

en_text: ShimRat has decompressed its core DLL using shellcode once an impersonated antivirus component was running on a system.
Text: ShimRat一旦在一个系统上运行假冒的防病毒组件，就会使用shellcode对其核心DLL进行解压

en_text: ShimRat has been delivered as a package that includes compressed DLL and shellcode payloads within a .dat file.
Text: ShimRat已被作为一个软件包交付，其中包括压缩的DLL和.dat文件中的shellcode有效载荷

en_text: ShimRat has installed a Windows service to maintain persistence on victim machines.
Text: ShimRat已经安装了一个Windows服务，以维持受害者机器上的持久性

en_text: ShimRat has installed a registry based start-up key HKCU\Software\microsoft\windows\CurrentVersion\Run to maintain persistence should other methods fail.
Text: ShimRat已经安装了一个基于注册表的启动键HKCU\Software\microsoft\windows\CurrentVersion\Run，以便在其他方法失败时保持持久性

en_text: ShimRat has used Windows API functions to install the service and shim.
Text: ShimRat已经使用Windows API函数来安装服务和垫片

en_text: ShimRat has installed shim databases in the AppPatch folder.
Text: ShimRat已经在AppPatch文件夹中安装了垫片数据库

en_text: ShimRat has the capability to upload collected files to a C2.
Text: ShimRat有能力将收集的文件上传到C2

en_text: ShimRat has used a secondary C2 location if the first was unavailable.
Text: ShimRat在第一个地点无法使用的情况下使用了第二个C2地点

en_text: SHIPSHAPE achieves persistence by creating a shortcut in the Startup folder.
Text: SHIPSHAPE通过在启动文件夹中创建一个快捷方式来实现持久性

en_text: SHOTPUT uses netstat to list TCP connection status.
Text: SHOTPUT使用netstat来列出TCP连接状态

en_text: SHOTPUT is obscured using XOR encoding and appended to a valid GIF file.
Text: SHOTPUT使用XOR编码进行遮蔽，并附加到一个有效的GIF文件

en_text: SHOTPUT has a command to retrieve information about connected users.
Text: SHOTPUT有一个命令可以检索连接用户的信息

en_text: SHOTPUT has a command to list all servers in the domain, as well as one to locate domain controllers on a domain.
Text: SHOTPUT有一条列出域中所有服务器的命令，以及一条定位域中域控制器的命令

en_text: SHOTPUT has a command to obtain a process listing.
Text: SHOTPUT有一条命令可以获得进程列表

en_text: SHOTPUT has a command to obtain a directory listing.
Text: SHOTPUT有一条命令可以获得目录列表

en_text: SHUTTERSPEED can capture screenshots.
Text: SHUTTERSPEED可以捕获屏幕截图

en_text: SHUTTERSPEED can collect system information.
Text: SHUTTERSPEED可以收集系统信息

en_text: SHUTTERSPEED can download and execute an arbitary executable.
Text: SHUTTERSPEED可以下载并执行一个任意的可执行文件

en_text: Silence has sent emails with malicious DOCX, CHM, LNK and ZIP attachments.
Text: Silence发送了带有恶意的DOCX、CHM、LNK和ZIP附件的电子邮件

en_text: Silence has named its backdoor "WINWORD.exe".
Text: Silence将其后门命名为 "WINWORD.exe"

en_text: Silence has injected a DLL library containing a Trojan into the fwmain32.exe process.
Text: Silence将一个含有木马的DLL库注入fwmain32.exe进程

en_text: Silence can create, delete, or modify a specified Registry key or value.
Text: Silence可以创建、删除或修改一个指定的注册表键或值

en_text: Silence has leveraged the Windows API, including using CreateProcess() or ShellExecute(), to perform a variety of tasks.
Text: Silence利用Windows API，包括使用CreateProcess()或ShellExecute()，来执行各种任务

en_text: Silence has used the Farse6.1 utility (based on Mimikatz) to extract credentials from lsass.exe.
Text: Silence使用Farse6.1工具（基于Mimikatz）从lsass.exe中提取凭证

en_text: Silence has used HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run, HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run, and the Startup folder to establish persistence.
Text: Silence使用HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run、HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run和Startup文件夹来建立持久性

en_text: Silence has used Nmap to scan the corporate network, build a network topology, and identify vulnerable hosts.
Text: Silence使用Nmap扫描公司网络，建立网络拓扑结构，并识别易受攻击的主机

en_text: Silence has used PowerShell to download and execute payloads.
Text: Silence使用PowerShell下载和执行有效载荷

en_text: Silence has used Winexe to install a service on the remote system.
Text: Silence使用Winexe在远程系统上安装了一个服务

en_text: Silence has used ProxyBot, which allows the attacker to redirect traffic from the current node to the backconnect server via Sock4\Socks5.
Text: Silence使用了ProxyBot，它允许攻击者通过Sock4/Socks5将流量从当前节点重定向到backconnect服务器

en_text: Silence has used RAdmin, a remote software tool used to remotely control workstations and ATMs.
Text: Silence使用了RAdmin，一种用于远程控制工作站和自动取款机的远程软件工具

en_text: Silence has used Windows command-line to run commands.
Text: Silence使用了Windows命令行来运行命令

en_text: Silence has used environment variable string substitution for obfuscation.
Text: Silence使用了环境变量字符串替换来进行混淆

en_text: Silence has used a valid certificate to sign their primary loader Silence.Downloader (aka TrueBot).
Text: Silence使用了一个有效的证书来签署他们的主要加载器Silence.Downloader（又名TrueBot）

en_text: SilverTerrier uses FTP for C2 communications.
Text: SilverTerrier使用FTP进行C2通信

en_text: SilverTerrier uses HTTP for C2 communications.
Text: SilverTerrier使用HTTP进行C2通信

en_text: SilverTerrier uses SMTP for C2 communications.
Text: SilverTerrier使用SMTP进行C2通信

en_text: Skidmap has created a fake rm binary to replace the legitimate Linux binary.
Text: Skidmap创建了一个假的rm二进制文件来取代合法的Linux二进制文件

en_text: Skidmap has monitored critical processes to ensure resiliency.
Text: Skidmap对关键流程进行了监测，以确保复原力

en_text: Skidmap has encrypted it's main payload using 3DES.
Text: Skidmap使用3DES对它的主要有效载荷进行了加密

en_text: Skidmap has used pm.sh to download and install its main payload.
Text: Skidmap使用pm.sh来下载和安装其主要的有效载荷

en_text: Skidmap is a kernel-mode rootkit that has the ability to hook system calls to hide specific files and fake network and CPU-related statistics to make the CPU load of the infected machine always appear low.
Text: Skidmap是一个内核模式的rootkit，它有能力钩住系统调用以隐藏特定文件，并伪造网络和CPU相关的统计数据，使受感染机器的CPU负载总是显得很低

en_text: Skidmap is a kernel-mode rootkit used for cryptocurrency mining.
Text: Skidmap是一个用于加密货币挖掘的内核模式rootkit

en_text: Skidmap has checked for the existence of specific files including /usr/sbin/setenforce and  /etc/selinux/config. It also has the ability to monitor the cryptocurrency miner file and process.
Text: Skidmap已经检查了特定文件的存在，包括/usr/sbin/setenforce和/etc/selinux/config。它还具有监控加密货币矿工文件和进程的能力。

en_text: Skidmap has installed itself via crontab.
Text: Skidmap已经通过crontab安装了自己

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to check whether the infected system’s OS is Debian or RHEL/CentOS to determine which cryptocurrency miner it should use.
Text: Skidmap有能力检查被感染系统的操作系统是Debian还是RHEL/CentOS，以确定它应该使用哪种加密货币矿工。

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to check if /usr/sbin/setenforce exists. This file controls what mode SELinux is in.
Text: Skidmap有能力检查是否 Skidmap有能力检查，如果 Skidmap有能力检测是否 Skidmap有能力检查是否有

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to set SELinux to permissive mode.
Text: Skidmap有能力将SELinux设置为允许模式

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to add the public key of its handlers to the authorized_keys file to maintain persistence on an infected host.
Text: Skidmap有能力将其处理程序的公钥添加到authorized_keys文件中，以保持在受感染主机上的持久性

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to download, unpack, and decrypt tar.gz files .
Text: Skidmap有能力下载、解包和解密tar.gz文件

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to replace the pam_unix.so file on an infected machine with its own malicious version that accepts a specific backdoor password for all users.
Text: Skidmap有能力用自己的恶意版本替换受感染机器上的pam_unix.so文件，该文件接受所有用户的特定后门密码

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to install several loadable kernel modules (LKMs) on infected machines.
Text: Skidmap有能力在受感染的机器上安装几个可加载的内核模块（LKMs）

en_text: Skidmap has the ability to download files on an infected host.
Text: Skidmap有能力在受感染的主机上下载文件

en_text: SLOWDRIFT uses cloud based services for C2.
Text: SLOWDRIFT使用基于云的服务进行C2

en_text: SLOWDRIFT collects and sends system information to its C2.
Text: SLOWDRIFT收集并向其C2发送系统信息

en_text: SLOWDRIFT downloads additional payloads.
Text: SLOWDRIFT下载额外的有效载荷

en_text: Smoke Loader spawns a new copy of c:\windows\syswow64\explorer.exe and then replaces the executable code in memory with malware.
Text: Smoke Loader产生了一个新的c:\windows\syswow64\explorer.exe副本，然后用恶意软件替换了内存中的可执行代码

en_text: Smoke Loader recursively searches through directories for files.
Text: Smoke Loader递归地在目录中搜索文件

en_text: Smoke Loader deobfuscates its code.
Text: Smoke Loader对其代码进行了反混淆处理

en_text: Smoke Loader launches a scheduled task.
Text: Smoke Loader启动了一个预定任务

en_text: Smoke Loader scans processes to perform anti-VM checks.
Text: Smoke Loader扫描进程以进行反病毒检查

en_text: Smoke Loader uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Smoke Loader使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Smoke Loader uses a simple one-byte XOR method to obfuscate values in the malware.
Text: Smoke Loader使用一个简单的单字节XOR方法来混淆恶意软件中的数值

en_text: Smoke Loader searches for credentials stored from web browsers.
Text: Smoke Loader搜索存储在网络浏览器中的凭证

en_text: Smoke Loader searches for files named logins.json to parse for credentials.
Text: Smoke Loader搜索名为logins.json的文件来解析证书

en_text: Smoke Loader searches through Outlook files and directories (e.g., inbox, sent, templates, drafts, archives, etc.).
Text: Smoke Loader通过Outlook文件和目录（如收件箱、发送、模板、草稿、档案等）进行搜索

en_text: Smoke Loader adds a Registry Run key for persistence and adds a script in the Startup folder to deploy the payload.
Text: Smoke Loader为持久性添加了一个注册表运行键，并在启动文件夹中添加了一个脚本来部署有效载荷

en_text: Smoke Loader downloads a new version of itself once it has installed. It also downloads additional plugins.
Text: Smoke Loader一旦安装完毕，就会下载自己的新版本

en_text: Smoke Loader adds a Visual Basic script in the Startup folder to deploy the payload.
Text: Smoke Loader在Startup文件夹中添加了一个Visual Basic脚本，以部署有效载荷

en_text: Smoke Loader injects into the Internet Explorer process.
Text: Smoke Loader注入到Internet Explorer进程中

en_text: SNUGRIDE is capable of executing commands and spawning a reverse shell.
Text: SNUGRIDE能够执行命令并生成一个反向的shell

en_text: SNUGRIDE encrypts C2 traffic using AES with a static key.
Text: SNUGRIDE使用AES与静态密钥对C2流量进行加密

en_text: SNUGRIDE communicates with its C2 server over HTTP.
Text: SNUGRIDE通过HTTP与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: SNUGRIDE establishes persistence through a Registry Run key.
Text: SNUGRIDE通过注册表运行键建立了持久性

en_text: Socksbot creates a suspended svchost process and injects its DLL into it.
Text: Socksbot创建了一个暂停的svchost进程并将其DLL注入其中

en_text: Socksbot can write and execute PowerShell scripts.
Text: Socksbot可以编写和执行PowerShell脚本

en_text: Socksbot can take screenshots.
Text: Socksbot可以进行屏幕截图

en_text: Socksbot can list all running processes.
Text: Socksbot可以列出所有正在运行的进程

en_text: Socksbot can start SOCKS proxy threads.
Text: Socksbot可以启动SOCKS代理线程

en_text: Soft Cell created rogue, high-privileged domain user accounts to maintain access across waves of a compromise.
Text: Soft Cell创建了流氓的、高权限的域名用户账户，以保持对一波又一波妥协的访问

en_text: Soft Cell collected data from the victim's local system, including password hashes from the SAM hive in the Registry.
Text: Soft Cell从受害者的本地系统中收集数据，包括来自注册表中SAM蜂巢的密码散列

en_text: Soft Cell established VPN access into victim environments.
Text: Soft Cell建立了进入受害者环境的VPN通道

en_text: Soft Cell exploited a publicly-facing server to gain access to the network.
Text: Soft Cell利用了一个面向公众的服务器来获得对网络的访问

en_text: Soft Cell leveraged valid accounts to maintain access to a victim network.
Text: Soft Cell利用有效的账户来维持对受害者网络的访问

en_text: Soft Cell ensured each payload had a unique hash, including by using different types of packers.
Text: Soft Cell确保每个有效载荷有一个独特的哈希值，包括使用不同类型的打包器

en_text: Soft Cell used DLL side-loading to covertly load PoisonIvy into memory on the victim machine.
Text: Soft Cell使用DLL侧面加载，将PoisonIvy隐蔽地加载到受害者机器的内存中

en_text: Soft Cell used netstat -oan to obtain information about the victim network connections.
Text: Soft Cell使用netstat -oan来获取有关受害者网络连接的信息

en_text: Soft Cell used PowerShell for execution to assist in lateral movement as well as for dumping credentials stored on compromised machines.
Text: Soft Cell使用PowerShell进行执行，以协助横向移动，以及倾倒存储在被攻击机器上的凭证

en_text: Soft Cell used reg commands to dump specific hives from the Windows Registry, such as the SAM hive, and obtain password hashes.
Text: Soft Cell使用reg命令从Windows注册表中转储特定蜂巢，如SAM蜂巢，并获得密码哈希值

en_text: Soft Cell used whoami and query user to obtain information about the victim user.
Text: Soft Cell使用whoami和查询用户来获取受害者用户的信息

en_text: Soft Cell used the Windows command shell to execute commands.
Text: Soft Cell使用Windows命令外壳来执行命令

en_text: Soft Cell used WMI for execution to assist in lateral movement as well as for installing tools across multiple assets.
Text: Soft Cell使用WMI进行执行，以协助横向移动，以及在多个资产上安装工具

en_text: Soft Cell packed some payloads using different types of packers, both known and custom.
Text: Soft Cell使用不同类型的包装器包装一些有效载荷，包括已知的和定制的

en_text: Soft Cell used a modified version of HTRAN to redirect connections between networks.
Text: Soft Cell使用了HTRAN的修改版来重定向网络之间的连接

en_text: Soft Cell used a modified version of HTRAN in which they obfuscated strings such as debug messages in an apparent attempt to evade detection.
Text: Soft Cell使用了一个修改过的HTRAN版本，他们在其中混淆了调试信息等字符串，显然是为了躲避检测

en_text: Soft Cell used Web shells to persist in victim environments and assist in execution and exfiltration.
Text: Soft Cell使用网络外壳在受害者环境中持续存在，并协助执行和渗透

en_text: Soft Cell used a modified version of nbtscan to identify available NetBIOS name servers over the network as well as ping to identify remote systems.
Text: Soft Cell使用修改过的nbtscan版本来识别网络上可用的NetBIOS名称服务器，并使用ping来识别远程系统

en_text: Soft Cell used a modified version of Mimikatz along with a PowerShell-based Mimikatz to dump credentials on the victim machines.
Text: Soft Cell使用一个修改过的Mimikatz版本和一个基于PowerShell的Mimikatz来转储受害者机器上的证书

en_text: Soft Cell used a renamed cmd.exe file to evade detection.
Text: Soft Cell使用一个重新命名的cmd.exe文件来逃避检测

en_text: Soft Cell used dumped hashes to authenticate to other machines via pass the hash.
Text: Soft Cell使用转储的哈希值，通过传递哈希值对其他机器进行认证

en_text: Soft Cell established persistence for PoisonIvy by created a scheduled task.
Text: Soft Cell通过创建一个计划任务为PoisonIvy建立持久性

en_text: Soft Cell dropped additional tools to victims during their operation, including portqry.exe, a renamed cmd.exe file, winrar, and HTRAN.
Text: Soft Cell在操作过程中向受害者投放了额外的工具，包括portqry.exe，一个重命名的cmd.exe文件，winrar和HTRAN

en_text: Soft Cell used WinRAR to compress and encrypt stolen data prior to exfiltration.
Text: Soft Cell在渗透前使用WinRAR压缩和加密被盗数据

en_text: SoreFang can download additional payloads from C2.
Text: SoreFang可以从C2下载额外的有效载荷

en_text: SoreFang can decode and decrypt exfiltrated data sent to C2.
Text: SoreFang可以解码和解密发送到C2的渗出数据

en_text: SoreFang can collect the TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, and network adapter configuration on a compromised host via ipconfig.exe /all.
Text: SoreFang可以收集TCP SoreFang可以收集到TCP SoreFang能够收集TCP SoreFang可以收集到的TCP

en_text: SoreFang can collect usernames from the local system via net.exe user.
Text: SoreFang可以通过net.exe用户从本地系统收集用户名

en_text: SoreFang can enumerate domain accounts via net.exe user /domain.
Text: SoreFang可以通过net.exe用户列举域名账户 SoreFang可以通过net.exe用户列举域名帐户 SoreFang可以通过net.exe用户来列举域名账户 SoreFang可以通过net.exe用户来列举域名账户

en_text: SoreFang can gain access by exploiting a Sangfor SSL VPN vulnerability that allows for the placement and delivery of malicious update binaries.
Text: SoreFang可以通过利用Sangfor SSL VPN的漏洞获得访问权，该漏洞允许放置和交付恶意的更新二进制文件

en_text: SoreFang can gain persistence through use of scheduled tasks.
Text: SoreFang可以通过使用计划任务获得持久性

en_text: SoreFang can enumerate processes on a victim machine through use of Tasklist.
Text: SoreFang可以通过使用任务列表来列举受害者机器上的进程

en_text: SoreFang can enumerate domain groups by executing net.exe group /domain.
Text: SoreFang可以通过执行net.exe组来列举域组

en_text: SoreFang can collect the hostname, operating system configuration, product ID, and disk space on victim machines by executing Systeminfo.
Text: SoreFang可以通过执行Systeminfo收集受害者机器的主机名、操作系统配置、产品ID和磁盘空间

en_text: SoreFang can use HTTP in C2 communications.
Text: SoreFang可以在C2通信中使用HTTP

en_text: SoreFang has the ability to list directories.
Text: SoreFang有列出目录的能力

en_text: SoreFang has the ability to encode and RC6 encrypt data sent to C2.
Text: SoreFang有能力对发送到C2的数据进行编码和RC6加密

en_text: SOUNDBITE is capable of enumerating and manipulating files and directories.
Text: SOUNDBITE能够列举和操作文件和目录

en_text: SOUNDBITE is capable of enumerating application windows.
Text: SOUNDBITE能够列举应用程序窗口

en_text: SOUNDBITE is capable of gathering system information.
Text: SOUNDBITE能够收集系统信息

en_text: SOUNDBITE is capable of modifying the Registry.
Text: SOUNDBITE能够修改注册表

en_text: SOUNDBITE communicates via DNS for C2.
Text: SOUNDBITE通过DNS进行C2通信

en_text: Sowbug extracted Word documents from a file server on a victim network.
Text: Sowbug从受害者网络上的一个文件服务器中提取Word文档

en_text: Sowbug obtained OS version and hardware configuration from a victim.
Text: Sowbug获得了受害者的操作系统版本和硬件配置

en_text: Sowbug named its tools to masquerade as Windows or Adobe Reader software, such as by using the file name adobecms.exe and the directory CSIDL_APPDATA\microsoft\security.
Text: Sowbug将其工具伪装成Windows或Adobe Reader软件，例如使用文件名adobecms.exe和目录CSIDL_APPDATA\microsoft\security

en_text: Sowbug listed remote shared drives that were accessible from a victim.
Text: Sowbug列出了可以从受害者那里访问的远程共享驱动器

en_text: Sowbug extracted documents and bundled them into a RAR archive.
Text: Sowbug提取了文件并将其捆绑到一个RAR档案中

en_text: Sowbug identified and extracted all Word documents on a server by using a command containing * .doc and *.docx. The actors also searched for documents based on a specific date range and attempted to identify all installed software on a victim.
Text: Sowbug通过使用包含*.doc和*.docx的命令识别并提取了服务器上的所有Word文档。行为者还根据特定的日期范围搜索文件，并试图识别受害者身上所有已安装的软件。

en_text: Sowbug has used keylogging tools.
Text: Sowbug已经使用了键盘记录工具

en_text: Sowbug has used credential dumping tools.
Text: Sowbug已经使用了凭证转储工具

en_text: Sowbug has used command line during its intrusions.
Text: Sowbug在其入侵过程中使用了命令行

en_text: Data SPACESHIP copies to the staging area is compressed with zlib. Bytes are rotated by four positions and XOR'ed with 0x23.
Text: SPACESHIP复制到暂存区的数据是用zlib压缩的。字节被旋转了四个位置，并与0x23进行XOR。

en_text: SPACESHIP identifies files with certain extensions and copies them to a directory in the user's profile.
Text: SPACESHIP识别具有某些扩展名的文件，并将它们复制到用户配置文件中的一个目录

en_text: SPACESHIP identifies files and directories for collection by searching for specific file extensions or file modification time.
Text: SPACESHIP通过搜索特定的文件扩展名或文件修改时间来确定要收集的文件和目录

en_text: SPACESHIP achieves persistence by creating a shortcut in the current user's Startup folder.
Text: SPACESHIP通过在当前用户的启动文件夹中创建一个快捷方式来实现持久性

en_text: SpeakUp downloads and executes additional files from a remote server.
Text: SpeakUp从远程服务器下载和执行额外的文件

en_text: SpeakUp encodes C&C communication using Base64.
Text: SpeakUp对C语言进行编码 SpeakUp编码的C SpeakUp对C语言进行编码

en_text: SpeakUp checks for availability of specific ports on servers.
Text: SpeakUp检查服务器上特定端口的可用性

en_text: SpeakUp can perform brute forcing using a pre-defined list of usernames and passwords in an attempt to log in to administrative panels.
Text: SpeakUp可以使用预先定义的用户名和密码列表进行暴力强迫，试图登录到管理面板

en_text: SpeakUp deletes files to remove evidence on the machine.
Text: SpeakUp删除文件以消除机器上的证据

en_text: SpeakUp uses the arp -a command.
Text: SpeakUp使用arp -a命令

en_text: SpeakUp uses cron tasks to ensure persistence.
Text: SpeakUp使用cron任务来确保持久性

en_text: SpeakUp uses POST and GET requests over HTTP to communicate with its main C&C server.
Text: SpeakUp使用HTTP的POST和GET请求与它的主C语言进行通信

en_text: SpeakUp uses the ifconfig -a command.
Text: SpeakUp使用ifconfig -a命令

en_text: SpeakUp uses Perl scripts.
Text: SpeakUp使用Perl脚本

en_text: SpeakUp uses Python scripts.
Text: SpeakUp使用Python脚本

en_text: SpeakUp uses the whoami command.
Text: SpeakUp使用whoami命令

en_text: SpeakUp uses the cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep -c "cpu family" 2>&1 command to gather system information.
Text: SpeakUp使用猫 SpeakUp利用猫 SpeakUp使用的猫 SpeakUp使用猫咪

en_text: SpeakUp attempts to exploit the following vulnerabilities in order to execute its malicious script: CVE-2012-0874, CVE-2010-1871, CVE-2017-10271, CVE-2018-2894, CVE-2016-3088, JBoss AS 3/4/5/6, and the Hadoop YARN ResourceManager.
Text: SpeakUp试图利用以下漏洞，以执行其恶意脚本。CVE-2012-0874, CVE-2010-1871, CVE-2017-10271, CVE-2018-2894, CVE-2016-3088, JBoss AS 3/4/5/6, 和Hadoop YARN ResourceManager。

en_text: SpeakUp encodes its second-stage payload with Base64.
Text: SpeakUp用Base64对其第二阶段的有效载荷进行编码

en_text: spwebmember is used to enumerate and dump information from Microsoft SharePoint.
Text: spwebmember用于列举和转储Microsoft SharePoint中的信息

en_text: sqlmap can be used to automate exploitation of SQL injection vulnerabilities.
Text: sqlmap可以用来自动利用SQL注入漏洞

en_text: SQLRat can make a direct SQL connection to a Microsoft database controlled by the attackers, retrieve an item from the bindata table, then write and execute the file on disk.
Text: SQLRat可以直接与攻击者控制的微软数据库进行SQL连接，从bindata表中检索一个项目，然后在磁盘上写入并执行该文件

en_text: SQLRat has used PowerShell to create a Meterpreter session.
Text: SQLRat使用PowerShell来创建一个Meterpreter会话

en_text: SQLRat has used a character insertion obfuscation technique, making the script appear to contain Chinese characters.
Text: SQLRat使用了一种字符插入的混淆技术，使脚本看起来包含中文字符

en_text: SQLRat relies on users clicking on an embedded image to execute the scripts.
Text: SQLRat依靠用户点击一个嵌入的图像来执行脚本

en_text: SQLRat has used SQL to execute JavaScript and VB scripts on the host system.
Text: SQLRat已经使用SQL在主机系统上执行JavaScript和VB脚本

en_text: SQLRat has created scheduled tasks in %appdata%\Roaming\Microsoft\Templates\.
Text: SQLRat已经在%appdata%\Roaming\Microsoft\Templates\中创建了计划任务

en_text: SQLRat has scripts that are responsible for deobfuscating additional scripts.
Text: SQLRat有一些脚本，负责对额外的脚本进行解密

en_text: SslMM contains a feature to manipulate process privileges and tokens.
Text: SslMM包含一个操纵进程权限和令牌的功能

en_text: SslMM creates a new thread implementing a keylogging facility using Windows Keyboard Accelerators.
Text: SslMM创建了一个新的线程，使用Windows键盘加速器实现键盘记录功能

en_text: SslMM sends the logged-on username to its hard-coded C2.
Text: SslMM将登录的用户名发送至其硬编码的C2

en_text: SslMM identifies and kills anti-malware processes.
Text: SslMM识别并杀死反恶意软件进程

en_text: SslMM sends information to its hard-coded C2, including OS version, service pack information, processor speed, system name, and OS install date.
Text: SslMM向其硬编码的C2发送信息，包括操作系统版本、服务包信息、处理器速度、系统名称和操作系统安装日期

en_text: SslMM has a hard-coded primary and backup C2 string.
Text: SslMM有一个硬编码的主要和备份C2字符串

en_text: Starloader decrypts and executes shellcode from a file called Stars.jps.
Text: Starloader对一个名为Stars.jps的文件进行解密并执行shellcode

en_text: Starloader has masqueraded as legitimate software update packages such as Adobe Acrobat Reader and Intel.
Text: Starloader伪装成合法的软件更新包，如Adobe Acrobat Reader和Intel

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware creates a scheduled task entitled "IE Web Cache" to execute a malicious file hourly.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件创建了一个名为 "IE Web Cache "的计划任务，每小时执行一个恶意文件

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers data from the local victim system.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件从本地受害者系统收集数据

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers passwords from multiple sources, including Internet Explorer, Firefox, and Chrome.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件从多个来源收集密码，包括Internet Explorer、Firefox和Chrome

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers passwords from multiple sources, including Windows Credential Vault and Outlook.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件从多个来源收集密码，包括Windows Credential Vault和Outlook

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers the Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) table from the victim.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件从受害者那里收集地址解析协议（ARP）表

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware uses PowerShell commands to perform various functions, including gathering system information via WMI and executing commands from its C2 server.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件使用PowerShell命令来执行各种功能，包括通过WMI收集系统信息和从其C2服务器执行命令

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware encrypts C2 traffic using RC4 with a hard-coded key.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件使用RC4与硬编码的密钥对C2流量进行加密

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware uses WMI to script data collection and command execution on the victim.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件使用WMI对受害者进行数据收集和命令执行的脚本

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware attempts to determine the installed version of .NET by querying the Registry.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件试图通过查询注册表来确定所安装的.NET版本

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers a list of running processes.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件收集了一个正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware communicates with its C2 server via HTTPS.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件通过HTTPS与它的C2服务器进行通信

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers system information via Windows Management Instrumentation (WMI).
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件通过Windows Management Instrumentation（WMI）收集系统信息

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers system information via WMI, including the system directory, build number, serial number, version, manufacturer, model, and total physical memory.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件通过WMI收集系统信息，包括系统目录、构建号、序列号、版本、制造商、型号和总物理内存

en_text: Stealth Falcon malware gathers the registered user and primary owner name via WMI.
Text: Stealth Falcon恶意软件通过WMI收集注册用户和主要所有者名称

en_text: Stolen Pencil sent spearphishing emails containing links to domains controlled by the threat actor.
Text: Stolen Pencil发送的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件包含威胁者控制的域的链接。

en_text: Stolen Pencil utilized RDP for direct remote point-and-click access.
Text: Stolen Pencil利用RDP直接进行远程点选访问

en_text: Stolen Pencil has a tool to log keystrokes to %userprofile%\appdata\roaming\apach.{{txt,log}}.
Text: Stolen Pencil有一个工具可以将按键记录到%userprofile%\appdata\roamingapach.{{txt,log}}

en_text: Stolen Pencil has a tool to add a Windows admin account in order to allow them to ensure continued access via RDP.
Text: Stolen Pencil有一个工具可以添加一个Windows管理账户，以便让他们确保通过RDP继续访问

en_text: Stolen Pencil has a tool to sniff the network for passwords.
Text: Stolen Pencil有一个工具可以嗅探网络的密码

en_text: StoneDrill can wipe the accessible physical or logical drives of the infected machine.
Text: StoneDrill可以擦除受感染机器的可访问物理或逻辑驱动器

en_text: StoneDrill can wipe the master boot record of an infected computer.
Text: StoneDrill可以擦除受感染计算机的主引导记录

en_text: StoneDrill can obtain the current date and time of the victim machine.
Text: StoneDrill可以获得受害者机器的当前日期和时间

en_text: StoneDrill can check for antivirus and antimalware programs.
Text: StoneDrill可以检查反病毒和反恶意软件程序

en_text: StoneDrill can take screenshots.
Text: StoneDrill可以进行屏幕截图

en_text: StoneDrill has used the WMI command-line (WMIC) utility to run tasks.
Text: StoneDrill使用了WMI命令行（WMIC）工具来运行任务

en_text: StoneDrill has used several anti-emulation techniques to prevent automated analysis by emulators or sandboxes.
Text: StoneDrill使用了几种反仿真技术来防止仿真器或沙盒的自动分析

en_text: StoneDrill has downloaded and dropped temporary files containing scripts; it additionally has a function to upload files from the victims machine.
Text: StoneDrill下载并丢弃了含有脚本的临时文件；此外，它还具有从受害者机器上传文件的功能

en_text: StoneDrill has relied on injecting its payload directly into the process memory of the victim's preferred browser.
Text: StoneDrill依靠将其有效载荷直接注入受害者首选浏览器的进程内存

en_text: StoneDrill has obfuscated its module with an alphabet-based table or XOR encryption.
Text: StoneDrill用基于字母表或XOR加密的方式混淆了其模块

en_text: StoneDrill has several VBS scripts used throughout the malware's lifecycle.
Text: StoneDrill有几个VBS脚本，在整个恶意软件的生命周期内使用

en_text: StoneDrill has the capability to discover the system OS, Windows version, architecture and environment.
Text: StoneDrill有能力发现系统操作系统、Windows版本、架构和环境

en_text: StoneDrill has a disk wiper module that targets files other than those in the Windows directory.
Text: StoneDrill有一个磁盘刮刀模块，针对Windows目录以外的文件

en_text: StoneDrill has looked in the registry to find the default browser path.
Text: StoneDrill在注册表中查找了默认的浏览器路径

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to enumerate processes.
Text: StreamEx具有列举进程的能力

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to enumerate drive types.
Text: StreamEx具有列举驱动器类型的能力

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to enumerate system information.
Text: StreamEx具有列举系统信息的能力

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to scan for security tools such as firewalls and antivirus tools.
Text: StreamEx具有扫描安全工具的能力，如防火墙和防病毒工具

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to modify the Registry.
Text: StreamEx具有修改注册表的能力

en_text: StreamEx has the ability to remotely execute commands.
Text: StreamEx具有远程执行命令的能力

en_text: StreamEx uses rundll32 to call an exported function.
Text: StreamEx使用rundll32来调用一个导出的函数

en_text: StreamEx establishes persistence by installing a new service pointing to its DLL and setting the service to auto-start.
Text: StreamEx通过安装一个指向其DLL的新服务并将该服务设置为自动启动来建立持久性

en_text: StreamEx obfuscates some commands by using statically programmed fragments of strings when starting a DLL. It also uses a one-byte xor against 0x91 to encode configuration data.
Text: StreamEx通过在启动DLL时使用静态编程的字符串片段来混淆一些命令

en_text: Strider has used local servers with both local network and Internet access to act as internal proxy nodes to exfiltrate data from other parts of the network without direct Internet access.
Text: Strider利用同时具有本地网络和互联网访问权限的本地服务器作为内部代理节点，从没有直接互联网访问权限的网络其他部分渗出数据

en_text: Strider has used a hidden file system that is stored as a file on disk.
Text: Strider使用了一个隐藏的文件系统，以文件形式存储在磁盘上

en_text: Strider has registered its persistence module on domain controllers as a Windows LSA (Local System Authority) password filter to acquire credentials any time a domain, local user, or administrator logs in or changes a password.
Text: Strider在域控制器上注册了其持久性模块，作为Windows LSA（本地系统授权）密码过滤器，以便在域、本地用户或管理员登录或更改密码时获取凭证

en_text: StrongPity has been bundled with legitimate software installation files for disguise.
Text: StrongPity被捆绑在合法软件的安装文件中进行伪装

en_text: StrongPity has created new services and modified existing services for persistence.
Text: StrongPity创建了新的服务，并修改了现有的服务以实现持久性

en_text: StrongPity has named services to appear legitimate.
Text: StrongPity对服务进行了命名，以显得合法

en_text: StrongPity can install a service to execute itself as a service.
Text: StrongPity可以安装一个服务，将自己作为一个服务执行

en_text: StrongPity can delete previously exfiltrated files from the compromised host.
Text: StrongPity可以从被攻击的主机上删除先前渗出的文件

en_text: StrongPity can add directories used by the malware to the Windows Defender exclusions list to prevent detection.
Text: StrongPity可以将恶意软件使用的目录添加到Windows Defender的排除列表中，以防止检测

en_text: StrongPity can parse the hard drive on a compromised host to identify specific file extensions.
Text: StrongPity可以解析被攻击主机上的硬盘，以识别特定的文件扩展名

en_text: StrongPity can identify the IP address of a compromised host.
Text: StrongPity可以识别被攻击主机的IP地址

en_text: StrongPity can identify the hard disk volume serial number on a compromised host.
Text: StrongPity可以识别被攻击主机上的硬盘卷序号

en_text: StrongPity can use the HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run Registry key for persistence.
Text: StrongPity可以使用HKCUSoftware\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run注册表键进行持久化

en_text: StrongPity can use PowerShell to add files to the Windows Defender exclusions list.
Text: StrongPity可以使用PowerShell将文件添加到Windows Defender排除列表中

en_text: StrongPity can use multiple layers of proxy servers to hide terminal nodes in its infrastructure.
Text: StrongPity可以使用多层代理服务器来隐藏其基础设施中的终端节点

en_text: StrongPity can exfiltrate collected documents through C2 channels.
Text: StrongPity可以通过C2渠道渗出收集的文件

en_text: StrongPity can determine if a user is logged in by checking to see if explorer.exe is running.
Text: StrongPity可以通过检查explorer.exe是否在运行来确定用户是否登录

en_text: StrongPity can compress and encrypt archived files into multiple .sft files with a repeated xor encryption scheme.
Text: StrongPity可以通过重复的xor加密方案将归档文件压缩并加密成多个.sft文件

en_text: StrongPity can download files to specified targets.
Text: StrongPity可以下载文件到指定目标

en_text: StrongPity can use HTTP and HTTPS in C2 communications.
Text: StrongPity可以在C2通信中使用HTTP和HTTPS

en_text: StrongPity can identify if ESET or BitDefender antivirus are installed before dropping its payload.
Text: StrongPity可以在投放其有效载荷之前识别是否安装了ESET或BitDefender防病毒软件

en_text: StrongPity can automatically exfiltrate collected documents to the C2 server.
Text: StrongPity可以自动将收集到的文件外泄到C2服务器

en_text: StrongPity has been executed via compromised installation files for legitimate software including compression applications, security software, browsers, file recovery applications, and other tools and utilities.
Text: StrongPity是通过合法软件的受损安装文件执行的，包括压缩应用程序、安全软件、浏览器、文件恢复应用程序以及其他工具和实用程序

en_text: StrongPity has encrypted C2 traffic using SSL/TLS.
Text: StrongPity已经使用SSL对C2流量进行了加密 StrongPity已使用SSL对C2流量进行了加密 StrongPity已经使用SSL对C2流量进行了加密

en_text: StrongPity has been signed with self-signed certificates.
Text: StrongPity已经用自签名证书签名

en_text: StrongPity has the ability to hide the console window for its document search module from the user.
Text: StrongPity有能力向用户隐藏其文档搜索模块的控制台窗口

en_text: StrongPity has a file searcher component that can automatically collect and archive files based on a predefined list of file extensions.
Text: StrongPity有一个文件搜索器组件，可以根据预定义的文件扩展名列表自动收集和存档文件

en_text: StrongPity has used HTTPS over port 1402 in C2 communication.
Text: StrongPity在C2通信中使用了HTTPS的1402端口

en_text: StrongPity has used encrypted strings in its dropper component.
Text: StrongPity在其dropper组件中使用了加密的字符串

en_text: S-Type uses Base64 encoding for C2 traffic.
Text: S-Type对C2流量使用Base64编码

en_text: S-Type may create the file %HOMEPATH%\Start Menu\Programs\Startup\Realtek {{Unique Identifier}}.lnk, which points to the malicious msdtc.exe file already created in the %CommonFiles% directory.
Text: S-Type可能会创建%HOMEPATH%\Start Menu\Programs\Startup\Realtek {{Unique Identifier}}.lnk文件，它指向已经在%CommonFiles%目录下创建的恶意msdtc.exe文件

en_text: S-Type may create a temporary user on the system named "Lost_{{Unique Identifier}}" with the password "pond~!@6"{{Unique Identifier}}."
Text: S-Type可能会在系统中创建一个名为 "Lost_{{Unique Identifier}}"的临时用户，密码为 "pond~！@6"{{Unique Identifier}}。

en_text: S-Type may save itself as a file named msdtc.exe, which is also the name of the legitimate Microsoft Distributed Transaction Coordinator service binary.
Text: S-Type可能将自己保存为一个名为msdtc.exe的文件，这也是合法的微软分布式交易协调员服务二进制文件的名称

en_text: S-Type may create a .lnk file to itself that is saved in the Start menu folder. It may also create the Registry key HKCU\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ IMJPMIJ8.1{{3 characters of Unique Identifier}}.
Text: S-Type可能为自己创建一个.lnk文件，保存在开始菜单文件夹中。它还可能创建注册表键HKCU\SOFTWARE\MicrosoftWindows\CurrentVersion\Run\IMJPMIJ8.1{{3个字符的唯一标识符}。

en_text: S-Type uses HTTP for C2.
Text: S-type使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: S-Type runs the command net user on a victim. S-Type also runs tests to determine the privilege level of the compromised user.
Text: S-TYPE在受害者身上运行net user命令。S-Type还运行测试以确定被攻击用户的权限级别。

en_text: S-Type runs the command net start on a victim.
Text: S-Type在一个受害者身上运行net start命令

en_text: S-Type primarily uses port 80 for C2, but falls back to ports 443 or 8080 if initial communication fails.
Text: S-Type主要使用80端口进行C2，但如果初始通信失败，则回落到443或8080端口

en_text: Several tools used by Suckfly have been command-line driven.
Text: Suckfly使用的几个工具都是命令行驱动的

en_text: Suckfly used legitimate account credentials that they dumped to navigate the internal victim network as though they were the legitimate account owner.
Text: Suckfly使用他们倾销的合法账户凭证来浏览内部受害者网络，就像他们是合法账户所有者一样

en_text: Suckfly has used stolen certificates to sign its malware.
Text: Suckfly使用偷来的证书来签署其恶意软件

en_text: Suckfly used a signed credential-dumping tool to obtain victim account credentials.
Text: Suckfly使用一个签名的凭证倾销工具来获取受害者的账户凭证

en_text: Sykipot contains keylogging functionality to steal passwords.
Text: Sykipot包含窃取密码的键盘记录功能

en_text: Sykipot injects itself into running instances of outlook.exe, iexplore.exe, or firefox.exe.
Text: Sykipot将自己注入outlook.exe、iexplore.exe或firefox.exe的运行实例中

en_text: Sykipot may use net view /domain to display hostnames of available systems on a network.
Text: Sykipot可使用网状视图 Sykipot可以使用网状视图 Sykipot可使用净值视图 Sykipot可使用净值查看

en_text: Sykipot may use ipconfig /all to gather system network configuration details.
Text: Sykipot可以使用ipconfig Sykipot可能使用ipconfig Sykipot可使用ipconfig Sykipot可能会使用ipconfig

en_text: Sykipot may use net group "domain admins" /domain to display accounts in the "domain admins" permissions group and net localgroup "administrators" to list local system administrator group membership.
Text: Sykipot可以使用net group "domain admins" /domain来显示 "domain admins "权限组中的账户，使用net localgroup "adminators "来列出本地系统管理员组成员。

en_text: Sykipot may use net start to display running services.
Text: Sykipot可以使用net start来显示正在运行的服务

en_text: Sykipot may use netstat -ano to display active network connections.
Text: Sykipot可以使用netstat -ano来显示活动的网络连接

en_text: Sykipot may gather a list of running processes by running tasklist /v.
Text: Sykipot可以通过运行任务列表来收集正在运行的进程列表

en_text: Sykipot uses SSL for encrypting C2 communications.
Text: Sykipot使用SSL对C2通信进行加密

en_text: SynAck gathers user names from infected hosts.
Text: SynAck从受感染的主机中收集用户名

en_text: SynAck payloads are obfuscated prior to compilation to inhibit analysis and/or reverse engineering.
Text: SynAck的有效载荷在编译之前被混淆，以抑制分析和

en_text: SynAck encrypts the victims machine followed by asking the victim to pay a ransom.
Text: SynAck对受害者的机器进行加密，然后要求受害者支付赎金

en_text: SynAck checks its directory location in an attempt to avoid launching in a sandbox.
Text: SynAck检查其目录位置，试图避免在沙盒中启动

en_text: SynAck parses the export tables of system DLLs to locate and call various Windows API functions.
Text: SynAck解析系统DLLs的导出表，定位并调用各种Windows API函数

en_text: SynAck can manipulate Registry keys.
Text: SynAck可以操作注册表键

en_text: SynAck abuses NTFS transactions to launch and conceal malicious processes.
Text: SynAck滥用NTFS事务来启动和隐藏恶意进程

en_text: SynAck enumerates all running services.
Text: SynAck列举了所有正在运行的服务

en_text: SynAck enumerates all running processes.
Text: SynAck列举了所有正在运行的进程

en_text: SynAck enumerates Registry keys associated with event logs.
Text: SynAck列举了与事件日志相关的注册表键

en_text: SynAck clears event logs.
Text: SynAck清除了事件日志

en_text: SynAck gathers computer names, OS version info, and also checks installed keyboard layouts to estimate if it has been launched from a certain list of countries.
Text: SynAck收集计算机名称、操作系统版本信息，还检查已安装的键盘布局，以估计它是否从某个国家的列表中启动

en_text: SYNful Knock can be sent instructions via special packets to change its functionality. Code for new functionality can be included in these messages.
Text: SYNful Knock可以通过特殊的数据包发送指令来改变其功能。新功能的代码可以包含在这些信息中。

en_text: SYNful Knock is malware that is inserted into a network device by patching the operating system image.
Text: SYNful Knock是通过修补操作系统镜像插入网络设备的恶意软件

en_text: SYNful Knock has the capability to add its own custom backdoor password when it modifies the operating system of the affected network device.
Text: SYNful Knock在修改受影响网络设备的操作系统时，有能力添加自己的自定义后门密码

en_text: Sys10 uses HTTP for C2.
Text: Sys10使用HTTP进行C2

en_text: Sys10 uses an XOR 0x1 loop to encrypt its C2 domain.
Text: Sys10使用一个XOR 0x1循环来加密其C2域

en_text: Sys10 collects the account name of the logged-in user and sends it to the C2.
Text: Sys10收集登录用户的账户名并将其发送到C2

en_text: Sys10 collects the group name of the logged-in user and sends it to the C2.
Text: Sys10收集登录用户的组名并将其发送到C2

en_text: Sys10 collects the computer name, OS versioning information, and OS install date and sends the information to the C2.
Text: Sys10收集计算机名称、操作系统版本信息和操作系统安装日期，并将这些信息发送到C2

en_text: Sys10 collects the local IP address of the victim and sends it to the C2.
Text: Sys10收集受害者的本地IP地址并将其发送到C2

en_text: SYSCON has been executed by luring victims to open malicious e-mail attachments.
Text: SYSCON是通过引诱受害者打开恶意的电子邮件附件来执行的

en_text: SYSCON has the ability to use Systeminfo to identify system information.
Text: SYSCON有能力使用Systeminfo来识别系统信息

en_text: SYSCON has the ability to use Tasklist to list running processes.
Text: SYSCON有能力使用任务列表来列出正在运行的进程

en_text: SYSCON has the ability to use FTP in C2 communications.
Text: SYSCON有能力在C2通信中使用FTP

en_text: SYSCON has the ability to execute commands through cmd on a compromised host.
Text: SYSCON有能力在被攻击的主机上通过cmd执行命令

en_text: Systeminfo can be used to gather information about the operating system.
Text: Systeminfo可以用来收集关于操作系统的信息

en_text: The initial beacon packet for S-Type contains the operating system version and file system of the victim.
Text: S型的初始信标数据包包含受害者的操作系统版本和文件系统

en_text: T9000 can take screenshots of the desktop and target application windows, saving them to user directories as one byte XOR encrypted .dat files.
Text: T9000可以对桌面和目标应用程序窗口进行截图，将其作为一个字节的XOR加密的.dat文件保存到用户目录中

en_text: T9000 uses the Skype API to record audio and video calls. It writes encrypted data to %APPDATA%\Intel\Skype.
Text: T9000使用Skype API来记录音频和视频通话

en_text: T9000 encrypts collected data using a single byte XOR key.
Text: T9000使用一个单字节的XOR密钥对收集的数据进行加密

en_text: T9000 gathers and beacons the operating system build number and CPU Architecture (32-bit/64-bit) during installation.
Text: T9000在安装过程中会收集并标明操作系统的构建号和CPU架构（32位/64位）。

en_text: T9000 searches removable storage devices for files with a pre-defined list of file extensions (e.g. * .doc, .ppt, .xls, .docx, .pptx, *.xlsx). Any matching files are encrypted and written to a local user directory.
Text: T9000搜索可移动存储设备中具有预定义文件扩展名列表的文件（例如*.doc, .ppt, .xls, .docx, .pptx, *.xlsx）

en_text: T9000 searches through connected drives for removable storage devices.
Text: T9000通过连接的驱动器搜索可移动存储设备

en_text: T9000 performs checks for various antivirus and security products during installation.
Text: T9000在安装过程中对各种防病毒和安全产品进行检查

en_text: T9000 gathers and beacons the username of the logged in account during installation. It will also gather the username of running processes to determine if it is running as SYSTEM.
Text: T9000在安装过程中会收集并标示出登录账户的用户名。它还会收集正在运行的进程的用户名，以确定它是否以SYSTEM身份运行。

en_text: T9000 gathers and beacons the system time during installation.
Text: T9000在安装过程中收集并标明了系统时间

en_text: T9000 gathers and beacons the MAC and IP addresses during installation.
Text: T9000在安装过程中收集并信标了MAC和IP地址

en_text: TA459 has targeted victims using spearphishing emails with malicious Microsoft Word attachments.
Text: TA459利用带有恶意微软Word附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件将受害者锁定

en_text: TA459 has used PowerShell for execution of a payload.
Text: TA459使用了PowerShell来执行一个有效载荷

en_text: TA459 has attempted to get victims to open malicious Microsoft Word attachment sent via spearphishing.
Text: TA459试图让受害者打开通过鱼叉式网络钓鱼发送的恶意微软Word附件

en_text: TA459 has exploited Microsoft Word vulnerability CVE-2017-0199 for execution.
Text: TA459已利用微软Word漏洞CVE-2017-0199进行执行

en_text: TA459 has a VBScript for execution.
Text: TA459有一个VBScript用于执行

en_text: TA505 has sent spearphishing emails containing malicious links.
Text: TA505发送了含有恶意链接的鱼叉式网络钓鱼邮件

en_text: TA505 has used msiexec to download and execute malicious Windows Installer files.
Text: TA505利用msiexec下载并执行恶意的Windows安装程序文件

en_text: TA505 has used PowerShell to download and execute malware and reconnaissance scripts.
Text: TA505利用PowerShell下载并执行恶意软件和侦察脚本

en_text: TA505 has leveraged rundll32.exe to execute malicious DLLs.
Text: TA505利用rundll32.exe来执行恶意的DLLs

en_text: TA505 has used malware to gather credentials from FTP clients and Outlook.
Text: TA505利用恶意软件从FTP客户端和Outlook收集凭证

en_text: TA505 has used malware to gather credentials from Internet Explorer.
Text: TA505利用恶意软件从IE浏览器中收集凭证

en_text: TA505 has leveraged malicious Word documents that abused DDE.
Text: TA505利用了滥用DDE的恶意Word文档

en_text: TA505 has used stolen domain admin accounts to compromise additional hosts.
Text: TA505利用偷来的域名管理账户入侵了其他主机

en_text: TA505 has used lures to get users to click links in emails and attachments. For example, TA505 makes their malware look like legitimate Microsoft Word documents, .pdf and/or .lnk files.
Text: TA505利用诱饵让用户点击电子邮件和附件中的链接。例如，TA505使他们的恶意软件看起来像合法的微软Word文档、.pdf和/或.lnk文件。

en_text: TA505 has used lures to get users to enable content in malicious attachments and execute malicious files contained in archives. For example, TA505 makes their malware look like legitimate Microsoft Word documents, .pdf and/or .lnk files.
Text: TA505利用诱饵让用户启用恶意附件中的内容并执行档案中的恶意文件。例如，TA505使他们的恶意软件看起来像合法的微软Word文档、.pdf和/或.lnk文件。

en_text: TA505 has executed commands using cmd.exe.
Text: TA505使用cmd.exe执行了命令

en_text: TA505 has used TinyMet to enumerate members of privileged groups. TA505 has also run net group /domain.
Text: TA505使用TinyMet来列举特权组的成员

en_text: TA505 has used spearphishing emails with malicious attachments to initially compromise victims.
Text: TA505使用带有恶意附件的鱼叉式网络钓鱼电子邮件，最初控制了受害者

en_text: TA505 has used the tool EmailStealer to steal and send lists of e-mail addresses to a remote server.
Text: TA505使用工具EmailStealer窃取并发送电子邮件地址列表到远程服务器

en_text: TA505 has used JavaScript for code execution.
Text: TA505使用了JavaScript来执行代码

en_text: TA505 has used UPX to obscure malicious code.
Text: TA505使用了UPX来掩盖恶意代码

en_text: TA505 has used VBS for code execution.
Text: TA505使用了VBS来执行代码

en_text: TA505 has used a wide variety of ransomware, such as Locky, Jaff, Bart, Philadelphia, and GlobeImposter, to encrypt victim files and demand a ransom payment.
Text: TA505使用了各种各样的勒索软件，如Locky、Jaff、Bart、Philadelphia和GlobeImposter，来加密受害者文件并要求支付赎金

en_text: TA505 has used fast flux to mask botnets by distributing payloads across multiple IPs.
Text: TA505通过将有效载荷分布在多个IP上，利用快速通量掩盖僵尸网络

en_text: TA505 has downloaded additional malware to execute on victim systems.
Text: TA505下载了额外的恶意软件，在受害者系统上执行

en_text: TA505 has used HTTP to communiate with C2 nodes.
Text: TA505已使用HTTP与C2节点进行通信

en_text: TA505 has signed payloads with code signing certificates from Thawte and Sectigo.
Text: TA505用Thawte和Sectigo的代码签名证书签署了有效载荷

en_text: TA505 has password-protected malicious Word documents and used base64 encoded PowerShell commands.
Text: TA505有密码保护的恶意Word文档，并使用base64编码的PowerShell命令

en_text: Taidoor can perform DLL loading.
Text: Taidoor可以进行DLL加载

en_text: Taidoor uses RC4 to encrypt the message body of HTTP content.
Text: Taidoor使用RC4来加密HTTP内容的信息体

en_text: TajMahal can set the KeepPrintedJobs attribute for configured printers in SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Print\Printers to enable document stealing.
Text: TajMahal可以在SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Print\Printers中为配置的打印机设置KeepPrintedJobs属性，以实现文档偷取

en_text: TajMahal has used an encrypted Virtual File System to store plugins.
Text: TajMahal使用了一个加密的虚拟文件系统来存储插件

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to capture keystrokes on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力捕捉被感染主机上的按键

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to capture VoiceIP application audio on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力捕捉受感染主机上的VoiceIP应用音频

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to steal web session cookies from Internet Explorer, Netscape Navigator, FireFox and RealNetworks applications.
Text: TajMahal有能力从Internet Explorer、Netscape Navigator、FireFox和RealNetworks应用程序中窃取网络会话cookies

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to steal documents from the local system including the print spooler queue.
Text: TajMahal有能力从本地系统中窃取文件，包括打印ooler队列

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to steal data from the clipboard of an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力从受感染主机的剪贴板上窃取数据

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to index files from drives, user profiles, and removable drives.
Text: TajMahal有能力对驱动器、用户配置文件和可移动驱动器的文件进行索引

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to manage an automated queue of egress files and commands sent to its C2.
Text: TajMahal有能力管理发送到其C2的出口文件和命令的自动队列

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to inject the LoadLibrary call template DLL into running processes.
Text: TajMahal有能力将LoadLibrary调用模板DLL注入到运行的进程中

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to inject DLLs for malicious plugins into running processes.
Text: TajMahal有能力将恶意插件的DLLs注入正在运行的进程

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to index and compress files into a send queue for exfiltration.
Text: TajMahal有能力将文件索引和压缩到发送队列中，以便进行渗出

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to determine local time on a compromised host.
Text: TajMahal有能力确定被破坏的主机上的当地时间

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify connected Apple devices.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别连接的苹果设备

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify which anti-virus products, firewalls, and anti-spyware products are in use.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别哪些反病毒产品、防火墙和反间谍软件产品正在使用

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify the MAC address on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别受感染主机的MAC地址

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify hardware information, the computer name, and OS information on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别受感染主机的硬件信息、计算机名称和操作系统信息

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify the Internet Explorer (IE) version on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别受感染主机上的Internet Explorer（IE）版本

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to identify running processes and associated plugins on an infected host.
Text: TajMahal有能力识别受感染主机上的运行进程和相关插件

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to use the open source libraries XZip/Xunzip and zlib to compress files.
Text: TajMahal有能力使用开源库XZip

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to send collected files over its C2.
Text: TajMahal有能力通过其C2发送收集的文件

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to take screenshots on an infected host including capturing content from windows of instant messaging applications.
Text: TajMahal有能力在受感染的主机上进行屏幕截图，包括从即时通讯应用程序的窗口捕捉内容

en_text: TajMahal has the ability to steal written CD images and files of interest from previously connected removable drives when they become available again.
Text: TajMahal有能力在以前连接的可移动驱动器再次可用时，从这些驱动器中窃取写入的CD图像和感兴趣的文件

en_text: TDTESS has a command to download and execute an additional file.
Text: TDTESS有一个命令可以下载和执行一个额外的文件

en_text: TDTESS creates then deletes log files during installation of itself as a service.
Text: TDTESS在安装自己的服务时创建然后删除了日志文件

en_text: TDTESS provides a reverse shell on the victim.
Text: TDTESS在受害者身上提供了一个反向外壳

en_text: TEMP.Veles has renamed files to look like legitimate files, such as Windows update files or Schneider Electric application files.
Text: TEMP.Veles对文件进行了重新命名，使其看起来像合法文件，如Windows更新文件或施耐德电气的应用程序文件

en_text: TEMP.Veles has used a VPN to persist in the victim environment.
